   Home » Recipes » Breakfast » Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast Crunch

   [INS: :INS]

Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast Crunch

     By My Honeys Place Breakfast, Recipes
   3 Shares
   Pin3

   Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast Crunch. Easy recipe for a yummy
   breakfast.

   [INS: :INS]


   Print
   Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast Crunch
   Ingredients
     * 1 egg mixed with 3 teaspoons milk
     * Salt and pepper to taste
     * 1 teaspoon butter
     * 3 pieces fried bacon crumbled
     * 1 slice frozen hash brown patties
     * 1 12 inch flour tortilla warmed

   Instructions
    1. Fry bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel and set aside.
    2. To warm hash brown: Pour a little oil onto a frying pan. Transfer
       your hash browns onto the pan. Don't use low heat. After about 3
       minutes, turn them once and keep frying until a golden brown. Leave
       in pan to keep warm.
    3. To fix tortilla: Over medium-high heat, in a small sauce pan, place
       tortilla in small amount of oil, brown on both sides. Remove from
       pan and set aside.
    4. After tortilla is warmed, use same pan to scramble eggs.
    5. To Scramble eggs: Beat egg, milk, salt and pepper in medium bowl
       until blended.
    6. Heat 1 teaspoon butter in a nonstick skillet over medium heat until
       hot. Pour in egg mixture and the crumbled fried bacon. As eggs
       begin to set, Gently pull the eggs across the pan with a spatula,
       forming large soft curds. Continue cooking – pulling, lifting and
       folding eggs – until thickened and no visible liquid egg remains.
    7. Put together: Lay tortilla flat. Place hash brown on top, then the
       scrambled egg. Fold the tortilla over the hash brown and scramble
       egg.

   Makes 1 Breakfast Crunch. Double recipe to make 2.


   See more our our delicious Breakfast Recipes
   Peach Dumpling Cobbler
   Slow Cooker Apple Spice Cake

   3 Shares
   Pin3

   [INS: :INS]

Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits

     By My Honeys Place Appetizers, Breakfast, Recipes
   24 Shares
   Pin24

   Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits. Serve for side dish or breakfast. Homemade
   makes them so delicious.

   [INS: :INS]


   Print
   Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits
   Ingredients
   Biscuits:
     * 2 cups flour
     * 4 teaspoons baking powder
     * 1/2 teaspoon salt
     * 1 tablespoon sugar
     * 1 teaspoon cream of tartar
     * 1/2 cup cold butter diced
     * 2/3 cup milk

   Honey Topping:
     * 1/4 pound butter
     * 1 tablespoon honey
     * 1 teaspoon granulated sugar
     * 1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon
     * 1/8 teaspoon vanilla extract

   Instructions
   Biscuits:
    1. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, salt, sugar
       and cream of tartar. Cut in butter until the mixture resembles
       cornmeal. Add the milk and mix well. Knead dough about 15 times.
    2. Divide dough into 1/4 cup size portions. Roll into balls and pat to
       about 1/2 inch thickness. Stretch or cut each ball to form biscuit
       shape.
    3. Heat 1/2 cup oil in a large frying pan to medium high heat.
    4. Fry biscuits 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
       Remove to a paper towel-lined plate.

   Honey Topping:
    1. In a sauce pan combine all ingredients. Mix well and heat until
       warm.
    2. Brush on top of biscuits while both are still warm.


   See more of our yummy Side Dishes

   Peach Dumpling Cobbler

   https://myhoneysplace.com/14-cold-remedies-that-work/ Thu, 03 Oct 2019
   12:33:59 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How To and
   Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=65006 14 Cold Remedies That Work.
   Some of the best tips... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/14-cold-remedies-that-work/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>14 Cold Remedies That Work</strong>. Some of the
   best tips I&rsquo;ve found that are natural!</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-65007 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/14-Cold-Remed
   ies-That-Work.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="14 Cold Remedies That Work. Some of the best tips
   I&rsquo;ve found that are natural!"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/14-Cold-Re
   medies-That-Work.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/14-Cold-Remedies-T
   hat-Work-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/14-Cold-Remedies-T
   hat-Work-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>I have seen lots of people posting about that feeling
   of the first cold coming on. Allergies are ba<span
   class="text_exposed_show">d too! Makes for a sore throat in the morning
   especially! <strong>A sore throat is usually the first sigh of a cold
   coming on.</strong></span></p> <p><strong>1.</strong> If you wake up
   with a <strong>sore throat</strong>, and begin to feel a cold coming
   on, mix hot water, 2 tablespoons of honey, 2 tablespoons of Apple Cider
   Vinegar, a dash of cinnamon and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice. Mix well
   and drink. You will feel better within the hour. Works every time!</p>
   <p><strong>2. Stay hydrated</strong>. Water, juice, clear broth or warm
   lemon water with honey helps loosen congestion and prevents
   dehydration.</p> <p><strong>3.</strong> <strong>Rest</strong>. Your
   body needs to heal.</p> <p><strong>4.</strong> Sip warm liquids. Like
   <strong>Lemon Tea</strong>:</p> <ul id="simple-list_1-0" class="comp
   text-passage simple-list simple-list--bulleted "><li
   class="simple-list__item js-checkbox-trigger
   ingredient"><strong>Ingredients:</strong></li> <li
   class="simple-list__item js-checkbox-trigger ingredient">4 tea
   bags</li> <li class="simple-list__item js-checkbox-trigger
   ingredient">2 teaspoons of grated lemon peel</li> <li
   class="simple-list__item js-checkbox-trigger ingredient">1 teaspoon
   lemon juice</li> <li class="simple-list__item js-checkbox-trigger
   ingredient">4 cups&nbsp;boiling water</li> <li id="mntl-sc-block_2-0-1"
   class="comp mntl-sc-block-group--LI mntl-sc-block
   mntl-sc-block-startgroup"> <div id="mntl-sc-block_2-0-2" class="comp
   mntl-sc-block mntl-sc-block-html">
   <p><strong>Instructions:</strong></p> <p>Boil water.&nbsp; Add lemon
   peel, lemon juice, and tea bags. Allow steeping for 10 minutes.Serve
   hot and add milk or sugar. For a variation, try adding vanilla
   sugar!</p> </div> </li> </ul><p><strong>5.</strong> Add moisture to the
   air with a cool mist <strong>vaporizer or humidifier</strong>.</p>
   <p><strong>6.</strong> If you have a sore throat, gargle with
   <strong>warm salt water</strong>. 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon salt dissolved in
   an 8-ounce glass of warm water.</p> <p><strong>7.</strong> Up your
   <strong>Vitamin C,</strong> with OTC capsules or foods high in Vitamin
   C:&nbsp; Broccoli, Brussels Sprouts, Lemons. Lychees, American
   Persimmons and Strawberries.It appears that for the most part
   taking&nbsp;vitamin C&nbsp;won&rsquo;t&nbsp;help&nbsp;the average
   person prevent&nbsp;colds. However, taking&nbsp;vitamin C&nbsp;before
   the onset of&nbsp;cold symptoms may shorten the duration of
   symptoms.&nbsp; The RDA or recommended daily allowance is 90 mg for men
   and 75 mg for women.</p> <p><strong>8.</strong> Eat<strong> chicken
   soup</strong>. Chicken soup has been recommended as a remedy for the
   common cold for hundreds of years, and for good reason. It&rsquo;s an
   easy-to-eat source of vitamins, minerals, calories and protein, which
   are nutrients your body needs in larger quantities while you&rsquo;re
   sick.</p> <p><strong>9.</strong> Eat <strong>Oranges</strong>. Oranges
   are packed with vitamin C, an essential nutrient when you&rsquo;re
   feeling under the weather.</p> <p><strong>10.</strong> Put Vicks
   <strong>VapoRub</strong> on your feet and cover with a towel or
   socks.&nbsp; Vicks VapoRub is a topical cough medication that is
   applied to the skin to treat coughs and applied to muscles to relieve
   aches and pain. Both symptoms are frequently caused by the common cold.
   Or Apply topically to the chest or neck for cough relief that starts
   working instantly.</p> <p><strong>11.</strong> <strong>Break up
   mucus</strong> by rubbing a bit of camphor or menthol salve around
   &ndash; not in! &ndash; your nose. You can also reduce congestion by
   breathing in aromatherapy oils, such as peppermint and eucalyptus.</p>
   <p><strong>12.</strong> A <strong>steamy shower</strong> or sauna is a
   great decongestant. One caution: If you are dizzy or weak from the flu,
   sit in a chair in your bathroom while you run a hot shower.</p>
   <p><strong>13.</strong> To help your sinuses drain, sleep with an
   <strong>extra pillow under your head</strong>.</p>
   <p><strong>14.</strong> To <strong>soothe a sore throat</strong>, steep
   two teaspoons of shredded ginger in a cup of hot water (if you prefer
   something cool, use a cup of sparkling water). Drink at least 2-3 cups
   a day.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/health/"
   rel="">Health Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/25-tasty-recipes-to-add-cabbage-to-your-diet/
   Tue, 01 Oct 2019 15:54:44 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Cooking Tips & Tricks Healthy Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64985 25 Tasty Recipes To Add Cabbage To
   Your Diet. Try... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/25-tasty-recipes-to-add-cabbage-to-your
   -diet/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>25 Tasty Recipes To Add Cabbage To Your
   Diet</strong>. Try these ways to cook cabbage. Healthy Cabbage can
   taste delicious.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64995
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/25-Tasty-Reci
   pes-To-Add-Cabbage-To-Your-Diet.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="25 Tasty Recipes To Add Cabbage To Your Diet. Try
   these ways to cook cabbage. Healthy Cabbage can taste delicious."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/25-Tasty-R
   ecipes-To-Add-Cabbage-To-Your-Diet.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/25-Tasty-Recipes-T
   o-Add-Cabbage-To-Your-Diet-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/25-Tasty-Recipes-T
   o-Add-Cabbage-To-Your-Diet-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Why eat
   cabbage:</strong></p> <p>Cabbage is high in fiber and contains powerful
   antioxidants, including polyphenols and sulfur compounds. Cabbage is
   especially high in vitamin C, a potent antioxidant that may protect
   against heart disease, certain cancers and vision loss. It is also low
   in calories.</p> <p>Cabbage contains powerful antioxidants that may
   help reduce inflammation. It will improve your digestive health because
   of it&rsquo;s high fiber content. Red Cabbage is high in potassium and
   may help reduce your blood pressure.</p> <p>Cabbage is a good source of
   soluble fiber and plant steroids. These substances have been shown to
   reduce LDL cholesterol.</p> <p><strong>Ways to cook cabbage and
   recipes:</strong></p> <p>1. Cut a couple of heads into small wedges,
   splash with a good oil (I use avocado) and pink salt and roast in a 400
   degree oven until the wedges are soft and lightly browned. It
   caramelizes a bit. It&rsquo;s delicious.</p> <p>2. Sauteed in olive oil
   and garlic.</p> <p>3. Slow simmer some smoked turkey necks in water or
   chicken broth for a couple of hours and then add cabbage for the last
   30 mins or until it reaches your desired tenderness. You eat the turkey
   meat with cabbage for a meal.</p> <p>4. Slice an onion shaved garlic
   saute in olive oil and butter. Cube the cabbage and saute together. Add
   more butter as needed. Add salt and pepper to taste.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64986" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64986"
   class="wp-image-64986 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Cream-Of-Cabb
   age-Soup.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Cream-Of-C
   abbage-Soup.jpg 300w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Cream-Of-Cabbage-S
   oup-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Cream-Of-Cabbage-S
   oup-50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64986" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Cream Of
   Cabbage Soup</strong>. Grab the recipe <a
   href="https://www.tasteofhome.com/recipes/cream-of-cabbage-soup/?fbclid
   =IwAR1p2O1ddtAycjeaUvuUvL30msAvCTdZCRR6VJTxWhBaG8QECiZwyr0vDjg"
   target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener
   noreferrer"><strong>HERE</strong></a></p></div> <p>5. Saute with
   kielbasa, season with salt, pepper, Cajun seasoning. Stir in cooked
   rice when finished.</p> <p>6. Fry with diced potatoes, onions , and
   polish sausage, little salt and pepper. Use a whole head of cabbage , a
   large onion, a whole pack of polish sausage, 4 or 5 potatoes ( just
   wash and dice, use the peelings and all ) and salt and pepper to
   taste.&nbsp; You can also put a little hot sauce and mine (in you
   plate) when it&rsquo;s done.</p> <p>7. Stir fry 4 cups of finely sliced
   cabbage in butter then crumble a wheel or 2 of feta cheese over and
   stir until it forms a sauce. Add black pepper and serve.</p> <p>8. Make
   sausage egg roll bowls. Fry it with shredded carrots, crumbled
   breakfast sausage and green onions. Top it with sweet and sour
   sauce.</p> <div id="attachment_64990" style="width: 410px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64990" class="wp-image-64990"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Green-Smoothi
   e.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="538" data-pin-description="Cabbage
   Smoothie. Healthy and delicious. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Green-Smoo
   thie.jpg 714w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Green-Smoothie-298
   x400.jpg 298w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Green-Smoothie-112
   x150.jpg 112w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64990" class="wp-caption-text">Cabbage
   Smoothie</p></div> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64991--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Cabbage Smoothie</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Green-Smoothi
   e-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 cup cabbage
   (chopped)</li> <li>1 cup celery (chopped)</li> <li>1/2 lemon (including
   peel and seed)</li> <li>1 tablespoon apple vinegar</li> <li>1
   tablespoon chia seeds</li> <li>1 teaspoon clove (whole cloves)</li>
   <li>1/2 cup cranberry juice cocktail</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Cut cabbage, celery
   and lemon into small pieces</li> <li>Add cabbage, celery, lemon, apple
   vinegar, chia seeds, clove and cranberry juice cocktail into
   blender</li> <li>Blend until smooth.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>9. Boil it with chopped up bacon with a bit of vinegar
   in the water. The kids love it.</p> <p>10. Make it with cooked chicken
   or pork chops. After whichever meat is cooked throw in cabbage a pinch
   of garlic powder, a pinch of cumin some chopped tomatoes and some
   water. Done when cabbage is soft.</p> <p><span dir="ltr"><span
   class="_3l3x">11. Fried with hamburger meat and
   onion.&nbsp;</span></span></p> <p>12. Chop it and fry in bacon grease.
   Cook up and crumble some bacon and onion. Cook it in the bacon grease
   and season with salt and pepper.</p> <div id="attachment_64987"
   style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64987" class="wp-image-64987
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Baked-Cabbage
   -Steaks-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Healthy Baked Cabbage Steaks. An easy, delicious,
   low calorie and crispy recipe."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Baked-Cabb
   age-Steaks-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Baked-Cabbage-Stea
   ks-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Baked-Cabbage-Stea
   ks-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64987" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Healthy
   Baked Cabbage Steaks.</strong> An easy, delicious, low calorie and
   crispy recipe. <strong>Grab the recipe <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/baked-cabbage-steaks/"
   rel="">HERE</a></strong></p></div> <p>13. My recipe is very good I call
   it heart attack cabbage lol.&nbsp; I use 2 slices of bacon cut up and
   fried, a stick of real butter garlic powder just sprinkle it on a
   little salt and pepper no water cook in the bacon grease and butter. I
   usually cook it in a big pan like my spaghetti pan cover with a lids
   keep stirring it about every couple of minutes it&rsquo;s amazing.</p>
   <p>14. Cook it in your crock pot with canned diced tomato and steak
   seasoning.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-64988"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cabbage4-400x
   287.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="287"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cabbage4-4
   00x287.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cabbage4-768x551.j
   pg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cabbage4-150x108.j
   pg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/cabbage4.jpg 960w"
   sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"></p> <p>15. Slice it up, add
   sliced carrots, onions, cauliflower and any other veg, stir fry with a
   good dash of soy sauce until cabbage is just
   soft&hellip;delicious!!</p> <p>16. Quarter the head of cabbage sprinkle
   with extra virgin olive oil garlic salt and pepper. Put on the grill
   get some char marks and then wrap it in aluminum foil and let it roast
   over the fire.</p> <p>17. Slice into wedges and drizzle with olive oil,
   sprinkle with salt n pepper. Roast in 375 oven for 20 to 30
   minutes.</p> <p><strong>18. Cabbage roll soup:</strong></p> <p>1 Tbsp
   olive oil<br> 1 1/2 lbs lean ground beef<br> Salt and freshly ground
   black pepper<br> 1 large yellow onion , chopped (1 3/4 cups)<br> 2
   large carrots , chopped (1 1/4 cups)<br> 5 cups packed chopped cabbage
   (16 &ndash; 19 oz)<br> 3 cloves garlic , minced<br> 2 (14.5 oz) cans
   low-sodium beef broth<br> 3 (8 oz) cans tomato sauce<br> 2 (14.5 oz)
   cans petite diced tomatoes<br> 2 Tbsp packed light brown sugar<br> 1
   Tbsp Worcestershire sauce<br> 1 1/2 tsp dried paprika<br> 1 tsp dried
   oregano or 1 Tbsp chopped fresh<br> 3/4 tsp dried thyme or 2 1/2 tsp
   chopped fresh<br> 2 bay leaves<br> 3/4 cup dry long-grain white
   rice<br> 1 Tbsp fresh lemon juice<br> 1/3 cup chopped fresh parsley<br>
   Instructions:<br> Heat 1 Tbsp olive oil in a large cast iron pot over
   medium-high heat.<br> Add beef, season with salt and pepper and cook,
   stirring and breaking up beef occasionally, until browned. Transfer
   beef to a plate lined with paper towels while reserving 2 Tbsp of the
   rendered fat in pan, set beef aside.<br> Add onion and carrots to pan
   and saute 1 minute, then add cabbage and saute 2 minutes, then add
   garlic and saute 1 minute longer.<br> Pour in beef broth, tomato sauce,
   tomatoes, brown sugar, Worcestershire, paprika, oregano, thyme and bay
   leaves. Return beef to soup mixture.<br> Season soup with salt and
   pepper to taste and bring to a light boil, then add rice, cover pot and
   reduce heat and simmer until rice is cooked through, stirring
   occasionally, about 25 minutes.<br> Stir in up to 1 cup water or more
   beef broth to thin as desired (it will thicken as it rests and become
   almost like a stew), then stir in lemon juice and parsley. Serve
   warm</p> <p><strong>19. Breakfast Cabbage:</strong></p> <p>1/2 cup
   diced onions, sauteed<br> 2 cups thinly sliced cabbage<br> Add garlic
   pepper and salt<br> Saute for 10 minutes<br> Mix 3 Scramble eggs into
   it.</p> <p><strong>20. Candy Cabbage: </strong>Boil green and purple
   cabbage together with a little apple juice or water, vinegar, brown
   sugar and a green Granny Smith apple (sliced thin NOT peeled) cook it
   low until the apple and cabbage are soft!!! Yummy!</p> <p><strong>21.
   Skinny soup:</strong>&nbsp; 2 boxes of College chicken stock, a head of
   (medium) cabbage and what ever veggies you like added, and boil. SO
   GOOD!</p> <p>22. Mix ground beef and stovetop stuffing mix, little
   ketchup. Take cabbage leaves and wrap a small portion of meat mixture
   then cover with diced tomatoes and spaghetti sauce in glass dish. Bake
   covered in foil for 45 min to 1 hour.</p> <p>23. Slice up some smoked
   sausage, large sweet onion , put in a large pot with butter fry them up
   then slice up cabbage put in pot with some turmeric and a little water
   enough to sizzle and make some steam put lid on wait for cabbage to get
   to texture you like stir frequently add salt and pepper can be made
   with or without sausages!<br> It&rsquo;s really good this way.</p>
   <p>24. 1 stick of butter, 1 pkg. of sausage, 1 onion, sliced. Brown the
   sausage and onion in the butter with salt and pepper to taste. Cut up
   the cabbage in large pieces. Then pour in 2 cans of tomatoes. Boil till
   done. So delicious!</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/cooking-tips-tr
   icks/" rel="">Cooking Tips and Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-scented-pine-cones/ Tue, 01 Oct
   2019 12:06:05 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips
   Household Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64976 How To Make Scented Pine Cones. An
   easy way to... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-scented-pine-cones/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Make Scented Pine Cones</strong>. An easy
   way to make your home have an aromatic scent throughout the Holidays.
   Give away as gifts or make a holiday decoration.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64981 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/How-To-Make-S
   cented-Pine-Cones.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Make Scented Pine Cones. An easy way to
   make your home have an aromatic scent throughout the Holidays. Give
   away as gifts or make a holiday decoration.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/How-To-Mak
   e-Scented-Pine-Cones.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/How-To-Make-Scente
   d-Pine-Cones-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/How-To-Make-Scente
   d-Pine-Cones-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64978--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">How
   To Make Scented Pine Cones</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/How-To-Make-S
   cented-Pine-Cones-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>You will need:</h4>
   <ul><li>Pine cones of various sizes</li> <li>Spray adhesive or
   glue</li> <li>Foam brush</li> <li>1/4 cup each cinnamon powder, ginger
   and nutmeg</li> <li>Plastic bag</li> <li>Cookie sheet</li> </ul></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Instructions:</h4>
   <ol><li>Rinse pine cones under running water, lay pine cones on an old
   cookie sheet and bake at 200 degrees F. for 2 to 3 hours or until the
   cones open up. This kills bugs, melts sap etc.</li> <li>Spread the
   cones out on layers of newspaper.</li> <li>Use a foam brush to apply
   glue on the pine cones.</li> <li>Mix equal amounts of cinnamon, ginger
   and nutmeg in plastic bag. Mix well.</li> <li>Add pine cones in spice
   mix. Shake to cover. Allow to dry overnight.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Use scented pine cones in gift
   baskets, on wreaths or placed in bowls.<br> Hang them from your door
   handles or from your Christmas tree.<br> They should last anywhere from
   8 to 12 weeks.</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips and Tricks&nbsp;</a></strong></p>

   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Layered Pineapple Cake.</strong> Dessert
   recipe that is tender, moist and delicious.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64971 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Layered-
   Pineapple-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Layer

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Layered Pineapple Cake</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Layered-
   Pineapple-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ul><li>1 box
   pineapple cake mix (baked according to package directions)</li>
   </ul><h4>Pineapple Filling:</h4> <ul><li>1 (20 ounce) can of crushed
   pineapple (saving 4 Tablespoons for whipped topping)</li> <li>1/2 cup
   granulated sugar</li> <li>2 Tablespoons cornstarch</li>
   </ul><h4>Whipped Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1 tub whipped topping</li>
   </ul><h4>Cinnamon to sprinkled on top, optional</h4> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol><li>Bake
   according to package directions. Cool.</li> </ol><h4>Pineapple
   Filling:</h4> <ol><li>Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook
   over medium heat. When the mixture begins to boil, stir constantly
   until it begins to thicken, approximately 1 to 2 minutes. Keep in mind
   that it will thicken even more as it cools. Cool.</li> <li>Spread over
   cooled cake.</li> </ol><h4>Whipped Topping:</h4> <ol><li> <p>Let thaw
   and stir in 4 Tablespoons crushed pineapple.</p> </li> <li>Spread on
   top of cooled filling.</li> </ol><h4>Sprinkle cinnamon to top, if
   desired.</h4> </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   <p>Refrigerate before serving&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End
   WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a

   https://myhoneysplace.com/short-rib-tortillas/ Sun, 29 Sep 2019
   15:35:26 +0000 My Honeys Place Appetizers Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64960 Short Rib Tortillas. Yummy recipe
   for a special family dinner... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/short-rib-tortillas/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Short Rib Tortillas</strong>. Yummy recipe for a
   special family dinner or an appetizer. You could also make the short
   ribs and place on top of rice.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64963 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Short-Rib-Tor
   tillas.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Short
   Rib Tortillas. Yummy recipe for a special family dinner or an
   appetizer. You could also make the short ribs and place on top of
   rice.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Short-Rib-
   Tortillas.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Short-Rib-Tortilla
   s-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Short-Rib-Tortilla
   s-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64961--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Short Rib Tortillas</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Short-Rib-Tor
   tillas-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Short Ribs:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 pounds boneless beef short ribs (cut into 2-inch long
   pieces)</li> <li>2 teaspoons kosher salt</li> <li>1 teaspoon black
   pepper</li> <li>1 1/2 cups your favorite BBQ sauce. I like Sweet Baby
   Rays.</li> </ul><h4>Toppings:</h4> <ul><li>1 cup shredded lettuce</li>
   <li>1/2 cup shredded carrots</li> <li>1/4 cup shredded onion</li>
   <li>1/2 cup melted Velveeta cheese (or cheese of your choice)</li>
   </ul><h4>Shell:</h4> <ul><li>4 soft flour tortillas</li> </ul></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Short Ribs:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat the oven to 300 degrees F.</li> <li>Season the ribs
   with salt and pepper, then arrange in a 13 by 9-inch baking dish.</li>
   <li> <p>Pour 1/3 of the BBQ sauce over the ribs. Using tongs, flip the
   ribs over and spoon another 1/3 of the sauce over top. Reserve the
   remaining BBQ sauce to spoon over the cooked ribs. Cover the pan with
   aluminum foil and roast for 2 hours.</p> </li> <li> <p>Remove the foil,
   pour the remaining BBQ sauce over the ribs and cook for 30 minutes
   more, uncovered, until the meat is tender and browned. Cut off any
   excess fat that remains around the short ribs. Let cool for about 15
   minutes.</p> </li> <li>Place the lettuce, carrots, onion, and melted
   cheese on top, in that order, in tortilla.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes 4 servings. </p> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits</strong>. Serve for
   side dish or breakfast. Homemade makes them so delicious.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64954 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Sweet-Honey-F
   ried-Biscuits.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits. Serve for side dish
   or breakfast. Homemade makes them so delicious.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Sweet-Hone
   y-Fried-Biscuits.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Sweet-Honey-Fried-
   Biscuits-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Sweet-Honey-Fried-
   Biscuits-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64952--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Sweet Honey Fried Biscuits</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Sweet-Honey-F
   ried-Biscuits-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Biscuits:</h4> <ul><li>2
   cups flour</li> <li>4 teaspoons baking powder</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   salt</li> <li>1 tablespoon sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon cream of
   tartar</li> <li>1/2 cup cold butter (diced)</li> <li>2/3 cup milk</li>
   </ul><h4>Honey Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1/4 pound butter</li> <li>1
   tablespoon honey</li> <li>1 teaspoon granulated sugar</li> <li>1/8
   teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>1/8 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Biscuits:</h4> <ol><li>In a medium bowl, whisk together flour,
   baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar. Cut in butter until the
   mixture resembles cornmeal. Add the milk and mix well. Knead dough
   about 15 times.</li> <li>Divide dough into 1/4 cup size portions. Roll
   into balls and pat to about 1/2 inch thickness. Stretch or cut each
   ball to form biscuit shape.</li> <li>Heat 1/2 cup oil in a large frying
   pan to medium high heat.</li> <li>Fry biscuits 3 to 5 minutes on each
   side or until golden brown. Remove to a paper towel-lined plate.</li>
   </ol><h4>Honey Topping:</h4> <ol><li>In a sauce pan combine all
   ingredients. Mix well and heat until warm.</li> <li>Brush on top of
   biscuits while both are still warm.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/side-dishes/"
   rel="">Side Dishes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/peach-dumpling-cobbler/ Tue, 24 Sep 2019
   13:42:11 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64934 Peach Dumpling Cobbler. Recipe for a
   peach cobbler with a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/peach-dumpling-cobbler/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Peach Dumpling Cobbler</strong>. Recipe for a
   peach cobbler with a twist. Using homemade dumpling in the filling. The
   best pie you will ever taste.</p> <div id="attachment_64937"
   style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64937" class="wp-image-64937
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Peach-Dumplin
   g-Cobbler.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Peach Dumpling Cobbler. Recipe for a peach
   cobbler with a twist. Using homemade dumpling in the filling. The best
   pie you will ever taste."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Peach-Dump
   ling-Cobbler.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Peach-Dumpling-Cob
   bler-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Peach-Dumpling-Cob
   bler-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64937" class="wp-caption-text">Photo
   credit:<br>Pauline Woodards-Respress</p></div> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64935--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Peach Dumpling Cobbler</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Peach-Dumplin
   g-Cobbler-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Crust:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 cups sifted all purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
   <li>2/3 cup shortening</li> <li>5 to 7 Tablespoons cold water</li>
   <li>Ground cinnamon and granulated sugar to taste for topping.</li>
   </ul><h4>Peach Filling:</h4> <ul><li>2 cans (1 lb 13 oz) sliced
   peaches, in syrup or juice</li> <li>1 can condensed milk</li> <li>1 cup
   brown sugar</li> <li>1 Tablespoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>2 teaspoons
   ground nutmeg</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   lemon extract</li> <li>2/3 stick butter</li> <li>1/4 tsp salt</li>
   </ul><h4>Dumpling dough:</h4> <ul><li>3 3/4 cups self-rising flour</li>
   <li>1/2 cups shortening</li> <li>1/2 cup cold water (add a little at a
   time)</li> </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Crust:</h4> <ol><li>Sift together flour and salt. Cut in shortening
   with pastry blender or blending fork until pieces are the size of small
   peas.</li> <li>To make pastry extra tender and flaky, divide shortening
   in half. Cut in first half until mixture looks like corn meal. Then cut
   in remaining half until looks like small peas.</li> <li>Sprinkle 1
   Tablespoon of the water over part of the flour mixture. Gently toss
   with a fork; push to one side of bowl.</li> <li>Sprinkle next
   Tablespoon water over dry part; mix lightly; push to moistened part at
   side. Repeat until all is moistened. Gather up with fingers; form into
   ball. Divide dough for upper and lower crust. Form each in ball.</li>
   <li>On a lightly floured surface roll out 1 of the balls. Flatten ball
   sightly and roll 1/8 inch thick. If edges split, pinch together. Always
   roll dough from center to edge. Using light strokes.</li> <li> <p>To
   transfer pastry, roll it over rolling pin; unroll pastry over
   9&times;13 inch baking pan, fitting loosely onto bottom and sides. Trim
   1/2 to 1 inch beyond edge; fold under and flute. DO NOT prick pastry.
   </p> </li> <li>Roll out the other pastry ball and cut into lattice
   shape. Set aside.</li> </ol><h4>To make the peach filling:</h4>
   <ol><li> <p>In a large pot, combine the peaches and syrup/juice,, brown
   sugar, condensed milk, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, lemon extract, salt
   and butter. Over medium heat, cover and bring mixture to a boil;
   stirring occasionally to ensure butter and seasonings are well
   dispersed. Cook for approximately 15 minutes.</p> </li>
   </ol><h4>Dumpling Dough:</h4> <ol><li>While the peaches are cooking,
   prepare the dumpling dough. Sift the flour in a medium or large bowl.
   Cut the shortening into the flour until you get a mealy consistency.
   Gradually add the cold water, mixing just until the dough holds
   together. Do not add too much water. Knead lightly 4 to 5 times.</li>
   <li>On a floured surface, roll out the dough very thinly (no thicker
   than about 1/4&Prime; thick). Cut into 2 to 2 1/2 inch wide strips;
   then cut each strip diagonally into even pieces.</li> <li> <p>Place
   enough strips of dough into the boiling peach mixture to cover and
   press them down into the juice. Cook those strips for approximately 7
   minutes. Repeat the process (of adding dough strips) and cook until all
   of the dough has been used up. Cook until the dumplings look
   translucent and start to settle into the juice and the juice
   thickens.</p> </li> <li> <p>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.</p> </li>
   <li>Place the mixture into the prepared pie crust.</li> <li>Add the
   lattice to the top.</li> <li> <p>Sprinkle Cinnamon and Sugar on top, to
   taste</p> </li> <li> <p>Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden
   brown.</p> </li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   <p>For an <strong>easier version of the dumplings</strong> you can use
   1 can of canned biscuits. Just fry the biscuits in 2 teaspoons
   vegetable oil. Brown on both sides and then turn down heat, cooking
   until done. Remove from pan and place on paper towel to drain. Cut into
   fourths and drop into peach mixture. Continue with recipe
   above.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>You could also use canned rolled dough
   instead of making your own pie crust.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-taco-bell-copycat-breakfast-crunch/ Sun,
   22 Sep 2019 14:03:47 +0000 My Honeys Place Breakfast Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64927 Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast
   Crunch. Easy recipe for a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-taco-bell-copycat-breakfast-crunch
   /">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast
   Crunch</strong>. Easy recipe for a yummy breakfast.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64930 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Taco-Bel
   l-Copycat-Breakfast-Crunch.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast Crunch. Easy
   recipe for a yummy breakfast.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Taco-
   Bell-Copycat-Breakfast-Crunch.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Taco-Bell-Cop
   ycat-Breakfast-Crunch-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Taco-Bell-Cop
   ycat-Breakfast-Crunch-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64928--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Taco Bell Copycat Breakfast
   Crunch</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Taco-Bel
   l-Copycat-Breakfast-Crunch-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 egg mixed with 3
   teaspoons milk</li> <li>Salt and pepper (to taste)</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   butter</li> <li>3 pieces fried bacon (crumbled)</li> <li>1 slice frozen
   hash brown patties</li> <li>1 12 inch flour tortilla (warmed)</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Fry
   bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel and set aside.</li> <li>To warm
   hash brown: Pour a little oil onto a frying pan. Transfer your hash
   browns onto the pan. Don&rsquo;t use low heat. After about 3 minutes,
   turn them once and keep frying until a golden brown. Leave in pan to
   keep warm.</li> <li>To fix tortilla: Over medium-high heat, in a small
   sauce pan, place tortilla in small amount of oil, brown on both sides.
   Remove from pan and set aside.</li> <li>After tortilla is warmed, use
   same pan to scramble eggs.</li> <li>To Scramble eggs: Beat egg, milk,
   salt and pepper in medium bowl until blended.</li> <li>Heat 1 teaspoon
   butter in a nonstick skillet over medium heat until hot. Pour in egg
   mixture and the crumbled fried bacon. As eggs begin to set, Gently pull
   the eggs across the pan with a spatula, forming large soft curds.
   Continue cooking &ndash; pulling, lifting and folding eggs &ndash;
   until thickened and no visible liquid egg remains.</li> <li>Put
   together: Lay tortilla flat. Place hash brown on top, then the
   scrambled egg. Fold the tortilla over the hash brown and scramble
   egg.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes
   1 Breakfast Crunch. Double recipe to make 2. </p> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more our our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-very-best-german-chocolate-cake/ Sun, 22
   Sep 2019 11:32:15 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64914 The Very Best German Chocolate Cake.
   A homemade cake with... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-very-best-german-chocolate-cake/">C
   ontinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>The Very Best German Chocolate Cake</strong>. A
   homemade cake with a coconut pecan frosting. Perfect recipe for
   Thanksgiving or Christmas.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64917 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Very-Best
   -German-Chocolate-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="The Very Best German Chocolate Cake. A homemade
   cake with a coconut pecan frosting. Perfect recipe for Thanksgiving or
   Christmas.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Very-B
   est-German-Chocolate-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Very-Best-Germ
   an-Chocolate-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Very-Best-Germ
   an-Chocolate-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64915--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">The
   Very Best German Chocolate Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/The-Very-Best
   -German-Chocolate-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>Cake:</li> <li>2 4
   oz. packages sweet chocolate baking bars</li> <li>2 cups all-purpose
   flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
   <li>1 cup butter (softened)</li> <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>4 large eggs
   (separated)</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1 cup
   buttermilk</li> <li>Frosting:</li> <li>2 cups chopped pecans</li> <li>1
   12 oz can evaporated milk</li> <li>1 1/2 cups sugar</li> <li>3/4 cup
   butter</li> <li>6 egg yolks (lightly beaten)</li> <li>2 cups sweetened
   flaked coconut</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Cake:</li> <li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.</li> <li>Lightly
   grease 3 (9-incround cake pans; line bottoms with parchment paper, and
   lightly grease paper.</li> <li>Microwave chocolate baking bars and 1/2
   cup water in a large microwave-safe bowl at HIGH for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes
   or until chocolate is melted and smooth, stirring once halfway
   through.</li> <li>Combine flour and next 2 ingredients in a medium
   bowl.</li> <li>Beat butter and sugar at medium speed with an electric
   mixer until fluffy. Add egg yolks, 1 at a time, beating just until
   blended after each addition. Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla. Add
   flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with
   flour mixture. Beat at low speed just until blended after each
   addition.</li> <li>Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff peaks
   form; gently fold into batter. Pour batter into prepared pans.</li>
   <li>Bake at 350&deg; for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick
   inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from oven, and cool in pans
   on wire racks 15 minutes.</li> <li>Remove from pans to wire racks;
   discard parchment paper. Cool completely (about 1 hour). Spread
   Coconut-Pecan Frosting between layers and on top and sides of
   cake.</li> <li>Frosting:</li> <li>Preheat oven to 350&deg;. Bake pecans
   in a single layer in a shallow pan 8 to 10 minutes or until toasted and
   fragrant, stirring halfway through. Cool completely (about 20
   minutes).</li> <li>Meanwhile, cook evaporated milk, sugar, butter, and
   egg yolks in a heavy 3-qt. saucepan over medium heat, stirring
   constantly, 3 to 4 minutes or until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
   Cook, stirring constantly, 12 to 14 minutes or until mixture becomes a
   light caramel color, is bubbling, and reaches a pudding-like
   thickness.</li> <li>Remove pan from heat; stir in coconut, vanilla, and
   pecans. Transfer mixture to a bowl. Let stand, stirring occasionally,
   45 minutes or until cooled and spreading consistency.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more our our yummy <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake+"
   rel="">Cake Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   Your Crock Pot. Your family with... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   ontinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Healthy Beef Stew In Your Crock Pot</strong>.
   Your family with get their veggie&rsquo;s in a delicious way with this
   recipe.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64910 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Healthy-Beef-
   Stew-In-Your-Crock-Pot.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Healthy Beef Stew In Your Crock Pot. Your family
   with get their veggie's in a delicious way with this recipe."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Healthy-Be
   ef-Stew-In-Your-Crock-Pot.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Healthy-Beef-Stew-
   In-Your-Crock-Pot-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Healthy-Beef-Stew-
   In-Your-Crock-Pot-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64907--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Beef Stew In Your Crock Pot</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Healthy-Beef-
   Stew-In-Your-Crock-Pot-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 tablespoons olive
   oil</li> <li>2 pounds stew meat (cut into 1-inch cubes)</li> <li>Salt
   and ground black pepper (to taste)</li> <li>1 pound potatoes
   (diced)</li> <li>2 carrots (diced, (I like to pre boil my carrots
   first, so they don't taste so strong in the stew))</li> <li>1 onion
   (diced)</li> <li>2 cloves garlic (minced)</li> <li>3 cups beef
   broth</li> <li>2 tablespoons tomato paste</li> <li>1 can green
   beans</li> <li>1 can whole Kernel corn</li> <li>1 can Lima beans</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.</li>
   <li>Season beef with salt and pepper, to taste. Add beef to the skillet
   and cook until evenly browned, about 2-3 minutes.</li> <li> <p>Pre boil
   carrots, if desired, for 2 minutes .</p> </li> <li>Place beef, and
   remaining ingredients into your crock pot. Stir until well mixed.</li>
   <li>Cover and cook on low heat for 7-8 hours or high heat for 3-4
   hours.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our yummy&nbsp; <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=crock+pot" rel="">Crock Pot
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-cracked-caramel-cupcakes/ Fri, 20
   Sep 2019 14:31:28 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64896 Homemade Cracked Caramel Cupcakes.
   Recipe for delicious cupcakes, with a... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-cracked-caramel-cupcakes/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Cracked Caramel Cupcakes</strong>.
   Recipe for delicious cupcakes, with a caramel buttercream frosting and
   topped with crack candies.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64899 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Crac
   ked-Caramel-Cupcakes.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Cracked Caramel Cupcakes. Recipe for
   delicious cupcakes, with a caramel buttercream frosting and topped with
   crack candies.&nbsp;&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-C
   racked-Caramel-Cupcakes.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Cracked-C
   aramel-Cupcakes-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Cracked-C
   aramel-Cupcakes-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64897--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Cracked Caramel
   Cupcakes</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Crac
   ked-Caramel-Cupcakes-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Caramel Cupcakes:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 and 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>3/4 teaspoon baking
   powder</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 cup packed dark brown
   sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup unsalted
   butter (softened to room temperature)</li> <li>2 large eggs (room
   temperature)</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1/2 cup whole
   milk or buttermilk</li> </ul><h4>Caramel Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup
   salted butter</li> <li>1 cup packed dark brown sugar</li> <li>1/3 cup
   heavy cream</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>2 to 3 cups powdered
   sugar (sifted)</li> <li>additional pinch of salt (as needed)</li>
   </ul><h4>Caramel Crack Candy Topping:</h4> <ul><li>28 to 35 saltine
   crackers (enough to fill a cookie sheet)</li> <li>1 cup packed dark
   brown sugar</li> <li>1 cup unsalted butter</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon kosher
   salt</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Caramel Cupcakes:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.</li> <li>Line 12-cup muffin pan
   with paper liners. Set aside.</li> <li>In a large bowl, whisk together
   the flour, baking powder, and salt.</li> <li>In a separate medium bowl,
   beat the butter and sugars together at medium-high speed until light
   and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes. Add the eggs and vanilla. Beat until
   combined.</li> <li>Slowly mix in the dry ingredients, scraping down the
   sides of the bowl as needed. Slowly stir in the milk. Do not over mix
   the batter.</li> <li>Fill each cupcake liner only 1/2 way full with
   batter. Bake cupcakes for 22-23 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted
   in the center of the cupcake comes out clean. Let the cupcakes cool
   before frosting, about 1 hour.</li> </ol><h4>Caramel Frosting:</h4>
   <ol><li>Melt the butter in a small saucepan.</li> <li>Once melted, add
   brown sugar and heavy cream.</li> <li>Stir constantly over medium heat
   until sugar is dissolved. Add salt. Allow to bubble for 3 full minutes,
   no more.</li> <li>Remove from heat and allow to slightly cool, only
   about 15 minutes.</li> <li>With a hand mixer at medium speed, beat in
   powdered sugar 1 cup at a time, until you reach desired consistency.
   Add a little heavy cream if you&rsquo;d like the frosting a little
   creamier or thinner.</li> <li>Add more salt if the frosting tastes too
   sweet.</li> <li>Frost cooled cupcakes and adorn with salted caramel
   crack candies.</li> </ol><h4>Caramel Crack Candy Topping:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat the oven to 400 Line a 10&times;15-inch cookie sheet
   with nonstick aluminum foil or regular heavy duty foil, making sure
   that the foil completely covers the bottom and sides of the pan. If
   using regular foil, spray lightly with baking spray. Line the saltine
   crackers in a single layer on the bottom.</li> <li>Start making the
   caramel-like sauce by placing the brown sugar, butter and salt in a
   medium sized saucepan. Cook on medium heat, stirring frequently, until
   the butter melts. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, for another
   3 to 5 minutes, just until the mixture comes to a boil and starts to
   darken. Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla extract.</li> <li>Pour
   the hot brown sugar mixture over the saltine crackers. Spread to evenly
   coat the crackers.Move the pan to the oven and bake for 5 minutes. The
   caramel will be hot and bubbly.</li> <li>Let the crackers cool to room
   temperature then move to the refrigerator and cool over night. The
   crackers will form a single sheet once cool. Remove from pan and gently
   peel the foil away, being careful not to tear the foil. Cut the candy
   into small sized pieces, or crack it with your hands.</li> <li>Place on
   top of cupcakes.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Make Caramel Crack Candy first,
   it need to refrigerate overnight.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End
   WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Blue Moon Milkshake or Hot Drink</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Blue-Moon-Mil
   kshake-or-Hot-Drink-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Milkshake:</h4> <ul><li>2
   cups milk</li> <li>1 quart vanilla ice cream</li> <li>1/2 cup
   granulated sugar</li> <li>1 Tablespoon vanilla extract</li> <li>15 to
   20 drops blue food coloring or 3 teaspoons butterfly pea powder</li>
   <li>Serves 4</li> </ul><h4>Hot Drink:</h4> <ul><li>1 cup Almond
   Milk</li> <li>1 Tablespoon maple syrup</li> <li>1 teaspoon butterfly
   pea flower powder</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>1
   pinch of ground nutmeg</li> <li>Makes 1 serving</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Milkshake:</h4>
   <ol><li>Combine milk, ice cream, sugar, vanilla, and food coloring in a
   blender and pulse until smooth.</li> <li>Pour into glasses.</li>
   </ol><h4>Hot Drink:</h4> <ol><li>In a small sauce pan whisk together
   milk with all other ingredients. Heat until warm but not
   simmering.</li> <li>Swirl briefly using a hand held frother for a latte
   like finish.</li> <li>Serve hot.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See

   https://myhoneysplace.com/chicken-broccoli-fettuccine/ Wed, 18 Sep 2019
   12:46:56 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64882 Chicken Broccoli Fettuccine. Recipe
   for pasta, chicken and broccoli tossed... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/chicken-broccoli-fettuccine/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Chicken Broccoli Fettuccine</strong>. Recipe for
   pasta, chicken and broccoli tossed in a creamy Alfredo Sauce.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64885 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Chicken-Brocc
   oli-Fettuccine.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Chicken Broccoli Fettuccine. Recipe for pasta,
   chicken and broccoli tossed in a creamy Alfredo Sauce.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Chicken-Br
   occoli-Fettuccine.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Chicken-Broccoli-F
   ettuccine-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Chicken-Broccoli-F
   ettuccine-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64883--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Chicken Broccoli Fettuccine</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Chicken-Brocc
   oli-Fettuccine-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 pound fettuccine
   pasta</li> <li>2 heads of broccoli (chopped, about 3&ndash;4 cups)</li>
   <li>4 6 oz. boneless skinless chicken breasts, cut into 1&Prime;
   cubes</li> <li>4 tablespoons butter</li> <li>3 cloves of garlic (grated
   or finely minced)</li> <li>2 cups heavy cream</li> <li>1 cup grated
   Parmesan cheese (plus more for garnish)</li> <li>2 tablespoons olive
   oil (divided)</li> <li>salt and pepper to taste</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Cook fettuccine
   according to package directions.</li> <li>Heat a large skillet over
   medium high heat with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Add the broccoli, season
   with a pinch of salt and pepper, and cook the broccoli uncovered for 4
   minutes until bright green. Add in 1/4 cup water, and cook uncovered
   until the water has evaporated, and the broccoli is crisp tender.
   Transfer the cooked broccoli to a medium size bowl and set aside.</li>
   <li>In the same skillet you cooked the broccoli, heat another
   tablespoon of olive oil, and cook the chicken in an even layer. Season
   with salt and pepper. Cook about 5-7 minutes, or until the chicken is
   golden brown and cooked thoroughly, turning the chicken several times.
   Transfer the cooked chicken to the same bowl as the broccoli.</li>
   <li>In the same skillet, melt the butter, then cook the garlic for 30
   seconds, or until fragrant. Add the heavy cream, and scrape up any
   brown bits from the bottom of the skillet. Add the grated Parmesan
   cheese, and cook until melted and just starting to bubble. Turn the
   heat to low.</li> <li>When the pasta is done cooking, reserve 1 cup of
   the pasta cooking water. Drain the pasta from the water, then add the
   cooked pasta to the skillet with the sauce, and toss to coat the
   noodles. Add in the cooked chicken and broccoli, toss to combine. If
   necessary, add in pasta water to thin the sauce to desired
   consistency.</li> <li>Serve warm, topped with grated Parmesan
   cheese.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   <p>Recipe will serve 4.</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our
   delicious&nbsp;<a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/" rel="">
   Main Dishes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Baked Garlic Parmesan Meatballs</strong>.
   Put on a toothpick for an appetizer or add to your favorite spaghetti
   sauce.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64867 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Baked-Ga
   rlic-Parmesan-Meatballs.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Baked Garlic Parmesan Meatballs. Put on a

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Baked

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Baked-Garlic-
   Parmesan-Meatballs-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64864--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Baked Garlic Parmesan
   Meatballs</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easy-Baked-Ga
   rlic-Parmesan-Meatballs-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 pound lean ground
   beef</li> <li>2 cloves garlic (minced)</li> <li>2 teaspoons dried
   basil</li> <li>1 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
   flakes</li> <li>2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce</li> <li>1/3 cup
   milk</li> <li>3/4 cup Parmesan cheese (grated)</li> <li>3/4 cup Panko
   bread crumbs</li> <li>1/4 cup green onion (chopped)</li> <li>1/4 cup
   yellow onion (chopped)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 400
   degrees F.</li> <li>Lightly spray a 9 x 13 pan or baking sheet with
   nonstick cooking spray.</li> <li>Combine all ingredients in a medium
   mixing bowl.</li> <li>Mix thoroughly until ingredients are evenly
   distributed.</li> <li> <p>Shape into 1 to 1 and 1/2 inch balls, evenly
   sized.</p> </li> <li>Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.</li> <li>Serve warm as
   an appetizer or mix with spaghetti sauce or just put on top of the
   sauce .</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizers&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:

   https://myhoneysplace.com/egg-noodles-with-spicy-italian-sausage/ Fri,
   13 Sep 2019 22:33:08 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64855 Egg Noodles With Spicy Italian
   Sausage. A delightful dinner recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/egg-noodles-with-spicy-italian-sausage/
   ">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Egg Noodles With Spicy Italian Sausage</strong>.
   A delightful dinner recipe that is spicy and yummy. A lot of
   ingredients but quick and easy to make.</p> <div id="attachment_64858"
   style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64858" class="wp-image-64858
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Egg-Noodles-W
   ith-Spicy-Italian-Sausage.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Egg Noodles With Spicy Italian Sausage. A
   delightful dinner recipe that is spicy and yummy. A lot of ingredients
   but quick and easy to make.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Egg-Noodle
   s-With-Spicy-Italian-Sausage.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Egg-Noodles-With-S
   picy-Italian-Sausage-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Egg-Noodles-With-S
   picy-Italian-Sausage-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><p id="caption-attachment-64858" class="wp-caption-text">Photo
   credit: Pauline Woodards-Respress</p></div> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   64856--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Egg Noodles With Spicy Italian
   Sausage</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Egg-Noodles-W
   ith-Spicy-Italian-Sausage-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>Olive oil</li> <li>4
   spicy Italian sausage links (casings removed)</li> <li>1 large onion
   (quartered and sliced thinly)</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons salt</li> <li>1
   teaspoon Italian seasoning</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper</li>
   <li>1 red bell pepper (cored and thinly sliced)</li> <li>1 yellow bell
   pepper (cored and thinly sliced)</li> <li>1 orange bell pepper (cored
   and thinly sliced)</li> <li>4 cloves garlic (pressed through garlic
   press)</li> <li>1/2 cup white wine</li> <li>1 28 oz. can diced tomatoes
   with juice</li> <li>2 tablespoons parsley (chopped)</li> <li>1/4 cup
   fresh basil leaves (cut into fine strips, divided use)</li> <li>8
   ounces Pappardelle noodles</li> <li>Parmesan cheese and olive oil to
   sprinkle on top</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li> <p>Place a large,
   heavy-bottom pan over medium-high heat; add about 2 tablespoons of
   olive oil.</p> </li> <li> <p>Once the oil is hot, crumble the spicy
   Italian sausage into the pan in small chunks (you want to keep the
   sausage fairly chunky), allowing it to brown in the oil for a few
   moments on each side.</p> </li> <li>When the crumbled sausage is
   browned, remove it from the pan with a slotted spoon and place into a
   small bowl and set aside.</li> <li> <p>Add the sliced onion into the
   pan with the sausage drippings, and allow it to caramelize and become
   golden for roughly 5 minutes, stirring to keep it from burning (add a
   touch more olive oil, if necessary).</p> </li> <li>Once the onion
   starts to become golden, add the salt, Italian seasoning and black
   pepper, and stir to combine, then add in the sliced bell peppers, and
   allow those to saute with the onion for about 2 minutes until slightly
   tender and golden;</li> <li>Add in the garlic, and once it becomes
   aromatic, add in the white wine and allow it to reduce for a few
   moments, until almost completely reduced.</li> <li>Add in the diced
   tomatoes with their juice, and return the browned spicy Italian sausage
   back into the pan, and gently fold the mixture to combine; allow it to
   gently simmer for about 3-4 minutes to blend the flavors, then turn the
   heat off;</li> <li> <p>Drizzle in about 2-3 tablespoons of the olive
   oil to create a silky, rich flavor, and add in the chopped parsley and
   about half of the basil, Stir and keep warm while you prepare the
   noodles.</p> </li> <li>Prepare the noodles according to instructions on
   package. Then, drain the noodles well, and add them directly into the
   sauce, using tongs to gently toss and combine the noodles with the
   sauce and all of the ingredients in it. Check the seasoning to see if
   you need to add any additional salt or pepper.</li> <li>To serve, add
   equal portions of the noodles to bowls, and garnish with a sprinkle of
   the remaining basil.</li> <li>Top with shaved Parmesan and an extra
   drizzle of olive oil.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Meal Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/crunchy-nutty-brownies/ Fri, 13 Sep 2019
   12:23:52 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64849 Crunchy Nutty Brownies. Recipe for a
   dessert brownies. Moist chocolate... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/crunchy-nutty-brownies/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Crunchy Nutty Brownies</strong>. Recipe for a
   dessert brownies. Moist chocolate brownie with a double crunchy
   topping.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64852 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Crunchy-Nutty
   -Brownies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Crunchy Nutty Brownies. Recipe for a dessert
   brownies. Moist chocolate brownie with a double crunchy topping.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Crunchy-Nu
   tty-Brownies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Crunchy-Nutty-Brow
   nies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Crunchy-Nutty-Brow
   nies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64850--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Crunchy Nutty Brownies</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Crunchy-Nutty
   -Brownies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2/3 cup
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>2/3 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>2/3 cup
   chopped bittersweet or semisweet chocolate or morsels</li> <li>1/4 cup
   unsweetened natural cocoa powder</li> <li>1/8 tsp. ground cinnamon</li>
   <li>1/4 tsp. baking powder</li> <li>1/4 tsp. table salt</li> <li>2
   large eggs (lightly beaten)</li> <li>1/3 cup vegetable oil</li>
   <li>Topping:</li> <li>1/2 cup chopped nuts (I combined pecans, cashews
   and walnuts)</li> <li>1 Tablespoon butter</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Heat the oven to
   350&deg;F.</li> <li>Lightly grease a 9-inch pan.</li> <li>In a medium
   bowl, mix the flour, sugar, chopped chocolate, cocoa, cinnamon, baking
   powder, and salt with spatula until well blended.</li> <li>Add the eggs
   and oil and mix until blended. Place batter into pan and spread
   evenly.</li> <li>Topping:</li> <li>In a small sauce pan combine nuts
   and butter. Heat until butter melted.</li> <li>Pour over batter.</li>
   <li>Bake in the center of the oven until a pick inserted in the center
   comes out with some gooey pieces clinging to it, 20 to 25 minutes.</li>
   <li>Let cool at least 10 minutes.</li> <li> <p>Cut into slices and
   serve warm or cold.</p> </li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our awesome <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
