   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64838 Homemade Brown Gravy With Onions.
   Such as easy recipe and... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-brown-gravy-with-onions/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Brown Gravy With Onions.</strong> Such
   as easy recipe and quick to make for dinner. Delicious.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64841" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64841"
   class="wp-image-64841 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Brow
   n-Gravy-With-Onions.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Brown Gravy With Onions. Such as easy
   recipe and quick to make for dinner. Delicious."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-B
   rown-Gravy-With-Onions.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Brown-Gra
   vy-With-Onions-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Brown-Gra
   vy-With-Onions-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><p id="caption-attachment-64841" class="wp-caption-text">Photo
   credit: Pauline Woodards-Respress</p></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM
   Recipe 64839--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Brown Gravy With Onions</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Brow
   n-Gravy-With-Onions-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1/4 cup unsalted
   butter (cut into 4 pieces)</li> <li>3/4 cup sliced onion</li> <li>2
   tablespoons all-purpose flour</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 cup
   beef broth or stock</li> <li>1 tablespoon whole milk</li> <li>Cooked
   Rice</li> </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Cook rice according to package directions.</li> <li>In a medium
   sauce pan, melt the butter. Once hot, add the onion and a big pinch of
   salt and cook until softened, about 5 to 7 minutes. Until onions are
   tender. Stir often to keep from burning.</li> <li>Stir in the flour and
   and salt and cook for 1 minute.</li> <li>Slowly whisk in the
   broth/stock and cook until thickened, about 3-5 minutes.</li>
   <li>Remove from the heat and whisk in the milk. Serve over rice while
   hot.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes
   4 servings.</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p>

   rel="">Main Meal Recipes</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>

   <html><body><p><strong>Easiest Honey Fried Biscuits</strong>. Topped
   with recipe for delicious easy honey butter.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64824" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64824"

   id="caption-attachment-64824" class="wp-caption-text">Photo credit:
   Pauline Woodards-Respress</p></div> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64822--></p>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easiest Honey Fried Biscuits</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Easiest-Honey
   -Fried-Biscuits-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Biscuits:</h4> <ul><li>1
   tube refrigerated canned biscuits</li> <li>oil for frying</li>
   </ul><h4>Honey Butter:</h4> <ul><li>1/4 pound butter</li> <li>1
   tablespoon honey</li> <li>1/8 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>1/8
   teaspoon vanilla extract</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Biscuits:</h4>
   <ol><li>Heat oil in a large frying pan to 375 F.</li> <li>Open canned
   biscuits and separate. Use your hands to stretch them out
   slightly.</li> <li> <p>Fry biscuits 2-3 minutes on each side or until
   golden brown. Remove to a paper towel-lined plate.</p> </li>
   </ol><h4>Honey Butter:</h4> <ol><li>Melt butter in a small saute pan
   over low heat.</li> <li>Add honey, cinnamon and vanilla. Stir.</li>
   <li>Brush top of biscuits with the honey butter while still warm.</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of yummy <a

   https://myhoneysplace.com/fluffy-homemade-chocolate-pancakes-with-maple
   -syrup/ Wed, 11 Sep 2019 14:22:15 +0000 My Honeys Place Breakfast
   Recipes https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64813 Fluffy Homemade Chocolate
   Pancakes With Maple Syrup. OMG yummy. Breakfast... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/fluffy-homemade-chocolate-pancakes-with
   -maple-syrup/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Fluffy Homemade Chocolate Pancakes With Maple
   Syrup</strong>. OMG yummy. Breakfast at it&rsquo;s best. Included is
   recipe for homemade maple syrup.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64816 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Fluffy-Homema
   de-Chocolate-Pancakes-With-Maple-Syrup.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900" data-pin-description="Fluffy Homemade Chocolate Pancakes
   With Maple Syrup. OMG yummy. Breakfast at it's best. Included is recipe
   for homemade maple syrup."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Fluffy-Hom
   emade-Chocolate-Pancakes-With-Maple-Syrup.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Fluffy-Homemade-Ch
   ocolate-Pancakes-With-Maple-Syrup-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Fluffy-Homemade-Ch
   ocolate-Pancakes-With-Maple-Syrup-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64814--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Fluffy Homemade Pancakes With Maple
   Syrup</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Fluffy-Homema
   de-Chocolate-Pancakes-With-Maple-Syrup-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Pancakes:</h4> <ul><li>1
   1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 Tablespoon white sugar</li> <li>1 1/4
   cups milk</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>3 tablespoons butter (melted)</li>
   <li>1/2 cup chocolate chips</li> <li>1/2 cup white chocolate chips</li>
   </ul><h4>Homemade Maple Syrup:</h4> <ul><li>8 cups granulated
   sugar</li> <li>1 cup packed light or dark brown sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup
   honey</li> <li>4 cups water</li> <li>2 teaspoons pure maple
   extract</li> <li>2 teaspoons pure vanilla extract</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Pancakes:</h4>
   <ol><li>In a large bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, salt
   and sugar. Make a well in the center and pour in the milk, egg and
   melted butter; mix until smooth.</li> <li> <p>Heat a lightly oiled
   large frying pan over medium low heat. Pour the batter onto the large
   frying pan, using approximately 1/2 cup for each pancake. Sprinkle the
   chocolate chips on top. Flip over as soon as you see the mixture
   bubbling and brown the remaining side.</p> </li> </ol><h4>Maple
   Syrup:</h4> <ol><li>In a large 5-6 quart pot, combine the sugars, honey
   and water. Bring the mixture to a boil and reduce the heat to low so
   the mixture gently simmers.</li> <li>Cover the pot and simmer the
   mixture for 15 minutes. Remove the pot from the heat and let it cool
   for 20 minutes before stirring in the maple and vanilla extracts. Let
   the syrup cool in the pot for another 40 minutes, or so, stirring
   occasionally, before filling containers. Once the containers are
   filled, let them cool to room temperature uncovered.</li> <li> <p>Pour
   over pancakes or store covered in jars or other containers in the
   refrigerator. It will keep for up to 2 months in the refrigerator.
   Gently reheat before serving, if desired. Add extra chocolate chips on
   top and sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.</p> </li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes 4 large pancakes and
   5 cups syrup.</p> <p>If you want a real feast, stack the pancakes.</p>
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   specifications I have to meet to shape her?&rdquo;</p> <p>She must
   function on all kinds of situations,<br> She must be able to embrace
   several kids at the same time,<br> Have a hug that can heal anything
   from a bruised knee to a broken heart,<br> She must do all this with
   only two hands,&rdquo;<br> She cures herself when sick and can work 18
   hours a day&rdquo;</p> <p>THE ANGEL was impressed&rdquo; Just two
   hands&hellip;..impossible!</p> <p>And this is the standard
   model?&rdquo;</p> <p>The Angel came closer and touched the

   &ldquo;She is soft&rdquo;, said the Lord,<br> &ldquo;But I have made
   her strong. You can&rsquo;t imagine what she can endure and

   can reason and negotiate&rdquo;</p> <p>The Angel touched her
   cheeks&hellip;.<br> &ldquo;Lord, it seems this creation is leaking! You
   have put too many burdens on her&rdquo;<br> &ldquo;She is not

   Angel&hellip;.. .<br> The Lord said. &ldquo;Tears are her way of
   expressing her grief, her doubts, her love, her loneliness, her
   suffering and her pride.&rdquo;&hellip;</p> <p>This made a big
   impression on the Angel,<br> &ldquo;Lord, you are a genius. You thought
   of everything.<br> A woman is indeed marvelous&rdquo;</p> <p>Lord
   said.&rdquo;Indeed she is.<br> She has strength that amazes a man.<br>
   She can handle trouble and carry heavy burdens.<br> She holds
   happiness, love and opinions.<br> She smiles when she feels like
   screaming.<br> She sings when she feels like crying, cries when happy
   and laughs when afraid.<br> She fights for what she believes in.</p>
   <p>Her love is unconditional.<br> Her heart is broken when a
   next-of-kin or a friend dies but she finds strength to get on with
   life&rdquo;</p> <p>The Angel asked: So she is a perfect being?<br> The
   lord replied: No. <strong>She has just one
   drawback</strong><br><strong>&ldquo;She often forgets what she is
   worth&rdquo;.</strong></p> <p><em>Author unknown.&nbsp;</em></p> </div>

   15:01:02 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Holiday Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64781 5 Easy Holiday Frostings. Use for
   cupcakes, cakes or even... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/5-easy-holiday-frostings/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>5 Easy Holiday Frostings</strong>. Use for
   cupcakes, cakes or even Christmas cookies.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64785 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5-Easy-Holida
   y-Frostings.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="5 Easy Holiday Frostings. Use for cupcakes, cakes
   or even Christmas cookies.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5-Easy-Hol
   iday-Frostings.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5-Easy-Holiday-Fro
   stings-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5-Easy-Holiday-Fro
   stings-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64782--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">5
   Easy Holiday Frostings</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/5-Easy-Holida
   y-Frostings-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Vanilla Butter
   Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup butter</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>4 cups sifted powdered
   sugar</li> <li>5 Tablespoons light cream</li> </ul><h4>Orange Butter
   Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup butter</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
   <li>2 teaspoons orange extract</li> <li>4 cups powdered sugar</li>
   <li>5 Tablespoons light cream</li> <li>A few drops red and yellow food
   coloring</li> </ul><h4>Creamy Cheese Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1 3 oz.
   package cream cheese (softened)</li> <li>1 Tablespoon light cream</li>
   <li>2 1/2 cups powdered sugar</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon vanilla
   extract</li> </ul><h4>Fudge Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>4 squares 1 oz each
   unsweetened chocolate</li> <li>2 cups powdered sugar</li> <li>1/4 cup
   milk</li> <li>4 egg yolks</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
   <li>1/2 cup butter</li> </ul><h4>Vanilla Filling:</h4> <ul><li>1/3 cup
   flour</li> <li>3/4 cup sugar</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li> <li>2 cups
   milk (scaled)</li> <li>2 eggs (beaten)</li> <li>1 Tablespoon
   butter</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Vanilla Butter
   Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Cream butter and salt together. Add vanilla,
   alternating with cream. Beat until blended. Makes 2 1/3 cups.</li>
   </ol><h4>Orange Butter Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Cream butter and salt
   together. Add orange extract, alternating with cream. Beat until
   blended and blend in food coloring. Makes 2 1/3 cups.</li>
   </ol><h4>Creamy Cheese Frosting:</h4> <ol><li> <p>Blend together the
   cream cheese and light cream, beat well. Gradually add and beat in
   sugar. Stir in vanilla. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.</p> </li>
   </ol><h4>Fudge Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Melt chocolate in the top of a
   double boiler, over hot water. Blend in sugar and milk, alternating.
   Add egg yolks one at a time, stir well after each addition. Blend in
   vanilla and butter. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.</li> </ol><h4>Vanilla
   Filling:</h4> <ol><li>Combine flour, 1/2 cup of the sugar and salt.
   Stir milk into the flour mixture. Bring to a boil over low heat,
   stirring constantly. Cook and stir for 3 minutes. Beat remaining sugar
   into eggs. Stir hot liquid slowly into eggs. Return to pan and stir 2
   minutes longer. Stir in butter. Cool; stir in vanilla. Makes 2 1/2
   cups.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>You
   can pipe these frostings or spread with a knife.&nbsp;</p> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See our <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake"
   rel="">Cake</a> or <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cupcakes"
   rel="">Cupcake Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/healthy-nutty-brussels-sprouts/ Wed, 04 Sep
   2019 13:53:24 +0000 My Honeys Place Healthy Recipes Recipes Side Dishes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64767 Healthy Nutty Brussels Sprouts.
   Recipe for a healthy salty twist... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/healthy-nutty-brussels-sprouts/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Healthy Nutty Brussels Sprouts.</strong> Recipe
   for a healthy salty twist to Brussels Sprouts. Your family will love
   this side dish.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64772 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Nutty-Brussel
   sSprouts2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Healthy Nutty Brussels Sprouts. Recipe for a
   healthy salty twist to Brussels Sprouts. Your family will love this
   side dish.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Nutty-Brus
   selsSprouts2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Nutty-BrusselsSpro
   uts2-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Nutty-BrusselsSpro
   uts2-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><b>Brussels sprouts</b>&nbsp;are high in fiber,
   vitamins, minerals and antioxidants, making them a nutritious addition
   to your diet.</p> <p><strong>Nuts</strong> are packed a number of
   vitamins and minerals, including magnesium and vitamin E. And are a
   good sources of fat, fiber and protein.</p> <p>With this recipe you get
   a double dose of<strong> healthy</strong>.</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   64768--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Nutty Brussels Sprouts</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Nutty-Brussel
   sSprouts2-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>15 Brussels
   sprouts (halved lengthwise)</li> <li>1 1/2 Tablespoons butter</li>
   <li>1 1/2 Tablespoons olive oil</li> <li>3 cloves garlic (smashed with
   the flat of a knife)</li> <li>1 cup salted peanuts or nuts of your
   choice</li> <li>Parmesan cheese (freshly grated)</li> <li>Pepper to
   taste</li> </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Melt butter and olive oil in a medium skillet (over medium-high
   heauntil butter is foamy.</li> <li>Reduce heat to medium, add smashed
   garlic and cook until lightly browned.</li> <li>Remove garlic and
   discard.</li> <li>Add sprouts cut side down, cover, and cook without
   stirring on medium-low heat 10-15 minutes or until tender when pierced
   with a knife.</li> <li>The cut side of the sprouts should get nice and
   browned, with a nutty, buttery flavor enhanced by garlic.</li> <li>Add
   the nuts.</li> <li>Top with freshly grated Parmesan and pepper to
   taste.</li> <li>Serve warm.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/side-dishes/"
   rel="">Side Dishes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:

   Sep 2019 12:32:57 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Cooking
   Tips & Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64758 What
   To Do If you Are Out Of Eggs. Have... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong>What To Do If you Are Out Of Eggs</strong>. Have
   a recipes but no eggs in the house? Use these substitutes:</p> <p><img

   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Each substitute equals 1

   peanut butter</li> <li>1/2 mashed banana</li> <li>1/4 Cup vegetable
   oil</li> <li>1/4 Cup yogurt or buttermilk</li> <li>3 Tablespoons Nut
   butter</li> <li>1/4 Cup carbonated water</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-coconut-red-velvet-cake/ Mon, 02 Sep
   2019 14:23:37 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64749 Homemade Coconut Red Velvet Cake.
   Recipe for a moist cake... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-coconut-red-velvet-cake/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Coconut Red Velvet Cake</strong>.
   Recipe for a moist cake with a coconut buttercream frosting.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64752 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Coco
   nut-Red-Velvet-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Coconut Red Velvet Cake. Recipe for a
   moist cake with a coconut buttercream frosting.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-C
   oconut-Red-Velvet-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Coconut-R
   ed-Velvet-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Coconut-R
   ed-Velvet-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64750--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Coconut Red Velvet Cake</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Homemade-Coco
   nut-Red-Velvet-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For The Cake:</h4>
   <ul><li>3 cups cake flour (leveled)</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking
   soda</li> <li>2 Tablespoons unsweetened natural cocoa powder</li>
   <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/2 cup unsalted butter (softened)</li>
   <li>2 cups granulated sugar</li> <li>1 cup vegetable oil</li> <li>4
   large eggs (room temperature and separated)</li> <li>1 Tablespoon pure
   vanilla extract</li> <li>1 teaspoon distilled white vinegar</li>
   <li>liquid or gel red food coloring</li> <li>1 cup buttermilk (at room
   temperature)</li> </ul><h4>For the Coconut Buttercream Frosting:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 8 oz package cream cheese (softened)</li> <li>1 cup butter or
   margarine (softened)</li> <li>6 tablespoons milk</li> <li>2 teaspoon
   vanilla extract</li> <li>2 16 oz package powdered sugar (sifted)</li>
   <li>2 7 oz package sweetened flaked coconut</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For The Cake:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350&deg;F.</li> <li> <p>Grease two 9-inch cake
   pans or three 8-inch cake pans, line with parchment paper, then grease
   the parchment paper.</p> </li> <li>Whisk the flour, baking soda, cocoa
   powder, and salt together in a large bowl. Set aside.</li> <li>Using a
   handheld mixer, beat the butter and sugar together on medium-high speed
   until combined, about 1 minute. Scrape down the sides and up the bottom
   of the bowl with a rubber spatula as needed. Add the oil, egg yolks,
   vanilla extract, and vinegar and beat on high for 2 minutes. (Set the
   egg whites aside.) Scrape down the sides and up the bottom of the bowl
   with a rubber spatula as needed.</li> <li>With the mixer on low speed,
   add the dry ingredients in 2-3 additions alternating with the
   buttermilk. Beat in your desired amount of food coloring just until
   combined. I use 1-2 teaspoons gel food coloring. Vigorously whisk or
   beat the 4 egg whites on high speed until fluffy peaks form as pictured
   above, about 3 minutes. Gently fold into cake batter.</li> <li>Divide
   batter between cake pans. Bake for 30-32 minutes or until the tops of
   the cakes spring back when gently touched and a toothpick inserted in
   the center comes out clean. If the cakes need a little longer as
   determined by wet crumbs on the toothpick, bake for longer. However,
   careful not to over bake as the cakes may dry out. Remove cakes from
   the oven and cool completely in the pans set on a wire rack. The cakes
   must be completely cool before frosting and assembling.</li>
   </ol><h4>For The Coconut Buttercream Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Beat cream
   cheese and butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy;
   add milk and vanilla, beating well. Gradually add sugar, beating until
   smooth. Stir in coconut.</li> <li>Frost cooled cake.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of your Delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake"
   rel="">Cake Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-tortellini-italian-pasta/ Thu, 29 Aug
   2019 14:50:55 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64737 Easy Tortellini Italian Pasta. A
   homemade recipe that is the... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-tortellini-italian-pasta/">Continu
   e reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Tortellini Italian Pasta</strong>. A
   homemade recipe that is the easiest way to get a delicious dinner
   meal.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64743 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Tortelli
   ni-Italian-Pasta.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Tortellini Italian Pasta. A homemade recipe
   that is the easiest way to get a delicious dinner meal.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Torte
   llini-Italian-Pasta.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Tortellini-It
   alian-Pasta-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Tortellini-It
   alian-Pasta-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64738--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Tortellini Italian Pasta</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Tortelli
   ni-Italian-Pasta-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 package three
   cheese Tortellini pasta</li> <li>Italian sauce ((recipe below))</li>
   <li>shredded ricotta cheese (for topping)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Make Italian sauce:</h4>
   <ol><li>1/2 cup olive oil</li> <li>1 large onion, minced</li> <li>3
   cloves garlic, minced</li> <li>4 cups water</li> <li> <p>2 (32 ounce)
   cans crushed diced tomatoes</p> </li> <li> <p>1 (16 ounce) can tomato
   paste</p> </li> <li>1/4 cup chopped fresh basil</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   baking soda</li> <li>1 teaspoon white sugar</li> <li>salt and pepper to
   taste</li> <li>Heat olive oil in a large saucepan over medium-high
   heat. Saute onion and garlic in hot oil until onion is translucent, 5
   to 7 minutes.</li> <li>Reduce heat to medium-low. Add water, crushed
   tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, baking soda, and sugar; season with salt
   and pepper. Stir mixture, bring to a simmer, and cook until the sauce
   is thickened, about 2 hours.</li> </ol><h4>Cook pasta as directed on
   package and drain.</h4> <ol><li> <p>Pour sauce over pasta and add
   shredded cheese on top.</p> </li> <li>Serve hot and enjoy.</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Will make 12
   servings.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-vanilla-cream-filled-donuts/ Wed, 28
   Aug 2019 23:52:04 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64726 Homemade Vanilla Cream Filled
   Donuts. Making donuts at home never... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-vanilla-cream-filled-donuts/">
   Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Vanilla Cream Filled Donuts</strong>.
   Making donuts at home never tasted so good.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64733 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Vani
   lla-Cream-Filled-Donuts.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Vanilla Cream Filled Donuts. Making
   donuts at home never tasted so good.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-V
   anilla-Cream-Filled-Donuts.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Vanilla-C
   ream-Filled-Donuts-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Vanilla-C
   ream-Filled-Donuts-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64730--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Vanilla Cream Filled Donuts</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Vani
   lla-Cream-Filled-Donuts-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the donuts:</h4>
   <ul><li>1/8 cup warm water 105 to 115 degrees F.</li> <li>1 package
   regular or quick-acting yeast</li> <li>3/4 cup lukewarm milk scalded
   then cooled</li> <li>1/4 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   salt</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1/6 cup solid vegetable shortening</li>
   <li>2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>vegetable oil for frying</li>
   </ul><h4>For the vanilla filling:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup butter</li>
   <li>2 cups sifted confectioners' sugar</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon clear
   vanilla extract</li> <li>1 tablespoon milk</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the donuts:</h4>
   <ol><li>Place the warm water in a mixing bowl. Sprinkle the yeast
   evenly over the water to dissolve. When it has bubbled (proofed), add
   the milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening, and 1 cup of the flour.</li>
   <li>Beat the mixture on medium speed, scraping down the sides of the
   bowl as needed, for about 2 minutes.</li> <li>Stir in the remaining
   flour by hand until the dough is smooth.</li> <li>Cover the dough with
   a damp towel and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about
   1 hour.</li> <li>Turn the dough out onto a floured work surface. Pat it
   flat then roll it out with a rolling pin until it is 1/2-inch
   thick.</li> <li>Cut the dough with round cookie cutters. Place the
   cutouts, evenly spaced, on floured baking sheets and let rise in a
   warm, draft-free place until doubled in size, about 30-40 minutes.</li>
   </ol><h4>While the donuts are rising, make the vanilla filling:</h4>
   <ol><li>In a mixing bowl, cream together the shortening and butter
   until smooth and blended. Gradually add the confectioners&rsquo; sugar
   (1/2 cup at a timwith the mixer running. Add the vanilla and milk and
   beat the filling until light and fluffy. The filling can be stored up
   to 2 weeks in an airtight container in the refrigerator.</li> <li>When
   the donuts have risen, heat the vegetable oil to 350 degrees F in a
   deep fryer or Dutch oven.</li> <li>Carefully slide the dough into the
   hot oil. Turn the doughnuts as they brown, they should cook for about 1
   minute per side. Do this in batches as needed making sure to keep the
   oil at 350 degrees F.</li> <li>Carefully remove the browned donuts from
   the oil with a slotted metal spoon. Set on a rack to drain.</li>
   <li>When the donuts are cool, using a sharp, narrow knife, carefully
   create a pocket inside the donuts to hold the filling.</li> <li>Fill a
   pastry bag with a plain tip with the vanilla filling. Insert the tip
   into the hole of the donuts and gently, but generously, fill with the
   cream filling.</li> <li>Dust the filled donuts with additional
   confectioners&rsquo; sugar</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Be sure to see
   more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64722 I Got Flowers Today. A Sad but
   beautiful story about... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong>I Got Flowers Today</strong>. A Sad but
   beautiful story about domestic abuse.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64723 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/I-got-flowers
   -today.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="I Got
   Flowers Today. A Sad but beautiful story about domestic abuse.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/I-got-flow
   ers-today.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/I-got-flowers-toda
   y-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/I-got-flowers-toda
   y-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>I
   got flowers today. It wasn&rsquo;t my birthday or any other special
   day. We had our first argument last night. He said a lot of cruel
   things that really hurt me. I&nbsp;<span class="text_exposed_show">know
   he was sorry and didn&rsquo;t mean the things he said. Because I got
   flowers today.</span></p> <div class="text_exposed_show"> <p>I got
   flowers today. It wasn&rsquo;t our anniversary or any other special
   day. Last night, he threw me into a wall and started to choke me. It
   seemed like a nightmare. I couldn&rsquo;t believe it was real. I woke
   up this morning sore and bruised all over. I know he must be sorry.
   Because he sent me flowers today.</p> <p>I got flowers today. It
   wasn&rsquo;t Mother&rsquo;s Day or any other special day. Last night,
   he beat me up again. And it was much worse than all other times. If I
   leave him, what will I do? How will I take care of my kids? What about
   money? I&rsquo;m afraid of him and scared to leave. But I know he must
   be sorry. Because he sent me flowers today.</p> <p>I got flowers today.
   Today was a very special day. It was the day of my funeral. Last night
   he finally killed me. He beat me to death. If only I had gathered
   enough courage and strength to leave him, I would not have gotten
   flowers today.</p> <p>This poem is dedicated to all the victims and
   survivors of Domestic Violence.</p> <p>You ask, why didn&rsquo;t she
   leave?</p> <p>I ask, why did he hit?</p> <p><strong><em>Author
   Unknown</em></strong></p> <p>If you are in an abusive relationship call
   <strong>1-800-799-7233</strong> for help.</p> </div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/amazing-information/"
   rel="">Amazing Information</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/yummiest-chocolate-bundt-cake/ Tue, 27 Aug
   2019 13:16:07 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64710 Yummiest And Easiest Chocolate Bundt
   Cake. Topped with creamy frosting... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/yummiest-chocolate-bundt-cake/">Continu
   e reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Yummiest And Easiest Chocolate Bundt
   Cake</strong>. Topped with creamy frosting makes this recipe the most
   delicious cake ever.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64713
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Yummiest-And-
   Easiest-Chocolate-Bundt-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Yummiest And Easiest Chocolate Bundt Cake. Topped
   with creamy frosting makes this recipe the most delicious cake
   ever.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Yummiest-A
   nd-Easiest-Chocolate-Bundt-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Yummiest-And-Easie
   st-Chocolate-Bundt-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Yummiest-And-Easie
   st-Chocolate-Bundt-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64711--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Yummiest And Easiest Chocolate Bundt
   Cake</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Yummiest-And-
   Easiest-Chocolate-Bundt-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the cake:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 package yellow cake mix</li> <li>1 package instant chocolate
   pudding mix</li> <li>1/2 cup white sugar</li> <li>3/4 cup water</li>
   <li>4 eggs (beaten)</li> <li>1 cup sour cream (softened )</li> <li>1/2
   cup milk chocolate chips (melted)</li> </ul><h4>For the topping:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 1/2 cups powdered sugar</li> <li>5 Tablespoons whole
   milk</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon pure vanilla extract</li> <li>1/8 teaspoon
   salt</li> </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>For the cake:</h4> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 325 degrees F.</li>
   <li>Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt pan.</li> <li>In a medium bowl,
   stir together the cake mix, instant pudding and sugar. Add the water,
   oil, eggs, and sour cream, mix until well blended.</li> <li> <p>Melt
   the chocolate chips in your microwave. About 30 seconds. Then stir into
   mix. They all do not have to be melted. </p> </li> <li>Pour into the
   prepared Bundt pan.</li> <li>Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in the preheated
   oven. Cake is done when a toothpick inserted comes out clean.</li>
   <li>Cool in pan for 10 minutes before inverting onto a wire rack to
   cool completely.</li> </ol><h4>For the topping:</h4> <ol><li>Whisk
   together powdered sugar, milk, vanilla, and salt. Pour over the cooled
   cake.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake+" rel="">Cake
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/loving-a-drug-addict/ Fri, 23 Aug 2019
   13:53:57 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How To and
   Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64690 Loving A Drug Addict. What it
   is like living with... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/loving-a-drug-addict/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Loving A Drug Addict</strong>. What it is like
   living with a person with a drug addiction. Tips that will help.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64691 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Loving-A-Drug
   -Addict.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Loving A Drug Addict. What it is like living with
   a person with a drug addiction. Tips that will help."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Loving-A-D
   rug-Addict.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Loving-A-Drug-Addi
   ct-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Loving-A-Drug-Addi
   ct-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Loving a drug addict or an active alcoholic is the
   hardest thing you will ever do.</p> <p>Watching someone you love, that
   has fought so hard to beat addiction, throw everything away and sink
   back into a life that will most likely lead to jail or death, is one of
   the hardest things you will ever do.</p> <p>All you wanted was to help
   them back to a clean and sober life but you realize by doing this, as
   you have so many times before, will now just be enabling them because
   it will show them th<span class="text_exposed_show">at you will always
   be there to bail them out. </span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">You want to grab and shake them and say
   &ldquo;What are you doing?!?!&rdquo; But, at some point you realize
   that it wouldn&rsquo;t make a difference. So you sit back and watch the
   tragedy unfold, as if you are watching a movie. </span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">Feeling helpless to stop it, feeling like you
   haven&rsquo;t done enough to help, even though you know only the addict
   can help themselves.</span></p> <p><span class="text_exposed_show"><br>
   Battling a drug and/or an alcohol addiction is a beast for the person
   addicted and the ones who love them.</span></p> <p>Helping a loved one
   struggling with drug or alcohol addiction is often a long and
   heartbreaking journey. At times, it can be so overwhelming that
   ignoring the situation may seem like an easier solution.</p>
   <p>Sweeping the issue under the rug can be more damaging to you, your
   family, and the person you&rsquo;re concerned about. As painful as it
   may be, it&rsquo;s important that you take the time to encourage your
   loved one to get the help they need.</p> <p>Although you may see this
   as selfish, it&rsquo;s incredibly important that you&rsquo;re able to
   be there for others and make the best decisions possible.<strong> Make
   sure your own needs are met</strong> by getting enough sleep,
   exercising, and eating well. Don&rsquo;t be afraid to go to therapy to
   get help if you find yourself struggling due to your loved one&rsquo;s
   drug addiction.</p> <p><strong>My story:</strong></p> <p>20 years ago
   my husband was an alcoholic. Other than the drinking he was the perfect
   man. Kind, loving, gentle&nbsp; and generous.&nbsp; But I could not
   live with the &ldquo;bad&rdquo; side of him. I gave him a choice. It
   was either me or the alcohol and prayed he would choose me. I stood my
   ground, even though it was VERY hard on both of us. On a couple
   occasions I threw him out of the house. It was a two year battle. But
   WE finally won. He has been alcohol free for 18 years now. He ended up
   loving me more that the alcohol. We are so very happy now. <strong>The
   answer is</strong>: that I did not enable him and stuck to my guns.
   Tough LOVE and PRAYERS do work. I am not telling you that it will work
   with your loved one, but if they can not change then you are better off
   without them. <strong>You must take care of yourself
   first!&nbsp;</strong>You can not help anyone who will not help
   themselves.</p> <p><span class="text_exposed_show">So l am asking you
   to stand with me in prayer for every family member and friend who has
   lost or is losing their battle with drugs and alcohol and those who
   continue to conquer it!&nbsp;</span></p> <p><strong>A Friend&rsquo;s
   Story:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64703"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/53081043_2006
   287059441122_5229622050137571328_n.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="623"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/53081043_2
   006287059441122_5229622050137571328_n.jpg 539w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/53081043_200628705
   9441122_5229622050137571328_n-225x400.jpg 225w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/53081043_200628705
   9441122_5229622050137571328_n-84x150.jpg 84w" sizes="(max-width: 350px)
   100vw, 350px"></p> <p>&ldquo;My name is Randall. 3 years ago, I spent
   the last $60 I had on pills to get high- instead of buying my baby
   Diapers or giving it to my kids before I checked int<span
   class="text_exposed_show">o a Detox Center. A few months before that on
   Christmas Eve 2015, my girlfriend left me and took my kids, I lost
   everything including my soul. I was told I was a worthless junkie, that
   I should kill myself, that I&rsquo;d never make it. They said my life
   would never change, that I would always be the same old
   Randall.</span></p> <div class="text_exposed_show"> <p>But
   &ldquo;They&rdquo; were wrong.</p> <p>Today by The Amazing Grace of God
   I have 3 years of recovery. 1,096 days that I have let God lead me 24
   hours at a time. I have 3 amazing and beautiful babies. I am a Father,
   a Son, a Brother, an Uncle, and a Friend. The Director of Addiction
   Recovery Care&rsquo;s Ashland Outpatient Center, a College Degree and
   working towards a Bachelor in Social Work Degree at Morehead State
   University. And I&rsquo;m not done yet!</p> <p>3 years ago I
   couldn&rsquo;t go 1 minute without wanting to get high. I had thoughts
   of killing my self daily, however, was too big of a coward to do it. I
   would go to my Sisters grave daily, praying for God to take my life
   because I hated who I was and had lost everything. If I could describe
   my life for 12 and a half years in a quote it would be this:</p>
   <p>&ldquo;The reason why many are still troubled, still seeking, still
   making little forward progress is because they haven&rsquo;t yet come
   to the end of themselves. We&rsquo;re still trying to give orders, and
   interfering with God&rsquo;s work within us.&rdquo;<br> ~ A. W.
   Tozer~</p> <p>But the best thing about this life is that it can change
   in one moment. Don&rsquo;t sit around and wait for it to happen. Stand
   up and be the change. Be your own hero.</p> <p>To any person who is
   addicted: You are not just a Junkie, a Nobody, you have a grand
   purpose. You are built from every mistake you have ever made. You are
   not too far gone, too hopeless, too unforgiven, to have a new life. You
   deserve recovery, you deserve to truly live. You are A Child of
   God!</p> <p>Today, I woke up happy to be alive. I looked in the mirror
   and respected the man staring back at me. Today, I know of freedom and
   what it means to be alive. Not because of anything I have done but
   because I surrendered my life to the Lord and let him take control. I
   give all Glory to Him.</p> <p>Faith will tell you to have patience when
   everything else is telling you to panic.<br> Faith will tell you to
   hold on when everything else is telling you to let go.<br> Faith will
   tell you to push forward when everything else is telling you to pull
   back.</p> <p>Choose freedom and recovery for yourself too. Call <a
   href="https://www.samhsa.gov/find-help/national-helpline"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">SAMHSA&rsquo;s National
   Helpline</a>,&nbsp;<strong>1-800-662-HELP (4357)</strong>, (also known
   as the Treatment Referral Routing Service) or TTY:&nbsp;1-800-487-4889
   is a confidential, free, 24-hour-a-day, 365-day-a-year, information
   service, in English and Spanish, for individuals and family members
   facing mental and/or substance use disorders. This service provides
   referrals to local treatment facilities, support groups, and
   community-based organizations. Callers can also order free publications
   and other information.</p> <p>Always remember the breath of life is so
   much purer after drowning for so long in your own pain and misery.
   Please don&rsquo;t be afraid of change- Embrace It. It may be hard at
   first but then again It may be that answered prayer you or someone else
   has been so desperately praying for all those years to set you
   free.</p> <p>Today because I put God First in my life everything the
   enemy had stolen has been restored and I can not walk one day without
   him or do anything without Him in my life.&rdquo;</p> </div>
   <p><strong>Great information:</strong></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zuW8euvDPKM" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/health/"
   rel="">Health Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/2-step-method-to-clean-your-grout/ Fri, 23
   Aug 2019 12:00:50 +0000 My Honeys Place Household Tips & Tricks How To
   and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64681 2 Step Method To Clean Your
   Grout. To clean your... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/2-step-method-to-clean-your-grout/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>2 Step Method To Clean Your Grout</strong>. To
   clean your dirtiest grout use this tip, it really works. Now you will
   not have to replace and you will save money. Makes it look like
   new.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64683 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2-Step-Method
   -To-Clean-Your-Grout.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="2 Step Method To Clean Your Grout. To clean your
   dirtiest grout use this tip, it really works. Now you will not have to
   replace and you will save money. Makes it look like new.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2-Step-Met
   hod-To-Clean-Your-Grout.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2-Step-Method-To-C
   lean-Your-Grout-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/2-Step-Method-To-C
   lean-Your-Grout-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Step 1:</strong></p> <p>Combine
   ingredients, mop onto floor, let set for 30 minutes. Then mop with a
   CLEAN damp mop with warm water.</p> <p>1 Cup white vinegar</p> <p>1
   Tablespoon Dawn dish soap</p> <p>1 Cup baking soda</p> <p>2 Gallons
   very warm tap water</p> <p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><span
   dir="ltr"><span class="_3l3x">Don&rsquo;t re-grout. Paint your grout
   with Grout Renew . You can buy it at Home Depot, Lowe&rsquo;s or
   Amazon. Very inexpensive. It also seals your grout too. I&rsquo;ve used
   it on my floors and in the shower for my grout there. You can do any
   color or match the current one.</span></span></p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-64682"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/grout-pic.jpg
   " alt="" width="225" height="225" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/grout-pic.
   jpg 225w,

   jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/grout-pic-50x50.jp
   g 50w" sizes="(max-width: 225px) 100vw, 225px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-pecan-vanilla-cream-cake/ Thu, 22
   Aug 2019 15:03:28 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64671 Homemade Pecan Vanilla Cream Cake.
   Dessert recipe for an amazing... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-pecan-vanilla-cream-cake/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Pecan Vanilla Cream Cake</strong>.
   Dessert recipe for an amazing and moist layered cake.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64674 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Peca
   n-Vanilla-Cream-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Pecan Vanilla Cream Cake. Dessert recipe
   for an amazing and moist layered cake."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-P
   ecan-Vanilla-Cream-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Pecan-Van
   illa-Cream-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Pecan-Van
   illa-Cream-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64672--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Pecan Vanilla Cream
   Cake</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Peca
   n-Vanilla-Cream-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the cake:</h4>
   <ul><li>8 tablespoons butter (softened)</li> <li>1/2 cup vegetable
   shortening</li> <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>5 egg yolks (saving the egg
   white in a separate bowl)</li> <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>1
   teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 cup
   buttermilk</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla</li> <li>1 1/4 cups
   sweetened shredded coconut</li> <li>1 cup chopped toasted pecans</li>
   <li>5 egg whites (stiffly beaten)</li> </ul><h4>For the frosting:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 8 oz. package cream cheese (softened)</li> <li>6 tablespoons
   butter (softened)</li> <li>1 pound box powdered sugar</li> <li>1
   teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1 3/4 cups chopped toasted pecans
   (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the cake:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees.</li> <li> <p>Grease and flour 3
   9-inch cake pans, I made a 2 layer cake and saved the other layer for a
   chocolate cake. Which is my husband's favorite.</p> </li> <li>Using an
   electric mixer, cream butter and shortening.</li> <li>Add sugar and
   beat until smooth.</li> <li>Add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.</li>
   <li>In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, and salt.</li>
   <li>Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternating with
   buttermilk.</li> <li>Stir in vanilla extract.</li> <li>Stir in coconut
   and pecans.</li> <li>Fold in egg whites and pour batter into prepared
   pans.</li> <li>Bake at 350 degrees for 22 to 25 minutes. Let cool.</li>
   </ol><h4>For the frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Beat cream cheese and butter
   until smooth.</li> <li>Beat in powdered sugar 1 cup at a time.</li>
   <li>Add vanilla extract and stir in pecans, if desired. If too thick
   you can add 2 Tablespoons of milk.</li> <li>Spread frosting on top of
   bottom layer of cake.</li> <li>Top with second layer. Cover with
   Frosting.</li> <li>Top with third layer and spread remaining frosting
   on top and sides.</li> <li>Store in refrigerator.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our
   delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake" rel="">Cake
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-chocolate-mint-brownies/ Mon, 19 Aug
   2019 15:11:43 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Holiday Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64665 The Best Chocolate Mint Brownies.
   Soft and chewy with a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-chocolate-mint-brownies/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>The Best Chocolate Mint Brownies</strong>. Soft
   and chewy with a peppermint taste. Easy recipe for Christmas or any
   Holiday.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64668 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Best-Choc
   olate-Mint-Brownies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="The Best Chocolate Mint Brownies. Soft and chewy
   with a peppermint taste. Easy recipe for Christmas or any
   Holiday.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Best-C
   hocolate-Mint-Brownies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Best-Chocolate
   -Mint-Brownies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Best-Chocolate
   -Mint-Brownies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64666--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">The
   Best Chocolate Mint Brownies</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Best-Choc
   olate-Mint-Brownies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 box fudgy brownie
   mix</li> <li>2 cups powdered sugar</li> <li>8 Tablespoons butter
   (softened)</li> <li>2 Tablespoons milk</li> <li>1 or 2 drops green food
   coloring</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoon mint extract</li> <li>6 ounces
   semi-sweet chocolate chips</li> <li>8 Tablespoons butter</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Bake brownies in 9&times;13 inch pan, according to package
   directions. Remove from pan and let cool.</li> <li>Combine the powdered
   sugar, milk, butter, green food coloring, and mint extract. Pour over
   the cooled brownies and smooth out with a spatula. Refrigerate for
   another half hour.</li> <li>Melt the chocolate chips in butter in the
   microwave or a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Pour over the
   chilled brownies &amp; mint. Place back in the refrigerator to let it
   set, at least a half hour.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our almost 2000 <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   22:15:22 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64649 Mexican Style Chilaquiles. Easy
   recipe that has chili sauce and... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mexican-style-chilaquiles/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Mexican Style Chilaquiles.</strong> Easy recipe
   that has chili sauce and tortillas mixed into one delicious plate.
   Topped with cheese. Serve with a salad for a delicious meal.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64653 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Mexican-Style
   -Chilaquiles.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Mexican Style Chilaquiles. Easy recipe that has
   chili sauce and tortillas mixed into one delicious plate. Topped with
   cheese. Serve with a salad for a delicious meal.&nbsp;&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Mexican-St
   yle-Chilaquiles.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Mexican-Style-Chil
   aquiles-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Mexican-Style-Chil
   aquiles-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64650--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Mexican Style Chilaquiles</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Mexican-Style
   -Chilaquiles-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 dozen corn
   tortillas (preferably stale, or left out overnight to dry out.)</li>
   <li>Corn oil</li> <li>Salt to taste</li> <li>1 1/2 to 2 cups red chili
   sauce or salsa</li> <li>Parmesan or Cotija cheese for topping</li>
   <li>Cilantro (chopped red onion for garnish, optional)</li> </ul></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Fry the
   tortillas: In a large sauteed pan, coat pan generously with corn oil,
   (1/8 inch), heat on medium high to high. When the oil is hot, add the
   tortillas and fry until golden brown. Remove tortillas to a paper towel
   lined plate to soak up excess oil. Sprinkle a little salt on the
   tortillas.</li> <li> <p>Heat the salsa or red chili sauce: Add 2 Tbsp
   oil to pan, bring to high heat again. Add the salsa or red chili sauce
   and let cook for several minutes.</p> </li> <li> <p>Add the fried
   tortillas to the sauce. Gently turn over the pieces of tortilla until
   they are all well coated with the sauce. Let cook for a few minutes
   more.</p> </li> <li>Remove from heat and top with cheese, cilantro and
   red onion.</li> <li>Serve warm.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><b>See more
   of our delicious&nbsp;&nbsp;<a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></b></p></body></html> <div

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/strawberry-buttercream-filled-puff-pastry/
   Sun, 18 Aug 2019 00:27:04 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64621 Strawberry Buttercream Filled Puff
   Pastry. Easy dessert recipe that has... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/strawberry-buttercream-filled-puff-past
   ry/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Strawberry Buttercream Filled Puff
   Pastry</strong>. Easy dessert recipe that has a light and tender pastry
   that puffs into flaky, golden layers. Filled with a strawberry
   buttercream filling.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64625
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strawberry-Bu
   ttercream-Filled-Puff-Pastry.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Strawberry Buttercream Filled Puff Pastry. Easy
   dessert recipe that has a light and tender pastry that puffs into
   flaky, golden layers. Filled with a strawberry buttercream
   filling.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strawberry
   -Buttercream-Filled-Puff-Pastry.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strawberry-Butterc
   ream-Filled-Puff-Pastry-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strawberry-Butterc
   ream-Filled-Puff-Pastry-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64622--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Strawberry Cream Filled Puff
   Pastry</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strawberry-Bu
   ttercream-Filled-Puff-Pastry-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the bottom and
   top:</h4> <ul><li>2 count frozen puff pastry sheets</li> </ul><h4>For
   the Strawberry Buttercream Filling:</h4> <ul><li>1 cup butter
   (softened)</li> <li>4 cups powdered sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla
   extract</li> <li>1/4 cup strawberry jam</li> <li>1 drop red food
   coloring (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the bottom and
   top:</h4> <ol><li> <p>Thaw pastry sheet (at room temperature) for 40
   minutes before using.</p> </li> <li>Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.</li>
   <li> <p>Unfold pastry on lightly floured surface. If there are any
   cracks in the pastry, sprinkle with water and press together to seal.
   Roll out to 1/2 inch thickness. Cut in round shapes with a cookie
   cutter.</p> </li> <li>Place on ungreased cookie sheet.</li> <li>Bake
   for 10 to 12 minutes or until the pastry is puffed, brown and
   crisp.</li> <li>For more golden brown color, brush top only of unbaked
   pastry with an egg wash (1 egg beaten with 1 tbsp water).</li> <li>Let
   cool and make Filling.</li> </ol><h4>Strawberry Cream Filling:</h4>
   <ol><li>With a mixer on medium speed, whip the butter for 2 minutes
   until it is almost white in color.</li> <li>Add in the powdered sugar,
   vanilla extract, and strawberry jam. (If you&rsquo;d like a pinker
   color then add in a drop of red food coloring.</li> <li>Beat on low
   speed for 2-3 minutes. If the filling is too stiff for spreading, you
   can add in a tablespoon more of jam.</li> <li>Place between 2 puff
   pastry.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our almost 2000 <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64595 The Winter Of Your Life. This is
   just a beautifully... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-winter-of-your-life/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>The Winter Of Your Life</strong>. This is just a
   beautifully written piece; and so true. Take a couple of minutes to
   read it. You&rsquo;ll be glad you did.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64596 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Winter-Of
   -Your-Life.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="The Winter Of Your Life. This is just a
   beautifully written piece; and so true. Take a couple of minutes to
   read it. You'll be glad you did."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Winter
   -Of-Your-Life.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Winter-Of-Your
   -Life-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Winter-Of-Your
   -Life-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p
   style="text-align: left;"><strong>AND THEN IT IS
   WINTER&nbsp;</strong><br> You know time has a way of moving quickly and
   catching you unaware of the passing years. It seems like yesterday that
   I was young, just married, and embarking on my new life with my mate.
   Yet in a way, it seems like eons ago and I wonder where all those years
   went.</p> <p>I know that I lived them all. I have glimpses of how it
   was back then and of all my hopes and dreams. But, here it is&hellip;
   the winter of my life, and it catches me by surprise&hellip; How did I
   get here so fast? Where did the years go and where did my youth go? I
   remember well seeing older people through the years and thinking that
   those &ldquo;older people&rdquo; were years away from me and that
   winter was so far off that I could not fathom it or imagine fully what
   it would be like.</p> <p>But, here it is&hellip;my friends are retired
   and getting grey&hellip; they move slower and I see an older person in
   myself now. Some are in better and some worse shape than me&hellip;
   but, I see the great change&hellip; Not like the ones that I remember
   who were young and vibrant&hellip;but, like me, their age is beginning
   to show and we are now those older folks that we used to see and never
   thought we&rsquo;d be.</p> <p>Each day now, I find that just getting a
   shower is a real target for the day! And taking a nap is not a treat
   anymore&hellip; it&rsquo;s mandatory! Cause if I don&rsquo;t on my own
   free will&hellip; I just fall asleep where I sit!</p> <p>And so&hellip;
   now I enter this new season of my life unprepared for all the aches and
   pains and the loss of strength and ability to go and do things that I
   wish I had done but never did!! But, at least I know, that though the
   winter has come, and I&rsquo;m not sure how long it will last&hellip;
   this I know, that when it&rsquo;s over on this earth&hellip; it&rsquo;s
   over. A new adventure will begin!</p> <p>Yes, I have regrets. There are
   things I wish I hadn&rsquo;t done&hellip; things I should have done,
   but indeed, there are also many things I&rsquo;m happy to have done.
   It&rsquo;s all in a lifetime.</p> <p>So, if you&rsquo;re not in your
   winter yet&hellip; let me remind you, that it will be here faster than
   you think. So, whatever you would like to accomplish in your life,
   please do it quickly! Don&rsquo;t put things off too long!! Life goes
   by quickly. So, do what you can TODAY, as you can never be sure whether
   this is your winter or not!</p> <p>You have no promise that you will
   see all the seasons of your life&hellip; so, LIVE FOR TODAY and say all
   the things that you want your loved ones to remember.. and hope that
   they appreciate and love you for all the things that you have done for
   them in all the years past!!</p> <p>&ldquo;Life&rdquo; is a GIFT to
   you. The way you live your life is your gift to those who come after.
   Make it a fantastic one.</p> <p>Remember: &ldquo;It is Health that is
   real Wealth and not pieces of gold and silver.&rdquo;</p> <p>~Your kids
   are becoming you&hellip;&hellip;but your grandchildren are perfect!<br>
   ~Going out is good.. coming home is even better!<br> ~You forget
   names&hellip; but it&rsquo;s OK, because other people forgot they even
   knew you!!!<br> ~You realize you&rsquo;re never going to be really good
   at anything&hellip;. especially golf.<br> ~The things you used to care
   to do, you no longer care to do, but you really do care that you
   don&rsquo;t care to do them anymore.</p> <p>~You sleep better on a
   lounge chair with the TV blaring than in bed. It&rsquo;s called
   &ldquo;pre-sleep.&rdquo;<br> ~You miss the days when everything worked
   with just an &ldquo;ON&rdquo; and &ldquo;OFF&rdquo; switch..<br> ~You
   tend to use more 4 letter words &hellip;
   &ldquo;what?&rdquo;&hellip;&rdquo;when?&rdquo;&hellip;???<br> ~Now that
   you can afford expensive jewelry, it&rsquo;s not safe to wear it
   anywhere.<br> ~You notice everything they sell in stores is
   &ldquo;sleeveless?!&rdquo;<br> ~What used to be freckles are now liver
   spots.<br> ~Everybody whispers.<br> ~You have 3 sizes of clothes in
   your closet&hellip;. 2 of which you will never wear.</p> <p>~But
   &ldquo;Old&rdquo; is good in some things:<br> Old Songs, Old movies
   &hellip;<br> and best of all, our dear &hellip;OLD FRIENDS!!</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong><em>Author unknown. But could have
   been written by me.</em></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Be sure
   to see more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/amazing-information/"
   rel="">Amazing Information</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
