   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/las-vegas-tips/ Tue, 13 Aug 2019 17:36:27
   +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64564 Las Vegas Tips. From someone who
   lives there. Places to... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/las-vegas-tips/">Continue reading</a>
   <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"> <html><body><p><strong>Las
   Vegas Tips</strong>. From someone who lives there. Places to stay, best
   places to eat, <strong>free places</strong> that are a must see and a
   map of&nbsp; the Vegas Strip.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64578 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-Tip
   s.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Las Vegas
   Tips. From someone who lives there. Places to stay, best places to eat,
   free places that are a must see and a map of&nbsp; the Vegas Strip."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-
   Tips.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-Tips-267
   x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-Tips-100
   x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;">I have lived in Las Vegas
   for over 10 years. It is a must visit city. There are many exciting
   places to see in Vegas.<br><em>I am not affiliated with any of the
   links I am giving you, just suggestions.</em></p> <p>My best advice is
   to visit Las Vegas in the spring or fall. The summers (July and August)
   are dreadfully hot. The Winter ( December and January) are usually
   cold, but has some nice days. The&nbsp;<b>best time</b> to visit Las
   Vegas is from March to May and from September to November. <strong>You
   don&rsquo;t have to gamble to have fun.&nbsp;</strong></p>
   <p><strong>Shows:</strong> Las Vegas has many great show with varying
   range of prices. <strong>Check out <a
   href="https://m.vegas.com/traveltips/top-10-las-vegas-shows/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">The Top 10
   shows.</a></strong></p> <p>There are <strong>bus rides</strong> that
   are inexpensive. You can ride from one end of the strip to the other,
   and even ride to downtown Vegas. I like to take a ride at night and see
   the beautiful town lit up.</p> <p><strong>Where to stay:</strong></p>
   <p><strong>The strips hotels</strong> <strong>are expensive</strong>.
   Watch out for added on &ldquo;resort fee&rdquo; that they don&rsquo;t
   mention until you get ready to pay. Always ask for the &ldquo;complete
   price&rdquo;. You usually can get a better price by calling the hotel
   directly.&nbsp; If you do stay on the strip, try to get one in the
   middle as there is a LOT of walking to see it end to end. Even if you
   stay on the strip you might want to visit other hotels away from the
   strip to eat your meals.<strong> Food is VERY expensive on the
   strip.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Most Hotels on the <strong>strip</strong>
   also charge a<strong> car parking fee</strong>. Up to $30 a day. A very
   few offer free parking. Check this link for up to date information for
   Hotel parking: <strong><a
   href="https://www.lasvegasdirect.com/las-vegas-parking-fees/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Las Vegas Hotel Parking
   Fees</a></strong></p> <p><strong>Circus Circus Hotel &amp;
   Resort.</strong> A family favorite Las Vegas resort since its
   inception, the Circus Circus Resort and Casino is full of family-fun
   activities. From the thrills of the Adventuredome to the<strong> live
   circus acts right on the casino floor</strong>! This affordable hotel
   is on the north end of the strip and is one of the best choices for a
   family vacation to Las Vegas.&nbsp; They also have a <strong>travel
   trailer parking</strong>.&nbsp; Even if you don&rsquo;t stay there, it
   is a great place for you and the kids to visit.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64582" style="width: 414px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64582"
   class="wp-image-64582 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Circus.jpg"
   alt="" width="404" height="404" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Circus.jpg
   404w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Circus-150x150.jpg
   150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Circus-400x400.jpg
   400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Circus-50x50.jpg
   50w" sizes="(max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64582" class="wp-caption-text">Circus Circus
   Live Free show</p></div> <p>Hotels right outside the strip are a lot
   cheaper and cost a lot less. Most of the hotels have shuttles to the
   strip.&nbsp; My favorite is<strong> <a
   href="https://www.orleanscasino.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow
   noopener noreferrer">The Orleans Hotel Casino </a></strong>It is
   inexpensive, close to the strip, has inexpensive food and is a
   beautiful place. Their buffet is delicious and very reasonable
   priced.&nbsp; They have shuttles to the strip.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64575" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64575"
   class="wp-image-64575 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Orleans-4
   00x355.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="355" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Orlean
   s-400x355.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Orleans-150x13
   3.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Orleans.jpg
   519w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64575" class="wp-caption-text">The Orleans Hotel
   And Casino</p></div> <p><a href="https://palacestation.sclv.com/"
   target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"><strong>Palace
   Station</strong></a> is another great place to stay off the strip. They
   have recently remodeled. The buffet is wonderful and very
   inexpensive.&nbsp; They have a large casino and nice rooms.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64566" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64566"
   class="wp-image-64566 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Statio
   n-400x267.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Sta
   tion-400x267.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Station-768
   x512.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Station-102
   4x683.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Station-150
   x100.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Palace-Station.jpg
   1200w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64566" class="wp-caption-text">Palace
   Station</p></div> <p>If you like a rustic look then <a
   href="https://www.arizonacharliesdecatur.com/" target="_blank"
   rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer"><strong>Arizona Charlies
   Decatur</strong> </a>it the place for you. The room are very nice. Some
   have a view of the strip, and they have one of the cheapest and tasty
   buffet, in town. If you are a <strong>Bingo</strong> fan, they have the
   only 24 hour bingo in town. My husband I eat there all the time. When
   family comes to visit us, we put them up in a room. Which is comped
   because of the advertisement they send me.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64567" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64567"
   class="wp-image-64567 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Charl
   es-400x300.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Ch
   arles-400x300.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Charles-76
   8x576.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Charles.jp
   g 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Charles-50
   0x375.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Arizona-Charles-15
   0x113.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64567" class="wp-caption-text">Arizona
   Charles</p></div> <p><b>Free stuff and inexpensive things to see and
   do:</b></p> <p>Don&rsquo;t forget to visit <strong><a
   href="https://vegasexperience.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow
   noopener noreferrer">Fremont Street</a></strong> (downtown Vegas). Go
   at night. It is covered and has a beautiful free light show at night.
   They also have free concerts, certain times of the year and days of the
   week.</p> <div id="attachment_64583" style="width: 410px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64583" class="wp-image-64583
   size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Fremont-stree
   t-400x263.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="263" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Fremont-st
   reet-400x263.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Fremont-street-150
   x99.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Fremont-street.jpg
   714w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64583" class="wp-caption-text">Fremont Street.
   Downtown Las Vegas.</p></div> <p>Located on the very north end of the
   strip is The Gold and Silver Pawn Shop, where the popular reality
   show&nbsp;<strong><em>Pawn Stars</em></strong> is filmed, has become a
   tourist destination now more popular than the wedding chapels with
   which it shares its bit of Las Vegas Boulevard. I visited when the
   stars of the show were still on site. Kinda cheesy now, long lines,
   none of the stars are usually there. But you can get a T-shirt and say
   you were there. Lords knows I&rsquo;ve wasted more time and money in
   worse ways.</p> <p>The <strong><a
   href="https://www.10best.com/destinations/nevada/las-vegas/the-strip/at
   tractions/flamingo-wildlife-habitat/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow
   noopener noreferrer">Flamingo Wildlife Habitat</a></strong>, is a great
   place to take a short serenity break from the hustle and bustle of the
   Strip. It is home to (naturally) flamingos, but you&rsquo;ll also find
   swans, ducks, koi, turtles and even two rescued pelicans. Lush
   landscaping makes for great pictures: think waterfalls, palms trees,
   and plenty of places to sit. The habitat is family-friendly, and
   it&rsquo;s free.</p> <p>At the <strong>Bellagio</strong>, for instance,
   you can visit the&nbsp;<a
   href="https://www.10best.com/destinations/nevada/las-vegas/the-strip/at
   tractions/bellagio-conservatory-botanical-gardens/">Conservatory and
   Botanical Garden</a>, watch the&nbsp;<a
   href="https://www.10best.com/destinations/nevada/las-vegas/las-vegas/at
   tractions/fountains-of-bellagio/">dancing waters</a>&nbsp;and inspect
   the fascinating Chihuly artwork on the ceiling near the front
   desk&ndash;<strong>all for zero dollars</strong>.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64571" style="width: 360px" class="wp-caption
   alignleft"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64571"
   class="wp-image-64571"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo2-150x
   150.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="244" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo2-4
   00x279.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo2-150x105.j
   pg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo2.jpg 480w"
   sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64571" class="wp-caption-text">Bellagio Water
   Show</p></div> <div id="attachment_64570" style="width: 360px"
   class="wp-caption alignright"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64570" class="wp-image-64570"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo-150x1
   50.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="233" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo-40

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo-768x512.jp
   g 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo-150x100.jp
   g 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Belligo.jpg 990w"
   sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64570" class="wp-caption-text">Bellagio
   Botanical Garden</p></div> <p>Shopping might not sound like a free
   activity, but in Las Vegas you can find shopping malls with free
   entertainment, like the <a
   href="https://www.10best.com/destinations/nevada/las-vegas/the-strip/at
   tractions/streetmosphere-at-the-venetian-grand-canal-shoppes/">Streetmo
   sphere</a>&nbsp;at the Venetian&rsquo;s Grand Canal Shoppes. The
   wandering performers and living statues are free, even if a trip inside
   your favorite store might not be.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>The
   Seven Magic Mountains</strong>. If you rent a car you can see art
   installation is easy to see from I- 15, with its 35-foot high towers of
   multi-colored boulders rising out of the desert east of I-15, about ten
   miles south of Las Vegas. The desert art installation featuring 7
   painted boulder totems up to 35 ft. high by Ugo Rondinone.</p> <div
   id="attachment_64573" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64573"
   class="wp-image-64573 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Seven-Mag
   ic-Mountains-400x126.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="126"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Seven-
   Magic-Mountains-400x126.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Seven-Magic-Mo
   untains-768x243.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Seven-Magic-Mo
   untains-1024x324.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-Seven-Magic-Mo
   untains-150x47.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64573" class="wp-caption-text">The Seven Magic
   Mountains</p></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Las Vegas is surrounded by
   <strong>mountains</strong> where you can camp, hike and enjoy the
   scenery. Even snow ski in the winter. Hiking may not be the first thing
   that pops to mind when you think of Las Vegas, but within an hour of
   the city, you can find some unexpected and extraordinary landscapes,
   with outstanding hiking trails. Make a day of it.</p> <p>Two or three
   times a day, the <strong>Mirage&rsquo;s volcano</strong> rumbles into
   life, spewing flames and doing a nice, friendly impersonation of a real
   volcano. Crowds gather early to get a glimpse of this iconic curb-side
   attraction&ndash;when it first appeared on the Strip, it was the first
   Vegas exterior entertainment of its kind. The entire lagoon area in
   front of the Mirage comes to life when the volcano is erupting.
   <strong>Best of all it is free to watch.</strong></p> <p><strong>Map Of
   Las Vegas Strip:</strong></p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full
   wp-image-64579"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-map
   .png" alt="" width="499" height="714"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-
   map.png 499w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-map-280x
   400.png 280w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Las-Vegas-map-105x
   150.png 105w" sizes="(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px"></p>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64556 Boozy Vanilla Pudding Shots. Super
   easy to make and can... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/boozy-vanilla-pudding-shots/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Boozy Vanilla Pudding Shots</strong>. Super easy
   to make and can be stored days ahead of time. They are a cool and
   creamy adults-only treat that are always a hit at parties!</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64559 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Boozy-Vanilla
   -Pudding-Shots.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Boozy Vanilla Pudding Shots. Super easy to make
   and can be stored days ahead of time. They are a cool and creamy
   adults-only treat that are always a hit at parties!"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Boozy-Vani
   lla-Pudding-Shots.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Boozy-Vanilla-Pudd
   ing-Shots-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Boozy-Vanilla-Pudd
   ing-Shots-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64557--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Boozy Vanilla Pudding Shots</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Boozy-Vanilla
   -Pudding-Shots-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 small package
   Vanilla instant pudding</li> <li>3/4 Cup Milk</li> <li>3/4 Cup Winter
   Jack Daniel's Tennessee Whiskey Or Vodka</li> <li>8 oz. tub Cool
   Whip</li> <li>1/2 cup dark chocolate (crumbled)</li> <li>1/2 cup milk
   chocolate (shredded )</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Whisk together the
   milk, liquor, and instant pudding mix in a bowl until combined.</li>
   <li>Add cool whip a little at a time with whisk.</li> <li>Using shot
   glasses, cups, disposable shot cups or 1 or 2 ounce cups with
   lids.</li> <li>Put crumbled dark chocolate on bottom of cups.</li>
   <li>Pour 1/2 the pudding mix on top. Put another layer of dark
   chocolate then the remaining pudding.</li> <li> <p>Then add the
   shredded milk chocolate on top.</p> </li> <li>Place in freezer for at
   least 2 hours. Then move to refrigerator.</li> <li>Keep refrigerated
   until ready to serve.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes 25 serving in shot cups or
   10 servings in glass cup. </p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=boozy"
   rel="">Boozy Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/free-oreo-cho
   c-cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 box
   chocolate cake (double batch)</li> <li>1 can vanilla frosting</li>
   <li>1 can chocolate frosting</li> <li>1 package Oreo Cookies
   (crumbled)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Bake cakes according
   to package directions. Let cool.</li> <li>Crumble cookies into small
   pieces.</li> <li>Warm can of vanilla frosting in microwave for 15
   seconds.</li> <li>Mix 1/4 of the cookies into the vanilla
   frosting.</li> <li> <p>Frost the bottom layer of cake with the vanilla
   frosting mix. Letting it run over the side.</p> </li> <li>Place the
   other cake layer on top.</li> <li>Frost the top with the chocolate
   frosting.</li> <li>Decorate the top of the cake with remaining Oreo
   Cookies</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p

   <html><body><p><strong>Chili Cheese Corn Chip Ground Beef
   Dinner</strong>. Such an easy, quick and yummy recipe, you will be
   making it often. Serve it for lunch or dinner. Add a salad and you have
   a compete quick dinner.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full
   wp-image-64545"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Chili-Cheese-
   Corn-Chip-Ground-Beef-Dinner.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"

   se-Corn-Chip-Ground-Beef-Dinner.jpg 600w,

   Chip-Ground-Beef-Dinner-267x400.jpg 267w,

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Chili Cheese Corn Chip Ground Beef
   Dinner</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Chili-Cheese-
   Corn-Chip-Ground-Beef-Dinner-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 pound ground
   beef</li> <li>2 hand fulls of Chili Cheese Corn Cheese OR Nacho Cheese
   Doritos (crumbled)</li> <li>Shredded American OR Cheddar Cheese</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Fry
   ground beef in skillet until crumbled and brown.</li> <li>With your
   hands crush the chips into small pieces.</li> <li>Place crumbled chips
   on a plate or bowl.</li> <li>Add the hot ground beef on top.</li>
   <li>Add the shredded cheese on top. I took American cheese and just
   sliced it with my hands.</li> <li>Serve while still warm</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Will serve two
   people. </p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

   ut-Hospice-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/The-REAL-Truth-Abo
   ut-Hospice-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><em><strong>As an RN I worked for Hospice
   for 5 years. Those were some of the most rewarding years of my 40 year
   career.</strong></em></p> <p>Enrolling in hospice care
   <strong>early</strong> helps loved ones live better and live longer.
   Hospice care decreases the burden on family, decreases the
   family&rsquo;s likelihood of having a complicated grief and prepares
   family members for their loved one&rsquo;s death.
   <b>Hospice</b>&nbsp;care is designed
   to<strong>&nbsp;provide</strong>&nbsp;pain management, symptom control,
   psychosocial support, and spiritual care to patients and their families
   when the illness cannot be cured.</p> <p>No one wants to think about
   losing someone they love. For that reason, <strong>many families
   delay</strong> discussions about end-of-life care. If you are asking
   yourself when to call hospice, there is a good chance your loved one
   may already be eligible to receive this added layer of uniquely
   specialized care and support. Even if your loved one is not currently
   eligible for hospice care, gathering information about when you should
   call hospice before a crisis hits will give you time to understand the
   different options available and determine the best fit for your
   family.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Hospice is a
   Blessing not a Burden</strong></p> <p><strong>Cost:</strong> Hospice is
   <strong>free</strong> for the terminally ill. Hospice gets paid
   <strong>100%</strong> through your insurance, medicaid, or medicare
   benefits. Most agencies will take the terminally ill even if they have
   no means to pay. Hospice does not pay for a place to stay except for a
   short period of time for <strong>pain management</strong>.&nbsp;
   Hospice also allows a patient to be cared for in a facility for a
   period of time, not because the patient needs it, but because the
   family caregiver needs a break. This is known as respite care.</p>
   <p><strong>Who qualifies:&nbsp;</strong> Two physicians, the attending
   physician and the&nbsp;<b>hospice</b> medical director, must certify
   the patient is terminally ill, with a six-month or less life expectancy
   <strong>if the disease takes its normal course</strong>.
   But&nbsp;hospice care can be provided for as long as the person&rsquo;s
   doctor and&nbsp;<b>hospice care</b> team certify that the condition
   remains life-limiting. I have had patients on Hospice for several
   years. A person needs to be <strong>home bound</strong>, meaning a
   <strong>taxing</strong> effort to get out of their home.
   <strong>Hospice</strong><b>&nbsp;care</b> is for people of any age and
   at any stage in an illness, whether that illness is curable, chronic,
   or life-threatening. I have had very young and very old patients. If
   you or a loved one are suffering from symptoms of a disease or
   disorder, be sure to ask your current physician if he/she thinks you or
   your loved one may qualify.&nbsp; <b>Hospice does not cover 24 hour
   care but they are always available for an emergency.&nbsp;</b></p>
   <p><strong>Symptoms your loved one may need Hospice:</strong> Frequent
   visits to the ER or hospital admissions. A decline in their ability to
   perform daily tasks including eating, getting dressed, walking, or
   using the bathroom. An increase in falls. Changes to their mental
   abilities.&nbsp; Progressive weight lose. Skin tears, infections, and
   other signs of deteriorating health.</p> <p><strong>Pain
   management:</strong> Hospice covers <strong>ALL</strong> medication.
   They work very hard with a doctor to manage pain.</p> <p><strong>The
   Hospice staff includes:</strong></p> <p><strong>Doctors</strong>
   &ndash; who oversees medications and oversees the nurses and to assure
   the best care possible.</p> <p><strong>Nurses</strong> -Who usually
   visit once a week or more often if needed.</p> <p><strong>Home Health
   Aids</strong>&ndash; Who usually visit 3 times a week for personal
   care.</p> <p><strong>Counselors</strong>&ndash; Who usually visit one a
   month.</p> <p><strong>Pharmacist</strong>&ndash; Where medication can
   be received 24 hours a day if needed.</p> <p><strong>Social
   Workers</strong>&ndash; Who assist with any problems and comfort
   measures.</p> <p><strong>Bereavement Counselors</strong> &ndash; To
   help with the end of life decision. Yes, Hospice helps even after your
   loved one has passed away.</p> <p><strong>Volunteers</strong> &ndash;
   Who will sit with a patient, while you get a break. Sometimes even
   while you take a short vacation.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Hospice staff is available 24 hours a
   day.&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><strong>Does my loved one have to stay
   on Hospice?</strong> No, they are free to op-out at any time. For
   instance, if they fall and break a leg, they can still go to the
   emergency room then may go to a rehab center. Their previous insurance
   will take back over. They can re-enroll when they return home.&nbsp;
   <strong>Please notify Hospice&nbsp; immediately.&nbsp;</strong></p>
   <p>As you can see I am a strong supporter. The end of life does not
   have to be a burden or painful.</p> <p><strong>Don&rsquo;t wait to call
   Hospice the very last days of a loved ones life</strong>. They offer
   support throughout the terminal illness.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/amazing-information/"
   rel="">Amazing Information</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64524 Muffin Pan Chocolate Chip Pumpkin
   Cookies. Recipe for homemade cookies... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/muffin-pan-chocolate-chip-pumpkin-cooki
   es/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Muffin Pan Chocolate Chip Pumpkin
   Cookies</strong>. Recipe for homemade cookies that are spicy with a
   sweet twist. Tender and melts in your mouth.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64527 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Muffin-Pan-Ch
   ocolate-Chip-Pumpkin-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Muffin Pan Chocolate Chip Pumpkin Cookies. Recipe
   for homemade cookies that are spicy with a sweet twist. Tender and
   melts in your mouth.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Muffin-Pan
   -Chocolate-Chip-Pumpkin-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Muffin-Pan-Chocola
   te-Chip-Pumpkin-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Muffin-Pan-Chocola
   te-Chip-Pumpkin-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64525--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Muffin Pan Chocolate Chip Pumpkin
   Cookies</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Muffin-Pan-Ch
   ocolate-Chip-Pumpkin-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 1/2 cups
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   baking powder</li> <li>1 teaspoon cinnamon</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   nutmeg</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 1/2 cups granulated
   sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup butter (softened)</li> <li>1 cup pure
   pumpkin</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1
   cup chocolate chips</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li> <p>Spray muffin
   pans with non-stick baking spray or use cupcake liners. Set aside.</p>
   </li> <li>Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg,
   and salt in a medium bowl.</li> <li>Beat sugar and butter with mixer on
   medium high speed, then blend in pumpkin, egg, and vanilla until well
   mixed.</li> <li>Gradually mix in flour and dry ingredients and
   chocolate chips. Refrigerate dough for 3-4 hours.</li> <li>Preheat oven
   to 375 degrees.</li> <li> <p>Scoop dough into one inch balls. Place in
   prepared muffin trays and bake for 11-13 minutes.</p> </li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cookies"
   rel="">Cookie Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   Cookies. Recipe for easy cookies.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/no-bake-chocolate-peanut-butter-cookies
   /">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0

   <html><body><p><strong>No Bake Chocolate Peanut Butter
   Cookies</strong>. Recipe for easy cookies. A mixture of cocoa, peanut
   butter and quick oatmeal. Rolled in coconut. Yummy snack.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64519 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/No-Bake-Choco
   late-Peanut-Butter-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="No Bake Chocolate Peanut Butter Cookies. Recipe
   for easy cookies. A mixture of cocoa, peanut butter and quick oatmeal.
   Rolled in coconut. Yummy snack.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/No-Bake-Ch
   ocolate-Peanut-Butter-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/No-Bake-Chocolate-
   Peanut-Butter-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/No-Bake-Chocolate-
   Peanut-Butter-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64517--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">No
   Bake Chocolate Peanut Butter Cookies</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/No-Bake-Choco
   late-Peanut-Butter-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 cups sugar</li>
   <li>1/2 cup cocoa</li> <li>1/2 cup milk</li> <li>1/4 pound butter ((1/2
   cup))</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>1 pinch salt</li> <li>1/2
   cup chunky peanut butter</li> <li>3 cups quick cooking oatmeal</li>
   <li>1 cup coconut flakes (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In a sauce pan
   combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Stir to mix.</li> <li>Put on
   medium heat and cook until mixture starts to boil.</li> <li>Remove from
   heat and cool for 1 minute.</li> <li>Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter,
   oatmeal and mix well.</li> <li>Roll cooled mixture into small balls.
   Coat with coconut flakes, if desired.</li> <li>Place on wax or
   parchment paper until set. About 1/2 hour.</li> <li>Cookies will be
   ready to eat when set.</li> <li>Refrigerate until ready to serve.</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64509 Traits To Add To Your Resume. If you
   are writing... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/traits-to-add-to-your-resume/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Traits To Add To Your Resume.</strong> If you
   are writing a resume or going to a job interview, then write/practice
   these tips.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64510 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Traits-To-Add
   -To-Your-Resume.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Traits To Add To Your Resume. If you are writing
   a resume or going to a job interview, then write/practice these tips."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Traits-To-
   Add-To-Your-Resume.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Traits-To-Add-To-Y
   our-Resume-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Traits-To-Add-To-Y
   our-Resume-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><b>FLEXIBILITY</b><strong>:</strong> I am
   able to adapt my priorities.</p> <p><strong>FOCUSED:</strong> I am
   goal-oriented.</p> <p><strong>FRIENDLY:</strong> I am easy to work
   with.</p> <p><strong>HONESTY:</strong> I value integrity.</p>
   <p><strong>IMAGINATIVE:</strong> I am inventive in my work process.</p>
   <p><strong>INDEPENDENT:</strong> I need little direction.</p>
   <p><strong>INEXPERIENCED:</strong> I am a blank pallet.</p>
   <p><strong>INQUISITIVE:</strong> I am excellent at gathering
   information.</p> <p><strong>INSIGHTFUL:</strong> I can read between the
   lines.</p> <p><strong>INTUITIVE:</strong> I can sense when there is a
   problem.</p> <p><strong>METICULOUS:</strong> I pay attention to the
   small details.</p> <p><strong>NEUROTIC:</strong> I am a
   perfectionist.</p> <p><strong>OPEN-MINDED:</strong> I take constructive
   criticism well.</p> <p><strong>OPINIONATED:</strong> I am comfortable
   voicing opinions.</p> <p><strong>ORGANIZED:</strong> I am a meticulous
   planner.</p> <p><strong>PATIENT:</strong> I am not easily ruffled.</p>
   <p><strong>PERCEPTIVE:</strong> I can read people effortlessly.</p>
   <p><strong>PERSUASIVE:</strong> I am a natural salesperson.</p>
   <p><strong>PROCEDURAL:</strong> I work best with structure.</p>
   <p><strong>PUNCTUAL:</strong> I have great time management skills.</p>
   <p><strong>QUIET:</strong> I am a great listener.</p>
   <p><strong>RELAXED:</strong> I do not stress easily.</p>
   <p><strong>RESOURCEFUL:</strong> I use every tool at hand.</p>
   <p><strong>RESPONSIBLE:</strong> I always finish a task on time.</p>
   <p><strong>TALKATIVE:</strong> I am comfortable initiating a
   dialogue.</p> <p><strong>TECHNOLOGICAL:</strong> I am industrially
   savvy.</p> <p><strong>Order of a resume:</strong></p> <ol
   class="X5LH0c"><li class="TrT0Xe">Contact details.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Opening statement.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">List of key
   skills.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">List of technical/software skills.</li>
   <li class="TrT0Xe">Personal attributes/career overview.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Educational qualifications.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Employment history/volunteering/work placements.</li>
   <li class="TrT0Xe">References/referees.</li> </ol><p><strong>Common
   Resume MISTAKES:</strong></p> <ul class="i8Z77e"><li
   class="TrT0Xe">Spelling and grammatical errors. Always have another
   person proof read your resume.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Incorrect or
   missing contact information.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Using an
   unprofessional email address.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Including
   outdated or irrelevant information.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Failure to
   demonstrate and quantify results</li> </ul><p><strong>Good Video to
   watch:</strong><br><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jLAhGJzhdzk" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/" rel="">How To
   And Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-fresh-peach-cake/ Mon, 05 Aug 2019
   12:46:05 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64497 Homemade Fresh Peach Cake. Dessert
   recipe that is yummy and... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-fresh-peach-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0

   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Fresh Peach Cake</strong>. Dessert

   frosting.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64500 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Fres
   h-Peach-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"

   ch-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Fresh-Pea
   ch-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64498--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Fresh Peach Cake</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Homemade-Fres
   h-Peach-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the
   cake:</h4> <ul><li>1/4 pound (1 stick) unsalted butter (at room
   temperature)</li> <li>1 1/2 cups sugar (divided)</li> <li>2 extra-large
   eggs (at room temperature)</li> <li>1 cup sour cream (at room
   temperature)</li> <li>1 teaspoon pure vanilla extract</li> <li>2 cups
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   baking powder</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon kosher salt</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   ground cinnamon</li> <li>3 large ripe peaches (peeled, pitted, and
   sliced)</li> </ul><h4>Buttercream Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>3 cups
   confectioners' sugar</li> <li>1 cup butter</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla
   extract</li> <li>1 to 2 tablespoons whipping cream</li>
   </ul><h4>Topping:</h4> <ul><li>2 peaches (peeled, pitted and sliced
   (optional))</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the Cake:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Grease a 9-inch square baking
   pan.</li> <li>In the bowl of an electric mixer fitted with the paddle
   attachment, beat the butter and 1 cup of the sugar for 3 to 5 minutes
   on medium-high speed, until light and fluffy. With the mixer on low,
   add the eggs, one at a time, then the sour cream and vanilla, and mix
   until the batter is smooth.</li> <li>In a separate bowl, sift together
   the flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. With the mixer on low,
   slowly add the dry ingredients to the batter and mix just until
   combined. In a small bowl, combine the remaining 1/2 cup sugar and the
   cinnamon.</li> <li>Spread half of the batter evenly in the pan. Top
   with half of the peaches, then sprinkle with two-thirds of the sugar
   mixture. Spread the remaining batter on top, arrange the remaining
   peaches on top.</li> <li>Bake the cake for 45 to 55 minutes, until a
   toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.</li> <li>Cool then
   frost the cake.</li> </ol><h4>Buttercream Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>In a
   standing mixer fitted with a whisk, mix together sugar and butter. Mix
   on low speed until well blended and then increase speed to medium and
   beat for another 3 minutes.</li> <li>Add vanilla and cream and continue
   to beat on medium speed for 1 minute more, adding more cream if needed
   for spreading consistency.</li> <li>Frost cake and place extra peaches
   on top, if desired.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more our our delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake"
   rel="">Cake Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64490 Easy Vanilla Pudding Donuts. Recipe
   made from canned biscuits and... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-vanilla-pudding-donuts/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Vanilla Pudding Donuts</strong>. Recipe
   made from canned biscuits and pudding. Perfect for breakfast, after
   school snack or a dessert.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64493 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Vanilla-
   Pudding-Donuts.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Vanilla Pudding Donuts. Recipe made from
   canned biscuits and pudding. Perfect for breakfast, after school snack
   or a dessert.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Vanil
   la-Pudding-Donuts.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Vanilla-Puddi
   ng-Donuts-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Vanilla-Puddi
   ng-Donuts-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64491--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Vanilla Pudding Donuts</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Vanilla-
   Pudding-Donuts-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 10 count can Texas
   style biscuits</li> <li>1 Cup Powdered Sugar</li> <li>1 1/2 Tablespoon
   cinnamon (optional)</li> <li>Vegetable Oil For Frying</li> <li>1
   package Vanilla pudding or flavor of your choice</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Prepare pudding
   according to package directions, set aside and let cool.</li> <li>Pour
   oil into skillet to the depth of a little less than 1/2 an inch and
   heat on medium to medium high for about five minutes.</li> <li>In a
   bowl, combine cinnamon (if desired) and powdered sugar.</li> <li>Using
   a small round cookie cutter, make an indention in each biscuit. 3/4 of
   the way through.</li> <li> <p>Drop dough into hot oil, watching
   carefully and turning when golden. Until doughnuts are golden on both
   sides.</p> </li> <li> <p>Remove to a paper towel lined plate. Repeat
   until all donuts are cooked.</p> </li> <li>Sprinkle sugar mixture on
   top.</li> <li>Place 1 tablespoon of pudding in the center of each of
   the donuts.</li> <li>Eat while warm or refrigerate until ready to
   serve.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>

   cocoa butter, shea butter</strong>. Natural is best, there&rsquo;s so
   much chemicals and everything that we eat drink smell listen to. Why

   been shown to increase expression of a protein called filaggrin in the
   skin. Filaggrin is intimately involved with keeping the skin moist and
   those without the gene for filaggrin often have very severe eczema. I
   added liquid vitamin D to Penetrix &ndash; which is absorbed into the
   skin. Penetrix, which is commercially available, is sort of a modern
   day DMSO. Penetrix appeared to bring the vitamin D into the body. No
   data, but seems promising. Had added <strong>about 50,000 IU of vitamin

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64445 Mom&#8217;s White Vinegar Salad
   Dressing. Easy recipe for a homemade... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/moms-white-vinegar-salad-dressing/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Mom&rsquo;s White Vinegar Salad
   Dressing</strong>. Easy recipe for a homemade family favorite.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64448 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Moms-White-Vi
   negar-Salad-Dressing.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Mom's White Vinegar Salad Dressing. Easy recipe
   for a homemade family favorite.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Moms-White
   -Vinegar-Salad-Dressing.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Moms-White-Vinegar
   -Salad-Dressing-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Moms-White-Vinegar
   -Salad-Dressing-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64446--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Mom's White Vinegar Salad
   Dressing</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Moms-White-Vi
   negar-Salad-Dressing-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>10 tablespoons
   sugar</li> <li>2 tablespoons cornstarch</li> <li>1/2 teaspoons
   salt</li> <li>Dash pepper</li> <li>2 eggs</li> <li>3/4 cup white
   vinegar</li> <li>1/4 cup water</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Mix dry ingredients,
   add eggs and blend thoroughly.</li> <li>Combine water and vinegar,
   blend with egg mixture.</li> <li>Cook over low heat, stirring
   constantly until mixture is thickened.</li> <li>Refrigerate until ready
   to use.</li> <li>Toss over your favorite salad.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/salads/" rel="">Salad
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Jello Boston Cream Pie</strong>. Recipe
   with no baking required using a prepared angel food cake.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64441 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Jello-Bo
   ston-Cream-Pie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Jello Boston Cream Pie. Recipe with no

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Jello
   -Boston-Cream-Pie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Jello-Boston-
   Cream-Pie-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Jello-Boston-
   Cream-Pie-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64437--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Jello Boston Cream Pie</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Easy-Jello-Bo
   ston-Cream-Pie-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 3.4 oz pkg. JELL-O
   Vanilla Flavor Instant Pudding</li> <li>1 1/2 cups cold milk</li> <li>1
   1/2 cups thawed COOL WHIP Whipped Topping (divided)</li> <li>1 prepared
   angel food cake, cut horizontally into 3 layers</li> <li>2 oz. BAKER'S
   Semi-Sweet Chocolate (chopped)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Beat pudding mix and
   milk in medium bowl with whisk 2 min. Stir in 1/2 cup COOL WHIP.</li>
   <li>Stack cake layers on plate, spreading pudding mixture between
   layers.</li> <li>Microwave chocolate and remaining COOL WHIP in
   microwaveable bowl on HIGH 30 sec.; stir until chocolate is completely
   melted and mixture is well blended. Spoon over cake.</li>
   <li>Refrigerate 1 hour.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p><em>Recipe courtesy and reprinted with permission

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64423 Southern Style Pork Chops With
   Gravy. Easy main meal recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/southern-style-pork-chops-with-gravy/">
   Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Southern Style Pork Chops With Gravy</strong>.
   Easy main meal recipe that you can serve with potatoes and/or
   vegetables.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64426 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Southern-Styl
   e-Pork-Chops-With-Gravy.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Southern Style Pork Chops With Gravy. Easy main
   meal recipe that you can serve with potatoes and/or vegetables."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Southern-S
   tyle-Pork-Chops-With-Gravy.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Southern-Style-Por
   k-Chops-With-Gravy-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Southern-Style-Por
   k-Chops-With-Gravy-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64424--></p>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Southern Style Pork Chops With
   Gravy</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Southern-Styl
   e-Pork-Chops-With-Gravy-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>4 boneless pork chops
   (1/2 inch thick)</li> <li>1 tbsp vegetable oil</li> <li>1 onion
   (chopped)</li> <li>1 cup chopped red and green peppers (optional)</li>
   <li>2 tbsp or 1/2 package Lipton onion soup mix</li> <li>2 cups
   water</li> <li>Seasoning to taste with salt and pepper and a pinch of
   cayenne (if desired)</li> <li>2 cubes pork stock cubes (crumbled )</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Rinse the pork chops and season to taste.</li> <li>In a black
   pot or heavy aluminum skillet, add oil and saut&eacute; the chopped
   onions and bell peppers over medium heat for approximately 5
   minutes.</li> <li>Add the seasoned pork chops to the skillet and
   brown.</li> <li> <p>Add 2 cups water or enough water to cover the meat,
   along with the Lipton onion soup mix and crumbled pork stock cubes,
   lower heat and simmer for approximately 45 minutes to one hour,
   depending on the thickness, until meat is tender.</p> </li> <li>
   <p>Serve hot with potatoes an/or vegetables.</p> </li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See

   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-keep-flies-and-wasp-away-with-zip-lock
   -bags-and-pennies/ Tue, 30 Jul 2019 14:54:38 +0000 My Honeys Place
   Camping and Outdoors How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64420
   How To Keep Flies And Wasp Away With Zip Lock... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-keep-flies-and-wasp-away-with-zi
   p-lock-bags-and-pennies/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC
   "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"> <html><body><p><strong>How
   To Keep Flies And Wasp Away With Zip Lock Bags And Pennies</strong>.
   Awesome tip that really works.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64421 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Keep-F
   lies-And-Wasp-Away-With-Zip-Lock-Bags-And-Pennies.jpg" alt=""
   width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="How To Keep Flies And
   Wasp Away With Zip Lock Bags And Pennies. Awesome tip that really
   works."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Kee
   p-Flies-And-Wasp-Away-With-Zip-Lock-Bags-And-Pennies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Keep-Flies-
   And-Wasp-Away-With-Zip-Lock-Bags-And-Pennies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Keep-Flies-
   And-Wasp-Away-With-Zip-Lock-Bags-And-Pennies-100x150.jpg 100w"
   sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Fill a
   zip lock bag with water and 5 or 6 shiny pennies and hang it in the
   problem area. In my case it was a particular window in my home. It had
   a slight passage way for insects. Every since I have done that, it has
   kept flies and wasps away. Some say that wasps and flies mistake the
   bag for some other insect nest and are threatened.</p> <p>Regarding the
   science behind zip log bags of water? Research found that the millions
   of molecules of water presents its own prism effect and given that
   flies have a lot of eyes, to them it&rsquo;s like a zillion disco balls
   reflecting light, colors and movement in a dizzying manner. When you
   figure that flies are prey for many other bugs, animals, birds, etc.,
   they simply won&rsquo;t take the risk of being around that much
   perceived action. I moved to a rural area and thought these
   &ldquo;hillbillies&rdquo; were just yanking my city boy chain but I
   tried it and it worked immediately! We went from hundreds of flies to
   seeing the occasional one, but he didn&rsquo;t hang around long.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/camping-and-out
   -doors/" rel="">Camping and Outdoor Tips</a></strong></p></body></html>

   +0000 My Honeys Place Recipes Salads https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64394
   Orange Jello Salad. Easy yummy recipe using jello, mandarin or... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/orange-jello-salad/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Orange Jello Salad.</strong> Easy yummy recipe
   using jello, mandarin or fresh oranges, mini marshmallows and cool
   whip.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64398 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Jello-
   Salad.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Orange
   Jello Salad. Easy yummy recipe using jello, mandarin or fresh oranges,
   mini marshmallows and cool whip."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Jel
   lo-Salad.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Jello-Salad
   -267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Jello-Salad
   -100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64395--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Orange Jello Salad</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Jello-
   Salad-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 box orange
   Jello</li> <li>1 box instant vanilla pudding</li> <li>1 cup boiling
   water</li> <li>1/2 cup cold water</li> <li>1 8 oz. tub Cool Whip </li>
   <li>1 cup fresh oranges or 1 can mandarin oranges (14 oz.)
   drained&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; (peeled and diced into small
   chunks)</li> <li>1 cup mini marshmallows</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li> <p>In a large bowl
   combine orange Jello and boiling water.</p> </li> <li> <p>Whisk until
   Jello is dissolved.</p> </li> <li>Add cold water and allow to chill for
   15 minutes in refrigerator.</li> <li>Slowly whisk in vanilla pudding
   mix until smooth and chill for another 15-20 minutes or until it
   becomes slightly thickened.</li> <li>Fold in Cool Whip, oranges and
   marshmallows.</li> <li> <p>Refrigerate until ready to serve.</p> </li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>

   recipe for beans just... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong>Crock Pot Grandma Beans</strong>. A delicious
   recipe for beans just like grandma use to make. Side dish for lunch or
   dinner.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64386 size-full"

   ndma-Beans2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Crock Pot Grandma Beans</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Crock-Pot-Gra
   ndma-Beans2-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 pound lean
   ground beef</li> <li>1 pound bacon (cooked and crumbled)</li> <li>2
   Tablespoons bacon drippings</li> <li>3 15 ounces 15 cans kidney
   beans</li> <li>3 15 ounces cans white beans</li> <li>3 15 ounces cans
   pork and beans</li> <li>3 small onions (diced)</li> <li>1 cup light
   brown sugar</li> <li>1 cup ketchup</li> <li>1/2 cup molasses</li> <li>3
   Tablespoons mustard</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In a large skillet,
   cook the ground beans and onions, until meat is no longer pink.
   Stirring constantly to separate the meat. Then drain and discard the
   ground beef drippings..</li> <li>Cook the bacon and crumble. Saving 2
   Tablespoon of the drippings for the beans.</li> <li>Drain all juice
   from the cans of beans and discard, except 1 can of pork and
   beans.</li> <li>Combine all ingredients into your crock pot.</li>
   <li>Cook for 4 hours on hing or 8 hours on low.</li> </ol></div> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/mock-watermelon-cake/ Sun, 28 Jul 2019
   12:07:23 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64374 Mock Watermelon Cake. Dessert recipe
   for a cake that looks... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mock-watermelon-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Mock Watermelon Cake</strong>. Dessert recipe
   for a cake that looks like a watermelon. Strawberry cake with green
   frosting and sprinkled with chocolate chips.&nbsp; Makes a yummy, fun
   birthday cake.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64377 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mock-Watermel
   on-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Mock
   Watermelon Cake. Dessert recipe for a cake that looks like a
   watermelon. Strawberry cake with green frosting and sprinkled with
   chocolate chips.&nbsp; Makes a yummy, fun birthday cake.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mock-Water
   melon-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mock-Watermelon-Ca
   ke-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mock-Watermelon-Ca
   ke-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64375--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Mock Watermelon Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mock-Watermel
   on-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 box strawberry cake mix</li> <li>3/4 cup milk</li> <li>1
   small (3 oz) package strawberry gelatin</li> <li>3/4 cup vegetable
   oil</li> <li>3 large eggs</li> <li>1 cup chocolate chips</li>
   </ul><h4>Center layered Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1 stick butter (softened
   to room temp)</li> <li>12 oz. cream cheese (softened to room temp)</li>
   <li>1 box (7 cups) powdered sugar</li> <li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
   <li>1 drop red food coloring</li> </ul><h4>Top Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1
   stick butter (softened to room temp)</li> <li>12 oz. cream cheese
   (softened to room temp)</li> <li>1 box (7 cups) powdered sugar</li>
   <li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li> <li>2-3 drops green food coloring</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees.</li> <li>Place
   baking rack in center of oven.</li> <li>Place parchment round in bottom
   of each cake pan.</li> <li>Spray cake pans with vegetable oil spray.
   Set aside.</li> <li>Combine cake mix and gelatin in mixing bowl.</li>
   <li>Add milk, oil and eggs.</li> <li>Mix with mixer until well
   blended~2-3 minutes.</li> <li>Stir in chocolate chips.</li> <li>
   <p>Pour into 3 (9-in.) or 4 (8-in.) cake pans sprayed with oil.</p>
   </li> <li>Bake for 20-25 minutes or until just set.</li> <li>Remove;
   allow to cool in cake pans for 30 minutes.</li> <li>Turn cake onto
   parchment paper to cool.</li> </ol><h4>Center layer frosting:</h4>
   <ol><li>Mix butter and cream cheese until creamy.</li> <li>Add powdered
   sugar, starting with 1 box.</li> <li>Add pink food coloring; mix until
   frosting is pink.</li> <li>Mix, adding more sugar as needed, until
   desired consistency.</li> <li>Spread over top of 3 of the 4 cake
   layers.</li> </ol><h4>Top Layer frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Place each layer
   on top of each other, be sure the unfrosted layer is on top.</li>
   <li>Mix butter and cream cheese until creamy.</li> <li>Add powdered
   sugar, starting with 1 box.</li> <li>Add green food coloring; mix until
   frosting is green.</li> <li>Mix, adding more sugar as needed, until
   desired consistency.</li> <li>Frost cake and enjoy!</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake"
   rel="">Cake Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-oven-dry-dried-food/ Sat, 27 Jul 2019
   14:32:49 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Cooking Tips &
   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64366 How To
   Oven-Dry Dried Food. Such a crackers, chips, cereal,... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-oven-dry-dried-food/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Oven-Dry Dried Food</strong>. Such a
   crackers, chips, cereal, etc. so they won&rsquo;t get stale.<strong>
   Plus how to freeze dry fruit in your oven and how to use oxygen
   absorbers.</strong></p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64372
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Oven-D
   ry-Dried-Food3.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Oven-Dry Dried Food. Such a crackers,
   chips, cereal, etc. so they won't get stale. Plus how to freeze dry
   fruit in your oven and how to use oxygen absorbers."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Ove
   n-Dry-Dried-Food3.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Oven-Dry-Dr
   ied-Food3-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Oven-Dry-Dr
   ied-Food3-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong> This is how to dry-oven canned
   dried food:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><strong> OVEN IS OFF!</strong> Put
   the dry goods in your jars leave the head space 1/<span
   class="text_exposed_show">4 &ldquo;.&nbsp; Make sure you wipe the rips
   of your jars and the lids are clean.</span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">Place the lids and rings on finger and
   tighten them . </span></p> <p><span class="text_exposed_show">Place
   them on a cookie sheet inside the cold oven. Then after you have all
   your jars in the oven (on cookie sheet) shut the door turn oven on 250
   degrees F.&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">After the oven heats to the temp then set the
   timer for 45 minutes. After the timer goes off just turn oven off, DO
   <strong>NOT OPEN THE OVEN DOOR</strong>! Let the jars cool off it the
   oven.</span></p> <p><span class="text_exposed_show">After the jars are
   cool pull them out and make sure each jar is sealed. If it is not seal
   remove lid and ring clean them again and repeat the process.
   </span></p> <p><span class="text_exposed_show">You can dry can many
   jars at the same time and they will last many years and still taste
   fresh.</span></p> <p>This can work for oats, oat meal, flour, cake
   mixes, pancake mixes. But&nbsp; freeze for a week before canning to
   kill any bugs.</p> <p>Watch video for more instructions:<br><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/304NgJg8AfA" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p> <p><em>Food such as
   green beans,etc. still need to be pressured cooked.&nbsp;</em></p>
   <p><strong>For potato chips</strong>. You would need an <strong>oxygen
   absorbers</strong> because of the oils in the chips. You can buy them
   off Amazon they are these little packets that you would drop in the jar
   after you put the product you want to preserve, then place the lid and
   the ring on the jar finger tight the packet will suck all the oxygen
   out of the jar, thus leaving the jar vacuumed packed. This DOES NOT go
   in the oven. To use oxygen absorbers. Open the jar a drop a packet
   inside the jar and make sure the rim of the jar is clean then put the
   lid and ring on the jar.. The oxygen absorber will suck the oxygen out
   of the jar. You want to keep it in a room temp. if it gets to hot the
   condensation can build up, and ruin your canned good. Being too cold
   can cause condensation when the product warms up after being to
   cold.</p> <div id="attachment_64367" style="width: 160px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64367" class="size-thumbnail
   wp-image-64367"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/oxygen-absorb
   ers-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/oxygen-abs
   orbers-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/oxygen-absorbers-4
   50x450.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/oxygen-absorbers-5
   00x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/oxygen-absorbers-5
   0x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64367" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Oxygen
   Absorbers</strong></p></div> <p>With oatmeal , flour or anything with
   flour or grains you need to freeze for a week then either dry can or
   use a oxygen absorbers. If you want a long term on spices it is
   recommend that you use oxygen absorbers. They will make them last for a
   very long time.</p> <p><strong>How To Dry fruit in the
   oven:</strong></p> <p>Start by choosing a fruit to dehydrate. Wash the
   fruit well and remove the stalks, leaves, or other inedible parts. You
   can leave on the peel if you want, but if you&rsquo;re going to do that
   then it&rsquo;s better to buy organic fruit. Some fruits, such as
   apples and peaches, will dry better if the peel is removed.</p> <p>Cut
   the fruit into small pieces so it will dry faster. In order to make the
   fruit look appealing and minimize discoloration, soak them in lemon
   juice and water for 10 minutes. Then drain and dry them with a
   lint-free towel.</p> <p>Preheat the oven to minimum temperature (about
   50 degrees). Use a lower temperature for thin fruits like sliced
   apples, bananas and peaches. Strawberries require a higher temperature.
   Over time, you will learn how long each fruit takes. If your oven does
   not go down to 50 degrees you can also leave the oven on for about 5
   minutes then turn it off for 10 minutes turn it back on for 5 minutes
   off for 10 sometimes it takes a little longer to do it but you still
   get the same result without worrying about burning.</p> <p>Line the
   baking sheet with wax paper and arrange the fruits in a single layer,
   without letting them touch. In order to prevent the fruit from curling
   during drying, cover them with a pizza pan with holes poked in it.</p>
   <p>Place them in the oven and leave the door slightly ajar, in order to
   prevent them from burning. This process normally takes around an hour
   and a half. When the fruit is dry, remove it from the oven and allow it
   to cool before eating.</p> <p>Watch video for more
   information:<br><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/kjLWtgOpOL4"
   width="450" height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark"
   style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden;
   line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p></body></html>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/chunky-meat-and-spaghetti-soup/ Fri, 26 Jul
   2019 13:14:26 +0000 My Honeys Place Recipes Soups
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64356 Chunky Meat And Spaghetti Soup. Can
   be cooked in your... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/chunky-meat-and-spaghetti-soup/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Chunky Meat And Spaghetti Soup</strong>. Can be
   cooked in your crock pot or stove top. Perfect recipe for an evening
   meal or lunch.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64359 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Chunky-Meat-A
   nd-Spaghetti-Soup.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Chunky Meat And Spaghetti Soup. Can be cooked in
   your crock pot or stove top. Perfect recipe for an evening meal or
   lunch.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Chunky-Mea
   t-And-Spaghetti-Soup.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Chunky-Meat-And-Sp
   aghetti-Soup-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Chunky-Meat-And-Sp
   aghetti-Soup-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64357--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Chunky Meat And Spaghetti Soup</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Chunky-Meat-A
   nd-Spaghetti-Soup-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 pounds stewing beef
   (trimmed and cubed)</li> <li>3 tablespoons flour</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   garlic powder</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon black
   pepper</li> <li>3 tablespoons olive oil</li> <li>1 green onion
   (chopped)</li> <li>1/2 cup red wine (optional)</li> <li>6 cups beef
   broth</li> <li>3 tablespoons tomato paste</li> <li>1 teaspoon dried
   rosemary</li> <li>1 pound potatoes (peeled and cubed)</li> <li>4 cups
   spaghetti (cooked according to package directions)</li> <li>4 celery
   stalks (cut into 1 inch pieces)</li> <li>2 tablespoons cornstarch</li>
   <li>2 tablespoons water</li> <li>Chives for topping (optional)</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Combine flour, garlic powder and salt &amp; pepper. Toss beef
   in flour mixture.</li> <li>Heat olive oil in a large pot. Cook the beef
   until browned. If using crock pot then transfer to the crock pot.</li>
   <li>Add red wine and beef stock while scraping up any brown bits in the
   pan.</li> <li>Stir in all remaining ingredients except for spaghetti,
   cornstarch and water. Reduce heat to medium low, cover and simmer 1
   hour or until beef is tender (up to 90 minutes). Or crock pot for 3
   hours on medium heat.</li> <li>Cook spaghetti according to package
   directions and drain juices.</li> <li>Mix equal parts cornstarch and
   water to create a thin sauce. Slowly add the sauce to the boiling stew
   to reach desired consistency stirring continuously. (you may not need
   all of the sauce).</li> <li>Stir in cooked spaghetti and simmer 5-10
   minutes before serving . Season with salt &amp; pepper to taste.</li>
   <li>Top with chives if desired.</li> <li>Serve hot.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes 8 servings</p> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/soups/" rel="">Soup
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64344 Homemade Slow Cooker Boozy Root
   Beer. Easy and yummy recipe.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-slow-cooker-boozy-root-beer/">

   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Slow Cooker Boozy Root Beer</strong>.
   Easy and yummy recipe. You party guest will love it.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64347 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Slow
   -Cooker-Boozy-Root-Beer.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Slow Cooker Boozy Root Beer. Easy and
   yummy recipe. You party guest will love it."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-S
   low-Cooker-Boozy-Root-Beer.jpg 600w,

   er-Boozy-Root-Beer-267x400.jpg 267w,

   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64345--></p>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Slow Cooker Boozy Root
   Beer</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Slow
   -Cooker-Boozy-Root-Beer-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>10 Cups water</li>
   <li>2 1/2 Cups granulated sugar</li> <li>1/4 Cup brown sugar</li> <li>1
   Tablespoon pure vanilla extract</li> <li>4 Tablespoons Root Beer
   extract</li> <li>1/2 Cup molasses&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;</li> <li>3
   Cups Vodka</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Add water, both
   sugars and vanilla extract into a large slow cooker.</li> <li>Cover and
   cook on high for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.</li> <li> <p>Turn off
   the slow cooker and stir in the root beer extract, vodka and molasses.
   </p> </li> <li> <p>Place in glass or plastic bottles, with a sealed
   top, in the refrigerator for 24 hours before drinking. You can store
   refrigerated root beer for about one month.</p> </li> <li>Serve
   cold.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div>
