   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64337--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Orange Vanilla Creamsicle
   Cheesecake</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Orange-Vanill
   a-Coke-Creamsicle-Cheesecake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Crust:</h4> <ul><li>1 3/4
   cups Graham Cracker Crumbs (about 15 full crackers)</li> <li>1/3 cup
   butter (melted)</li> <li>1/4 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   kosher salt</li> </ul><h4>Filling:</h4> <ul><li>3 8-ounce packages
   cream cheese (at room temperature)</li> <li>1 1/2 cups sugar</li> <li>5
   large eggs</li> <li>1/2 cup Coke Vanilla Orange soda</li> <li>2
   teaspoons vanilla extract</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon orange extract</li>
   <li>zest of 1 medium orange</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Crust:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350&deg;F</li> <li>In a large bowl mix the
   graham cracker crumbs, butter, granulated sugar, and salt together
   evenly. Press the mixture into the bottom and up the sides of 9-inch
   pan.</li> <li>Bake the crust for 8-10 minutes, or until lightly golden.
   Set aside while you make the cheesecake.</li> </ol><h4>Filling:</h4>
   <ol><li>Slowly mix the cream cheese and sugar until well blended,
   scraping the sides and bottom of the bowl.</li> <li>Mix in the eggs one
   at time, then the coke, flavorings, and zest.</li> <li>Pour the filling
   into the baked crust, and reduce the oven heat to 325&deg;Bake for 50
   to 55 minutes, until the cheesecake is set around the edges.</li>
   <li>Turn the oven off, prop the door open, and let the cheesecake sit
   for an hour.</li> <li>Run a knife or spatula around the edges.</li>
   <li>Cool for several hours before serving.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See

   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64330--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Strawberry Jello Parfait</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Strawberry-Je
   llo-Parfait-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 package
   strawberry Jello (mixed according to package directions)</li> <li>4
   Cups vanilla yogurt</li> <li>1 Cup sliced fresh strawberries (sliced
   and mashed)</li> <li>1/8 Cup sugar</li> <li>1/2 Cups Mini marshmallows
   (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Make jello according
   to package directions, Place in square ice cube trays and refrigerate
   until firm.</li> <li>Remove the stems of the strawberries. Slice and
   then smash with a fork, adding the sugar. Let set until the
   strawberries have a juice texture and until the Jello is firm.</li>
   <li> <p>Fold in the strawberries with the juice and the mini
   marshmallows, into the yogurt. If too thin add more yogurt.</p> </li>
   <li>Gently fold in the firmed jello cubes.</li> <li>Refrigerate until
   ready to serve.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>You could also substitute any
   flavor Jello and fresh fruit. </p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Crunchy-Apple
   -Cobbler-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Filling:</h4>
   <ul><li>3 lbs golden delicious apples</li> <li>1 1/2 Tbsp fresh lemon
   juice</li> <li>1/3 cup packed light-brown sugar</li> <li>2 tsp
   cornstarch</li> <li>1/2 tsp cinnamon</li> <li>1/2 cup apple juice</li>
   <li>1/4 cup unsalted butter (diced into small cubes)</li>
   </ul><h4>Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
   <li>3/4 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>2 tsp baking powder</li> <li>1/4
   tsp baking soda</li> <li>1/2 tsp salt</li> <li>10 Tbsp unsalted butter
   (cold, diced into small cubes)</li> <li>1 cup buttermilk</li> <li>1 tsp
   vanilla extract</li> <li>1 Tbsp granulated sugar mixed with 1/2 tsp
   cinnamon (for topping)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 375
   degrees. Spray a 13 by 9-inch baking dish with non-stick cooking
   spray.</li> </ol><h4>Filling:</h4> <ol><li>Peel and core apples then
   cut into slices a little over 1/4-inch thick. Cut slices in half.</li>
   <li>Place apples in a prepared baking dish then toss with lemon juice.
   Set aside.</li> <li>In a small saucepan whisk together brown sugar,
   cornstarch, cinnamon and apple juice. Add butter then heat mixture over
   medium-high heat, stirring constantly until it reaches a simmer. Let
   simmer 30 seconds then remove from heat.</li> <li>Pour brown sugar
   mixture over apples in baking dish, toss to coat. Set aside.</li>
   </ol><h4>Topping:</h4> <ol><li>In a large mixing bowl whisk together
   flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.</li> <li>Add butter
   and using a pastry cutter or fork cut butter into mixture until it
   resembles coarse meal. Make a well in center of mixture.</li> <li>Pour
   buttermilk into center then pour vanilla into buttermilk. Fold mixture
   with a rubber spatula just until combined (don&rsquo;t over-mix, it
   should be lumpy).</li> <li>Dollop spoonfuls of mixture across apple
   layer (about 12 across top, don&rsquo;t spread it will spread as it
   bakes).</li> <li>Sprinkle evenly with 1 Tbsp sugar and cinnamon
   mixture.</li> <li>Bake in preheated oven until apples are soft, about
   35 to 45 minutes (tent will foil to prevent excess browning during last
   10 minutes as needed).</li> <li>Let cool 10 minutes</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/i-found-the-perfect-way-to-clean-my-laminate-
   flooring/ Sat, 20 Jul 2019 12:18:39 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing
   Information DIY And Tips Household Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64303 I Found The Perfect Way To Clean My
   Laminate Flooring.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/i-found-the-perfect-way-to-clean-my-lam
   inate-flooring/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC
   "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"> <html><body><p><strong>I
   Found The Perfect Way To Clean My Laminate Flooring</strong>. We have
   an asphalt driveway that we have to cross every time we enter the
   house. My floors get very dirty with the black tar from the asphalt.
   When we walk barefoot in our home our feet get black. As you can see in
   the picture. After trying many different solutions, I finally found an
   easy one that worked!&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64304 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/I-Found-The-P
   erfect-Way-To-Clean-My-Laminate-Flooring.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900" data-pin-description="I Found The Perfect Way To Clean My
   Laminate Flooring. We have an asphalt driveway that we have to cross
   every time we enter the house. My floors get very dirty with the black
   tar from the asphalt. When we walk barefoot in our home our feet get
   black. As you can see in the picture. After trying many different
   solutions, I finally found an easy one that worked!&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/I-Found-Th
   e-Perfect-Way-To-Clean-My-Laminate-Flooring.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/I-Found-The-Perfec
   t-Way-To-Clean-My-Laminate-Flooring-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/I-Found-The-Perfec
   t-Way-To-Clean-My-Laminate-Flooring-100x150.jpg 100w"
   sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px">&nbsp;</p> <p>Saves money and
   works better than expensive manufacturer&rsquo;s cleaner.</p>
   <ol><li>Use a microfiber mop. I bought mine at Home Depot, but you can
   buy them at Walmart or online.&nbsp;</li> </ol> <div
   id="attachment_64305" style="width: 160px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64305"
   class="size-thumbnail wp-image-64305"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/microfiber-mo
   p-150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/microfiber
   -mop-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/microfiber-mop-450
   x450.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/microfiber-mop-500
   x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/microfiber-mop-50x
   50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64305" class="wp-caption-text">&nbsp; Microfiber
   Mop&nbsp;</p></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>2. In a spray bottle mix 1 part
   white vinegar to 3 parts warm water.</p> <p>3. Add 1 squirt Dawn dish
   washing liquid.&nbsp;<br>Shake bottle to mix.</p> <p>4. Spray onto your
   microfiber mop, just enough to make it damp. Do not mop your laminate
   floors&nbsp; with a cloth mop. Excessive water are not good for
   laminate flooring.&nbsp;</p> <p>5. Mop your floors with even strokes
   covering the whole floor. I bought an extra microfiber covering, so I
   could do my whole house. They are washable. Just throw the dirty ones
   in the washer and dryer.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> <p>It works like a
   charm!&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips And Tricks</a></strong></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/easiest-fresh-strawberry-cupcakes/ Fri, 19
   Jul 2019 13:28:48 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63999 Easiest Fresh Strawberry Cupcakes.
   Recipe for a perfect after school... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easiest-fresh-strawberry-cupcakes/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Easiest Fresh Strawberry Cupcakes</strong>.
   Recipe for a perfect after school snack or a dessert after a meal.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64294 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easiest-Fresh
   -Strawberry-Cupcakes.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easiest Fresh Strawberry Cupcakes. Recipe for a
   perfect after school snack or a dessert after a meal."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easiest-Fr
   esh-Strawberry-Cupcakes.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easiest-Fresh-Stra
   wberry-Cupcakes-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easiest-Fresh-Stra
   wberry-Cupcakes-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64000--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easiest Fresh Strawberry
   Cupcakes</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easiest-Fresh
   -Strawberry-Cupcakes-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ul><li>1
   (18.25-ounce) Package white cake mix</li> <li>1 (3-ounce) Package
   strawberry gelatin</li> <li>4 Large eggs</li> <li>1/2 Cup sugar</li>
   <li>1/2 Cup finely chopped fresh strawberries</li> <li>1/2 Cup
   milk</li> <li>1/2 Cup Vegetable oil</li> <li>1/3 Cup all-purpose
   flour</li> <li>Garnish with whole or halved strawberries</li>
   </ul><h4>Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1 Cup butter (softened)</li> <li>4 Cups
   powdered sugar</li> <li>1 Cup finely chopped fresh strawberries</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees Beat cake mix,
   strawberry gelatin, eggs, sugar, chopped fresh strawberries, milk,
   vegetable oil and all-purpose flour at low speed with an electric mixer
   for 1 minute. Scrape down sides, and beat at medium speed for 2 more
   minutes, stopping to scrape down sides, as needed. (The Strawberries
   should be well blended.)</li> <li> <p>Pour batter into 12 cupcake
   liners in a cupcake pan.</p> </li> <li> <p>Bake at 350 degrees for 20
   minutes, or until cakes spring back when pressed lightly with a finger.
   Let cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove from pans, and
   cool completely (about 1 hour.)</p> </li> <li> <p>Spread the Strawberry
   Buttercream Frosting on top of the cupcakes or use decorative piping.
   Garnish with whole and halved strawberries. Serve immediately, or chill
   for up to 1 week.</p> </li> </ol><h4>Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Beat butter
   at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy (about 20 seconds).
   Add sugar and strawberries, beating at low speed until creamy. (Add
   more sugar if frosting is too thin, or add strawberries if too
   thick.)</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-64298"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/cake.jpg"
   alt="" width="355" height="273" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/cake.jpg
   355w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/cake-150x115.jpg
   150w" sizes="(max-width: 355px) 100vw, 355px">You could also make a
   strawberry cake with this recipe. Just put cake mix into a well greased
   and floured 9 inch pan. Or double the recipes for a layered
   cake.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our
   delicious<a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel=""> Dessert Recipe</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64274 Easy Chocolate Pudding Cookies. So
   easy they only take 15... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-chocolate-pudding-cookies/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Chocolate Pudding Cookies.</strong> So easy
   they only take 15 minutes from start to your mouth. Mix it up with
   different flavor puddings to create your own deliciousness! You could
   also add chocolate chips for a yummy recipe.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64277 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easy-Chocolat
   e-Pudding-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Chocolate Pudding Cookies. So easy they only
   take 15 minutes from start to your mouth. Mix it up with different
   flavor puddings to create your own deliciousness! You could also add
   chocolate chips for a yummy recipe.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easy-Choco
   late-Pudding-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easy-Chocolate-Pud
   ding-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easy-Chocolate-Pud
   ding-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64275--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Chocolate Pudding Cookies</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Easy-Chocolat
   e-Pudding-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>3/4 cup buttermilk
   baking mix</li> <li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1
   (3.9 ounce) package instant chocolate pudding mix, or pudding of your
   choice</li> <li>1/2 cup chopped walnuts (optional)</li> <li>Powered
   sugar for dusting top of cookies</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Combine the baking
   mix, vegetable oil, egg and pudding mix in a bowl. Mix well. Stir in
   the nuts (optional).</li> <li>Place teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie
   sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes or until toothpick comes
   clean.</li> <li>Dust top with powdered sugar, if desired.</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-a-better-nights-sleep/ Mon, 15 Jul
   2019 15:37:55 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How To
   and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64268 How To Get A Better Nights
   Sleep. Tired of tossing... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-a-better-nights-sleep/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Get A Better Nights Sleep</strong>. Tired
   of tossing and turning at night? Try these tips to help when you have
   insomnia.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64269 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Get-A-
   Better-Nights-Sleep.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Get A Better Nights Sleep. Tired of
   tossing and turning at night? Try these tips to help when you have
   insomnia.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Get
   -A-Better-Nights-Sleep.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Get-A-Bette
   r-Nights-Sleep-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-To-Get-A-Bette
   r-Nights-Sleep-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><strong>Go to bed and get up at the same time each
   day</strong>, even on the weekends. This will create a habit that helps
   you sleep.</p> <p><strong>Limit nap time during the day</strong>. Nap
   only for 15 minutes or less. If you get drowsy during the day, get up
   and move around.</p> <p><strong>Sleep in clothes</strong> that are
   comfortable for YOU.</p> <p><strong>Do not watch TV</strong> during you
   sleeping time. The TV will end up disrupting your sleep.</p> <p>Make
   sure your <strong>bedroom is dark</strong>. Try a sleep mask or heavy
   curtains.</p> <p>Do not use <strong>caffeine</strong> at least 4 hours
   before bedtime. Caffeine is a stimulate and will make it harder to get
   to sleep.</p> <p><strong>Cut down on all liquids 2 hours</strong>
   before bedtime. The urge to urinate will make you wake up.</p>
   <p><strong>Stressed?</strong> Try these <a
   href="https://www.helpguide.org/articles/stress/relaxation-techniques-f
   or-stress-relief.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer">Relaxing Techniques&nbsp;</a></p> <p><strong>Keep your
   bedroom cool</strong>. People sleep better in a cool environment.</p>
   <p><strong>Think pleasant thoughts</strong>. Like birds singing,</p>
   <p>Put <strong>lavender</strong> around your bed. Lavender is very
   soothing. It could be a plant or lavender oil.</p> <p><strong>If wake
   up at night</strong> for more than 15 minutes, get out of bed and do a
   quiet, non-stimulating activity, such as reading a book. Keep the
   lights dim and avoid screens so as not to cue your body that it&rsquo;s
   time to wake up.</p> <p><strong>Try this just before you try to go to
   sleep</strong>: breathe in through your nose for four seconds, hold
   your breath for seven seconds, and exhale through your mouth for eight
   seconds.</p> <p>Take a <strong>warm bath or shower</strong> just before
   bedtime.</p> <p>Try a <strong>Melatonin</strong> Supplement. Or other
   over the counter sleeping pills such as:</p> <ul class="i8Z77e"><li
   class="TrT0Xe">Diphenhydramine (found in brand names like Nytol,
   Sominex, Sleepinal, Compoz)</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Doxylamine (brand
   names such as Unisom, Nighttime Sleep Aid)</li> </ul><p>For at least 1
   hour before bedtime: <strong>Put aside your work</strong>. Turn off the
   computer. Stay off the phone and away from social media like Facebook
   or Twitter. There will always be more to do, but you have done enough
   for today. Now it&rsquo;s time to relax and prepare for sleep. Fill the
   time with relaxing activities like reading or watching a boring
   movie.</p> <p><strong>Foods</strong> that might help you sleep better
   at night:</p> <ol class="X5LH0c"><li class="TrT0Xe">Almonds.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Turkey</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Chamomile Tea</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Kiwi</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Tart Cherry Juice</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Fatty Fish</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Walnuts</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Passionflower Tea</li> <li>White rice</li>
   <li>Pistachios- one of the most melatonin rich food.</li>
   </ol><p><strong>If you continue to struggle</strong>, speak with your
   doctor about additional treatment options.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Try more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/health/"
   rel="">Healthy Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64259 Pecan Custard Pie. Easy dessert
   recipe with an egg custard... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/pecan-custard-pie/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Pecan Custard Pie</strong>. Easy dessert recipe
   with an egg custard filling then topped with pecans.</p> <p>For this
   recipe you can buy a 9 inch pie crust or <strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-the-perfect-pie-crust/"
   rel="">Make Your Own&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64262 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Pecan-custard
   -pie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Pecan
   Custard Pie. Easy dessert recipe with an egg custard filling then
   topped with pecans.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Pecan-cust
   ard-pie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Pecan-custard-pie-
   267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Pecan-custard-pie-
   100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64260--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Pecan Custard Pie</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Pecan-custard
   -pie-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>3 eggs</li>
   <li>1 cup white sugar</li> <li>1/4 cup butter (melted)</li> <li>2
   tablespoons all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 cup milk</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   vanilla extract</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon ground nutmeg</li> <li>1 9 inch
   pie crust</li> <li>1 cup pecans (for topping)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Bake pie shell at
   400 degrees for 5 minutes. Set aside.</li> <li>Combine melted butter or
   margarine, sugar, flour, milk, vanilla, and nutmeg. Add beaten eggs,
   and blend well. Pour filling into partially baked pie shell. Top with
   pecans.</li> <li>Bake at 325 degrees for 45 to 55 minutes, or until an
   inserted knife comes out clean. Do not overcook.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Check out more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=pie" rel="">Pie
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Taste Just Like Orange Julius</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Taste-Just-Li
   ke-Orange-Julius-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 cup milk</li> <li>2
   teaspoons vanilla extract</li> <li>1 6 ounce can frozen orange juice
   concentrate</li> <li>1/2 cup sugar</li> <li>1 1/2 cups ice</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Blend the milk and vanilla: Pour the milk and vanilla in a
   blender and blend until combined.</li> <li>Add the frozen orange juice
   concentrate. Blend until fully combined with the milk.</li> <li>Add the
   sugar and ice cubes: Blend until cubes are crushed and mixture has
   thickened. If things end up a little thick, just add a tablespoon of
   water and mix once again.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM

   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-battle-with-depression/ Fri, 12 Jul 2019
   13:51:30 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64244 The Battle With Depression. Sign and
   Symptoms, Treatment, Quiz, and... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-battle-with-depression/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>The Battle With Depression</strong>. Sign and
   Symptoms, Treatment, Quiz, and Help. Depression can happen to anyone at
   anytime. Young or old. Depression (major depressive disorder) is a
   common and serious medical illness that negatively affects how you
   feel, the way you think and how you act. Fortunately, it is also
   treatable. Depression causes feelings of sadness and/or a loss of
   interest in activities once enjoyed. It can lead to a variety of
   emotional and physical problems and can decrease a person&rsquo;s
   ability to function at work and at home.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64247 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/The-Battle-Wi
   th-Depression.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="The Battle With Depression. Sign and Symptoms,
   Treatment, Quiz, and Help. Depression can happen to anyone at anytime.
   Young or old. Depression (major depressive disorder) is a common and
   serious medical illness that negatively affects how you feel, the way
   you think and how you act. Fortunately, it is also treatable.
   Depression causes feelings of sadness and/or a loss of interest in
   activities once enjoyed. It can lead to a variety of emotional and
   physical problems and can decrease a person&rsquo;s ability to function
   at work and at home."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/The-Battle
   -With-Depression.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/The-Battle-With-De
   pression-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/The-Battle-With-De
   pression-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>Depression symptom</strong>s can vary from mild to severe
   and can include:</p> <ul><li>Feeling sad or having a depressed
   mood</li> <li>Loss of interest or pleasure in activities once
   enjoyed</li> <li>Changes in appetite &mdash; weight loss or gain
   unrelated to dieting</li> <li>Trouble sleeping or sleeping too
   much</li> <li>Loss of energy or increased fatigue</li> <li>Increase in
   purposeless physical activity (e.g., hand-wringing or pacing) or slowed
   movements and speech (actions observable by others)</li> <li>Feeling
   worthless or guilty</li> <li>Difficulty thinking, concentrating or
   making decisions</li> <li>Thoughts of death or suicide</li>
   </ul><p>Symptoms must last at least two weeks for a diagnosis of
   depression.</p> <p>Great links to read about Depression:</p> <p><a
   href="https://smokefree.gov/challenges-when-quitting/mood/depression-qu
   iz" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener
   noreferrer"><strong>Depression Quiz</strong></a></p> <h4 class="a-title
   td-post-title"><a
   href="https://medical-news.org/22-surprising-habits-of-people-hiding-de
   pression/13880/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">22
   Surprising Habits of People Hiding Depression</a></h4> <h4
   data-fontsize="36" data-lineheight="39"><a
   href="https://www.helpguide.org/articles/depression/depression-treatmen
   t.htm" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Depression
   Treatment&nbsp;</a></h4> <h4>National Helpline &ndash;&nbsp;<a
   id="anch_58" href="https://www.samhsa.gov/find-help/national-helpline"
   target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">1-800-662-HELP
   (4357)</a></h4> <h3><a
   href="https://www.psycom.net/depression-treatment-overview"
   target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Types of Medication
   and Treatments</a></h3> <p><img class="aligncenter size-medium
   wp-image-64245"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/depression-40
   0x400.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="400" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/depression

   .jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/depression-50x50.j
   pg 50w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/depression.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"></p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter size-medium wp-image-64246"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/depression2-4

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Mouthwatering Sauteed Spinach And
   Mushrooms</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Mouthwatering
   -Sauteed-Spinach-And-Mushrooms-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 Tablespoon
   butter</li> <li>1 Tablespoon extra-virgin olive oil</li> <li>1/2 to 1
   tablespoon minced garlic</li> <li>16 ounces white mushrooms (washed and
   cut in half)</li> <li>Salt and freshly ground black pepper</li> <li>10
   ounce package baby spinach</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In a large
   saut&eacute; pan (you want the mushrooms to fit in a single layer),
   heat olive oil and butter over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, garlic
   and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat all mushrooms with the
   oil and then spread them into a single layer. Cook for four minutes on
   medium-high heat without stirring.</li> <li>Stir and cook for 2 more
   minutes without stirring.</li> <li>Cook until soft, about 3
   minutes.</li> <li>Add the spinach and cook, stirring, until spinach is
   wilted.</li> <li>Serve warm.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Check out more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/salads/" rel="">Salad
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   <html><body><p><strong>Inspiring Pineapple Pie.</strong> Flavorful,
   tasty, yummy and is very easy to make. A No-Bake dessert recipe.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64218 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Inspiring-Pin
   eapple-Pie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Inspiring Pineapple Pie. Flavorful, tasty, yummy
   and is very easy to make. A No-Bake dessert recipe."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Inspiring-
   Pineapple-Pie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Inspiring-Pineappl
   e-Pie-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Inspiring-Pineappl
   e-Pie-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64216--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Inspiring Pineapple Pie</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Inspiring-Pin
   eapple-Pie-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For crust:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 and 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs</li> <li>1/2 cup unsalted
   butter (melted)</li> </ul><h4>For filling:</h4> <ul><li>1 20 oz. can
   Crushed Pineapple (drained very well)</li> <li>2 (3.4 ounce) packages
   vanilla instant pudding mix</li> <li>8 oz. sour cream</li> <li>8 ounces
   cool whip (optional)</li> </ul><h4>For garnish:</h4> <ul><li>Maraschino
   cherries</li> <li>Pineapple slices</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For crust:</h4>
   <ol><li>In a food processor ground whole graham crackers to get fine
   crumbs</li> <li>Combine graham crackers crumbs with &frac12; cup melted
   butter and stir until evenly moistened.</li> <li>Press mixture into the
   bottom and up the sides of 8&Prime; pie plate. Press hard to compact.
   You can use a glass to press the bottom, but use your fingers to press
   the sides.</li> <li>Set in the fridge to firm while making the
   filling.</li> </ol><h4>For filling:</h4> <ol><li>In a large bowl,
   combine crushed pineapple, sour cream and vanilla pudding mix</li>
   <li>Mix until well combined</li> <li>Pour into pie crust and spread
   evenly</li> <li>Top the pie with cool whip. Optional</li> </ol><h4>For
   garnish:</h4> <ol><li>Decorate top with Maraschino cherries and
   pineapple slices.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Be sure to check

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-tater-tots-on-a-stick/ Tue, 09 Jul
   2019 12:26:52 +0000 My Honeys Place Appetizers Breakfast Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64205 Homemade Tater Tots On A Stick.
   Recipe for breakfast or... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-tater-tots-on-a-stick/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Tater Tots On A Stick</strong>. Recipe
   for breakfast or an after school snack in one bite. Throw away those
   frozen tater tots.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64207
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Tate
   r-Tots-On-A-Stick.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Tater Tots On A Stick. Recipe for
   breakfast or an after school snack in one bite. Throw away those frozen
   tater tots.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-T
   ater-Tots-On-A-Stick.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Tater-Tot
   s-On-A-Stick-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Tater-Tot
   s-On-A-Stick-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64208--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Tater Tots On A Stick</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Homemade-Tate
   r-Tots-On-A-Stick-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For Tater Tots:</h4>
   <ul><li>Kosher salt (to taste)</li> <li>2 russet potatoes (1 1/2 pounds
   total, peeled and halved lengthwise)</li> <li>2 Tbsp. finely chopped
   chives</li> <li>1 Tbsp. finely chopped thyme</li> <li>1 tsp. freshly
   ground nutmeg</li> <li>1/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper</li>
   <li>3/4 cup instant mashed potatoes flakes</li> <li>Canola oil (for
   frying)</li> </ul><h4>For Bacon:</h4> <ul><li>1 pound bacon (fried to
   desired crispness)</li> <li>Toothpicks or skewers</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Bring a large pot of
   generously salted water to a boil. Add potatoes and cook until just
   slightly tender, 6 to 7 minutes; drain and set aside to let cool
   briefly. While still warm, grate potatoes on the large holes of a box
   grater and transfer to a large bowl. Using your hands, mix in chives,
   thyme, 1 1/2 tsp. salt, nutmeg, and pepper.</li> <li>Form mixture into
   24 balls, using about 1 1/2 Tbsp. of the potato mixture for each. Press
   them together firmly so they hold their shape. (Clean your hands from
   time to time to make the shaping easier.) Place potato flakes in a
   medium bowl, then roll potato balls through flakes to coat, shaking off
   any excess; transfer to a sheet tray.</li> <li>Pour oil into a large,
   deep skillet to a depth of 1/2 inch, then heat over medium-high heat;
   oil is ready when a potato ball sizzles vigorously when dropped in.
   Working in two or three batches, fry potato balls, turning
   occasionally, until deep golden brown, 6 to 8 minutes. Using a slotted
   spoon, transfer to a paper towel-lined sheet tray to let drain.</li>
   <li>Fry bacon to desired crispness. Stick toothpicks or skewers through
   tater tots and top with slices of fried bacon.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>TO FREEZE: Transfer cooled tater
   tots to an airtight container. Freeze up to 1 month. To bake, preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F and bake until heated through, about 15-17
   minutes.</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:
   #ff0000;"><strong>Check out more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a> or <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizers</a></strong></span></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <html><body><p><strong>Perfect Air Fryer Eggs.</strong> Easy way to
   cook your eggs. They will cook perfectly and will be very easy to
   peel.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64197 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Perfect-Air-F

   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;">Put eggs in your air

   https://myhoneysplace.com/3-recipes-using-california-wine/ Sun, 07 Jul
   2019 12:46:22 +0000 My Honeys Place Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64177 3 Recipes Using California Wine. A
   small quantity of&#160;wine&#160;will enhance... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/3-recipes-using-california-wine/">Conti
   nue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>3 Recipes Using California Wine</strong>. A
   small quantity of&nbsp;wine&nbsp;will enhance the flavor of the dish.
   The alcohol in the&nbsp;wine&nbsp;evaporates while the food
   is&nbsp;cooking, and only the flavor remains.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64188 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/3-Recipes-Usi
   ng-California-Wine.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="3 Recipes Using California Wine. A small quantity
   of&nbsp;wine&nbsp;will enhance the flavor of the dish. The alcohol in
   the&nbsp;wine&nbsp;evaporates while the food is&nbsp;cooking, and only
   the flavor remains."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/3-Recipes-
   Using-California-Wine.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/3-Recipes-Using-Ca
   lifornia-Wine-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/3-Recipes-Using-Ca
   lifornia-Wine-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64185--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Seared Pork Chops with Caramelized
   Grapes, Dried Fruit and Pistachios</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wine3-150x150
   .jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>6 bone-in thick pork
   chops (10-12 oz each)</li> <li>6 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil
   (divided)</li> <li>sea salt (to taste)</li> <li>freshly ground pepper
   (to taste)</li> <li>3 Cups red seedless grapes</li> <li>1 Cup dried
   fruit (peaches, apricots, prunes)</li> <li>3 small red onions (peeled
   and sliced thin)</li> <li>8 garlic cloves (peeled)</li> <li>1/2 Cup
   California red wine</li> <li>1/2 Cup fresh sage leaves (divided)</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Let
   pork chops sit at room temperature for about 20 minutes.</li>
   <li>Position a rack in the upper third of oven and preheat to
   400&deg;F.</li> <li>Rub pork chops with 3 Tbsp olive oil; sprinkle
   generously with salt and pepper.</li> <li>In a bowl, toss together
   grapes, dried fruit, red onions, garlic, and half of the sage leaves
   with remaining olive oil; sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. In a
   large pan, saut&eacute; fruit/onion mixture until caramelized, about 8
   minutes; remove to a bowl and set aside.</li> <li>In the same pan, sear
   pork chops over medium-high heat until both sides are browned very
   well; place pork chops in an oven-safe baking dish, top with
   fruit/onion mixture, add red wine to dish and roast about 20 minutes,
   until the chops are done and the grapes are starting to burst; let rest
   for 5 minutes.</li> <li>Transfer to a serving platter, drizzle with pan
   juices and garnish with remaining sage leaves.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64182--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Dark Chocolate Wine Truffles</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/wine2-150x150
   .jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>8 oz bittersweet
   chocolate (coarsely chopped)</li> <li>1/2 Cup heavy cream</li> <li>6
   Tbsp unsalted butter (cut into small pieces)</li> <li>pinch of sea
   salt</li> <li>1/2 Cup California red wine</li> <li>raw cacao or cocoa
   powder</li> </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Place chocolate in a medium-sized bowl. Bring heavy cream to a
   simmer, add butter and stir until melted; pour over chocolate and stir
   with a spatula until chocolate is melted.</li> <li>Add a big pinch of
   salt, red wine and stir until wine is incorporated. Pour into an
   8&times;8-inch baking dish and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.</li>
   <li>When ready to form truffles, use a small metal cookie scoop for
   even portions. Coat your hands in cocoa powder and gently roll
   chocolate until it forms a uniform ball; roll in cocoa to coat. Keep
   truffles refrigerated and take them out about 30 minutes before
   serving.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM
   Recipe 64179--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Baked Brie with Caramelized Apples
   and Onions</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Wine-150x150.
   jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 Tbsp unsalted
   butter</li> <li>2 Tbsp extra virgin olive oil</li> <li>3 Cups sliced
   onions</li> <li>4 garlic cloves (minced)</li> <li>1 Cup apples (peeled,
   cored and sliced thin)</li> <li>1 1/2 tsp sea salt</li> <li>freshly
   ground pepper</li> <li>1/2 Cup California dry white wine</li> <li>1
   French Brie round (2 lbs)</li> <li>crackers (baguette slices, and
   crostini)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to
   350&ordm;F.</li> <li>Heat a very large cast iron skillet over
   medium-high heat.</li> <li>Add butter, olive oil and onions;
   saut&eacute; 15 minutes, or until tender and well-caramelized.</li>
   <li>Add garlic and apples and cook for another 2 minutes to soften the
   apples. Add salt and pepper and stir to scrape any brown bits on the
   bottom. Stir in wine and continue to cook until the liquid evaporates;
   cool.</li> <li>Unwrap Brie and cut off only the top rind, leaving sides
   and bottom intact. Place Brie, cut-side up, in a round ceramic baking
   dish slightly larger than the Brie round (9-inch deep dish pie plate or
   ceramic quiche pan works well too). Top Brie evenly with caramelized
   onion mixture, place dish on a baking pan to catch any cheese drips and
   bake 30 minutes, until melted, oozing and bubbling; remove from oven
   and transfer to a heatproof platter. Serve with crackers, baguette
   slices, and/or crostini.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>The
   California Wine Club</strong> proudly offers five different wine of the
   month club levels.&nbsp; Whether for yourself (just pay as you go) or
   as a gift (just pay for the number of months you want to send) our wine
   club is unmatched for quality wine and impeccable service.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>Click on picture below and Check it
   out:</strong></span></p> <p><a
   href="https://shareasale.com/r.cfm?b=1256297&amp;u=1643906&amp;m=10286&
   amp;urllink=&amp;afftrack=" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer"><img
   src="https://static.shareasale.com/image/10286/300x250-CWCXmas2018-Sign
   ature.jpg" border="0"></a></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   together all dressing ingredients.</li> <li>Pour over salad Toss to

   https://myhoneysplace.com/vanilla-brown-sugar-biscuits/ Tue, 02 Jul
   2019 23:43:49 +0000 My Honeys Place Breads Breakfast Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64155 Vanilla Brown Sugar Biscuits. These
   homemade, flaky and tender biscuits... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/vanilla-brown-sugar-biscuits/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Vanilla Brown Sugar Biscuits</strong>. These
   homemade, flaky and tender biscuits are sweet and yummy. Baked to
   perfection for breakfast or a snack.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64159 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Vanilla-Brown
   -Sugar-Biscuits.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Vanilla Brown Sugar Biscuits. These homemade,
   flaky and tender biscuits are sweet and yummy. Baked to perfection for
   breakfast or a snack.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Vanilla-Br
   own-Sugar-Biscuits.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Vanilla-Brown-Suga
   r-Biscuits-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Vanilla-Brown-Suga
   r-Biscuits-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64156--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Vanilla Brown Sugar Biscuits</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Vanilla-Brown
   -Sugar-Biscuits-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 cup unsalted butter
   (cut into cubes)</li> <li>3 cups self rising flour</li> <li>1 1/2
   teaspoon baking powder</li> <li>1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar
   (light or dark)</li> <li>1 cup buttermilk (plus more if needed)</li>
   <li>2 teaspoons of vanilla extract or vanilla bean paste</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Melt butter over medium heat in a 2 quart saucepan. Let it cook
   and watch it closely until 3 to 5 min until the butter begins to foam,
   forms a golden brown color and browned bits form on the bottom.
   Immediately remove it from the heat. Allow to cool for about 10 min,
   then place butter in a small bowl, and freeze until solid, about 2
   hours.</li> <li>In a large bowl combine the flour, baking powder, and
   brown sugar and stir together with a fork. Tap the small bowl of butter
   on the counter to shake it out (it should be in one large blocUse the
   large holes on a box grater to grate the butter directly into the dry
   ingredients. Stir with a fork.</li> <li>Make a well in the center of
   the dry ingredients and pour in the buttermilk with the vanilla. Use a
   large fork and a large rubber spatula to stir the mixture together. If
   it seems a little dry you may add more buttermilk until it forms a
   shaggy dough.</li> <li>Sprinkle a pastry mat, wooden cutting board or a
   clean smooth counter top with flour. Turn the dough out onto the
   surface and pat a few times with your hands until it loosely holds
   together. (Don&rsquo;t knead it too much or the warmth in your palms
   will melt the butter and cause the biscuits to be tough.)</li> <li>Use
   a large sharp knife to divide the dough in half. Roughly shape each
   half into a square. Stack one of the halves on top of the other and use
   a rolling pin to roll it together into one mass. Repeat this process
   two to three more times before patting it into one final rectangle.
   (This way the biscuits will bake flaky).</li> <li>Wrap the dough in
   plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours and up to
   overnight.</li> <li>Preheat oven to 425*. Line a baking sheet with
   parchment paper. Place a shallow pan of water on the bottom rack of the
   oven.</li> <li>Sprinkle your work surface with flour and unwrap the
   biscuit dough out onto it. Use a bench scraper or very sharp knife to
   trim the edges of the rectangle. Use a square cookie cutter, or a knife
   to cut the remaining dough into squares, about 2&Prime; each.</li>
   <li>Remove the cut biscuits to the baking sheet you&rsquo;ve lined with
   parchment paper, placing them rather close to each other (it will help
   them rise higher). Freeze until cold, about 15 min.</li> <li>Bake until
   golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/moistest-lemon-bundt-cake/ Tue, 02 Jul 2019
   16:19:56 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64141 Moistest Lemon Bundt Cake. A dessert
   recipe that is OMG... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/moistest-lemon-bundt-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Moistest Lemon Bundt Cake</strong>. A dessert
   recipe that is OMG delicious. So sweet you do not even need icing.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64148 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Moistest-Lemo
   n-Bundt-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Moistest Lemon Bundt Cake. A dessert recipe that
   is OMG delicious. So sweet you do not even need icing."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Moistest-L
   emon-Bundt-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Moistest-Lemon-Bun
   dt-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Moistest-Lemon-Bun
   dt-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64145--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Moistest Lemon Bundt Cake</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Moistest-Lemo
   n-Bundt-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4>
   <ul><li>3 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking powder</li>
   <li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 cup
   buttermilk</li> <li>1/4 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice</li> <li>1
   teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1 cup unsalted butter (softened)</li>
   <li>2 cups granulated sugar</li> <li>zest of 4 lemons</li> <li>4 large
   eggs</li> </ul><h4>Syrup:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup granulated sugar</li>
   <li>1/2 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol><li>
   <p>Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to
   350&deg;F/180&deg;Grease well a 10-inch Bundt pan and set aside.</p>
   </li> <li> <p>In a medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder,
   baking soda, and salt. In a small bowl, mix together buttermilk,, lemon
   juice, and vanilla extract. Set bowls aside.</p> </li> <li>In a
   standing mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, beat together butter,
   sugar, and lemon zest on medium speed for 3-4 minutes until fluffy.
   Occasionally scrape down the sides and bottom of the bowl. Add eggs,
   one at a time, beating well after each addition. On low speed, beat in
   the flour mixture in 3 additions, alternating with the lemon juice
   mixture in 2 additions, starting and ending with the flour. Do not over
   mix.</li> <li>Scrape batter into prepared pan and smooth the top. Bake
   for 45-55 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the center of the
   cake comes out clean. If the top is browning too fast while baking,
   cover pan loosely with aluminum foil.</li> <li>Allow cake to cool for
   10-15 minutes, then remove from pan, carefully inverting it onto a
   plate.</li> </ol><h4>Syrup:</h4> <ol><li>In a small saucepan, combine
   sugar and lemon juice.</li> <li>Cook on medium-low heat until sugar
   dissolves and syrup forms.</li> <li>After inverting the cake to a
   plate, brush top and sides of the cake evenly with syrup. Use all
   syrup. Allow cake to cool to room temperature and enjoy!</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Check out more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake" rel="">Cake
   Recipes</a></strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"></p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/cooling-lemon-juice-cocktail/ Tue, 02 Jul
   2019 15:23:06 +0000 My Honeys Place Drinks Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64134 Cooling Lemon Juice Cocktail. Watch
   the sunset with this recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/cooling-lemon-juice-cocktail/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Cooling Lemon Juice Cocktail</strong>. Watch the
   sunset with this recipe on a summer evening. It will take the stress
   out of your day.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64137
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Cooling-Lemon
   -Juice-Cocktail.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Cooling Lemon Juice Cocktail. Watch the sunset
   with this recipe on a summer evening. It will take the stress out of

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Cooling-Le

   e-Cocktail-267x400.jpg 267w,

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Cooling Lemon Juice Cocktail</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Cooling-Lemon
   -Juice-Cocktail-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 cups vodka</li>
   <li>1/2 cup freshly squeezed lemon juice</li> <li>1/2 cup superfine
   sugar</li> <li>1 lemon (thinly sliced)</li> <li>Sea salt</li>
   <li>Ice</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Combine the vodka,
   lemon juice, and sugar and pour into a cocktail shaker with ice. Pour
   into martini glasses or regular glass and garnish with lemon slices and
   sea salt around the rim of the glass.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM

   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-walnut-pineapple-cake/ Sun, 30 Jun
   2019 12:17:10 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64125 The Best Walnut Pineapple Cake. Easy
   dessert recipe with a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-walnut-pineapple-cake/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>The Best Walnut Pineapple Cake</strong>. Easy
   dessert recipe with a moist and yummy cake. Frosting filled with
   walnuts, coconut and cream cheese.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64128 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Waln
   ut-Pineapple-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="The Best Walnut Pineapple Cake. Easy dessert
   recipe with a moist and yummy cake. Frosting filled with walnuts,
   coconut and cream cheese.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-W
   alnut-Pineapple-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Walnut-Pi
   neapple-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Walnut-Pi
   neapple-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64126--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">The
   Best Walnut Pineapple Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Waln
   ut-Pineapple-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>CAKE</h4> <ul><li>1 box
   yellow or white cake mix</li> <li>1 can (20 ounce) crushed pineapple in
   juice</li> <li>1 cup California walnuts (finely chopped)</li> <li>1 cup
   shredded sweetened coconut</li> <li>2 large eggs</li>
   </ul><h4>FROSTING</h4> <ul><li>1 (10-ounce) container of non-dairy
   whipped topping (defrosted)</li> <li>8 ounces cream cheese
   (softened)</li> <li>1/4 cup powdered sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup chopped
   toasted walnuts</li> <li>1/2 cup toasted toasted coconut</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>CAKE</h4> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350&deg; Grease a 13&times;9
   baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.</li> <li>In a large bowl,
   combine cake mix, crushed pineapple (with the juice), chopped walnuts,
   coconut and eggs. Stir together until mixed well.</li> <li>Pour cake
   batter into the greased baking pan and bake in the preheated oven for
   45-50 minutes, or until cake is golden and a toothpick inserted in the
   center comes out clean.</li> <li>Cool cake completely before
   frosting.</li> </ol><h4>FROSTING</h4> <ol><li>In a stand mixer with the
   paddle attachment (or with a hand mixebeat softened cream cheese and
   powdered sugar on medium speed until light and fluffy; about 1-2
   minutes. Stir in Cool Whip on low speed just until blended.</li>
   <li>Spread frosting evenly over the top of the cooled cake.</li>
   <li>Sprinkle with chopped walnuts and toasted coconut.</li> <li>Chill
   until ready to serve.</li> <li>To store, cover tightly and keep in the
   refrigerator for up to 4 days.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>Recipe courtesy and reprinted with permission
   of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.walnuts.org/" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener noreferrer">California Walnuts Board&nbsp;</a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake" rel="">Cake
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64110 Oreo Chocolate Cake. So easy to
   make. Pretty dessert recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/oreo-chocolate-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0

   <html><body><p><strong>Oreo Chocolate Cake</strong>. So easy to make.
   Pretty dessert recipe for chocolate lovers.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64113 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Oreo-Chocolat
   e-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Oreo
   Chocolate Cake. So easy to make. Pretty dessert recipe for chocolate
   lovers.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Oreo-Choco
   late-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Oreo-Chocolate-Cak
   e-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Oreo-Chocolate-Cak
   e-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64111--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Oreo Chocolate Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Oreo-Chocolat
   e-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 box Jiffy
   cake mix</li> <li>1 Container white vanilla frosting</li> <li>1 8 inch
   round Oreo pie crust</li> <li>1/2 6.8 oz package dark chocolate bar
   (Grated)</li> <li>cherries (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Mix cake mix
   according to package directions. Pour the mix into an 8 inch baking
   pan. Bake at 350 degrees or until tooth pick inserted into center comes
   out clean. About 25 to 30 minutes. Let cake cool.</li> <li>Using
   vanilla frosting, frost cooled cake. Smoothing with a spatula.</li>
   <li>Lifting cake carefully and put into round Oreo pie crust.</li>
   <li>Shred dark chocolate bar with grater. To grate chocolate, cut it
   into a chunk that fits comfortably in your hand. Grate the chocolate
   using a microplane grater, handheld grater, or the smallest holes on a
   box grater. Place on top of cake.</li> <li>Add cherries on top if
   desired.</li> <li>Enjoy!!</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
