   https://myhoneysplace.com/strawberry-delight-recipe/ Tue, 25 Jun 2019
   12:32:29 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64103 Strawberry Delight Recipe. Yummy
   dessert with a crunchy crust, homemade... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/strawberry-delight-recipe/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Strawberry Delight Recipe</strong>. Yummy
   dessert with a crunchy crust, homemade whipped cream center and topped
   with fresh strawberries.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64106
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-De
   light-Recipe.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Strawberry Delight Recipe. Yummy dessert with a
   crunchy crust, homemade whipped cream center and topped with fresh
   strawberries.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry
   -Delight-Recipe.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-Delight
   -Recipe-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-Delight
   -Recipe-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64104--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Strawberry Delight Recipe</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-De
   light-Recipe-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Crust:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 and 1/2 cups sifted all purpose flour</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   salt</li> <li>1/2 cup shortening</li> <li>4 to 5 Tablespoons cold
   water</li> </ul><h4>Whipped Cream Center:</h4> <ul><li>4 ounces cream
   cheese softened</li> <li>&#8531; cup powdered sugar</li> <li>1 and
   &frac12; teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>1 cup heavy whipping cream</li>
   </ul><h4>Strawberry topping:</h4> <ul><li>1 pint fresh
   strawberries</li> <li>1/3 cup white sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   vanilla</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Crust:</h4> <ol><li>Sift
   together flour and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or
   blending fork until pieces are the size of small peas.</li> <li>To make
   pastry extra tender and flaky, divide shortening in half. Cut in first
   half until mixture looks like corn meal. Then cut in remaining half
   until looks like small peas.</li> <li>Sprinkle 1 Tablespoon of the
   water over part of the flour mixture. Gently toss with a fork; push to
   one side of bowl.</li> <li>Sprinkle next Tablespoon water over dry
   part; mix lightly; push to moistened part at side. Repeat until all is
   moistened. Gather up with fingers; form into ball.</li> <li>On a
   lightly floured surface; flatten ball sightly and roll 1/8 inch thick.
   If edges split, pinch together. Always roll dough from center to edge.
   Using light strokes.</li> <li> <p>To transfer pastry, roll it over
   rolling pin; unroll pastry over pie plate, fitting loosely onto bottom
   and sides into 8 inch square pan.</p> </li> <li>Prick bottom and sides
   well with a fork. Bake in very hot oven (450 degrees F.) 10 to 12
   minutes. Set aside to cool.</li> </ol><h4>Whipped Cream:</h4>
   <ol><li>In a large mixing bowl, beat the softened cream cheese,
   powdered sugar and vanilla until light and creamy. Remove cream cheese
   mixture from mixing bowl and set aside.</li> <li>Add 1 cup heavy
   whipping cream to mixing bowl and whip until soft peaks form.</li>
   <li>Add cream cheese mixture to heavy cream and beat just until stiff
   peaks form.</li> <li>Keep refrigerated until ready to use.</li>
   <li>Spread over cooled crust.</li> </ol><h4>Strawberries:</h4> <ol><li>
   <p>Wash strawberries and remove stems; cut large berries in half,
   smaller strawberries can be left whole.</p> </li> <li>Combine
   strawberries, sugar, and vanilla in a saucepan.</li> <li>Cook over
   medium-high heat, stirring occasionally. The mixture will sizzle for a
   while, but then juice will begin to form.</li> <li>Continue stirring;
   mash a few strawberries with a wooden spoon or heat-proof spatula to
   help produce the syrup.</li> <li>Cook until sauce thickens, about 15
   minutes.</li> <li> <p>Cool and spread on top of the crust and whipped
   cream.</p> </li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our recipe using <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=strawberry"
   rel="">Strawberries</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/cookie-time/ Sun, 23 Jun 2019 14:57:19 +0000
   My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64083
   Cookie Time. 4 homemade dessert recipes for amazing and delicious... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/cookie-time/">Continue reading</a>
   <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Cookie Time</strong>. 4 homemade dessert recipes
   for amazing and delicious cookies. Including&nbsp; &ldquo;I Love
   You&rdquo; Cookies, Peach Filled Thumbprint Cookies, Peanut Butter
   Filled Cookies and Chocolate Dipped Oatmeal Cookies.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64097 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Cookie-Time.j
   pg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description='Cookie Time.
   4 homemade dessert recipes for amazing and delicious cookies.
   Including&nbsp; "I Love You" Cookies, Peach Filled Thumbprint Cookies,
   Peanut Butter Filled Cookies and Chocolate Dipped Oatmeal
   Cookies.&nbsp;'
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Cookie-Tim
   e.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Cookie-Time-267x40
   0.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Cookie-Time-100x15
   0.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64094 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/I-Love-You-Co
   okies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description='I Love
   You Cookies. The perfect way to say "I Love You" with these decorated
   sugar cookies. Adorable and tasty, '
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/I-Love-You
   -Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/I-Love-You-Cookies
   -267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/I-Love-You-Cookies
   -100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64095--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">I Love You Cookies</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/I-Love-You-Co
   okies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cookies:</h4>
   <ul><li>2 cups unsalted butter (softened)</li> <li>2 cups Sugar</li>
   <li>2 Eggs</li> <li>2 tbsp. Vanilla</li> <li>4 tsp. Baking Powder</li>
   <li>6 cups Flour</li> </ul><h4>Frosting:</h4> <ul><li>1 1/2 cups
   confectioners' sugar</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> <li>1
   teaspoon light corn syrup</li> <li>2 to 2.5 Tablespoons room
   temperature water</li> <li>pinch salt</li> <li>2 drops pink food
   coloring gel</li> <li>2 drops black food coloring. equal parts of red
   (blue, and green food coloring to make black.)</li> <li>2 dozen thin
   pretzels</li> </ul><h4>Items needed:</h4> <ul><li>Heart shaped cookie
   cutter</li> <li>Small pipping kit or 3 small squeeze bottles</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Cookies:</h4> <ol><li>Add butter and sugar to your mixer. Cream the
   butter and sugar until it is completely mixed. Do not over-mix.</li>
   <li>Add vanilla and eggs and mix until completely incorporated.</li>
   <li>Add Baking Powder and mix.</li> <li>Mix in the flour two cups at a
   time.</li> <li>Do not chill the dough, the cookies will bake better if
   the dough is at room temperature.</li> <li>Roll a handful of the dough
   out on a prepared surface until it&rsquo;s about 3/8&Prime; thick and
   cut out shapes with a cookie cutter.</li> <li>Bake at 350 degrees for
   6-8 minutes depending on the size of the cookie. Do not over-bake.</li>
   </ol><h4>Frosting:</h4> <ol><li>Whisk the confectioners&rsquo; sugar,
   vanilla, corn syrup, and 2 tablespoons of water in a medium bowl. It
   should be quite thick. If it is much too thick, add 1/2 Tablespoon more
   water. If it is much too thin, add 2 more Tablespoons of
   confectioners&rsquo; sugar. If you drizzle a little of the icing with
   the whisk, the ribbon of icing will hold for a few seconds before
   melting back into the icing. That is when you know it&rsquo;s the right
   consistency and is ready to use.</li> <li>Divide the mixture into 3
   different bowl . To one of the bowls add the pink food coloring. With a
   smaller bowl add 1/8 of the mixer with black food coloring.</li>
   <li>Frost 1/2 of each cookie with the white frosting and 1/2 of the
   cookies with the pink frosting. Spread with a knife until VERY smooth
   saving part of the frosting for piping.</li> <li> <p>Using a piping kit
   or small tipped squeeze bottle, piping around the edge of the cookies
   with the white frosting.</p> </li> <li>Place a thin pretzel across the
   bottom of the cookie. Securing underneath with dabs of frosting. Pipe 8
   lines across the top of the pretzel in sections of 2 lines.</li>
   <li>Pipe the mouth with part of the white frosting.</li> <li>Pipe the
   eyes with part of the black frosting.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64091
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peanut-Butter
   -Filled-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Peanut Butter Filled Cookies. If you like peanut
   butter then you will love this recipe. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peanut-But
   ter-Filled-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peanut-Butter-Fill
   ed-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peanut-Butter-Fill
   ed-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64092--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Peanut Butter Filled Cookies</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peanut-Butter
   -Filled-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cookies:</h4> <ul><li>1/2
   cup unsalted butter (softened)</li> <li>1 cup creamy peanut butter</li>
   <li>1 cup brown sugar</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li>
   <li>1 2/3 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
   <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/4 cup granulated sugar</li>
   </ul><h4>Center:</h4> <ul><li>1 cup butterscotch chips</li> <li>1/4 cup
   creamy peanut butter</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In a large bowl
   using a hand-held mixer, cream the butter, peanut butter, and brown
   sugar together on high speed until lightened and fluffy. Beat in the
   egg and vanilla until combined.</li> <li>Add the flour, baking soda,
   and salt, and continue to beat on low until mixture forms a dough. Cool
   dough in refrigerator for about 2 to 4 hours until firm.</li>
   <li>Preheat oven to 350F degrees and line a baking sheet with parchment
   paper.</li> <li>Place granulated sugar in a small bowl. Use your hands
   to scoop out about 2 Tablespoons of dough, flatten. Mix the
   butterscotch chips with the peanut butter. Wrap the dough around the
   mixture, Then roll into a ball, making sure that the dough is fully
   sealed around the mixture.</li> <li>Place on the prepared baking sheet,
   and flatten cookie slightly. Roll in sugar. Repeat with the remaining
   peanut butter mixture and dough.</li> <li>Bake cookies for 9-10
   minutes, or until cookies look puffed and edges are set. Allow to cool
   on the baking sheet for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack
   to cool completely.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full
   wp-image-64088"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peach-Filled-
   Thumbprint-Cookies-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peach-Fill
   ed-Thumbprint-Cookies-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peach-Filled-Thumb
   print-Cookies-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peach-Filled-Thumb
   print-Cookies-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64089--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Peach Filled Thumbprint Cookies</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Peach-Filled-
   Thumbprint-Cookies-1-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 cup butter (room
   temperature)</li> <li>2/3 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   vanilla extract</li> <li>1 teaspoon almond extract</li> <li>2 cups + 2
   tablespoons all-purpose flour</li> <li>1/2 cup peach jam</li> <li>1 1/4
   cup pecans (very finely chopped)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In a large bowl fit
   with a mixer, beat butter on high speed until light and fluffy, about a
   minute or two.</li> <li>Add sugar, and vanilla and almond extract and
   beat on medium speed.</li> <li> <p>Slowly, add flour 1/2 cup at a time
   and continue to beat on low until Soft dough forms. Compact dough and
   cover it with plastic wrap for at least 2-4 hours; dough should be firm
   when working with.</p> </li> <li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees Line a
   cookie sheet with parchment paper.</li> <li>Scoop 1 inch balls of dough
   and roll them until they are smooth. Place on cookie sheet and press
   thumb into dough on each ball. Dough may crack, simply smooth over with
   finger.</li> <li>Fill each thumbprint center with jam and bake for
   13-14 minutes. Do not over bake, cookies will harden but will be
   soft.</li> <li>Allow cookies to slightly cool then roll in very finely
   chopped pecans.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64084
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Chocolate-Dip
   ped-Oatmeal-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Chocolate Dipped Oatmeal Cookies. Recipe for
   traditional oatmeal cookies with a chocolate flare. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Chocolate-
   Dipped-Oatmeal-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Chocolate-Dipped-O
   atmeal-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Chocolate-Dipped-O
   atmeal-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64085--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Chocolate Dipped Oatmeal Cookies</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Chocolate-Dip
   ped-Oatmeal-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cookies:</h4> <ul><li>1/2
   cup butter (room temperature)</li> <li>1/2 cup sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup
   brown sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>3/4 cup
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon cinnamon</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   salt</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1 1/2 cups rolled
   oats</li> <li>2/3 cup raisins</li> </ul><h4>Chocolate Dipping
   Sauce:</h4> <ul><li>3/4 cup semisweet chocolate chips</li> <li>1/4 cup
   unsalted butter</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>2/3 cup
   granulated sugar</li> <li>2/3 cup evaporated milk</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Cookies:</h4>
   <ol><li>Pre-heat your oven to 375 degrees Then line to large cookie
   sheets with parchment paper and set aside.</li> <li>In a medium bowl
   combine the dry ingredients, apart from the sugars. Set aside.</li>
   <li>In a large bowl cream together the butter, white and brown sugar.
   Once light and fluffy add the egg and the vanilla and whip until
   combined.</li> <li>Add the dry ingredients into the wet and mix with a
   spatula until the flour has just absorbed, do not over mix.</li>
   <li>Fold in the oats and the raisins.</li> <li>Using a tablespoon
   measure scoop heaped tablespoons of the cookie dough onto your lined
   cookie sheet, leaving about 1 1/2 to 2 inches between the cookies.</li>
   <li>Bake for about 9-10 minutes or until the cookies are golden brown
   and slightly risen. Don&rsquo;t be tempted to bake for longer or you
   will loose the gooey center.</li> <li>Allow the cookies to cool
   slightly before transferring on to a wire rack to cool fully. Dip one
   end of the cookies in the chocolate sauce.</li> </ol><h4>Chocolate
   Dipping Sauce:</h4> <ol><li>In a medium saucepan combine the chocolate,
   butter, and cinnamon.</li> <li>Set over medium heat and cook, stirring
   often, until melted through.</li> <li>Stir in the sugar, and gradually
   stir in the evaporated milk.</li> <li>Bring to a boil, reduce heat, and
   simmer over low heat for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from
   heat, let cool slightly before dipping the cookies.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cookies+"
   rel="">Cookie Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   don&#8217;t have to be... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong>10 Ways To Feel Younger</strong>. You
   don&rsquo;t have to be young and perfect to feel younger. Do these
   steps and I guarantee you will feel younger.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64077 size-full" title="10 Ways To Feel
   Younger. You don't have to be young and perfect to feel younger. Do

   unger-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>Listen to this song as you scroll though the tips. I promise you it
   will put you in a good mood:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/d-diB65scQU" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <div
   id="attachment_64076" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64076"
   class="wp-image-64076"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic.jpeg"
   alt="" width="450" height="675" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic.jpeg
   867w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic-267x400.jpeg
   267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic-768x1152.jpeg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic-683x1024.jpeg
   683w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/pic-100x150.jpeg
   100w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64076"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Smile.</strong> This is my number 1 tip
   to do. Smile at everyone you meet, does not matter if they don&rsquo;t
   smile back. Smiling will make you look and feel younger. See how nice
   this older woman looks. What do you think she would look like with a
   frown on her face?</p></div> <div id="attachment_64074" style="width:
   460px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64074" class="wp-image-64074"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post8.jpg
   " alt="" width="450" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post8.
   jpg 960w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post8-400x267.
   jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post8-768x512.
   jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post8-150x100.
   jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64074"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Hair</strong>. &ldquo;Hair is your
   crowning glory&rdquo; Keep it clean and soft. You will surprised how
   good it will make you feel if you go to a good hair stylist and get an
   up to date haircut. Go to a wig shop with an honest friend and see what
   color would look good on you. Then ask your hair dresser to color your
   hair. Be funky and put a blue or purple steak in your hair.</p></div>
   <div id="attachment_64073" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64073"
   class="wp-image-64073"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post7.jpg
   " alt="" width="450" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post7.
   jpg 960w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post7-400x267.
   jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post7-768x512.
   jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post7-150x100.
   jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64073"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Teeth</strong>. You may not have
   perfect teeth, but see your dentist regularly. Keep your teeth clean
   and healthy. It may be expensive but get braces if you need them.
   Believe me it will be well worth the money. Having nice teeth is not
   only healthy but will build up your confidence.</p></div> <div
   id="attachment_64071" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64071"
   class="wp-image-64071"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-400x
   400.png" alt="" width="450" height="450" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-4
   00x400.png 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-150x150.p
   ng 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-768x768.p
   ng 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-450x450.p
   ng 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-500x500.p
   ng 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post-50x50.png
   50w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post.png
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64071"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Sing</strong>. You do not have to be a
   good singer to enjoy singing. Sing while you work. Singing 10 minutes
   daily will reduce stress, clear sinuses, improve posture and can help
   you live longer.</p></div> <div id="attachment_64070" style="width:
   460px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64070" class="wp-image-64070"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post5-400
   x265.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="298" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post5-
   400x265.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post5-768x509.
   jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post5-150x99.j
   pg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post5.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64070"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Laugh</strong>. &ldquo;Laughter is the
   best medicine&rdquo; Watch funny TV shows or videos. Spend time with
   friends that make you laugh. Laughter may seem forced at first but over
   time it will become natural. Surround yourself with funny people. Make
   jokes and laugh at their jokes.</p></div> <div id="attachment_64069"
   style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64069" class="wp-image-64069"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post3-400
   x267.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   data-pin-description=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post3-
   400x267.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post3-768x512.
   jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post3-150x100.
   jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post3.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64069"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Dance.</strong> Dancing will uplift you
   and put you in a good mood. As the old saying goes &ldquo;dance as if
   no one is watching&rdquo;. You don&rsquo;t have to be a good dancer to
   dance. Just enjoy yourself. Turn on the music while doing household
   chores. Then dance to your heart content.</p></div> <div
   id="attachment_64068" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64068"
   class="wp-image-64068"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post16-40
   0x319.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="358" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post16
   -400x319.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post16-768x612
   .jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post16-1024x81
   6.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post16-150x119
   .jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64068" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Be
   sociable.</strong> Talk to friends or family. Go to parties. Visit a
   nursing home, not only will you make them happy, you will be thankful
   for what you have. Talk about &ldquo;happy&rdquo; times. DO NOT
   complain to your friends. You will just drag yourself and them
   down.</p></div> <div id="attachment_64067" style="width: 460px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64067" class="wp-image-64067"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post12-40
   0x267.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post12
   -400x267.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post12-768x512
   .jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post12-1024x68
   2.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post12-150x100
   .jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64067" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Be
   funny.</strong> To be funny, start by taking a few cracks at your own
   expense. &ldquo;Laugh and the world laughs with you, cry and you cry
   alone&rdquo;. Trust that buried somewhere inside of you there is at
   least a nugget of humor and be yourself. Don&rsquo;t be afraid to do
   crazy things.</p></div> <div id="attachment_64066" style="width: 460px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-64066" class="wp-image-64066"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post19-40
   0x266.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="299" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post19
   -400x266.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post19-768x511
   .jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post19-1024x68
   1.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/for-post19-150x100
   .jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-64066"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Mediate</strong>. Go someplace by
   yourself that is relaxing. Could be a park, a garden, a quite place in
   your office, etc. Close your eyes and just think of nothing for 5
   minutes. It will surprise you with how much better you will
   feel.</p></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64056 Super Delicious Coconut Cookies.
   Very easy recipe for one of... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/super-delicious-coconut-cookies/">Conti
   nue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p>Super Delicious Coconut Cookies. Very easy recipe for
   one of my favorite cookies.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-64060 size-full" title="Super Delicious Coconut Cookies. Very
   easy recipe for one of my favorite cookies.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Super-Delicio
   us-Coconut-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Super-Deli
   cious-Coconut-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Super-Delicious-Co
   conut-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Super-Delicious-Co
   conut-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64057--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Super Delicious Coconut Cookies</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Super-Delicio
   us-Coconut-Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 1/4 cups flour</li>
   <li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/2
   cup butter</li> <li>1/2 cup brown sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup white
   sugar</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>11/3 cups
   coconut</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to
   350.</li> <li>In a mixing bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, salt
   and set aside.</li> <li>In a separate bowl cream butter and sugars
   together.</li> <li>Add the egg and mix well.</li> <li>Combine the flour
   mixture with the sugar mixture.</li> <li>Add coconut and vanilla.</li>
   <li>Bake for 8-10 or until lightly brown. Shorter period of time for
   soft cookies and longer for crunchy cookies.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>If you&rsquo;d like to dip in
   chocolate or white chocolate, melt 10 oz chopped chocolate, chocolate
   melts or white chocolate melts in a microwave safe bowl on 50% power in
   20 second intervals until melted and smooth.</p> </div> </div>

   center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a

   Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p><strong>Check out our YouTube
   Video:</strong></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Pw9D8EJ2Ojk" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span

   Tue, 18 Jun 2019 13:15:36 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64043 Banana And Peanut Butter Upside Down
   Cake. Easy recipe with... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/banana-and-peanut-butter-upside-down-ca
   ke/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Banana And Peanut Butter Upside Down
   Cake</strong>. Easy recipe with banana&rsquo;s on top and peanut butter
   with brown sugar mixed for the center. Yummy.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64046 size-full" title="Banana And Peanut
   Butter Upside Down Cake. Easy recipe with banana's on top and peanut
   butter with brown sugar mixed for the center. Yummy.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Banana-And-Pe
   anut-Butter-Upside-Down-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Banana-And
   -Peanut-Butter-Upside-Down-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Banana-And-Peanut-
   Butter-Upside-Down-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Banana-And-Peanut-
   Butter-Upside-Down-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Video from: <a
   href="https://www.delish.com/cooking/recipe-ideas/a27376046/peanut-butt
   er-banana-upside-down-cake-recipe/?fbclid=IwAR12OJmgjjMKso8wjbxPYR9_1pC
   qICMZ8Ou21HCYXfU37yZYXDKjsh2OIeY" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer">Delish.com</a></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64044--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Banana And Peanut Butter Upside Down
   Cake</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Banana-And-Pe
   anut-Butter-Upside-Down-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 1/2 cups
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>3/4 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>2 tsp.
   baking powder</li> <li>1/2 tsp. kosher salt</li> <li>3/4 cup whole
   milk</li> <li>1/2 cup smooth peanut butter</li> <li>1/4 cup vegetable
   oil</li> <li>1 large egg</li> <li>1/4 cup (1/2 stick) butter</li>
   <li>1/2 cup dark brown sugar</li> <li>1 tsp. pure vanilla extract</li>
   <li>5 ripe bananas (halved lengthwise)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to
   350&deg;. In a medium bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder,
   and salt. In a large bowl, whisk milk, peanut butter, oil, and egg
   until well combined.</li> <li>Stir dry mixture into wet mixture until
   just combined. In a 10&Prime; cast-iron skillet over medium heat, melt
   butter. Stir brown sugar and vanilla into butter and remove skillet
   from heat.</li> <li>Arrange banana slices on top, cut side down. Pour
   batter evenly over bananas and bake until just set, about 30
   minutes.</li> <li>Let cake cool in pan for 5 minutes, then carefully
   turn out onto a plate.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our over 1800 delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   gallons of hot water.</p> <p>Crush the pills beforehand to speed up the
   process.</p> <p>Then soak your white laundry in the mixture, and leave
   it overnight. Or use the soak cycle on your washing machine.</p> <p>In
   the morning, place the clothes in the washing machine, add a few
   aspirin pills again, and wash them as usually.</p> <p>Surely you have

   y-Cheesecake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">

   packages cream cheese, softened</li> <li>1/2 cup sugar</li> <li>1/2
   teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>2 eggs</li> <li>1 6-ounce graham cracker pie
   crust</li> <li>1 20-ounce can cherry pie filling</li> </ul></div> <div

   325&deg;F.</li> <li>Beat cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla with mixer
   until well blended. Add eggs; beat just until blended. Pour into
   crust.</li> <li>Bake for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.</li>

   n-Nuggets-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Honey-Cor
   n-Nuggets-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 64021--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">The
   Best Honey Corn Nuggets</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/The-Best-Hone
   y-Corn-Nuggets-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 11 oz. can creamed
   corn</li> <li>1 11 oz. can whole kernel corn, drained</li> <li>1/2 cup
   yellow cornmeal</li> <li>1/2 cup all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 egg</li>
   <li>2 Tablespoons milk</li> <li>4 Tablespoons honey</li> <li>salt and
   pepper to taste</li> <li>3 cups vegetable oil for deep frying</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In
   a medium bowl, stir together the creamed corn and drained whole kernel
   corn.</li> <li>Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil, and coat with
   vegetable oil or cooking spray.</li> <li>Drop spoonfuls of the corn
   mixture onto the sheet, and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.</li>
   <li>Heat one inch of oil to 350 degrees F in a large deep skillet, or
   fill a deep-fryer with oil as directed by the manufacturer. Mix
   together the cornmeal, flour, egg white, milk, honey and salt and
   pepper in a medium bowl.</li> <li>Dip frozen corn nuggets in the
   batter, and quickly fry in hot oil until golden brown. Remove to paper
   towels to drain.</li> <li>Best if served warm.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizer Recipes</a>&nbsp;</strong></p></body></html>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-glazed-sour-cream-donuts/ Sun, 16
   Jun 2019 23:40:15 +0000 My Honeys Place Breakfast Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64009 Homemade Glazed Sour Cream Donuts.
   Recipe for a sweet dessert... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-glazed-sour-cream-donuts/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Glazed Sour Cream Donuts</strong>.
   Recipe for a sweet dessert for breakfast. Yummy at it&rsquo;s best.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64010 size-full" title="Homemade
   Glazed Sour Cream Donuts. Recipe for a sweet dessert for breakfast.
   Yummy at it's best."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Homemade-Glaz
   ed-Sour-Cream-Donuts.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Homemade-G
   lazed-Sour-Cream-Donuts.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Homemade-Glazed-So
   ur-Cream-Donuts-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Homemade-Glazed-So
   ur-Cream-Donuts-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p style="text-align: center;">Picture adapted from <a
   href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Sour_cream_glazed,2011-11
   -28.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer">Wikimedia.org</a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   64011--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Homemade Glazed Sour Cream
   Donuts</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Homemade-Glaz
   ed-Sour-Cream-Donuts-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Donuts:</h4> <ul><li>2
   1/4 cups of cake flour</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons of baking powder</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon of salt</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon of ground nutmeg</li>
   <li>1/2 cup of sugar</li> <li>2 tablespoons room temperature
   butter</li> <li>2 egg yolks</li> <li>1/2 cup of sour cream</li>
   <li>canola oil</li> </ul><h4>Glaze:</h4> <ul><li>3 1/2 cups of sifted
   powdered sugar</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons of corn syrup</li> <li>1/4
   teaspoon of salt</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon of vanilla extract</li> <li>1/3
   cup of hot water</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Donuts:</h4> <ol><li>In
   a bowl, sift together cake flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.</li>
   <li> <p>Using a mixer,beat together butter and sugar until well
   blended..</p> </li> <li> <p>Add the egg yolks and mix until it turns
   light and thick.</p> </li> <li>Add dry ingredients to mixing bowl in
   three parts, ending with flour and alternating sour cream.</li> <li>Mix
   until the dough is sticky before covering it in plastic and chilling it
   for an hour.</li> <li>Roll the dough out on a floured surface until
   it&rsquo;s about a half-inch thick.</li> <li>Take a doughnut cutter and
   cut shapes out of it until it&rsquo;s all used up.</li> <li>Pour about
   two inches of oil into a deep pan.</li> <li>Fry the donuts on each side
   for about two minutes each.</li> <li>When done, drain them on paper
   towels.</li> </ol><h4>Glaze:</h4> <ol><li>Mix all the ingredients in a
   bowl with a whisk.</li> <li>Dunk the donuts in the glaze gently on each
   side and put them on a wire rack to dry.</li> <li>Wait about 15 minutes
   and enjoy!</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/moving-tips-and-tricks/ Sat, 15 Jun 2019
   13:00:18 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Household Tips &
   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=64003 Moving Tips
   and Tricks. When moving to a new home... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/moving-tips-and-tricks/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Moving Tips and Tricks. </strong>When moving to
   a new home it can be a difficult task. Tips to make it much easier.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64005 size-full" title="Moving Tips
   and Tricks. When moving to a new home it can be a difficult task. Tips
   to make it much easier."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Moving-Tips-a
   nd-Tricks.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Moving-Tip
   s-and-Tricks.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Moving-Tips-and-Tr
   icks-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Moving-Tips-and-Tr
   icks-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>Make a check list before moving:</strong></p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64004 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/moving-check-
   list.jpg" alt="" width="481" height="628" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/moving-che
   ck-list.jpg 481w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/moving-check-list-
   306x400.jpg 306w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/moving-check-list-
   115x150.jpg 115w" sizes="(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px"></p>
   <p><strong>Throw out stuff</strong> you no longer need before you move.
   <strong>Clean everything</strong> before packing it.</p>
   <p><strong>Mark your boxes</strong> for each room, and sit down and
   make your first things first list of priority in bills and calculate it
   up. Pack a box or two with clothes and items you&rsquo;ll need right
   away for work, showers etc.</p> <p><strong>Pack a big overnight
   bag</strong> with all the most important things you need to survive the
   first few days</p> <p><span dir="ltr"><span class="_3l3x">Put
   <strong>cleaning supplies</strong> in a labeled box and load it last to
   make sure it is one of the first boxes you unload. Put plenty of paper
   towels and toilet paper in it.</span></span></p> <p>Mark each box list
   what is in the box and tape the list to it. Day 1 only unpack what is
   needed . you know you are not going to cook that day so just unpack
   bathroom and bedroom. Day 2 unpack the kitchen don&rsquo;t rush it as
   you will end up reorganizing.</p> <p><strong>Label your moving boxes by
   room</strong>. Bedroom, bathroom, kitchen etc. You can use color coded
   labels so it is a quick at a glance process. Collect boxes and packing
   materials early. Pack non-essentials early to get that out of the
   way.</p> <p><strong>When moving the bed</strong> put the screws in a
   ziplock and take the bag with you in the car so you don&rsquo;t have to
   look for them at the new place. Same goes for any shelf support
   hardware.</p> <p>Make a <strong>fanny pack</strong> of tape, sharpies,
   box cutters while you are packing.</p> <p>Buy or rent a
   <strong>dolly</strong>. Makes loading and unloading much easier.</p>
   <p>Don&rsquo;t forget <strong>toilet paper</strong>. Don&rsquo;t pack
   it all. Put a roll or 2 in your purse! Sure will come in handy.</p>
   <p><strong>Pack the truck thinking ahead</strong> put the last room you
   have most likely the living room in first so it will be the last 1 you
   unload and put the furthest room probably bedroom in last so it&rsquo;s
   the first of the truck and won&rsquo;t be nothing in your way
   moving.</p> <p>If you have a lot of <strong>books</strong> move them in
   suitcases not totes they are heavy and suitcases tend to have
   wheels.</p> <p>Put <strong>Styrofoam plates</strong> between real ones
   to protect them.</p> <p>Dollar Store is great to get <strong>simple
   essentials</strong> like your utensil organizers, ice cube trays.
   (Don&rsquo;t get the pot holders they sucks unless they&rsquo;re all
   cloth)</p> <p>Make a <strong>special box</strong>. Use for immediate
   things you will need. Birth certificates, change of address forms,
   pens, pencils, scissors, safety pins, tape, needle, thread, extra
   toothbrushes, toothpaste, immunizations forms for kids &amp; pets,
   things like this that you will need immediately.</p> <p><strong>Egg
   cartons</strong> from grocery store work great for packing smaller
   items, like jewelry, etc.</p> <p>Use a <strong>trash bags</strong> as
   well a <strong>note pad</strong> to keep on the fridge or near the door
   on a hook. You will find this tip very handy.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Exit plan and plan before moving with a friend or
   S/O:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>If you are moving in with anyone you are not
   married to, be sure to <strong>make a list</strong> of what is yours
   and what is their&rsquo;s. Will make a huge difference if one or the
   other moves out. <strong>The courts will not enforce</strong> it you
   both do not have a signed list. Have an exit plan in writing, signed by
   both of you, such as who will pay the rent if one moves.</p> <p>1.
   <strong>Put into writing</strong> what each of you is responsible for
   paying, what chores each of you are responsible for doing, date it and
   <strong>BOTH OF YOU sign it</strong>. 2. As to photographs, MAKE
   CERTAIN that before you take the photos that you have a paper in the
   shot on which you have written the date &ndash; that way, all of the
   photos will clearly display when the photos were taken &ndash; if need
   in the future, this will be your BEST proof as to how the room, or
   whatever it is you are photographing, looked like at the time you moved
   in.</p> <p>Make sure the<strong> both of you are on the lease</strong>.
   If anyone leaves. You both are responsible for the lease.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips and Tricks</a></strong></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63993 Easy Blueberry Danish Recipe. Yummy

   <html><body><p><strong>Easy Blueberry Danish Recipe.</strong> Yummy
   dessert using canned crescent rolls and canned pie filling. Drizzled
   with a powdered sugar coating.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63996 size-full" title="Easy Blueberry Danish Recipe. Yummy
   dessert using canned crescent rolls and canned pie filling. Drizzled
   with a powdered sugar coating.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Blueberr
   y-Danish.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Blueb
   erry-Danish.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Blueberry-Dan
   ish-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Blueberry-Dan
   ish-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63994--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Blueberry Danish Recipe</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Blueberr
   y-Danish-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 roll
   Pillsbury Crescent Rolls</li> <li>Small amount of flour (just for
   dusting)</li> </ul><h4>Filling:</h4> <ul><li>4 ounces soft cream
   cheese</li> <li>&#8531; cup sugar</li> <li>splash vanilla</li> <li>1
   can blueberry pie filling</li> </ul><h4>Glaze</h4> <ul><li>&#8531; cup
   powdered sugar</li> <li>2 tsp. milk</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Open container of
   rolls and do not unroll them. Use a sharp, serrated knife to cut
   through them like slice/bake cookies. Make 10 slices.</li> <li>Lay each
   slice on a parchment lined cookie sheet.</li> <li>Use a measuring cup
   to flatten each roll out and build a small wall around the edge.</li>
   <li>Use a drop of flour to prevent sticking and press with your
   fingertips, too.</li> </ol><h4>Filling:</h4> <ol><li>With an electric
   mixer whip cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Dollop a small
   amount into each danish.</li> <li>Add a Tablespoon of pie filling.</li>
   <li>Bake at 350 for 18-20 minutes.</li> <li>Let cool and add a drizzle
   of glaze.</li> </ol><h4>Glaze:</h4> <ol><li>Combine milk and powdered
   sugar and drizzle on danishes.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Best if served warm. You can
   substitute pie filling for cherry or your favorite flavor. </p> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our many <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"

   14 Jun 2019 15:09:42 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Household Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63989 Best Ways To Clean Shower Glass
   Doors. Tips on how... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/best-ways-to-clean-shower-glass-doors/"
   >Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Best Ways To Clean Shower Glass Doors.</strong>
   Tips on how to get rid of the water deposits, scum, grit,mold and grime
   on your glass doors. Works well for windows too.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-63990 size-full" title="Best Ways To Clean
   Shower Glass Doors. Tips on how to get rid of the water deposits, scum,
   grit,mold and grime on your glass doors. Works well for windows
   too.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Best-Ways-To-
   Clean-Shower-Glass-Doors.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Best-Ways-
   To-Clean-Shower-Glass-Doors.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Best-Ways-To-Clean
   -Shower-Glass-Doors-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Best-Ways-To-Clean
   -Shower-Glass-Doors-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>I have use just <strong>vinegar</strong>
   but with the smell you might need a candle but the shower walls are
   clean.</p> <p><strong>Rubbing alcohol</strong> works great !!</p>
   <p><strong>Dawn dish soap with white vinega</strong>r and warm water,
   in a spray bottle then rinse well. Best cleaner I&rsquo;ve ever tried.
   &nbsp;1 cup white vinegar heated in microwave 1 minute. Add 1 cup blue
   dawn, shake together in spray bottle. Works wonders!</p> <p>Mix
   <strong>Windex with lime juice and WD40</strong>. Spray on and
   rinse.</p> <p>Use a <strong>Magic Eraser</strong>. It was a miracle
   like oven cleaner but without the chemicals.</p> <p><strong>Toilet bowl
   cleaner</strong> from the dollar tree. Trust me, I used it when I
   worked CLEANING houses or Blue Lysol toilet bowl cleaner takes all the
   hard water stains off. Works awesome!!!</p> <p><strong>Bounce dryer
   sheets</strong>. They take the soap scum right off.</p> <p>Scrub with
   <strong>Soft</strong> <strong>Scrub</strong> and rinse.</p>
   <p><strong>Scrubbing Bubbles</strong> is an awesome cleaner. Just spray
   and wipe. Makes everything shine!</p> <p><strong>Clorox Wipes</strong>
   for the doors. Easy to use.</p> <p>If it is textured glass <strong>baby
   oil</strong> works wonders.</p> <p>If you have <strong>mold</strong>
   use <strong>bleach</strong> mixed with water: 1 cap to 1 gallon
   water.</p> <p>Once you get them sparkling, I would recommend getting a
   high quality<strong> rubber window squeegee</strong> and using it after
   every shower. &nbsp;Put car wax on and wipe off after cleaning. Mine
   has cut down the need to clean the doors to only occasionally. Everyone
   who takes a shower should wipe it down afterwards.</p> <p>Some shower
   doors have <strong>manufacture recommendations</strong> depending on if
   they are glazed or other specs.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips and
   Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   Information Camping and Outdoors How To and Tips

   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/ways-to-keep-stray-cats-from-spraying-o
   n-your-property/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC
   "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"

   <html><body><p><strong>Ways To Keep Stray Cats From
   &ldquo;Spraying&rdquo; On Your Property.</strong> Feral cats can make a
   nasty smelling spray around the outside if your home. Here are some
   tips to keep them away the humane way.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63981 size-full" title='Ways To Keep Stray Cats From
   "Spraying" On Your Property. Feral cats can make a nasty smelling spray
   around the outside if your home. Here are some tips to keep them away
   the humane way.&nbsp;'
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Keep-
   Stray-Cats-From-Spraying-On-Your-Property.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Ke
   ep-Stray-Cats-From-Spraying-On-Your-Property.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Keep-Stray
   -Cats-From-Spraying-On-Your-Property-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Keep-Stray
   -Cats-From-Spraying-On-Your-Property-100x150.jpg 100w"
   sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>Cats mark their
   territory by &ldquo;spraying&rdquo; the area and it smells bad. Most of
   us love furry animals but they can be a pest.</p> <p><strong>DO NOT
   FEED STRAY CATS!</strong> It makes the problem worse. <strong>Keep them
   away from your children</strong>. They can be dangerous and have
   diseases.&nbsp; Feral cats will find their own food in the wild.</p>
   <p><b>Try these tips to keep them away the Humane way:&nbsp;</b></p>
   <p><strong>Bounce dryer sheets</strong>: Place them around where the
   cats sprayed. They don&rsquo;t like the smell and will stay away.</p>
   <p>Tip my cat breeder told me. It&rsquo;s totally weird but she swears
   by it: have a man in your family go out in the middle of the night and
   <strong>pee</strong> all around the perimeter of your proper (or area
   of concern) and they will stay away.&nbsp; She swears it&rsquo;s works
   for her and my sister had her husband do it and they say it worked!</p>
   <p>Spray <strong>vinegar</strong>. Gets rid off smell and odors so the
   cats can&rsquo;t retrace their steps.</p> <p>Place <strong>moth balls
   </strong>around the area.</p> <p>Try a <strong>Cat Scram</strong>. It
   it motion activated, and it puts out a sound they hate, but is hardly
   audible to humans! You can buy them on Amazon but cost between $35 to
   $50.</p> <p><strong>Cinnamon</strong>, <strong>Cayenne pepper</strong>
   or <strong>Chili powder</strong> sprinkled around.</p> <p>A fake
   <strong>rattlesnake statue</strong> that is motion activated to shake
   and it rattles.</p> <p>Use Motion activated <strong>water
   sprinkler</strong>.</p> <p>If you use <strong>traps from rescue
   shelter</strong>, they will come get them if trapped. Look into a place
   that will do a trap and release basically neutering a cat and it will
   actually stop spraying. Look into cat rescues not a shelter.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/camping-and-out
   -doors/" rel="">Outdoor Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63968 Southern Style Fried Green Tomatoes.
   Very quick and easy recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/southern-style-fried-green-tomatoes/">C
   ontinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Southern Style Fried Green Tomatoes</strong>.
   Very quick and easy recipe that is crispy on the outside, just like mom
   use to make. Start gathering your green tomatoes and enjoy.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-63974 size-full" title="Southern Style
   Fried Green Tomatoes. Very quick and easy recipe that is crispy on the
   outside, just like mom use to make. Start gathering your green tomatoes
   and enjoy."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Southern-Styl
   e-Fried-Green-Tomatoes2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Southern-S
   tyle-Fried-Green-Tomatoes2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Southern-Style-Fri
   ed-Green-Tomatoes2-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Southern-Style-Fri
   ed-Green-Tomatoes2-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63969--></p>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Southern Style Fried Green
   Tomatoes</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Southern-Styl
   e-Fried-Green-Tomatoes2-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>3 medium (firm green
   tomatoes)</li> <li>Salt to taste</li> <li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li>
   <li>1/2 cup milk or buttermilk</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1/3 cup
   cornmeal</li> <li>1/2 cup fine dry bread crumbs</li> <li>1/4 cup peanut
   oil or other vegetable oil</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Slice and salt green
   tomatoes: Cut unpeeled tomatoes into 1/2 inch slices. Sprinkle slices
   with salt. Let tomato slices stand for 5 minutes.</li> <li>Set out
   shallow bowls with coating ingredients: While the salted green tomato
   slices are resting, place in separate shallow bowls: the flour,
   buttermilk and egg, and breadcrumbs and cornmeal.</li> <li>Dip green
   tomato slices in flour, egg, then breadcrumbs: Heat the peanut oil in a
   skillet on medium heat. Beat the egg and the buttermilk together. Dip
   the green tomato slices in the flour-seasoning mix, then the
   buttermilk-egg mixture, then the cornmeal-breadcrumb mix.</li> <li>Fry
   the green tomatoes: In the skillet, fry half of the coated tomato
   slices at a time, for 3-5 minutes on each side or until brown.</li>
   </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Best if served
   warm </p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/side-dishes/"
   rel="">Side Dish Recipes</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html>

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/squash-and-cornbread-casserole/ Thu, 13 Jun
   2019 16:24:08 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63959 Squash and Cornbread Casserole. Old
   southern recipe that my grandma... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/squash-and-cornbread-casserole/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Squash and Cornbread Casserole.</strong> Old
   southern recipe that my grandma made often for dinner.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-63962 size-full" title="Squash and
   Cornbread Casserole. Old southern recipe that my grandma made often for
   dinner.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Squash-and-Co
   rnbread-Casserole.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Squash-and
   -Cornbread-Casserole.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Squash-and-Cornbre
   ad-Casserole-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Squash-and-Cornbre
   ad-Casserole-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63960--></p>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Squash and Cornbread Casserole</h2>
   <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Squash-and-Co
   rnbread-Casserole-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1/4 cup unsalted
   butter</li> <li>1/2 cup diced onion</li> <li>1/4 cup each diced bell
   pepper and celery</li> <li>1 tablespoon minced garlic</li> <li>4-1/2
   cups chopped yellow summer squash</li> <li>1 (10-3/4 ounce can)
   condensed cream of chicken soup</li> <li>2 cups cooked and crumbled
   cornbread</li> <li>1 teaspoon kosher salt</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon black
   pepper</li> <li>2 large eggs (beaten)</li> <li>1 cup diced cherry
   tomatoes for topping</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350
   degrees F.</li> <li>In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
   Add onion, celery and green pepper; saute until tender, about 3 to 4
   minutes. Add garlic and cook another minute. Add squash, cook and stir
   for 2 minutes; stir in cream soup, stir until heated through and remove
   from heat.</li> <li>Add cornbread crumbs and seasonings; mix well.</li>
   <li>Stir in eggs and transfer to a greased 9 inch round baking
   dish.</li> <li>Add diced tomatoes to top.</li> <li>Bake, uncovered, at
   350 degrees F for about 55 to 60 minutes, or until lightly browned on
   top.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>About
   4 servings</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dishes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63949 Summertime Cucumber Salad. Easy
   recipe and so delicious. Crispy with... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/summertime-cucumber-salad/">Continue

   <html><body><p><strong>Summertime Cucumber Salad</strong>. Easy recipe
   and so delicious. Crispy with onions and bell peppers added. Topped
   with a saucy balsamic vinaigrette dressing.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-63952 size-full" title="Summertime Cucumber
   Salad. Easy recipe and so delicious. Crispy with onions and bell
   peppers added. Topped with a saucy balsamic vinaigrette dressing."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime-Cu
   cumber-Salad.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime

   r-Salad-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63950--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Summertime Cucumber Salad</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime-Cu
   cumber-Salad-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Salad
   Dressing:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 Cup Extra Virgin Olive Oil</li> <li>1/4 Cup
   Balsamic Vinegar or white vinegar</li> <li>2 Cloves Minced Garlic</li>
   <li>2 Teaspoons Dried Italian Seasoning</li> <li>1 Teaspoon Sugar</li>
   <li>1/4 Teaspoon Black Pepper</li> </ul><h4>Salad:</h4> <ul><li>3
   Sliced Cucumbers</li> <li>1 Teaspoon Salt</li> <li>1 Cup Sliced Bell
   Pepper (red and/or green)</li> <li>1 Cup thinly sliced onion</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>In
   a small bowl, whisk together all dressing ingredients. Set aside.</li>
   <li>In a large bowl, toss the sliced cucumbers with 1 teaspoon salt,
   then allow to sit 1 hour at room temperature. Drain off liquid.</li>
   <li>Add bell pepper, onions and dressing to drained cucumbers and toss
   until ingredients are evenly coated.</li> <li>Cover and refrigerate 1
   hour before serving.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Makes 6 servings</p> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a

   https://myhoneysplace.com/10-best-ways-to-marinate-a-steak/ Wed, 12 Jun
   2019 14:13:18 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63946 10 Best Ways To Marinate A Steak.
   Using a grill... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-best-ways-to-marinate-a-steak/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>10 Best Ways To Marinate A Steak</strong>. Using
   a grill to BBQ your steaks, try these different award winning ways to
   marinate your steak or steak rubs.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63947 size-full" title="10 Best Ways To Marinate A Steak.
   Using a grill to BBQ your steaks, try these different award winning
   ways to marinate your steak or steak rubs."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/10-Best-Ways-
   To-Marinate-A-Steak.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/10-Best-Wa
   ys-To-Marinate-A-Steak.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/10-Best-Ways-To-Ma
   rinate-A-Steak-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/10-Best-Ways-To-Ma
   rinate-A-Steak-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>Marinating a steak is about flavor, not tenderizing.</p>
   <p>Less tender cuts should be marinated for at least 6 hours, but no
   more than 24 hours. Tender cuts of beef, like a tenderloin, only need
   to be marinated for 15 minutes to 1 hour for flavor. Marinating hold
   the juices in the steak.</p> <p>Place the marinade and meat in a sealed
   plastic bag or glass container so that the beef can &ldquo;sit&rdquo;
   in the liquid. Place in refrigerator to marinate anything over 30
   minutes.</p> <p>We recommend making 1/4 to 1/2 cup of marinade for each
   one to two pounds of beef.</p> <p><strong>Marinate
   ingredients:</strong></p> <p>Make a paste of Honey, Dijon mustard and
   garlic pepper.</p> <p>Mix a package of French Onion soup with 2 cups
   water, and 1 cup coffee.</p> <p>Marinate in Root Beer and Apple juice.
   Apple juice and will also tenderize the steak</p> <p>Marinate with
   garlic, olive oil and 1 can cranberry sauce.</p> <p>Apple wood and
   McCormick&rsquo;s sweet and tangy rub. BBQ at low temp.</p>
   <p>Marinading in Orange juice, or beer makes a steak delicious.</p>
   <p>Pineapple juice.</p> <p><span dir="ltr"><span class="_3l3x">A can of
   cream of onion &amp; golden mushroom mixed together.</span></span></p>
   <p>1 can of coke, 1 can of mushrooms, juice too, 1 can cream of
   mushroom soup, and 1 pkg dry onion soup mix.</p> <p>For a
   <strong>Mexican flare</strong>: marinate in a jar of salsa.</p>
   <p><strong>Awesome dry rubs. </strong></p> <p><strong>No need to
   marinate but let it set 2 hours or more for best results:</strong></p>
   <p>Lipton&rsquo;s onion soup.</p> <p>French onion soup.</p> <p>Mixed
   brown sugar and mustard.</p> <p>Italian salad dressing.</p> <p>My
   husband loves <strong>McCormick&rsquo;s Montreal Steak
   Seasoning</strong>.</p> <p>Cover with yellow mustard and grill. Yes, I
   said mustard. It won&rsquo;t taste at all like mustard, it will create
   a crust with the juiciest steak ever.</p> <p><strong>Homemade
   rub</strong>: 8 tablespoons light brown sugar tightly packed, 3
   tablespoons kosher salt, 1 tablespoon chili powder, 1/2 teaspoon ground
   black pepper, 1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper, 1/2 teaspoon thyme
   (crushed), 1/2 teaspoon onion powder.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Great video on how to grill the perfect
   steak:</strong></p> <p><iframe

   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Mix

   deep skillet until hot</li> <li>Drop by SMALL spoonfuls into oil and
   cook 2-3 minutes per side, or until deep golden brown</li> <li>Remove
   to paper towel-lined plate to drain.</li> <li>Serve warm and dipped in

   https://myhoneysplace.com/dog-separation-anxiety-cures/ Tue, 11 Jun
   2019 22:27:07 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Household Tips
   & Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63930 Dog
   Separation Anxiety Cures. Some dog&#8217;s get anxious when you... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/dog-separation-anxiety-cures/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Dog Separation Anxiety Cures</strong>. Some
   dog&rsquo;s get anxious when you are not home. Here are some tips that
   will help relieve that anxiety.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63931 size-full" title="Dog Separation Anxiety Cures. Some
   dog's get anxious when you are not home. Here are some tips that will
   help relieve that anxiety."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Dog-Separatio
   n-Anxiety-Cures.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Dog-Separa
   tion-Anxiety-Cures.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Dog-Separation-Anx
   iety-Cures-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Dog-Separation-Anx
   iety-Cures-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Wear a large shirt</strong> for a
   couple of days, to get your smell on it real good, and then try leaving
   it with them when you go.</p> <p>Try<strong> Melatonin</strong>. 1/4
   human tab. Calming is seen within 15 minutes and our fur kid
   doesn&rsquo;t look or act &lsquo;drugged&rsquo; but handles
   thunderstorms and fireworks while on this. We did some research years
   ago and also talked to our vet. She approved it to see if it would
   work, as Valium was not working for our storm phoetic. Might be worth a
   try to check with your vet to try Melatonin.</p> <p>Some <strong>crate
   training</strong> will help. Put in crate for a little bit and leave
   the room then next time do it for a little longer and so on. Not
   necessarily teaching to be in a crate but working on the separation.
   Crates are a huge help. Sometimes the space without you can be
   frightening and a crate smaller and they kinda make that feel like a
   safe place. Eventually you can just leave the crate door open and
   they&rsquo;ll go there when there having anxiety.</p> <p>Some dogs
   owners have reported success in using&nbsp;<strong>CBD
   oil&nbsp;</strong>to treat dog anxiety. CBD is a compound found in
   cannabis and hemp that dog owners, as well as humans, have found useful
   for treating a variety of different health conditions. If you&rsquo;re
   considering using CBD oil as a treatment for dog anxiety, it&rsquo;s
   best to consult with your <strong>veterinarian.</strong> Your
   veterinarian can help you determine if CBD oil might be a good
   treatment for your dog&rsquo;s anxiety</p> <p><b class="whb">Use a
   Thundershirt. </b><sup id="_ref-6" class="reference" aria-label="Link
   to Reference 6"></sup>These shirts are worn over the dog&rsquo;s torso
   and apply pressure when the dog gets anxious.&nbsp;The dog interprets
   the pressure like a baby interprets swaddling. It is comforting for
   some dogs.</p> <p>Spend five minutes a couple times a day and up the
   amount of time <strong>leaving your dog</strong>. Best to only go into
   the next room or<strong> fake them out</strong> by going out your
   normal door you would leave through. Again this isn&rsquo;t to train
   them to be in a crate it&rsquo;s to condition them to understanding you
   will be back.</p> <p><b class="whb">Use pheromone
   diffusers.</b>&nbsp;Pheromones are chemical messengers given off by a
   dog&rsquo;s mother during nursing to reassure her pups that they are
   safe and secure. Synthetic versions of this chemical, known as&nbsp;Dog
   Appeasing Pheromones (DAPs) are available for purchase as many pet
   superstores. Simply plug them into the wall or attach them to your
   dog&rsquo;s collar and watch them calm your canine companion.</p>
   <p><strong>Play Deep Separation Anxiety Music</strong> to Relax Your
   Dog while you are away or classical music. Such as this:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sXtdXcB8BTs" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p> <p><strong>Talk to your
   veterinarian</strong>. They will be able to advise you on what measures
   will work best &ndash; either behavioral or medical. If necessary, you
   can get a prescription for stronger medications.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/" rel="">How To
   and Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
