   Cream</strong>&rdquo;&nbsp; It&rsquo;s formulated to protect against
   and kill bacteria, fungus and yeast. This antimicrobial gel can be
   applied on scrapes, cuts and minor burns. It works for up to three days
   and doesn&rsquo;t sting or stain. This antimicrobial gel also hydrates
   to help minimize scarring.&nbsp; It comes in many different brands and
   can be bought at Walmart and many pharmacies. It can also be bought in
   small packages to take on trips. I once had a very bad scrape on my leg
   and it worked for the pain and helped healed the scrape. For more
   severe burns get a <strong>prescription for a stronger Silverdine

   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64117"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Poison-Ivy.jp
   g" alt="" width="400" height="710" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Poison-Ivy
   .jpg 541w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Poison-Ivy-225x400
   .jpg 225w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Poison-Ivy-85x150.
   jpg 85w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"></p> <p>What
   you&rsquo;ll most likely encounter with&nbsp;poison ivy&nbsp;is a stem
   with a larger leaf at the end, and two smaller leaves shooting off the
   sides. The leaves can be notched or smooth on the edges, and they have
   pointed tips. The&nbsp;plant is reddish in the spring, green in summer,
   and yellow/orange in the fall.</p> <p><strong>Signs and symptoms you
   have a poison ivy rash:</strong></p> <p>Skin redness, itching, swelling
   or blisters. You could have difficulty breathing, if you&rsquo;ve
   inhaled the smoke from burning poison ivy.</p> <p><strong>How to get
   rid of it:</strong></p> <p>First of all: <strong>DO NOT BURN POISON
   IVY</strong>. It will spread through the air and infect others. This
   happened to my son and it was the worse case of poison ivy he ever
   had.</p> <p>If you find poison ivy and wish to <strong>destroy
   it</strong>,&nbsp; put on gloves and cover the rest of your body with
   clothing that has been secured with duct tape around the edges. Being
   careful to not let the poison ivy touch your shin.</p> <p>Pull the
   plant out 8 inches below the roots.</p> <p><strong>Dissolve 1 cup of
   salt in 1 gallon of water and add in 1 tablespoon of dish
   soap</strong>. Mix well, pour into a water sprayer, and spray away at
   the pulled vines. Spray the ground around where you pulled it
   out.&nbsp; <strong>Careful</strong> this mixture will kill all plants
   near where you spray.</p> <p>Depose in a large plastic bad and place in
   the garbage.</p> <p>Be sure to <strong>take a shower</strong>
   afterwords and wash all clothing you wore in hot water and laundry
   soap.</p> <p><strong>You could rent a goat</strong>. &nbsp;It
   doesn&rsquo;t hurt them, and no use of chemicals.</p> <p>If you break
   out with poison ivy then read this: <a
   href="https://www.aad.org/media/news-releases/treating-poison-ivy-ease-
   the-itch-with-tips-from-dermatologists" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer">Treating poison Ivy</a></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/camping-and-out
   -doors/" rel="">Camping and Outdoor Tips</a></strong></p></body></html>

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/slow-cooker-dr-pepper-pork/ Mon, 10 Jun 2019
   15:15:33 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63899 Slow Cooker Dr. Pepper Pork. Makes a
   tender and tasty... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/slow-cooker-dr-pepper-pork/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Slow Cooker Dr. Pepper Pork.</strong> Makes a
   tender and tasty pull apart sandwich. Serve for lunch or I also use it
   as a main dish with mashed potatoes.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63902 size-full" title="Slow Cooker Dr. Pepper Pork. Makes a
   tender and tasty pull apart sandwich. Serve for lunch or I also use it
   as a main dish with mashed potatoes.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Slow-Cooker-D
   r.-Pepper-Pork.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Slow-Cooke
   r-Dr.-Pepper-Pork.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Slow-Cooker-Dr.-Pe
   pper-Pork-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Slow-Cooker-Dr.-Pe
   pper-Pork-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><strong>Cook with or without BBQ sauce!</strong></p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63900--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Slow Cooker Dr. Pepper Pork</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Slow-Cooker-D
   r.-Pepper-Pork-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 1/2-3 lb pork
   shoulder</li> <li>2 cans Dr. Pepper</li> <li>1 medium onion (cut in
   quarters and then again in half)</li> <li>2 garlic cloves (minced)</li>
   <li>1 1/2 teaspoons dry ground mustard</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon cayenne
   pepper</li> <li>Salt and black pepper to taste</li> <li>1/4 cup apple
   cider vinegar</li> <li>3 tablespoons Worcestershire Sauce</li>
   <li>Barbecue Sauce of choice (I like Sweet Baby Ray's)</li> </ul></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Place the
   chopped onions in the bottom of the slow cooker. Place the pork
   shoulder on top of the onions and add the garlic, ground mustard,
   cayenne pepper, salt, pepper, apple cider vinegar and Worcestershire
   sauce. Pour the Dr. Pepper on top and cook on high for 4-5 hours (or on
   low for 8 hours).</li> <li>Very carefully, because the pork will be
   hot, remove the meat from the slow cooker and place on a large cutting
   board. Using two forks, shred the pork by pulling away from each other.
   The meat should be very tender by this point. Place the shredded pork
   back into the slow cooker and continue to cook for an additional
   hour.</li> <li>Drain the remaining juices and toss the meat and onion
   mixture in the barbecue sauce of choice. I don&rsquo;t have an exact
   amount listed-just add a bit at a time until you get to your desired
   sauciness!</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=slow+cooker" rel="">Slow Cooker
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63888 Easiest Shepherd&#8217;s Pie. Make
   it easier with this comfort food... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easiest-shepherds-pie/">Continue

   <html><body><p><strong>Easiest Shepherd&rsquo;s Pie.</strong> Make it
   easier with this comfort food recipe. Serve for your main dish. A tasty
   classic meat and vegetable casserole.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63891 size-full" title="Easiest Shepherd's Pie. Make it easier
   with this comfort food recipe. Serve for your main dish. A tasty
   classic meat and vegetable casserole."
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easiest-Sheph
   erds-Pie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easiest-Sh
   epherds-Pie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easiest-Shepherds-
   Pie-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easiest-Shepherds-
   Pie-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Recipe For the <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-5-cheese-french-bread/"
   rel="">Easy 5 Cheese French Bread</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63889--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easiest Shepherd's Pie</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easiest-Sheph
   erds-Pie-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Filling:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 pound ground beef</li> <li>1/2 cup chopped onion</li> <li>1
   garlic clove crushed or minced</li> <li>6 ounce can tomato paste</li>
   <li>1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce</li> <li>1 and 1/2 cups beef
   broth</li> <li>4 cups frozen mixed vegetables</li> <li>Salt and pepper
   to taste</li> </ul><h4>Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1 Box instant mashed
   potatoes</li> <li>1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese- optional</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <ol><li>Preheat your oven to 350&deg;F</li> <li>Spray a 1.5 quart
   casserole dish with cooking spray. Set aside.</li> <li>Heat a skillet
   on your stove to medium heat.</li> <li>Add the ground beef, onion,
   garlic, and cook, breaking up the meat, until it is browned. Drain any
   excess grease.</li> <li>Stir in the tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce,
   and beef broth. Add vegetables, bring to a simmer, and cook for 10-15
   minutes or until thickened slightly. Season to taste with salt and
   pepper.</li> <li>Add the meat mixture to the prepared casserole
   dish,</li> <li>Make instant mash potatoes according to package
   direction.</li> <li>Spread on top of the meat mixture in the casserole
   dish.</li> <li>Top with cheddar cheese if desired.</li> <li>Bake for
   30-35 minutes, or until heated through, and cheese and potatoes are
   slightly browned.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/keto-chocolate-bars/ Sun, 09 Jun 2019
   13:31:31 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Healthy Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63876 Keto Chocolate Bars. Recipe for an
   impressive low carb dessert.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/keto-chocolate-bars/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Keto Chocolate Bars</strong>. Recipe for an
   impressive low carb dessert. A healthier choice.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-63879 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Keto-Chocolat
   e-Bars.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="Keto
   Chocolate Bars. Recipe for an impressive low carb dessert. A healthier
   choice.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Keto-Choco
   late-Bars.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Keto-Chocolate-Bar
   s-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Keto-Chocolate-Bar
   s-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63877--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Keto Chocolate Bars</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Keto-Chocolat
   e-Bars-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Bars:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 1/2 Cup &ndash; Cacao Butter</li> <li>1 1/4 Cup &ndash; Cacao
   Powder</li> <li>Sweetener to taste</li> </ul><h4>Topping:</h4>
   <ul><li>Sea salt and almond slices</li> <li>Instant coffee</li>
   <li>Orange oil</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Make a bain-marie by
   fitting a glass or ceramic bowl over a saucepan of water. Do not let
   the bottom of the bowl touch the actual water.</li> <li>Bring the water
   to the boil then turn it down to a simmer. Very slowly melt the cacao
   butter in the bowl of the bain-marie. Take the cacao butter to no
   higher than 40&ndash;45&deg;C/104&ndash;113&deg;If you think it is
   getting too hot but hasn&rsquo;t all melted, take it off the heat to
   finish melting. It is important not to overheat it or the chocolate
   will taste grainy and be &lsquo;bloomed&rsquo;, with a white cloudy
   appearance.</li> <li>When the cacao butter has melted and is at around
   40&ndash;45&deg;C/104&ndash;113&deg;F, add the rest of the ingredients.
   This should lower the temperature and we now want to bring it down to
   28&ndash;30&deg;C/82&ndash;86&deg;F; just above or below will be
   fine.</li> <li>Blend all the ingredients together with a hand-held
   blender to get rid of any cacao powder lumps and until velvety smooth
   and glossy. Do not over-blend or the chocolate will stiffen too much.
   If it is too stiff, place the bowl back over the hot water and stir
   gently for a minute or so then remove from the heat.</li> <li>Keep
   stirring the chocolate gently to cool it then, when around
   28&ndash;30&deg;C/82&ndash;86&deg;F, pour it into a silicon mold. Add
   your toppings. Then refrigerate until hard.</li> <li>****Watch Video
   for full instructions</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/healthy-recipes/"

   How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63859 How To Get The Smell
   Out Of Old Doll Clothes.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-the-smell-out-of-old-doll-cl
   othes/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Get The Smell Out Of Old Doll
   Clothes</strong>. This easy 2 ingredients will remove that old musty
   smell.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-63860 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-Th
   e-Smell-Out-Of-Old-Doll-Clothes.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Get The Smell Out Of Old Doll Clothes.
   This easy 2 ingredients will remove that old musty smell.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get
   -The-Smell-Out-Of-Old-Doll-Clothes.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-The-Sme
   ll-Out-Of-Old-Doll-Clothes-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-The-Sme
   ll-Out-Of-Old-Doll-Clothes-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>When storing old doll clothes they
   will usually have a musty old smell. This tip will remove that smell
   and make them soft at the same time.</p> <p>Use a combination, equal
   parts, of blue Dawn dish soap and Downy fabric softener.</p> <p>Letting
   each small batch soak in the sink for an hour or more. The smell is
   gone. All the clothes will need to be<span class="text_exposed_show">
   ironed to look perfect.</span></p> <p>Automatic Dishwasher detergent
   works well too, but must be dissolved in warm water, first.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips and

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63849 Strawberry French Toast. Homemade
   recipe for a sweet breakfast. &#160;... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/strawberry-french-toast/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Strawberry French Toast</strong>. Homemade
   recipe for a sweet breakfast.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63852 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-Fr
   ench-Toast.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Strawberry French Toast. Homemade recipe for a
   sweet breakfast."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry
   -French-Toast.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-French-
   Toast-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-French-
   Toast-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63850--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Strawberry French Toast</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Strawberry-Fr
   ench-Toast-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>French
   Toast:</h4> <ul><li>4 large eggs</li> <li>2/3 cup milk</li> <li>1/4 cup
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>1/4 cup granulated sugar</li> <li>1/4
   teaspoon salt</li> <li>1 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   vanilla extract</li> <li>8 thick slices bread or Texas Toast</li>
   </ul><h4>Strawberry Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1 lb fresh or frozen
   strawberries</li> <li>1/2 cup sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon lemon juice</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>French Toast:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat a skillet over medium heat. Grease well with
   butter.</li> <li>Add all ingredients, except the bread, and whisk with
   fork until blended.</li> <li>Dip bread slices into the mixture, coating
   them well on both sides, and place on hot, greased skillet.</li>
   <li>Cook for a few minutes, until the bottom of the breads starts to
   get golden brown. Flip and cook on the other side the same.</li>
   </ol><h4>Strawberry Topping:</h4> <ol><li>Chop strawberries and add
   them to a medium sauce pot, heating over medium heat.</li> <li>Add
   sugar, vanilla and lemon juice. Stir well.</li> <li>Cover and cook for
   about 15 minutes, stirring often.</li> <li>Cool sightly and serve over
   hot french toast.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>Make Strawberry Topping
   first.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>What is a migraine headache:</strong> A
   migraine can cause severe throbbing pain or a pulsing sensation,
   usually on one side of the head. It&rsquo;s often accompanied by
   nausea, vomiting, and extreme sensitivity to light and sound. Migraine
   attacks can last for hours to days, and the pain can be so severe that
   it interferes with your daily activities. Source <a
   href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/diseases-conditions/migraine-headache/
   symptoms-causes/syc-20360201" target="_blank" rel="noopener
   noreferrer">Mayo Clinic&nbsp;</a></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Home treatments from people who have
   migraines:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Make sure to stay <strong>hydrated
   with water</strong>.</p> <p>Take <strong>Benadryl with Tylenol</strong>
   and sleep in a dark quiet area.</p> <p>Place an <strong>ice
   pack</strong> on the back of the neck. Cold compresses decreases
   inflammation, slows nerve conduction and constricts blood vessels, all
   of which help reduce migraine pain.</p> <p>My doctor told me to try a
   can of regular coke and lay down in a dark room, I usually end up
   falling asleep and when I wake up it&rsquo;s gone! He said it&rsquo;s a
   ingredient in the coke that helps.</p> <p>Try the <strong>tension
   headache pills</strong> from target or Walmart. Extra strength first

   480w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"></p> <p>Try: <strong>1

   headaches. Take 600 mg of magnesium and 400 mg of B2.</p> <p>Limit

   chocolate, fermented food, beer, wine, hot dogs, sausage, smoked fish
   and cured meats.</p> <p>Apply <strong>peppermint essential oil</strong>
   to the temples has been shown to reduce the symptoms of tension
   headaches. Or <strong>Lavender oil</strong> to&nbsp;the upper lip and
   inhaled.</p> <p>Taking up <strong>yoga</strong> may even help reduce
   the intensity and frequency of your headaches.</p> <p><strong>Avoid
   strong odors</strong>, especially perfumes.</p> <p>Drink some
   <strong>ginger tea.</strong></p> <p><strong>Stop the migraine when it
   first starts</strong>: A friend told me: &ldquo;The doctor usually
   prescribes 800 mg&nbsp; of Ibuprofen and the one I bought from the
   store is 200 so I usually take four of those, drink a bottle of water
   and then hop in the shower. I slowly turn the water up as high as I can
   stand it and run my head and forehead under the water. I also filled my
   ears with hot water and plug them for a second then release and do that
   again. sometimes I also pull my hair from the root lightly and
   surprisingly enough it actually really helps!&rdquo;</p> <p>Another

   for me or slices of garlic on your temples. It won&rsquo;t get rid of

   you and relaxing.&nbsp; Sudafed bc and Benadryl 2tablets each and slice
   cucumbers over eye. Then lay at the end of bed with your head handing
   over edge relives tension.</p> <p>Wear <strong>dark sunglasses</strong>
   if you have to go outside.</p> <p><strong>Migraine Formula</strong> is
   recommended by <a
   href="https://www.webmd.com/drugs/2/drug-64327/migraine-formula-oral/de

   <strong>Goody&rsquo;s Headache Powder</strong> (orange flavored). It

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63827 Easy Chocolate Rice Krispie Balls.
   Delicious no-bake recipe with chocolate... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-chocolate-rice-krispie-balls/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p>Easy Chocolate Rice Krispie Balls. Delicious no-bake
   recipe with chocolate filled with coconut, peanut butter, rice krispies
   and pecans.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-63833 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Chocolat
   e-Rice-Krispie-Balls.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Easy Chocolate Rice Krispie Balls. Delicious
   no-bake recipe with chocolate filled with coconut, peanut butter, rice
   krispies and pecans."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Choco
   late-Rice-Krispie-Balls.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Chocolate-Ric
   e-Krispie-Balls-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Chocolate-Ric
   e-Krispie-Balls-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>You can use white or dark chocolate.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 63831--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Easy Chocolate Rice Krispie
   Balls.&nbsp;</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Easy-Chocolat
   e-Rice-Krispie-Balls-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the centers:</h4>
   <ul><li>1 cup shredded coconut</li> <li>1/2 cup peanut butter</li>
   <li>3 Tablespoons softened butter</li> <li>1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
   <li>1 cup Rice Krispies</li> <li>1/2 cup chopped pecans</li>
   </ul><h4>For the chocolate coating:</h4> <ul><li>1 (24 oz.) package
   chocolate almond bark or chocolate candy coating or white
   chocolate</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the centers:</h4>
   <ol><li> <p>Mix together,refrigerate for a half hour then form into
   balls. Return to fridge and let chill at least an hour.</p> </li>
   </ol><h4>For the chocolate coating:</h4> <ol><li>Melt chocolate
   according to package directions.</li> <li>Remove ball from refrigerator
   and dip into chocolate.</li> <li>Place on waxed paper or parchment
   paper and let sit until set.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM

   https://myhoneysplace.com/ways-to-use-bacon-grease/ Thu, 06 Jun 2019
   14:12:07 +0000 My Honeys Place Cooking Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63817 Ways To Use Bacon Grease. Some
   people say to throw... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/ways-to-use-bacon-grease/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Ways To Use Bacon Grease</strong>. Some people
   say to throw it away. Not me.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63818 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Use-B
   acon-Grease.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Ways To Use Bacon Grease. Some people say to
   throw it away. Not me.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Us
   e-Bacon-Grease.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Use-Bacon-
   Grease-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Ways-To-Use-Bacon-
   Grease-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>For the people saying throw it away, you haven&rsquo;t
   tried cooking your veggies and meat in bacon grease,<strong> it&rsquo;s
   a game changer!</strong> So delicious!</p> <p>Actually its animal fat
   which <strong>is a lot healthier</strong> for you than the store bought
   coconut oil or vegetable oils.&nbsp; Our bodies process the animal fats
   as it is without all the chemical additives.</p> <p><strong>Pop
   popcorn</strong> in the grease. DELICIOUS!</p> <p>Use it for
   <strong>frying eggs. </strong>&nbsp;And if your a liver eater
   it&rsquo;s really good fried in bacon grease. Tasty when making
   <strong>fresh green beans</strong> and in<strong> wilted lettuce
   salad</strong>. Great for fried potatoes. Love it for <strong>cooking
   cornbread.</strong> Put a table spoon in a <strong>cast iron
   skillet</strong>, preheated heated in the oven then pour cornbread in
   and cook.</p> <p><span dir="ltr"><span class="_3l3x">I cooked bacon in
   electric skillet, kept grease, used it to cook hamburg for
   <strong>Chili</strong>, BEST CHILI EVER!</span></span></p> <p>I love
   <strong>gravy with bacon grease</strong>. I substitute the butter in
   this recipe with bacon grease: <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/sh-t-on-a-shingle/" rel="">Sh..T On A
   Shingle&nbsp;</a></p> <p>You can <strong>strain bacon grease into ice
   cube trays.</strong> Once frozen, pop them out into a plastic dish, and
   keep this in the freezer. When I need bacon grease, I grab one or two.
   It&rsquo;s always fresh, and one less thing on my counter.
   &nbsp;You<span dir="ltr"><span class="_3l3x _1n4g"> can preserve small
   amounts and take them out as as need. Take a plastic ice cube tray and
   line the cups with plastic wrap. After the bacon drippings have cooled
   completely, pour the grease into the lined cup. Put a piece of plastic
   wrap loosely over the whole tray and place it the fridge until you have
   solids. Wrap each piece and place them in a freezer bag. If you want
   more protection for this you can place the baggie in a container and
   place in the freezer, then you can take them out as you need them. Easy
   peasy.. NOTE: let them thaw a bit before using.</span></span></p>
   <p>Use it in <strong>peanut butter cookies</strong> in place of
   butter.</p> <p>Use to <strong>season cast iron</strong> keeps from
   rusting and makes food taste awesome.</p> <p>You can <strong>make
   soap</strong> with bacon grease:&nbsp; <a
   href="https://sustainablescientist.net/2013/03/04/making-bacon-soap/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Making Bacon Soap</a></p>
   <p>Make Suet for Winter <strong>Bird Feeders</strong>: <a
   href="https://www.almanac.com/content/homemade-bird-food-recipe-suet"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Homemade Suet For
   Birds</a></p> <p>Get rid of it after one month. You can <strong>store
   it</strong> in a glass jar or cleaned coffee can. Strain any meat that
   might be in the grease. Store on counter top, cabinet above your stove
   or in the refrigerator. Mine is in sealed glass jar and it never molds
   or smells rancid. It will last longer if it&rsquo;s refrigerated.
   Otherwise it gets rancid after a couple months. &nbsp;2 months on
   counter 3 months in refrigerator.</p> <p>Whatever you do, <strong>DO
   NOT put it down your drain</strong>. It will eventually clog your sink
   from build up. If must&nbsp; discard it.&nbsp; Put in tinfoil lined pan
   in refrigerator until it hardens and then throw the entire thing in
   trash. Protects your&nbsp; drain.</p> <p>In summary: stick to a simple
   rule that applies to most processed food products: <strong>moderation
   is key</strong>.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/cooking-tips-tr
   icks/" rel="">Cooking Tips And Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/summertime-spinach-salad/ Wed, 05 Jun 2019
   12:11:54 +0000 My Honeys Place Recipes Salads
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63807 Summertime Spinach Salad. Healthy
   Recipe for a delicious multi ingredient... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/summertime-spinach-salad/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Summertime Spinach Salad</strong>. Healthy
   Recipe for a delicious multi ingredient salad. Party perfect.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Cool yummy and Healthy!</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-63811 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime-Sp
   inach-Salad.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Summertime Spinach Salad. Healthy Recipe for a
   delicious multi ingredient salad. Party perfect.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime
   -Spinach-Salad.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime-Spinach
   -Salad-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Summertime-Spinach
   -Salad-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Double recipe for more than 2 people.</p> <p><!--WPRM
   Recipe 63808--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Summertime Spinach Salad</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/salad3-150x15
   0.jpeg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 cups spinach
   leaves</li> <li>1 cup fresh strawberries (sliced and divided)</li>
   <li>1/2 cup cucumbers (sliced)</li> <li>1/2 cup cherry tomatoes
   (sliced)</li> <li>1/4 cup cashews</li> <li>1/2 cup sour cream</li>
   <li>1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese</li> </ul><h4>For Strawberry
   Sauce:</h4> <ul><li>1/2 cup strawberries</li> <li>1/3 cup sugar</li>
   <li>1/3 cup water</li> <li>1/2 Tablespoon lemon juice</li> <li>1
   Tablespoon corn starch mixed in 3 Tablespoon water</li> </ul></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Make Strawberry
   Sauce:</h4> <ol><li>Combine fresh diced strawberries, sugar, water, and
   lemon juice in a saucepan on medium-high heat and bring to a boil.</li>
   <li>Once the mixture begins to boil, lower the heat and allow the
   strawberries to cook and soften, breaking up the strawberries and
   stirring occasionally with a wooden spoon for about 8-10 minutes.</li>
   <li>Remove sauce from heat and press through a fine mesh strainer into
   a separate bowl, discard the seeds and solid pieces. Pour liquid back
   into saucepan and return to stove.</li> <li>Add 1 tablespoon of
   cornstarch to 3 Tbsp of water and whisk until combined and cornstarch
   is dissolved. Add to sauce and cook on medium-high heat, constantly
   whisking until glaze thickens, about 1 minute.</li> <li>Set aside to
   cool.</li> </ol><h4>Put it together:</h4> <ol><li>Place spinach on
   bottom of bowl or plate.</li> <li>In a separate bowl combine
   strawberries. cucumbers, tomatoes and cashews. Mix together.</li>
   <li>Place on top of spinach.</li> <li>Place the sour cream and cheddar
   cheese on top.</li> <li>Drizzle with strawberry sauce.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong> See more of our
   <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/salads/"
   rel="">Salad Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/important-information-about-hummingbird-feede
   rs/ Tue, 04 Jun 2019 14:12:27 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Camping and Outdoors How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63802
   IMPORTANT Information About Hummingbird Feeders. Great tips for the
   health... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/important-information-about-hummingbird
   -feeders/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>IMPORTANT Information About Hummingbird
   Feeders</strong>. Great tips for the health of your hummingbirds.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-63803"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMPORTANT-Inf
   ormation-About-Hummingbird-Feeders.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="IMPORTANT Information About Hummingbird Feeders.
   Great tips for the health of your hummingbirds.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMPORTANT-
   Information-About-Hummingbird-Feeders.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMPORTANT-Informat
   ion-About-Hummingbird-Feeders-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/IMPORTANT-Informat
   ion-About-Hummingbird-Feeders-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p><strong>Keep your hummer feeders clean, or
   don&rsquo;t put them out at</strong><span
   class="text_exposed_show"><strong>&nbsp;all</strong>. Mildew forming
   inside the nectar infects their tongues, causing their tongues to
   swell, and they slowly starve to death. Then all the babies in their
   nests die as well.</span></p> <p><strong>Clean it at least least every
   3 to 4 days</strong>. For a good cleaning use some vinegar in hot water
   and rinse well. Empty your feeder and dispose of any leftover nectar.
   Use a cleaning mop, scrub away any nectar residue or mold buildup.
   Then, mix 2 parts water and&nbsp;1 part white vinegar to make
   a&nbsp;cleaning&nbsp;mixture. <strong>Avoid using dish soap</strong> if
   possible since the leftover residue is bad
   for&nbsp;hummingbirds<b>.&nbsp;</b> Rinse your hummingbird feeder with
   cold water. Allow&nbsp;feeder&nbsp;to air dry before refilling.</p>
   <p>Or <strong>once a month</strong> use 1/4 cup bleach in a gallon of
   hot water, soak about 30 minutes, rinse well and that&rsquo;s it.</p>
   <p>It&rsquo;s recommended that feeders be changed and thoroughly
   cleaned every other day, but it is important that they are cleaned and
   refilled at least twice a week in hot weather (summer) and once a week
   in cooler weather (spring/fall) to prevent the growth of mold.</p>
   <p><strong>Safe Hummingbird food:</strong></p> <p>Mix 1 part table
   sugar with 4 parts water (for example, 1 cup of sugar with 4 cups of
   water) until the sugar is dissolved.</p>
   <p>Do&nbsp;<strong>not</strong> add red dye.</p> <p>Place mixture in
   feeder and put outside.</p> <p>Change feeder food every 3 to 4 days and
   thoroughly clean them each time to prevent harmful mold growth.</p>
   <p><strong>Just an FYI:</strong> Hummingbirds will not hurt you. They
   may come close to you but they are just exploring you. Don&rsquo;t be
   afraid of them. There are very few cases of hummingbirds attacking
   humans though, and they can&rsquo;t do much harm unless they aim for
   the eyes or other particularly vulnerable areas.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=outdoor+tips+" rel="">Outdoor
   Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/why-you-should-not-use-dryer-sheets/ Mon, 03
   Jun 2019 15:45:22 +0000 My Honeys Place Household Tips & Tricks How To
   and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63779 Why You Should NOT Use
   Dryer Sheets. Sure they smell... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/why-you-should-not-use-dryer-sheets/">C
   ontinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Why You Should NOT Use Dryer Sheets.</strong>
   Sure they smell good but are not a healthy choice. Here are the reasons
   why:</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-63780"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Why-You-Shoul
   d-NOT-Use-Dryer-Sheets.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Why You Should NOT Use Dryer Sheets. Sure they
   smell good but are not a healthy choice. Here are the reasons
   why:&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Why-You-Sh
   ould-NOT-Use-Dryer-Sheets.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Why-You-Should-NOT
   -Use-Dryer-Sheets-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Why-You-Should-NOT
   -Use-Dryer-Sheets-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><strong>Do not use them with towels</strong>: Dryer
   sheets makes towels <strong>less absorbent</strong>. Avoid using dryer
   sheets when washing bath, kitchen, microfiber or cleaning towels or
   rags.</p> <p>The coating from a dryer sheet can make <strong>pajamas
   less fire resistant</strong>.</p> <p><strong>Fabric softener</strong>
   is a better choice because it doesn&rsquo;t have all the problems that
   dryer sheets have. As long as you use the right amount, clothes should
   come out soft and static-free. Use odor free softener. Don&rsquo;t use
   fabric softener on pajamas, it also will make them less fire
   resistant.</p> <p>One of the most toxic things we do, on a regular
   basis, is use dryer sheets. Those perfume-laden (even fragrance-free)
   sheets and liquid are <strong>full of toxic chemicals</strong>.</p>
   <p><strong>Replace your fabric softener or dryer sheets with</strong>
   1/4 cup of baking soda or 1/2 cup of white vinegar to the wash during
   the rinse cycle. Your clothes will feel softer and look brighter
   without any irritating chemicals. <strong>FYI:</strong> Don&rsquo;t mix
   vinegar with bleach. It creates dangerous fumes.<strong>
   FYI</strong>:&nbsp; Don&rsquo;t use vinegar in front loading washers.
   The acid in the vinegar can eat through the door seal.</p>
   <p><strong>For static cling:</strong> make&nbsp;aluminum foil balls for
   your dryer. All you need is two or three foil balls made with 3 or 4
   square feet of aluminum foil each, mashed into a ball that is around 2
   to 3 inches in diameter. Once they&rsquo;re made, all you do is toss
   them in the dryer with your wet clothes.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips And
   Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"

   a bread bowl filled... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong>Penne Pasta Bread Bowls</strong>. Recipe for a
   bread bowl filled with Penne pasta, mushrooms and a creamy Alfredo
   sauce.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-63776"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Penne-Pasta-B
   read-Bowls.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Penne Pasta Bread Bowls. Recipe for a bread bowl
   filled with Penne pasta, mushrooms and a creamy Alfredo sauce.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Penne-Past
   a-Bread-Bowls.jpg 600w,

   Bowls-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Penne-Pasta-Bread-
   Bowls-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>You can use alternate Pasta if desired. You can also
   use the scooped bread to cut into cubes, melt a little butter and
   garlic, then coat and toast.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   63773--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Penne Pasta Bread Bowls</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Penne-Pasta-B
   read-Bowls-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 loaf
   sourdough bread</li> <li>1 package penne pasta (cooked according to
   package directions)</li> <li>1/2 cup Thinly sliced mushrooms</li>
   <li>1/2 cup unsalted butter</li> <li>1 block (8 oz.) cream cheese (cut
   into chunks)</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoons garlic powder</li> <li>1 cup
   heavy whipping cream</li> <li>1 cup chicken broth</li> <li>8 oz wedge
   Parmesan cheese (shredded)</li> <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
   </ul></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Cut
   off the top of the bread. Use a spoon to scoop out the center of the
   bread. Set aside.</li> <li>Cook Penne pasta, according to package
   directions. Drain the pasta.</li> <li>Melt butter in a saucepan over
   medium-high heat. Once melted, add in the chunked cream cheese and
   garlic powder. Stir with a whisk until smooth.</li> <li>Add the
   whipping cream and chicken broth a little bit at a time, while whisking
   constantly. Bring to a low boil. When starting to boil reduce heat to
   medium-low and add the Parmesan cheese, salt &amp; pepper. Simmer for
   5-10 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring occasionally.</li> <li>
   <p>Add the drained pasta and sliced mushrooms. Stir until well
   blended.</p> </li> <li>Place into the scooped bread and serve
   warm.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div>
   </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Check out more of our <a

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-use-to-progressive-lenses-glasses/
   Sat, 01 Jun 2019 13:07:18 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY
   And Tips How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=63756 How To Get
   Use To Progressive Lenses Glasses.&#160; Also called... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-use-to-progressive-lenses-gl
   asses/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Get Use To Progressive Lenses
   Glasses.</strong>&nbsp; Also called No-Line Bifocals. They often cause
   dizziness or nausea. Here are tips to help you get use to them.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-63757"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-Us
   e-To-Progressive-Lenses-Glasses.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Get Use To Progressive Lenses
   Glasses.&nbsp; Also called No-Line Bifocals. They often cause dizziness
   or nausea. Here are tips to help you get use to them: "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get
   -Use-To-Progressive-Lenses-Glasses.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-Use-To-
   Progressive-Lenses-Glasses-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/How-To-Get-Use-To-
   Progressive-Lenses-Glasses-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>It is <strong>normal</strong> to
   get <strong>dizzy</strong> when first using progressive lenses glasses.
   That is because you look down and see thru the bifocal. It will take
   some time for your eyes to adjust. But in the meantime if you have to
   do stairs or escalators <strong>use the rail so you don&rsquo;t
   fall</strong> and be careful. If you have someone with you, let them
   know that you have the bifocal and ask for help if you need it. When
   you first get them, use them only while sitting for awhile and
   gradually add walking with them .I have been thru this, <strong>it does
   get better</strong>. You will have to <strong>practice</strong> wearing
   them!</p> <p>Make sure that they are <strong>sitting correctly on your
   face</strong>. If they aren&rsquo;t you surely will have trouble. Might
   need to be adjusted around your ears. See your optometrist to adjust
   them. Most places where you bought your glasses will adjust them for
   free.</p> <p><strong>When you are walking, </strong>don&rsquo;t look
   straight down at the floor because you will trip and or fall.</p>
   <p><em>Just <strong>move your eyes not your head</strong> to look at
   things. Your eyes will look down for the bifocal and straight for the
   distant. Move your eyes up and down not your head . That&rsquo;s
   what&rsquo;s making you dizzy. It takes practice but once you get use
   to doing this every thing will clear up.</em></p> <p>Some people they
   just <strong>don&rsquo;t work</strong> well. Then you should get
   separate regular glasses, then buy readers from the drug store.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Also see our other <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/" rel="">How To
   And Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Should serve 9, but my husband ate the whole thing.
   Now I have to make another one.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   63749--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Triple Chocolate Pie</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Triple-Chocol
   ate-Pie-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   </p><div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Crust:</h4>
   <ul><li>3/4 cup crushed chocolate graham crackers</li> <li>4
   Tablespoons unsalted butter melted</li> </ul><h4>Center:</h4> <ul><li>1
   pkg. (3.4 oz. JELL-O Vanilla Flavor Instant Pudding)</li> <li>1 and 1/2
   cups cold milk</li> <li>1/2 tub (8 oz. Whipped Topping, thawed)</li>
   <li>1 cup dark chocolate chips</li> </ul><h4>Topping:</h4> <ul><li>1
   cup softened butter</li> <li>1/2 cup cocoa powder sifted</li> <li>5
   cups powdered sugar</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li> <li>3-4
   tablespoons milk</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Crust:</h4>
   <ol><li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.</li> <li>Line a 8 inch round pan
   with parchment paper</li> <li>In a blender crush chocolate graham
   cracker and melted butter until well blended</li> <li>Press into
   prepared pan</li> <li>Bake for 7 minutes</li> <li>Remove and cool</li>
   </ol><h4>Center:</h4> <ol><li>Whisk pudding mix and milk in large bowl
   for 2 minutes or until blended.</li> <li>Blend in whipped topping and
   chocolate chips</li> <li>Place on top of crust and refrigerator for 2
   hours</li> </ol><h4>Topping:</h4> <ol><li>Whip butter and cocoa
   together until smooth in large bowl.</li> <li>Stir in vanilla and
   powdered sugar.</li> <li>Slowly add in milk until topping reaches
   desired consistency.</li> <li>Scrape sides and whip again until light,
   fluffy and smooth, 1-2 minutes</li> <li>Smooth on top of cooled
   pie</li> <li>Refrigerate until ready to serve</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a

   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>I have used Corning Ware for many many
   years. I love them because in over 20 years none of them have broken.
   You can put them in the microwave and oven.</p> <p>Now they are stained
   and ugly looking. I have scrubbed and scrubbed them and they now
   stained to the point I started to throw them away. Then I found the
   perfect way to clean them and now they look brand new.</p> <p>I use
   this method with the plates and dishes:</p> <p>Fill your sink with hot
   water and dawn dish soap. Then add 1 cup bleach. Soak for at least 2
   hours. Rinse and you will be amazed at how beautiful they are
   again.</p> <p>Guess I will keep them another 25 years.</p> <p

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Vegan Mushroom and Cauliflower
   Salad</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Vegan-Mushroo
   m-and-Cauliflower-Salad-150x150.jpg"></p> <p

   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>3&nbsp;
   Tablespoons&nbsp; olive oil</li> <li>3&nbsp; Tablespoons&nbsp;
   butter</li> <li>1/2 &nbsp; pound&nbsp; baby mushrooms</li> <li>1/2
   pound cauliflower (sliced)</li> <li>1/2 red or green pepper
   (sliced)</li> <li>1/4 red onion (sliced)</li> <li>1&nbsp; clove&nbsp;
   garlic,&nbsp;thinly sliced</li> <li>1&nbsp; Tablespoon&nbsp; white
   cooking wine</li> <li>1/2&nbsp; Tablespoon&nbsp; Worcestershire
   sauce</li> <li>1/4&nbsp; teaspoon&nbsp; garlic powder</li> <li>Salt and
   pepper to taste</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li> <p>Heat olive oil
   and butter in a large skillet over medium heat.</p> </li> <li>Add
   mushrooms and cauliflower. Cook in the hot oil and butter until
   mushrooms and cauliflower are lightly browned, about 5 minutes.</li>
   <li> <p>Reduce heat to low then add remaining ingredient and simmer
   until mushrooms and cauliflower are tender, about 5 to 8 more
   minutes.</p> </li> <li>Serve cold or over lettuce.</li> </ol></div>

   tes/ Wed, 29 May 2019 16:31:43 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60814 Best Ways To Relieve Itching From
   Mosquito Bites. Try these... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/best-ways-to-relieve-itching-from-mosqu
   ito-bites/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Best Ways To Relieve Itching From Mosquito
   Bites</strong>. Try these tips to stop the itching. Your mosquito bites
   will stop itching and go away.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full
   wp-image-60819"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Best-Ways-To-
   Relieve-Itching-From-Mosquito-Bites.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900" data-pin-description="Best Ways To Relieve Itching From
   Mosquito Bites. Try these tips to stop the itching. Your mosquito bites
   will stop itching and go away."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Best-Ways-
   To-Relieve-Itching-From-Mosquito-Bites.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Best-Ways-To-Relie
   ve-Itching-From-Mosquito-Bites-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Best-Ways-To-Relie
   ve-Itching-From-Mosquito-Bites-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>You first need to take <strong>Benadryl
   tablets</strong> so that it can stop the histamine reaction. Then try
   these tips and see what works best for you.</p> <p><strong>Silver
   Solution</strong> by Curad. I buy it at WalMart &amp; any pharmacy
   should have it. Bites are gone in an hour or two.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60815"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mosquito-bite
   s.jpg" alt="" width="261" height="195" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mosquito-b
   ites.jpg 261w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mosquito-bites-150
   x112.jpg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 261px) 100vw, 261px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Benadryl cream</strong> in a tube is also good
   gets the swelling down and also stops the itch. It is available at all
   pharmacies.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-thumbnail
   wp-image-60816"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-ultr
   atabs-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-u
   ltratabs-150x150.png 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-ultratabs
   -400x400.png 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-ultratabs
   -450x450.png 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-ultratabs
   -50x50.png 50w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/benadryl-ultratabs
   .png 500w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></p> <p>Dissolve
   <strong>Extra Strength Aspirin or Tylenol</strong> into a paste and dab
   into them.</p> <p><strong>Witch Hazel</strong> works great.</p>
   <p>Rub<strong> toothpaste</strong> on the bites.</p>
   <p><strong>Spit</strong>:&nbsp; Put some spit on your finger and rub
   the bit. I&rsquo;m from the south rice fields and bayous my great
   grandma&rsquo;s old time trick and it works.</p> <p><strong>Skin So
   Soft</strong> by Avon.</p> <p><strong>Johnson&rsquo;s baby oil</strong>
   gel in green tube.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-thumbnail
   wp-image-60817"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby
   -oil-150x150.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-b
   aby-oil-150x150.png 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby-oil-
   400x400.png 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby-oil-
   450x450.png 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby-oil-
   500x500.png 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby-oil-
   50x50.png 50w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Johnsons-baby-oil.
   png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></p>
   <p><strong>Deodorant</strong> instantly stops the itching. For bad
   itching, grab your antiperspirant dry-stick deodorant and just swipe it
   across the bites. It seals the bite from the air and your itching will
   just stop.</p> <p>Cotton balls soaked in<strong> rubbing
   alcohol</strong>. It stops the itch and helps heal them quicker.</p>
   <p><strong>&nbsp;Vicks vapor rub</strong>. &nbsp;Smear it on pulse
   points and the mosquitoes will leave you alone. Why it works: Vicks
   VapoRub contains cedar leaf oil, which is a natural insect repellent.
   If it&rsquo;s too late to prevent mosquito bites, rubbing VapoRub on
   the bumps will also relieve your itching.</p> <p><strong>Lemon grass
   oil</strong> and water in spray bottle. They will still be around you
   but won&rsquo;t bite. It&rsquo;s all natural and can even be put on
   animals/pets because it&rsquo;s safe.</p> <p>Believe it or not
   <strong>Preparation H</strong> works. I didn&rsquo;t believe it until a
   doctor in the emergency room where I work told me about it. If you
   don&rsquo;t believe it just try it once one mosquito bite. And
   you&rsquo;ll be a believer!</p> <p>Dab a tiny bit of <strong>tea tree
   oil</strong> on each one and the swelling goes down and they stop
   itching.</p> <p>Wet your finger and rub on a bar of ordinary
   <strong>bath soap</strong> then rub on the bite takes the itch
   away.</p> <p><strong>Hand sanitizer</strong>. Rub it on the bites and
   they won&rsquo;t itch for awhile.</p> <p><span dir="ltr"><span
   class="_3l3x"><strong>Camphor-Phenique</strong> works wonders I apply
   it and they vanish.</span></span></p> <p><strong>Windex</strong>:
   It&rsquo;s the ammonia that kills the itch. It works incredibly well,
   you won&rsquo;t believe the relief!</p> <p>Strangely enough
   <strong>apple slices.</strong> I use granny smiths. Cut an apple into
   slices save 2 (eat the rest) and rub over the mosquito bites. It works
   and is chemical free.</p> <p><strong>Resist scratching</strong>, the
   less you scratch the sooner your bites will heal and not leave
   scarring.</p> <p>Use some some <strong>BIOFREEZE f</strong>or the itch
   from the bites. I have the roll on and it takes the mild swelling out
   of my feet and relieves the pain. Works great for muscle pain
   too.&nbsp; I can&rsquo;t say enough wonderful stuff about this
   product.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-thumbnail wp-image-60818"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 3/4cupsmilk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pure vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large
   egg</span></li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cheery pie filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   vanilla</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 to 2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Pancakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   together the flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a
   large-sized bowl. Make a well in the center and add the milk, slightly
   cooled melted butter, vanilla and egg. Mixture needs to be thin.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use a
   wire whisk to whisk the wet ingredients together first before slowly
   folding them into the dry ingredients. Mix together until smooth
   .</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat a
   nonstick pan over low-medium heat and wipe over with a little butter to
   lightly grease pan. Pour  cup of batter onto the pan and spread out
   gently into a round shape with the back of ladle.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the underside is golden and bubbles begin to appear on the surface,
   flip with a spatula and cook until golden. Repeat with remaining
   batter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>For the Cherry Filling:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cherries into a large saucepan. Add 1/2 cup honey (or sugar), lemon
   juice, cornstarch, vanilla extract, then stir to coat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn on
   the heat to medium. Cook the filling, stirring often, until glossy and
   thickened, about 5 to 10 minutes. Remove pan from the heat and let the
   filling cool slightly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Frosting: </strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   medium bowl, mix powdered sugar and butter with spoon or electric mixer
   on low speed. Stir in vanilla and 1 tablespoon of the milk.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Gradually beat in just enough remaining milk to make frosting
   smooth and spreadable. If frosting is too thick, beat in more milk, a
   few drops at a time. If frosting becomes too thin, beat in a small
   amount of powdered sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Put it together:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lay the
   pancakes flat. Add 1/4 cup of cheery filling in the center and fold the
   pancake over the filling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60810-step-0-12" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the frosting on top. Best if served warm.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a> and <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipes.</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large potatoes</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled and cut into
   cubes</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put 3/4
   cup of flour on a plate.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   the 2 eggs in a shallow bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   cooking oil to medium heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Coat
   the steaks lightly, one at a time, into the egg mixture, then into the
   flour. This will seal in the juices.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in medium hot oil and fry for 2 minutes on each side. Or until slightly
   brown.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the meat on top of each other and mix 1/4 cup of flour to the hot oil,
   to make the gravy. Stir until a thin paste. Slowly add 1 cup water and
   mix until smooth. Add more water if too thick. Spread the steaks around
   the pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Peel
   potatoes, cut into small cubes then place in the pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60799-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   covered on simmer heat until potatoes are soft. (About 1 hour)</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a

   <html><body><p><strong>Blue Or Green Jello Shots</strong>. Festive
   Party drinks that will be the hit of the day. Easy recipe.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60791 size-full" title="Blue Or Green Jello
   Shots. Festive Party drinks that will be the hit of the day. Easy
   recipe.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Blue-Or-Green
   -Jello-Shots.jpg" alt="Blue Or Green Jello Shots. Festive Party drinks
   that will be the hit of the day. Easy recipe.&nbsp;" width="600"
   height="900"

   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-real-difference-between-brown-and-white-e
   ggs/ Fri, 24 May 2019 12:10:11 +0000 My Honeys Place Cooking Tips &
   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60783 The Real
   Difference Between Brown And White Eggs. Is there... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-real-difference-between-brown-and-w
   hite-eggs/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p>The Real Difference Between Brown And White Eggs. Is
   there really a difference? Check and see.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60784 size-full" title="The Real Difference
   Between Brown And White Eggs. Is there really a difference? Check and
   see.&nbsp;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/The-Real-Diff
   erence-Between-Brown-And-White-Eggs.jpg" alt="The Real Difference
   Between Brown And White Eggs. Is there really a difference? Check and
   see.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/The-Real-D
   ifference-Between-Brown-And-White-Eggs.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/The-Real-Differenc
   e-Between-Brown-And-White-Eggs-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/The-Real-Differenc
   e-Between-Brown-And-White-Eggs-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p><strong>Contrary to some beliefs</strong>&nbsp;the color of an egg
   is not an indicator of quality. When it comes to taste and nutrition,
   there is no difference between white and brown eggs.</p> <p>Despite the
   fact that they&rsquo;re often&nbsp;<strong>more
   expensive</strong>,&nbsp;brown eggs&nbsp;aren&rsquo;t any&nbsp;better
   for you&nbsp;than white&nbsp;eggs, and vice versa.</p> <p>Egg color
   depends&nbsp;on the <strong>breed of the chicken</strong>. For example,
   White Leghorn chickens lay white-shelled eggs, while Plymouth Rocks and
   Rhode Island Reds lay brown-shelled eggs.</p> <p><strong>Eggs contain a
   lots of vitamins</strong>, minerals and high-quality protein, with less
   than 80 calories each.</p> <p>Eggs that are bought directly from
   <strong>small,&nbsp;local farmers&nbsp;</strong>are likely to be the
   freshest and usually come from hens that live in more natural
   environments with plenty of access to sunshine.</p> <p>If you are
   trying to&nbsp;<strong>cut back on&nbsp;calories</strong>, choose
   poached or boiled eggs.</p> <p>White eggs&nbsp;are <strong>easier to
   peel</strong> then brown.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/cooking-tips-tr
   icks/" rel="">Cooking Tips &amp; Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
