   wprm-block-text-bold">Easy Vanilla Wafer Banana Pudding</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 teaspoons vanilla
   extract</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla wafersabout 60
   cookies</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large ripe bananascut into 1/4-inch
   slices</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Whipped cream for
   topping</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cherries for top if
   desired.</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt. Whisk in milk. Cook and stir
   over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat to low; cook
   and stir about 2 minutes . Remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, whisk eggs. Add the whisked eggs into the warm mixture,
   whisking constantly. Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes.
   Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla. Cool 15 minutes, stirring
   occasionally.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After
   cooled gently stir in the banana slices and 1/2 of the vanilla
   wafers.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   into 4 individual bowls, top with whipped cream, then CRUMBLE up the
   other half of the vanilla wafers and spread on top.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   cherries on top if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60777-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until ready to serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our
   delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small tomato</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   topping</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups shredded rotisserie
   chicken</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 10-</span> <span

   below)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Shredded cabbage</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for topping</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for topping</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Small dollop of sour cream</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for topping</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Shredded Cheddar cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for topping</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Mexican rice</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for
   serving</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60771-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 450 degrees F.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60771-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   the butter with 2 tablespoons vegetable oil in a skillet; transfer to a
   bowl. Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons oil in the skillet. Add the
   onion, garlic and cook until soft, about 3 minutes. Add the chili
   powder, cumin, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon salt; saute for 30 seconds. Add
   the tomato and cilantro and cook until slightly dry, about 2 minutes.
   Stir in the chicken and sour cream and warm through. Remove from the
   heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60771-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush a
   baking sheet with some of the butter-oil mixture. Spread 2 tablespoons
   refried beans down the center of each tortilla, leaving a 2-inch border
   on both ends. Top with 1 cup chicken mixture and 1/4 cup cheese. Fold
   in the ends and roll up.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60771-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   chimichangas seam-side down on the baking sheet; brush with the
   butter-oil mixture. Bake 8 to 10 minutes per side, brushing again after
   you flip. Top with the sauce (recipe below), sour cream, avocado sauce,
   more cheese, shredded cabbage and tomato. Serve with rice and the
   remaining beans.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Sauce:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60771-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Saute
   1/2 cup chopped onion and 2 chopped garlic cloves in a skillet with
   vegetable oil. Add a pinch each of chili powder, cumin, sugar and salt;
   cook 30 seconds. Stir in two 4-ounce cans chopped green chiles (drained
   and rinsed); cook 2 minutes. Add 1 cup chicken broth and simmer until
   thickened, then puree. Stir in 1/4 cup chopped cilantro.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Be sure to see more <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and cupswater</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3-4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oil</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for frying</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oil</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   chicken breasts into 1-inch cubes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium-large bowl, mix together cornstarch, flour and salt &amp;
   pepper. Add the egg, oil and water. Whisk until smooth. Add the chicken
   cubes to the mixture and marinate for 30 minutes in the
   refrigerator.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium-large saucepan, heat the oil to 350F. Add the marinated chicken
   cubes in batches and deep fry them for 3-5 minutes until golden brown.
   Remove to a paper towel-lined plate and cover with foil to keep
   warm.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, mix together orange juice, soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar
   and orange zest.Heat a skillet, medium-high heat and add oil. Then add
   garlic and stir-fry for a few seconds until fragrant. Add in the sauce
   mixture and stir to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   cornstarch and water in a separate bowl, and then add the mixture to
   the pan to thicken the sauce. Stir until mixture is smooth and thick,
   about 5 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60765-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   back the fried chicken and toss to coat completely! Serve warm.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/do-you-know-a-narcissist/ Thu, 16 May 2019
   14:30:03 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60721 Do You Know A Narcissist? Tips on
   what is a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/do-you-know-a-narcissist/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Do You Know A Narcissist?</strong> Tips on what
   is a Narcissist and how a Narcissist acts:</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60725"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Do-You-Know-A
   -Narcissist.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Do You Know A Narcissist? Tips on what is a
   Narcissist and how a Narcissist acts:"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Do-You-Kno
   w-A-Narcissist.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Do-You-Know-A-Narc
   issist-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Do-You-Know-A-Narc
   issist-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>1- Everything will revolve around this
   person. It will be all about their <strong>needs</strong>, their
   <strong>wants</strong>, their <strong>life</strong>.</p> <p>2- Nothing
   will ever be<strong> their fault</strong>. Even with evidence to the
   contrary, it still is<strong> Never their fault. </strong></p>
   <p>3-<strong>They neglect you</strong>, take you for granted, and never
   make you feel important or valuable.</p> <p>4- <strong>Selfish</strong>
   is an understatement when you are dealing with them.</p> <p>5- They
   <strong>lack</strong> <strong>empathy and compassion</strong>, and the
   only feelings they care about is their own.</p> <p>6- Everyone around
   them are <strong>objects</strong> to be used for <strong>their own
   gratification</strong> or needs.</p> <p>7-They have a a deep need for
   <strong>excessive attention</strong> and admiration.</p> <p>8-A
   Narcissist will have fantasies about <strong>power</strong> and a sense
   of <strong>entitlement</strong>.</p> <p>If you know one, <strong>stay
   away</strong> from them and don&rsquo;t have a relationship with them.
   They are troubled and will <strong>exploit you and others for personal
   gain</strong>.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of
   our <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/amazing-information/"
   rel="">Amazing Information</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cheesy Potato Broccoli Casserole</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">russet potatoes</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced into 1/4 inch
   slices</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen
   broccoli</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">diced onions</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sliced mushrooms</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded Mozzarella or Cheddar
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">slices</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bacon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cooked and crumbled or bacon
   bits</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or dried parsley or bay
   leaves</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to garnish
   (optional)</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375 degrees. Butter a 9x13 -inch baking dish. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Layer
   half of the potato slices in the dish, overlapping slightly. Season
   with salt and pepper. Sprinkle the cheese on top of the potatoes and
   add the crumbled bacon pieces, broccoli, mushrooms and onions. Add the
   other half of the potato slices on top of the cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, mix together the milk and eggs. Pour the mixture over top
   of the potatoes and gently stir.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the parsley or bay leaves on top (optional).</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   with foil and bake for 1 hour or until the casserole is lightly
   browned.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60713-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   the dish to rest for 15-20 minutes before serving.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">19</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">graham crackers</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 pounds fresh
   strawberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cream
   powdered sugar, vanilla, and salt with the heavy cream a mixer. Beat
   until the cream mixture holds stiff peaks.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   a thin layer of heavy cream mix in a 9x13 round or square pan just to
   coat the bottom.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Layer 5
   graham crackers across the center of the pan, then 2 more,breaking them
   as needed to fit around the top and bottom edges.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   a thick layer of heavy cream mix over grahams and top with a hearty
   layer of sliced strawberries.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   graham crackers on top of strawberries, then heavy cream mix, then
   layer of thinly sliced strawberries. Repeat the
   graham-strawberries-cream layers 1 more time (3 times total) and you
   should reach the top of the pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight until the graham
   crackers have softened completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with more sliced strawberries or whole strawberries if you
   desired.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60708-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   chilled.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Homemade Cream Horns</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package puff pastry</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">defrosted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups heavy
   cream</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Crunched up Oreo Cookies</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">You will also need a Cream Horn
   Mold. They are very inexpensive.</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F. Line a shallow baking sheet with parchment
   paper.Roll out one sheet of puff pastry on a lightly floured surface
   and flatten out any creases.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut the
   sheet in half vertically, then cut each half into six long, thin strips
   of pastry.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Working
   with one strip of pastry at a time, wrap the pastry around a cream horn
   mold.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Begin
   at the pointed end of the cone, pinching the pastry together at the
   base.Overlap the pastry slightly as you wind it up. Place the cone
   seam-side down on the prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining
   pastry.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 15 minutes, or until horns are golden brown. Remove horns from the
   baking sheet and slide out the molds. Allow horns to cool completely
   before filling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60704-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat heavy cream to soft peaks. Beat in vanilla extract and
   powdered sugar. Transfer mixture to a piping bag and pipe into each
   cooled horn. Place crunched up Oreo cookies on top if desired. Best if
   serve immediately.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   This easy dessert or appetizer... <a class="continue-reading-link"

   ontinue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0

   <html><body><p><strong>Sweet And Easy Candied Strawberries</strong>.
   This easy dessert or appetizer recipe will make your strawberries even
   tastier.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-60689"

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Sweet And Easy Candied Strawberries</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Strawberries</span></li></ul></div>
   </div> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the sugar, water and corn syrup in a saucepan over medium heat.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the sugar is dissolved turn the heat up and simmer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   candy thermometer heat the candy to 300-310 and turn the heat to
   low.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put a
   toothpick in the strawberries and dip the strawberries in the coating
   and shake it off.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   parchment paper and let harden (it wont take long)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60688-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   the same day.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizer Recipes</a> and <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring 2
   cups of water to a boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60676-step-0-1"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl mix sugar and Jell-O mix. Stir in boiling water, stirring

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir 2
   cups of cold water into bowl and then pour mixture into Popsicle
   molds.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60676-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   Popsicle's into the freezer until completely frozen.</div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60671-step-0-1"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine

   5px">Sprinkle over the batter.</div> </li><li

   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 for 40-50 minutes until center springs back when touched.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60671-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div

   served warm. You could sprinkle powdered sugar over top or serve with
   whipped cream or peach ice cream.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-dipping-sauce/ Tue, 07 May 2019
   22:55:42 +0000 My Honeys Place Appetizers Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60654 Homemade Dipping Sauce. Great
   appetizer recipe for dipping boiled shrimp,... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-dipping-sauce/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Homemade Dipping Sauce</strong>. Great appetizer
   recipe for dipping boiled shrimp, steamed crab legs or as a marinade
   for grilled c<span class="text_exposed_show">hicken. Taste delicious on
   a hamburger, too.&nbsp;</span></p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-60656 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Homemade-Dipp
   ing-Sauce.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Homemade Dipping Sauce. Great appetizer recipe
   for dipping boiled shrimp, steamed crab legs or as a marinade for
   grilled chicken. Taste delicious on a hamburger, too.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Homemade-D
   ipping-Sauce.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Homemade-Dipping-S
   auce-267x400.jpg 267w,

   auce-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/beet-and-pineapple-smoothie/ Mon, 06 May 2019
   13:55:30 +0000 My Honeys Place Drinks Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60644 Beet and Pineapple Smoothie. One a
   day may keep the... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/beet-and-pineapple-smoothie/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Beet and Pineapple Smoothie.</strong> One a day
   may keep the doctor away. Make this healthy tasty recipe for breakfast
   or a snack. Has a more pineapple taste than beet.</p> <p>Beets are low
   in calories, yet high in valuable vitamins and minerals. In fact, they
   contain a bit of almost all the vitamins and minerals that you need.
   Pineapples are tropical fruit that are rich in vitamins, enzymes and
   antioxidents. They may help boost the immune system, build strong bones
   and aid indigestion. Also, despite their sweetness, pineapples are low
   in calories. According to <a href="https://www.livescience.com/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live Science</a></p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60645 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Beet-and-Pine
   apple-Smoothie.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Beet and Pineapple Smoothie. One a day may keep
   the doctor away. Make this healthy tasty recipe for breakfast or a
   snack. Has a more pineapple taste than beet."

   ineapple-Smoothie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Beet-and-Pineapple
   -Smoothie-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Beet-and-Pineapple
   -Smoothie-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div id="wprm-recipe-container-60646"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="60646"><div

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Beet and Pineapple Smoothie</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened almond
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small beet peeled and diced</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">about 8 ounces</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4cupfrozen
   pineapple</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plain Greek yogurt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Optional sweetener: 1-2 teaspoons
   honey</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60646-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the almond milk, beet, pineapple, and Greek yogurt in a high speed
   blender. Blend until smooth. Taste and if you desire a sweeter
   smoothie, add a little honey and blend again.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60646-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Enjoy
   immediately or refrigerate for up to 1 day.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups unsalted butter</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups powdered
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">The
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   and flour two 9 inch round cake pans. Line bottoms of pans with
   parchment paper and set pans aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   medium bowl, sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and
   salt; set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using
   an electric mixer, cream together butter, sugar, corn syrup and brown
   sugar until light and fluffy (about 3 to 4 minutes on medium
   speed).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   eggs one at a time, mixing after each addition until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   half of the flour mixture to the bowl; mix on low speed until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   vanilla extract and half of the milk to the bowl; mix on low speed
   until well combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   with the remaining flour and milk, mixing after each addition until
   well combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   the chopped walnuts into the batter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   the batter evenly between the 2 cake pans. Bake at 350F for 28-32
   minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake
   comes out clean.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cakes stand for 10 minutes before transferring to a cooling rack until
   completely cool.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-11"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Frosting:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-12" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   walnuts onto a sheet pan and bake at 350F for 6-8 minutes, or until
   fragrant; set walnuts aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-13" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, using an electric mixer, softened butter, powdered
   sugar and salt together on a low speed until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-14" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   corn syrup, milk and vanilla extract; mix until well combined. If
   frosting is too thin, add a couple more Tablespoon of powdered sugar.
   If frosting is too thick, add a Tablespoon of milk.)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-15" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Frost
   the cake by placing one layer of cake on large platter. Spread 1 cup of
   frosting on top. Repeat with 2nd layer of cake.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-16" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use
   remaining frosting on top and sides of cake.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60628-step-0-17" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   chopped walnuts into sides of the cake.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake" rel="">Cake
   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dump
   both cans of the fruits and their juices into a 9 x 12 Pyrex baking
   dish.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the dry cake mix on top of the fruit, spread out evenly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   oatmeal and coconut and sprinkle over cake mixture with fingers.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   butter and pour on top evenly. It should cover the entire cake
   mix.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for one hour and cool.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60590-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.</div>

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">mashed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 to 3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cake according to package directions, set aside to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   mixer, beat the cream cheese well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate mixer bowl, whisk together the Dream Whip (save some of the
   dream whip for top of cake). with the milk and vanilla, according to
   package directions. Whisk it until it begins to form soft peaks, about
   4 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   cream cheese and powdered sugar to the Dream Whip mixture, and whisk
   for 3 to 5 minutes, or until its smooth and creamy. Place in
   refrigerator for 15 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Crush
   your blackberries with a fork. Combine the blackberries, sugar and
   water in a small saucepan over medium heat until thick. Cook for 5 to 7
   minutes, stirring occasionally. Break down the blackberries with the
   back of your spoon. Drain any excess juice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take
   the cream cheese mixture out of the refrigerator and stir in the
   blackberry mixture. Pour over baked cake, smooth out evenly and return
   to refrigerator.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60586-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   ready to serve add dollop of dream whip over cake and a blackberry on
   top. (optional)</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh mushroom</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">halved</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">spray olive oil cooking
   spray</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">table salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">black pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">clove</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">medium garlic clove, minced or
   pressed</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh thyme</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">balsamic
   vinegar</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60581-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 450F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60581-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Arrange
   mushrooms in a single layer on a large jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet
   and coat with cooking spray; season to taste with salt and pepper.
   Roast mushrooms for 15 minutes and then turn mushrooms and roast for 5
   to 10 minutes more, until cooked through.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60581-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, place garlic and thyme in a large bowl. When mushrooms
   are done cooking, immediately place in bowl and toss to coat with
   garlic and thyme. Add vinegar and toss again.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60581-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   over your grilled steak.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60581-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Yields
   about 1 cup per serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizer Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html>

   look like donuts.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60576-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fry
   each in medium heated vegetable oil until golden brown on each side.
   Flipping with thongs.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60576-step-0-2"

   on paper towel until cooled.</div> </li></ul></div><div

   5px">Refrigerate 1 hour before using. Frost donuts.</div> </li><li

   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60574-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   chocolate using a double boiler or microwave. Place in a glass bowl and
   microwave on DEFROST for a couple minutes. Make sure to check it often
   and stir, DO NOT WHIP. Stir in peppermint extract.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60574-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   crackers, one by one, into the chocolate mixture using tongs or a
   chocolate dipping tool.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60574-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   each cookie on waxed paper.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60574-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   rest until chocolate has hardened.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups coarsely chopped
   pecans</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">8-ounce package cream cheese,
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">3-ounce package cream cheese,
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">16-ounce package powdered
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   two 9 inch cake pans with parchment paper circles in the bottom and
   grease the sides.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar together until light in
   color and fluffy, about 3-4 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   sour cream and vanilla extract and mix until well combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs one at a time, mixing until combined after each. Scrape down the
   sides of the bowl as needed to be sure all ingredients are well
   incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the dry ingredients in a separate bowl, then combine the milk and water
   in a measuring cup.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   half of the dry ingredients to the batter and mix until well combined.
   Add the milk mixture and mix until well combined. Add remaining dry
   ingredients and mix until well combined. Scrape down the sides of the
   bowl as needed to be sure all ingredients are well incorporated.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Gently
   stir 1 cup of the pecans into the batter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   the batter evenly between the cakes pans and bake for about 24-26
   minutes, or until a toothpick comes out with a few crumbs.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the cakes from the oven and allow to cool for about 2-3 minutes, then
   remove to cooling racks to cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt 2
   tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add pecans, and
   cook, stirring constantly, 10 minutes or until pecans are toasted.
   Remove from heat. Cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter at medium speed with an electric mixer
   until creamy. Gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy. Stir in
   buttered pecans and vanilla. Cover and chill at least 1 hour before
   frosting cake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60570-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html>

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Fresh Pineapple Drink</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh pineapple</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">crushed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white wine</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Ice
   cubes</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Peel
   the pineapple and chop it into small pieces.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   pineapple pieces in a blender along with water and sugar.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   to make a smooth juice.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Strain
   the juice using a soup strainer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   more water if the juice is too thick. Or add white wine if
   desired.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the juice in serving glasses.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60563-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   some ice cubes in the juice.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   powder</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Frosting:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li

   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
