   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">semi-sweet chocolate
   chips</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Brownies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spray
   the 9x13 inch non-stick baking dish with a non-stick cooking
   spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   butter in a microwave-safe bowl and melt the butter in a microwave. Mix
   the cocoa powder with the butter. Whisk the eggs, sugar and vanilla in
   another large bowl. Add the butter and cocoa mixture to the egg and mix
   so everything is combined. Add flour, salt and baking powder to the
   liquid mixture, and stir until combined (don't over mix).</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the brownie batter into the baking dish, put in the oven on the middle
   rack and bake for 25 minutes. Make sure it's on the middle rack, not
   the top one (brownies on the top rack are too close to the heating
   element and turn out more cake like).</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   brownie are warm frost them. Cool and cut it into squares.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Frosting:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60549-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   butter, milk and granulated sugar to a saucepan and place over medium
   heat. Bring to a boil and boil for one minute. Remove from heat, stir
   in salt and chocolate chips. Whisk vigorously until smooth then
   immediately pour onto warm brownies spreading before it starts to set.
   The frosting starts to harden quickly so work fast! Let brownies set
   for at least an one hour before cutting into them.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more of our <a

   Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-often-to-water-your-garden/ Sat, 20 Apr
   2019 12:55:03 +0000 My Honeys Place Gardening
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60541 How Often To Water Your Garden.
   Plants widely vary in... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-often-to-water-your-garden/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How Often To Water Your Garden.</strong> Plants
   widely vary in their watering needs. Tips on when to water different
   garden plants.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60543 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-often-to-
   water-your-garden.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How Often To Water Your Garden. Plants widely
   vary in their watering needs. Tips on when to water different garden
   plants.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-often-
   to-water-your-garden.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-often-to-water
   -your-garden-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/how-often-to-water
   -your-garden-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Best time to water your garden is early in
   the morning.</p> <p>General rule of thumb is about an inch or two of
   water each week with deep, infrequent watering as opposed to the more
   frequent shallow watering.</p> <p>If you live in a hot dry climate your
   plants may need more frequent watering.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Scheduling:</strong></p> <p><strong>Twice a
   week:</strong> lettuce, celery, spinach, beets, carrots, turnips,
   potatoes, broccoli, cauliflower, cabbage, strawberries, raspberries,
   blackberries, peas.</p> <p><strong>Once a week:</strong> beans, green
   beans, corn, peppers, eggplants, zucchini, yams, peanuts, rhubarb,
   onions, pumpkins.</p> <p><strong>Every 10 days to 2 weeks:</strong>
   tomatoes, watermelon, cantaloupes, butternut squash, banana squash,
   peaches, nectarines, pears, apples, plums, cherries, grapes,
   asparagus.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our
   <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/gardening/"
   rel="">Gardening Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted semi sweet chocolate
   chips</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sliced roasted
   almonds</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 350F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl melt the chocolate chips in your microwave, checking every
   30 seconds until melted. Mix the softened cream cheese, sugar and
   melted chocolate chips together. Mix well and set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Open
   the can of crescent roll dough and on a large greased pan, arrange the
   dough in a circle with the points facing out. Generously spoon the
   cream cheese, sugar, chocolate chip mixture into the center of the
   crescent roll dough. Starting at the wide end cover the mixture. Pinch
   to seal and cover then place in the baking dish.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350F for 15-20 minutes or until lightly brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with sliced almonds while still hot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60522-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   the crescent roll ring to cool to room temperature before
   serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/desserts/"
   rel="">Dessert Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60511 Best Way To
   Clean Dirty Pillows. How to wash away... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"

   nue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Best Way To Clean Dirty Pillows.</strong> How to
   wash away dust, mold, bacteria, dead skin and allergens.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60512 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Way-To-C
   lean-Dirty-Pillows.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Best Way To Clean Dirty Pillows. How to wash away
   dust, mold, bacteria, dead skin and allergens."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Way-T
   o-Clean-Dirty-Pillows.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Way-To-Clean-
   Dirty-Pillows-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Way-To-Clean-
   Dirty-Pillows-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>Pillows need to be washed ever 3 months.</p> <p>Wash
   with 2 pillows at a time to keep your machine balanced.<br> Place in
   washing machine with <strong>HOT</strong> water. Pour 1 cup baking soda
   or white vinegar with liquid laundry soap.</p> <p>Let soak for 1 to 2
   hours.<br> Wash on heavy duty setting.</p> <p>After washing place in
   dryer with 2 tennis balls covered with a sock. This will help fluff up
   the pillows.</p> <p>Or best bet is to dry outside in direct sunlight
   until thoroughly dry.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/" rel="">How To
   Tips</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mayonnaise</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream or
   milk</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60508-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Toss
   apples, pineapple, carrots, marshmallows and walnuts in a large bowl.
   Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60508-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl mix all the dressing ingredients.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60508-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   dressing over the apple mixture and toss to mix.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60508-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until ready to serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/salads/" rel="">Salad
   Recipe</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   mosquitoes and more. You can even print the instructions.</p> <p><img

   Get-Rid-Of-Insects-In-Your-Home-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150

   id-Of-Insects-In-Your-Home-450x450.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Ways-To-Get-R
   id-Of-Insects-In-Your-Home-500x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Best-Ways-To-Get-R

   id-Of-Insects-In-Your-Home-225x225.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 150px)
   100vw, 150px" /></div> </div> <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/60499" style=""

   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Best Ways To Get Rid Of Insects</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Ants: </strong>Mix 1/2 cup sugar.1 cup warm water. 2 TBS
   Borax. and soak a cosmetic pad in the mixture. Allow ants to collect
   the solution and bring food back to the queen.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Fruit Flies</strong>: In a small bowl mix apple cider or
   wine with dish soap. The soap breaks the surface tension while trapping
   the flies when they come to eat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Spiders:</strong> Gently mix 1/4 cup of liquid soap with 2
   gallons of water. Spray the front of the house and all of the bushes
   around it using a pump up garden sprayer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Mosquitoes:</strong> Spray yourself with a 16 oz bottle
   filled with 15 drops of lavender oil, 3-4 TBS of vanilla extract and
   1/4 cup of lemon juice. Also grow lemongrass or mint plants around your
   yard to them coming to indoors.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Cockroaches:</strong> Mix equal parts baking soda with
   equal parts sugar (1/4 cup of each is a good start). Now, all youll
   need to do is sprinkle them in the areas that youve seen roaches. Youll
   need to leave this bait out and repeat your sprinkling of the mixture
   often to ensure there is enough to kill the roaches Sugar isnt the
   deadly portion of the mixture, but it will work to attract the
   roaches.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Centipedes:</strong> You should leave them alone though,
   they kill other bugs. They even take care of bed bugs. They do bite,
   but are harmless. If ones in plain sight, just sweep it into a
   container and return it outside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Bed Bugs:</strong> First wash all of your linens in the
   hottest water possible, and vacuum your home thoroughly. Then apply100%
   Pure Diatomaceous Earthpowder around the infested area, and eventually,
   youll see dead bed bugs that can be vacuumed away. While it takes as
   long as 10 days for it to kill them, it has a very high mortality rate
   at greater than 90%, and its also easy to sprinkle in cracks and
   crevices that can otherwise be hard to get to.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Flies:</strong> Mix a natural fly repellent in a spray
   bottle. Flies will stay away from the scent of cayenne pepper. Mix a
   little in a spray bottle with water. Spray the cayenne mixture in
   doorways, window sills and other cracks and corners where flies might
   try to come in. The smell of the cayenne will keep them out.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60499-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Fleas:</strong> This home flea remedy involves creating a
   flea trap using dish soap and some water. All you have to do is fill a
   plate or bowl with a mixture of warm water and dish soap and place it
   in the rooms of your house which receive the most flea activity. The
   water and dish soap solutions act as a glue, trapping the fleas due to
   the high viscosity of the solution. You should repeat this method with
   a fresh batch every day.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/household-tips-
   tricks/" rel="">Household Tips and
   Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">buttermilk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Frosting</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">12</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">nearly at room
   temperature</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">nearly at room
   temperature</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2cups powdered
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees. Spray one 13-inch baking pans well with non-stick
   baking spray then lightly dust with flour and shake out excess. Set
   pans aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   mixing bowl whisk together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt,
   cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger, allspice and cloves for 20 seconds, set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   brown sugar into the bowl of an electric stand mixer. Break up brown
   sugar with fingertips until no clumps remain.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour in
   vegetable oil and applesauce, set mixer with paddle attachment and
   blend until well combined (occasionally stop and scrape bowl throughout
   mixing process).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix in
   eggs and vanilla.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add in
   1/2 of the flour mixture and mix on low speed until combined, then
   blend in buttermilk, then add remaining 1/2 of the flour mixture and
   mix until well combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   mixture evenly among two prepared baking pans. Bake in preheated oven
   until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, about 28 - 32
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   completely then level tops of cakes as needed. Frost with cream cheese
   frosting, sprinkle pecans around edges if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>For the frosting:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   bowl of an electric stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment cream
   butter and cream cheese until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix in
   powdered sugar and vanilla and mix until well blended</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60495-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Frost
   on cooled cake.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Churro
   Dough:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Vegetable oil
   forfrying</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Freezer bags for
   piping</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cooking thermometer</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">coarse sugar crystals for
   coating</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   saucepan, heat the vanilla, milk, butter, salt and sugar with half a
   cup of water. Bring the mix to a simmer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix in
   the flour and stir for 30 seconds or until dough forms. Remove from
   heat and place the dough in a large mixing bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs one at a time, making sure each egg is completely mixed into the
   dough before adding another. Continue to mix until the dough has a
   smooth and glossy appearance.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill a
   large pot with vegetable oil and heat to 350 degrees. Use a cooking
   thermometer to maintain this temperature.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   your dough in a freezer bag and cut a corner off the bag.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Squeeze
   the dough through the cut corner of the bag into the oil. Swirling as
   you pipe into the oil to make a circle. Repeat until you have four
   churros in the pot.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fry for
   two to three minutes, then flip each churro and fry for another two to
   three minutes, or until golden brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   done frying, carefully remove the churros and place them on paper
   towels to remove excess oil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60485-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Coat
   the churros with the coarse sugar crystals while still warm.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Flaky
   Crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">14</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1 and 3/4 sticks, at room
   temperature, cut into tablespoons</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unbleached all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1 teaspoon superfine
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fine sea
   salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">jar of your favorite
   jam</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Flaky
   Crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   the butter in the bowl of a heavy-duty stand mixer fitted with the
   paddle attachment at high speed until the butter is smooth, about two
   minutes. With the mixer running, slowly dribble in the milk,
   occasionally stopping the mixer and scraping down the sides of the bowl
   with a silicone spatula. The butter mixture should be fluffy, smooth,
   and shiny, like a butter cream frosting.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   flour, sugar, and salt together in a small bowl. With the mixer speed
   on low, gradually add the flour mixture and incorporate just until the
   dough forms a mass on the paddle and the sides of the bowl are clean.
   Turn out the dough onto a lightly floured surface. Knead a few times
   until it is smooth and supple. Divide the dough in half. Shape each
   portion into a disk, about one-inch thick. Wrap each disk in plastic
   wrap.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until chilled but not hard, 30 minutes to an
   hour.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Putting it
   together:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 450 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface; flatten ball sightly and roll 1/8 inch thick.
   If edges split, pinch together. Always roll dough from center to edge.
   Using light strokes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   dough into circles with a large round cap.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   on cookie sheet and add about 2 Tablespoons of your favorite jam.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   dough over filling. Pinch edges.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60481-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   and serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html>

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-author-container wprm-recipe-block-container

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">walnuts</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60471-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F. Spray muffin tins or place jumbo liners into the
   muffin tins.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60471-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl mix together flour and baking powder. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60471-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl mix together eggs, sugar, buttermilk, oil, bananas, and
   vanilla. Fold wet ingredients into dry ingredients. Mix until just
   combined. Stir in walnuts. Careful not to over mix.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60471-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scoop
   batter into prepared tins <strong>making sure to fill to the
   top</strong>. I used an ice cream scoop.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60471-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   400 degrees F for 30 to 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into
   center comes out clean.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">crushed walnuts for topping</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">&nbsp;</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">&nbsp;</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F. You may want to lightly grease your muffin tin
   so that the crown of the muffin doesn't stick to the pan. Place eight
   muffin liners in the pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the sugar, egg, oil, milk, and vanilla in a bowl and stir until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   flour, baking powder and salt. Once the baking powder and salt are
   pretty well distributed in the flour, stir them into the wet
   ingredients until combined. Don't over mix. Just stir until it's no
   longer lumpy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   the sour cream just until well distributed. Fold in the
   blueberries.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill
   the 8 muffin tin cups all the way to the top. I used an ice cream
   scoop. Sprinkle crushed walnuts on top if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   muffins for about 25 to 35 minutes. Just be sure you get them out as
   soon as a toothpick comes out clean.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60468-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 8 large domed muffins</span></div></div>
   </div></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div

   sugar</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60463-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Cake:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60463-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   saucepan, mix Coca Cola, oil, butter and cocoa and bring to a boil. In
   another bowl, combine the sugar, flour and salt. Pour the boiling Cola
   mixture over the flour mixture and beat well. Add the eggs, buttermilk,
   soda and vanilla and beat well. Pour mixture into a greased and floured
   13 x 9 inch baking pan and bake at 350 degrees or 20 to 25 minutes.
   Remove pan. Cool for about 10 minutes before frosting.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60463-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Frosting:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60463-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   saucepan, combine the butter, cocoa, and milk. Heat until the butter
   melts. Beat in the remaining ingredients and spread on the cake while
   it's still warm.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   crust</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package of cream cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can sweetened condensed
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the ingredients well together and pour into prepared graham cracker
   crust</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60455-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Chill
   for at least 30 minute.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and  cups graham cracker

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cheesecake filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">peach marmalade</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 8-</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packages of cream cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the swirl
   topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">peach marmalade</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   the oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl combine the graham cracker crumbs, sugar, and melted
   butter. Stir the mixture until all the crumbs are evenly coated in the
   butter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   spray a 9-inch springform pan with non-stick cooking spray. Press the
   crumbs evenly into the bottom of the pan, pressing the crumbs up -inch
   up the side of the pan. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until the crust
   is lightly golden brown. Cool to room temperature.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   brown sugar, cinnamon, cream cheese, sugar, cornstarch, eggs and
   marmalade together.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   sour cream, heavy cream and vanilla to the cream cheese mixture and
   process for 10 seconds to combine. Carefully pour the cream cheese
   mixture into the prepared crust, gently tapping the pan on the counter
   to release any large air bubbles.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the cheesecake for 20 minutes at 350 F, then reduce the heat to 325 F
   and bake for an additional 40 to 50 minutes, or until the center of the
   cheesecake is slightly jiggly, but the edges are firm. Turn off the
   oven, crack the oven door slightly and cool for 1 hour, then remove the
   cheesecake from the oven and cool to room temperature. Carefully remove
   the outer ring and wrap with plastic wrap and chill for at least 4
   hours.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the swirl
   topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   peach marmalade with the brown sugar and vanilla extract. Swirl over
   cooled cheesecake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60453-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Raspberry Sauce:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups frozen
   raspberries</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thawed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">corn starch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Graham Cracker
   Crust:</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups graham cracker
   crumbs</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Filling:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white chocolate
   chips</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">24</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">3 packages</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups powdered
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen thawed
   raspberries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Raspberry Sauce:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small pot, add the raspberries and sugar. Bring to a simmer over medium
   heat and cook for 2-3 minutes. Mash with a spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   water and corn starch and stir into sauce to thicken. Set aside to cool
   completely (you can speed this up by pouring into a new bowl and
   placing in the fridge).</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Crust:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Press
   into the bottom and 1" up the sides of a 9-10" pan. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Filling:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, stir together white chocolate and 1/2 cup cream. Microwave
   on high for 40 seconds, then stir until completely smooth (heat another
   15 seconds if necessary). Place in the fridge to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until smooth. Add
   sugar, vanilla, and remaining 1/2 cup cream and beat on high until
   light and fluffy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   melted white chocolate and beat on medium speed until
   incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   fresh or thawed raspberries into the bottom of the crust and pour the
   cheesecake filling over top, smoothing with a spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drop
   teaspoonfuls of raspberry sauce on the top, and gently swirl. Save
   remaining sauce for serving.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60451-step-1-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Chill
   at least 5 hours or overnight before serving. Serve with remaining
   raspberry sauce and fresh raspberries as desired.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p>&nbsp;</p> <div
   id="attachment_60448" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption

   id="caption-attachment-60448" class="wp-caption-text">No Bake Chocolate
   Ganache cheesecake . Dessert recipe with an Oreo crust, a chocolate
   filling and a swirl of white chocolate. <strong>Recipe
   below</strong>.&nbsp;</p></div> <div id="wprm-recipe-container-60449"

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">No Bake Chocolate Ganache cheesecake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Oreo
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/3 cup Oreo baking
   crumbs</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate
   Cheesecake Filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">10</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">very soft</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">semi-sweet chocolate</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted and cooled</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">White Chocolate
   Ganache:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Heavy Cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">White Chocolate
   Chips</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line an
   8 inch round pan with aluminium foil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl stir together the Oreo crumbs and melted butter.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   into the bottom of the prepared pan and place in the freezer while you
   make the filling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate
   Cheesecake Filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl beat the whipping cream and 1/4 cup of the powdered sugar
   until stiff peaks form.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl beat together the cream cheese and remaining powdered
   sugar (3/4 cup) until soft. Then beat in the sour cream, melted
   chocolate and vanilla extract.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   whipping cream into the cream cheese mixture until evenly
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   the filling over top of the Oreo cookie crust and place the cheesecake
   in the fridge for at least 4 hours to harden.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">White Chocolate Ganache:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   white chocolate chips to a heat resistant bowl and set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small pot, heat cream over low heat, stirring occasionally. Heat until
   just before boiling, bubbles will start to appear in the cream at the
   edge of the pot.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the cream from the heat and pour over the chocolate chips. Let stand
   for 2-3 minutes and then stir until completely smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60449-step-2-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let the
   white chocolate ganache cool to room temperature and swirl over top of
   cheesecake.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <div
   id="attachment_60446" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-60446"
   class="wp-image-60446 size-full"

   id="caption-attachment-60446" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Chocolate
   Marble Cheesecake.</strong> Dessert Recipe made with a chocolate graham
   cracker crust, a cream cheese filling and chocolate swirl topping.
   <strong>Recipe below</strong>.</p></div> <div

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate Marble Cheesecake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Crust:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">9</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole chocolate graham
   crackers</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Stick Butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Filling:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oz.cream cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Chocolate Swirl:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60447-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oven to 350F. Line a 9-in. round baking pan with foil, letting foil
   extend above pan on opposite sides; coat with nonstick spray.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Crust: </h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60447-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Process
   crackers in food processor until fine crumbs form. Add butter and egg
   white; pulse until crumbs are moistened. Using bottom of a small
   measuring cup, press evenly over bottom of pan. Bake 10 minutes or
   until firm and set. Cool.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:
   </h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60447-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   cream cheese, sour cream, 1/2 cup sugar, and the eggs in a large bowl
   until smooth. Remove 1/4 cup. Pour remaining batter over crust.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate Swirl:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60447-step-3-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   cocoa, 2 Tbsp water and 3 Tbsp sugar in a cup to mix. Stir into
   reserved 1/4 cup batter until blended. Spoon over filling, then drag a
   toothpick or skewer through filling in a spiral motion to create
   marbled effect.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60447-step-3-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 30
   minutes or until firm around edges but slightly jiggly in center. Cool
   in pan on rack in refrigerator at least 3 hours until firm.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <div id="attachment_60444"
   style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-60444" class="wp-image-60444
   size-full"

   recipe topped with a taste of blueberries, a cream cheese filling and a
   graham cracker crust. "

   Cheesecake.jpg 600w,
