   ke-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Blueberry-Cheeseca
   ke-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-60444" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Blueberry
   Swirl Cheesecake</strong>. A light version recipe topped with a taste
   of blueberries, a cream cheese filling and a graham cracker crust.
   <strong>Recipe below.</strong></p></div> <div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-60445" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="60445"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Blueberry Cheesecake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Blueberry Syrup:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups fresh
   blueberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">watercold</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Crust:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">graham cracker
   crumbs</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Filling:</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package small cream cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">largeeggslightly
   beaten</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Blueberry Syrup:</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   blueberries, sugar and lemon juice in a small saucepan. Over medium
   heat, cook the mixture for about 5 minutes, stirring often until the
   blueberries are soft.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, dissolve cornstarch in water and stir until mixture turns
   into a smooth paste. Add this to the saucepan and let the mixture boil
   and let simmer for about a minute or so, until the mixture is thick.
   Remove from heat and allow to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer to a blender or a small food processor and blend until
   smooth. Transfer to a container or jar. Cover and refrigerate until
   needed.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Crust:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 F.Whisk together graham cracker crumbs and sugar in a
   mixing bowl. Add the melted butter and stir mixture until combined.
   Press the mixture into an 8 inch-spring-from pan. Bake for ten minutes
   and set aside to cool while you make the filling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Filling:</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 F. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until
   smooth. Add the sour cream, vanilla extract, and the flour. Beat just
   until combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs and beat on low speed just until incorporated. Pour mixture over
   the crust in the spring-formpan. Spoon about three tablespoons of the
   blueberry syrup on top of the batter. Use a knife to cut through the
   batter to create the swirled effect.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60445-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   a preheated oven for 45-50 minutes or until the center of cheesecake is
   almost set. Cool cake slightly on a wire rack. Then run a knife thru
   the sides of the cake to loosen it. Once the cake is at room
   temperature, refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. Drizzle more
   blueberry syrup upon serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of salted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups all purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chocolate chips</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">Use a combination of chocolate
   chips and chocolate chunks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raisins</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar for dusting
   (optional</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 350 degrees. Microwave the butter for about 40 seconds
   until just barely melted.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   stand mixer or electric beaters, beat the butter with the sugars until
   creamy. Add the vanilla and the egg; beat on low speed until just
   incorporated for about 10-15 seconds.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   flour, baking soda, and salt. Mix until crumbles form. Use your hands
   to press the crumbles together into a dough. It should form one large
   ball that is easy to handle. Add the chocolate chips and raisins then
   blend with your hands.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   the dough into 9 or 12 large balls and place on a cookie sheet. Bake
   for 9-11 minutes until the cookies look puffy and just barely golden.
   DO NOT OVERCOOK</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   them cool on the pan for a good 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60441-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dust
   with powdered sugar if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Parmesan cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic
   salt</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60432-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 425 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60432-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slice
   baked french bread in half, long ways.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60432-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   5 cheeses and garlic salt in a bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60432-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   bread on a cookie sheet and sprinkle mixed ingredients evenly over
   bread.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60432-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   oven for 7 to 9 minutes, or until cheese melts.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">largeeggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Sliced strawberries</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cool
   whip</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60413-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add all
   ingredients to a blender and pulse for 5 seconds. Use a rubber spatula
   to scrape down the sides of the blender, then pulse for another 5-10
   seconds or until the mixture is smooth and combined. Cover and
   refrigerate for at least 1 hour.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60413-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   youre ready to cook the crepes, melt 1/4 tablespoon butter in an 8- to
   10-inch round saute pan over medium heat. Pour 1/4 cup of the chilled
   crepe batter into the center of the saute pan, then immediately tilt
   and swirl the pan so that the batter forms a large circle. Let the
   batter cook for about 1 minute, or until the edges of the batter begin
   to slightly brown. Then carefully slip a thin spatula (or rubber
   spatula) underneath the crepe, and flip it to the other side. Cook for
   another 45-60seconds, then transfer the crepe to a separate plate and
   set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60413-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   with the remaining batter, adding extra butter to the pan occasionally
   when needed so that the crepes do not stick.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60413-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   crepes immediately, filled with sliced strawberries and cool
   whip.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">15.25 ounce box vanilla cake
   mix</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">4 serving sized box instant vanilla
   pudding</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">16 ounce container sour
   cream</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vegetable oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">diced raspberries -
   optional</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60408-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F. Liberally grease a 10- inch bundt pan with butter or
   shortening and lightly dust with flour. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60408-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   bowl of your stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment combine all
   the cake ingredients. Mix on low for 30 seconds until combined and then
   on medium speed until smooth, about 1 minute. Stir in the raspberries,
   if desired, and pour the batter into the prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60408-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 50-55 minutes, until the cake is set. Allow the cake to cool in the
   pan for 10 minutes and then invert the pan onto a cake plate.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ALMOND CUPCAKES</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/3 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely ground
   almonds</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted
   buttersoftened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole buttermilk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Garnish: sliced
   almonds</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">VANILLA BUTTERCREAM
   FROSTING</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted
   buttersoftened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups confectioners'
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla beansplit lengthwise and
   seeds scraped and reserved</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Almond Cupcakes:</strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine flour, almonds, baking powder, baking soda, and
   salt, whisking to combine.Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and sugar at medium-high speed with a mixer
   until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla, beating until mixture is
   smooth. Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture in thirds,
   alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture
   and beating on low speed until well combined. Divide batter evenly
   among prepared muffin cups.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until a wooden pick inserted in the center of cupcakes comes out clean,
   15 to 20 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cool for 10 minutes. Remove from pan, and let cool completely on a wire
   rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   Vanilla Buttercream Frosting over cooled cupcakes. Garnish with
   almonds, if desired. Store in refrigerator.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">VANILLA
   BUTTERCREAM FROSTING</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60395-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter with a mixer at high speed until creamy. Add
   confectioners' sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each
   addition. Add cream as needed until mixture is smooth. Add reserved
   vanilla bean seeds, beating to combine.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   sec and ice cream.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60391-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   and serve in the outer layer of the oranges or in a glass.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60391-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with a slice of orange, a decorative umbrella or a straw.</div>

   soft, buttery, with raisins and full of flavor breadsticks.</p> <p><img

   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-author-container wprm-recipe-block-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container-columns wprm-block-text-normal"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details-label wprm-block-text-bold
   wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">warm water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">active dry yeast</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">softened butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups white
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raisins</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Garlic salt to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60387-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   all ingredients (except for topping ingredients) in the bowl of a stand
   mixer and mix using the dough hook until combined on low. Continue
   mixing about 5 minutes, adding just a little more flour if needed.
   Dough will be soft and slightly sticky; it won't completely pull away
   from side of bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60387-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   dough out onto a floured surface and knead two or three times, forming
   a ball. Cover with a kitchen towel and let rise 1 to 1.5 hours, until
   nearly double in size.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60387-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On
   floured surface, roll dough into a 12x16 inch rectangle. Use pizza
   cutter to slice into 16 pieces. Pinch the long sides of each piece
   together to form a breadstick shape.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60387-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   sticks pinched side down on a greased cookie sheet, cover with towel,
   and let rise about 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60387-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 degrees for 15-18 minutes until golden brown. Brush with melted
   butter.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Yields 16 Breadsticks</span></div></div>

   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">18.25-ounce Package white cake
   mix</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">3-ounce Package strawberry
   gelatin</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped fresh
   strawberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Vegetable oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Garnish with whole and halved
   strawberries</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Strawberry
   Buttercream Frosting Ingredients: </h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">32-ounce Package powdered sugar,
   sifted</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped fresh
   strawberries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F. Beat cake mix, strawberry gelatin, eggs, sugar,
   chopped fresh strawberries, milk, vegetable oil and all-purpose flour
   at low speed with an electric mixer for 1 minute. Scrape down sides,
   and beat at medium speed for 2 more minutes, stopping to scrape down
   sides, as needed. (The Strawberries should be well blended.)</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 degrees for 23 minutes, or until cakes spring back when pressed
   lightly with a finger. Let cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
   Remove from pans, and cool completely (about 1 hour.)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   the Strawberry Buttercream Frosting between layers and on top and sides
   of cake. Garnish with whole and halved strawberries. Serve immediately,
   or chill for up to 1 week. To make ahead: Prepare recipe as directed.
   Chill, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until frosting is set. Cover well
   with wax paper, and store in refrigerator up to a week.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Strawberry Buttercream Frosting Preparation:
   </h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy (about 20
   seconds).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60377-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sugar and strawberries, beating at low speed until creamy. (Add more
   sugar if frosting is too thin, or add strawberries if too thick.)</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   with additional whipped topping and a few slices of fresh strawberries
   if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dry red wine</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">teriyaki sauce</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">saltto
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60367-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   skillet, soften the garlic in oil and butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60367-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   mushrooms and increase the heat slightly. Fry the mushrooms while
   stirring them until they begin to let go of their moisture. About 5
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60367-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   remaining ingredients.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60367-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Simmer
   6-10 minutes or until the liquid has reduced by about one third.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">12-oz. pkg.NESTLɮ TOLL HOUSE
   Semi-Sweet Chocolate Morsels,divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">14 oz.NESTLɮ CARNATION Sweetened
   Condensed Milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">toasted</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60361-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><b>PREHEAT</b>oven to 350 F. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60361-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><b>BEAT</b>butter in large mixer bowl on medium speed for 30
   seconds. Beat in flour, sugar and salt on low speed until crumbly.
   Press<i>2 cups</i>of mixture onto bottom of prepared pan. Bake for 12
   to 14 minutes or until lightly browned on edges.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60361-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><b>COMBINE</b><i>1 1/2 cups</i>of morsels and sweetened condensed
   milk in small saucepan over medium-low heat. Heat until morsels are
   melted, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla extract.
   Pour evenly over hot crust. Add<i>remaining</i>morsels and chopped
   pecans to the reserved crust mixture; sprinkle over the chocolate
   layer.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60361-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><b>BAKE</b>for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is set. Cool in
   pan on wire rack. Cut into diamond-shaped pieces.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p>Recipe courtesy and reprinted

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and cook on high for 4 hours or until beef is tender.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60346-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the beef is done, place the beef on a plate and shred it with 2 forks.
   Return the beef to the crock pot sauce and mix well. Lower crock pot
   heat to low and simmer for another 2 hours.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60346-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Split
   Hawaiian Rolls in half and spoon beef between rolls.</div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/12-amazing-benefits-for-cream-of-tartar/ Tue,
   05 Mar 2019 13:43:46 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Household Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60337 12 Amazing Benefits For Cream Of
   Tartar. DIY tips for... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/12-amazing-benefits-for-cream-of-tartar
   /">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>12 Amazing Benefits For Cream Of
   Tartar.</strong> DIY tips for uses from itch relief to cleaning
   silverware and more.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60338
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-Amazing-Be
   nefits-For-Cream-Of-Tartar.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="12 Amazing Benefits For Cream Of Tartar. DIY tips
   for uses from itch relief to cleaning silverware and more."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-Amazing
   -Benefits-For-Cream-Of-Tartar.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-Amazing-Benefit
   s-For-Cream-Of-Tartar-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/12-Amazing-Benefit
   s-For-Cream-Of-Tartar-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Meringue</span> &ndash; Use 1/8 teaspoon per egg white to
   keep the meringue stable and add volume.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Creamier Frostings</span> &ndash; Add a small amount to sugar
   as it is cooking.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Homemade baking
   powder</span> &ndash; Combine 2 parts cream of tartar, 1 part baking
   soda and 1 part cornstarch.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Metal
   Cleaner</span> &ndash; Make a paste using cream of tartar and vinegar.
   Buff paste on the metal surface and wipe with a clean rag.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">Homemade Cleaning Scrub</span> &ndash; Mix 2
   and 1/2 cups baking soda, 1 and 1/2 cups salt and 2 tablespoons of
   cream of tartar. Store and use when needed.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Silver Cleaner</span> &ndash; In a sauce pan place a ball of
   aluminum foil,&nbsp; 1 quart of water and 2 tablespoons of cream of
   tartar. Bring the water to a boil and add silver items to be
   cleaned.&nbsp; Boil for 10 minutes then remove from heat and let cool.
   Then rinse.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Porcelain
   Cleaner</span> &ndash; Make a paste of cream of tartar and hydrogen
   peroxide. Apply the paste to the stain and let it dry. When the paste
   is dry remove the paste and rinse.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Ant repellent</span> &ndash; Make a paste of cream of tartar
   and vinegar. Place the paste where ants are getting into your home. You
   can also sprinkle around the nests. Safe to be used around kids and
   pets.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Heartburn relief</span>
   &ndash; Mix&nbsp; 1/2 teaspoon of cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon of
   baking soda in an 8 ounce glass of warm water and drink slowly. You
   should feel relief in a few minutes.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Itch relief</span> &ndash; Make a paste of cream of tartar
   and water.&nbsp; Apply to the area and allow it to dry. Remove and
   rinse.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Urinary Tract
   infections</span> &ndash; Mix 2 teaspoons of cream of tartar with a 1/2
   cup warm water. Drink twice a day.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">High Blood Pressure</span> &ndash; Mix a cup of water with
   1/2 teaspoon of cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice. Drink
   three times a day with meals.</p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   </div> <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/60333" style=""

   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60333-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oil in large pot on medium heat. Add pork, onion, and garlic. Saut 3-4
   minutes searing pork on all sides.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60333-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   broth, enchilada sauce, green chilies, and spices. Bring to a boil on
   high heat. Cover and reduce heat to low. Simmer 40 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60333-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   hominy. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60333-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   lime juice and cilantro.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/15-home-remedies-for-your-furry-friends/ Wed,
   27 Feb 2019 13:06:30 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And
   Tips Health How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60323 15 Home
   Remedies For Your Furry Friends. These tips are... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/15-home-remedies-for-your-furry-friends
   /">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>15 Home Remedies For Your Furry
   Friends</strong>. These tips are safe and effective for dogs and
   cats.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60324 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/15-Home-Remed
   ies-For-Your-Furry-Friends.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="15 Home Remedies For Your Furry Friends. These
   tips are safe and effective for dogs and cats.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/15-Home-Re
   medies-For-Your-Furry-Friends.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/15-Home-Remedies-F
   or-Your-Furry-Friends-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/15-Home-Remedies-F
   or-Your-Furry-Friends-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Skin
   infections:</span> Use vitamin E oil and massage it into inflamed
   skin.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Cat hair balls:</span> Give
   them a spoon full of butter or vegetable oil.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">Homemade shampoo:</span> Animals should not use
   human shampoo. Mix dish soap with water and white distilled
   vinegar.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Diarrhea:</span> Mix
   plain yogurt with their food.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Stinky gas:</span> Sprinkle some fennel seed in their food
   once a day.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Bee sting:</span> Use
   a credit card to pull out the stinger then wash with baking soda. If
   they have an allergic reaction to the sting, then give 1 mg per 1 pound
   ratio of Benadryl.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Skunk
   spray:</span> Bathe your pet in hydrogen peroxide mixed with baking
   soda and dish soap.Then soak in tomato juice for several minutes.</p>
   <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Irritated&nbsp; eyes:</span> Use
   regular saline eye drops several times a day,</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">Ear mites:</span> Clean the ears with a cotton
   ball dipped in regular vegetable oil and wipe gently.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">Sores:</span> Clip the fur around the area,
   clean with hydrogen peroxide then put a small amount of cortisone cream
   to the sore. Do this two times a day.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Fleas:</span> Wash in dish soap and water then gently run a
   comb gently through their fur.</p> <p><span style="color:
   #ff0000;">Sore or cracked paws:</span> Use lotion and antibiotic
   ointment.</p> <p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Itchy skin</span>:
   Combine baby oatmeal with water then rub into fur.</p> <p>Use <span
   style="color: #ff0000;">metal bowls</span> to feed your pets. Metal
   bowls tend to collect less bacteria than plastic bowls.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">Constipation:</span> Use purred pumpkin or
   prunes every few days. Just be sure to remove the pits.</p> <p><span
   style="color: #ff0000;">If any symptoms last more than 3 days contact
   your veterinarian.</span></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Pretzels:
   </h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cooking spray</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">16.3-oz. can refrigerated biscuit
   dough</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">beaten</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Coarse
   salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cheese
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cheddar cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Kosher salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Freshly ground black pepper</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60305-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 425. Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper and spray
   with cooking spray.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Make the
   pretzels:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60305-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Quarter
   each biscuit, then roll each piece into a slices (about 1 inch in
   length). Using a knife, carve an X into each slice.In a medium
   saucepan, combine water and baking soda. Bring to boil then reduce to a
   simmer. Add slices and cook for 30 seconds. (The dough will float to
   top.)Remove with a slotted spoon and transfer to baking sheet, making
   sure the pretzelsaren't touching.Brush beaten egg over each pretzel,
   then sprinkle with coarse salt.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60305-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 10 to15 minutes or until golden brown.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Then make
   cheese sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60305-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   butter in a small saucepan over medium heat. Whisk in flour and cook
   for 1 minute. Stir in milk and bring to a simmer. When milk begins to
   thicken, stir in cheese, whisking constantly until sauce is smooth.
   Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with the pretzels.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg whites</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups all purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room
   temperature</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups
   shortening</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">10</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5 to 6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maraschino cherry
   juice</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Pink icing color</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped
   cherries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   three 8 inch cake pans with parchment paper circles in the bottom and
   grease the sides. Preheat oven to 350F (176C) .</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light in color
   and fluffy, about 3-4 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sour cream and almond extract and mix until well combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add egg
   whites in two batches, mixing until well combined after each. Scrape
   down the sides of the bowl as needed to be sure all ingredients are
   well incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   dry ingredients in a separate bowl, then combine the milk and water in
   a small measuring cup.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   half of the dry ingredients to the batter and mix until well combined.
   Add the milk mixture and mix until well combined. Add remaining dry
   ingredients and mix until well combined. Scrape down the sides of the
   bowl as needed to be sure all ingredients are well incorporated.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   the batter evenly between the cakes pans and bake for about 21-23
   minutes, or until a toothpick comes out with a few crumbs.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the cakes from the oven and allow to cool for about 2-3 minutes, then
   remove to cooling racks to cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large mixer bowl, beat the butter and shortening together until
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add half of the powdered sugar and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add 4-5
   tablespoons of cherry juice and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add the remaining powdered sugar and mix until smooth. Add additional
   cherry juice, as needed.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Color
   the frosting with some additional pink icing color.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60297-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Frost
   the cake with a spatula.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   Easter Egg Chicks</strong>. What an adorable idea for your deviled
   eggs. Not only aren&rsquo;t they delicious but everyone one will get
   Everyone will enjoy the cuteness of them. <strong>Instructions<a
   href="https://makelifespecial.com/deviled-easter-egg-chicks/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener"> HERE </a></strong></p></div> <div

   cinnamon twist and baked. Make them for breakfast or a dessert.
