   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bittersweet chocolate</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plus 1 and 1/4 cups butter
   softened</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">miniature semisweet chocolate
   chips</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 3/4 cups confectioners'
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2 to 3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">2% milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">miniature semisweet chocolate
   chips</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In top
   of a double boiler or a metal bowl over barely simmering water, melt
   chocolate and 3 Tbsp. butter; stir until smooth. Cool to room
   temperature.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375. Line the bottoms of three greased 8-in. round baking pans
   with parchment paper; grease the paper.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, cream remaining butter and the sugar until light and
   fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
   Beat in vanilla. Whisk the flour, baking powder and salt; add to
   creamed mixture alternately with the sour cream, beating well after
   each addition.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   2 cups of the batter to a small bowl; stir in cooled chocolate mixture
   and, if desired, the chocolate chips, until blended. Drop both the
   plain and chocolate batters by tablespoonfuls into prepared pans,
   dividing batters evenly among pans. To make the batter level in pans,
   bang cake pans several times on counter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 20-25 minutes.
   Cool in pans 10 minutes before removing to wire racks; remove paper.
   Cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl,beat the butter until smooth. Gradually beat in
   confectioners' sugar, vanilla and enough milk to reach desired
   consistency.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If cake
   layers have rounded tops, trim with a serrated knife to make level. In
   a microwave, melt the chocolate chips; stir until smooth. Cool
   slightly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   one cake layer on a serving plate; spread with 1/2 cup frosting. Repeat
   layers. Top with remaining cake layer. Frost top and sides of
   cake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60279-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drop
   chocolate by 1/2 teaspoonfuls over frosting. Using an offset spatula,
   smear chocolate to create marbling in the frosting.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   fillets</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chili powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground
   cumin</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60273-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven 400 F. Line baking pan with foil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60273-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   resealable plastic bag, mix together brown sugar, chili powder, cumin,
   cinnamon, and season to taste. Add salmon, coating all over and pat in
   seasoning.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60273-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer to prepared pan. Bake 12-15 minutes or until fish flakes
   easily.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Check out more</span> <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/healthy-recipes/"
   rel="">Healthy Recipes</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded Parmesan
   cheese</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Salad:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60264-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add all
   ingredients and toss until blended.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Dressing:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60264-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   mayo, mustard, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper with blender until
   well blended.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60264-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   pour in the olive oil and blend until thick and creamy.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60264-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold in
   the Parmesan cheese.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60264-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   over salad.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 4 servings.</span></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/things-that-will-go-away-in-the-near-future/
   Sat, 09 Feb 2019 12:20:55 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60257 Things That Will Go Away In The Near
   Future. Something... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/things-that-will-go-away-in-the-near-fu
   ture/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Things That Will Go Away In The Near
   Future</strong>. Something to think about. Here today gone
   tomorrow.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60260 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Things-That-W
   ill-Go-Away-In-The-Near-Future2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Things That Will Go Away In The Near Future.
   Something to think about. Here today gone tomorrow."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Things-Tha
   t-Will-Go-Away-In-The-Near-Future2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Things-That-Will-G
   o-Away-In-The-Near-Future2-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/Things-That-Will-G
   o-Away-In-The-Near-Future2-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Auto repair shops</strong>
   will go away.&nbsp; A gasoline engine has 20,000 individual
   parts.&nbsp; An electrical motor has 20.&nbsp; Electric cars are sold
   with lifetime guarantees and are only repaired by dealers.&nbsp; It
   takes only 10 minutes to remove and replace an electric motor.&nbsp;
   Faulty electric motors are not repaired in the dealership but are sent
   to a regional repair shop that repairs them with robots.&nbsp; Your
   electric motor malfunction light goes on, so you drive up to what looks
   like a Jiffy-auto wash, and your car is towed through while you have a
   cup of coffee and out comes your car with a new electric motor!</p>
   <p><strong>Gas stations</strong> will go away.&nbsp; Parking meters
   will be replaced by meters that dispense electricity.&nbsp; Companies
   will install electrical recharging stations; in fact, they&rsquo;ve
   already started.&nbsp; You can find them at select Dunkin Donuts
   locations.</p> <p>Most (the smart) major auto manufacturers have
   already designated money to start building new plants that only build
   electric cars.</p> <p><strong>Coal industries</strong> will go
   away.&nbsp; Gasoline/oil companies will go away.&nbsp; Drilling for oil
   will stop.&nbsp; So say goodbye to OPEC!</p> <p>Homes will produce and
   store more electrical energy during the day and then they use and will
   sell it back to the grid. The grid stores it and dispenses it to
   industries that are high electricity users.&nbsp; Has anybody seen the
   Tesla roof?</p> <p>A baby of today will only see personal cars in
   museums.</p> <p><strong>The FUTURE</strong> is approaching faster than
   most of us can handle.</p> <p>In 1998, <strong>Kodak</strong> had
   170,000 employees and sold 85% of all photo paper worldwide.&nbsp;
   Within just a few years, their business model disappeared and they went
   bankrupt.&nbsp; Who would have thought of that ever happening?</p>
   <p>What happened to Kodak will happen in a lot of industries in the
   next 5-10 years and, most people don&rsquo;t see it coming.</p> <p>Did
   you think in 1998 that 3 years later, you would never take pictures on
   film again?&nbsp; With today&rsquo;s smart phones, who even has a
   camera these days?</p> <p>Yet <strong>digital cameras</strong> were
   invented in 1975.&nbsp; The first ones only had 10,000 pixels, but
   followed Moore&rsquo;s law.&nbsp; So as with all exponential
   technologies, it was a disappointment for a time, before it became way
   superior and became mainstream in only a few short years.&nbsp; It will
   now happen again (but much faster) with Artificial Intelligence,
   health, autonomous and electric cars, education, 3D printing,
   agriculture and jobs.</p> <p>Forget the book, &ldquo;Future
   Shock&rdquo;, welcome to the 4th Industrial Revolution.</p>
   <p><strong>Software</strong> has disrupted and will continue to disrupt
   most traditional industries in the next 5-10 years.</p>
   <p><strong>UBER</strong> is just a software tool, they don&rsquo;t own
   any cars, and are now the biggest taxi company in the world!&nbsp; Ask
   any taxi driver if they saw that coming.</p> <p><strong>Airbnb</strong>
   is now the biggest hotel company in the world, although they
   don&rsquo;t own any properties.&nbsp; Ask Hilton Hotels if they saw
   that coming.</p> <p><strong>Artificial Intelligence</strong>: Computers
   become exponentially better in understanding the world.&nbsp; This
   year, a computer beat the best Go-player in the world, 10 years earlier
   than expected.</p> <p>In the USA, young lawyers already don&rsquo;t get
   jobs.&nbsp; Because of IBM&rsquo;s Watson, you can get legal advice (so
   far for right now, the basic stuff) within seconds, with 90% accuracy
   compared with 70% accuracy when done by humans.&nbsp; So, if you study
   law, stop immediately.&nbsp; There will be 90% fewer lawyers in the
   future, (what a thought!) only omniscient specialists will remain.</p>
   <p>Watson already helps nurses diagnosing cancer, its 4 times more
   accurate than human nurses.</p> <p><strong>Facebook</strong> now has a
   pattern recognition software that can recognize faces better than
   humans.&nbsp; In 2030, computers will become more intelligent than
   humans.</p> <p><strong>Autonomous cars</strong>: In 2018 the first
   self-driving cars are already here.&nbsp; In the next 2 years, the
   entire industry will start to be disrupted.&nbsp; You won&rsquo;t want
   to own a car anymore as you will call a car with your phone, it will
   show up at your location and drive you to your destination.&nbsp; You
   will not need to park it you will only pay for the driven distance and
   you can be productive while driving.&nbsp; The very young children of
   today will never get a driver&rsquo;s license and will never own a
   car.</p> <p>This will change our cities, because we will need 90-95%
   fewer cars.&nbsp; We can transform former parking spaces into
   parks.</p> <p>1.2 million people die each year in car accidents
   worldwide including distracted or drunk driving.&nbsp; We now have one
   accident every 60,000 miles; with autonomous driving that will drop to
   1 accident in 6 million miles.&nbsp; That will save a million lives
   plus worldwide each year.</p> <p>Most traditional car companies will
   doubtless become bankrupt.&nbsp; Traditional car companies will try the
   evolutionary approach and just build a better car, while tech companies
   (Tesla, Apple, Google) will do the revolutionary approach<br> and build
   a computer on wheels.</p> <p>Look at what <strong>Volvo</strong> is
   doing right now; no more internal combustions engines in their vehicles
   starting this year with the 2019 models, using all electric or hybrid
   only, with the intent of phasing out hybrid models.</p> <p>Many
   engineers from Volkswagen and Audi; are completely terrified of
   <strong>Tesla</strong> and so they should be.&nbsp; Look at all the
   companies offering all electric vehicles.&nbsp; That was unheard of,
   only a few years ago.</p> <p><strong>Insurance companies</strong> will
   have massive trouble because, without accidents, the costs will become
   cheaper.&nbsp; Their car insurance business model will disappear.</p>
   <p><strong>Real estate</strong> will change.&nbsp; Because if you can
   work while you commute, people will move farther away to live in a more
   beautiful or affordable neighborhood.</p> <p><strong>Electric
   cars</strong> will become mainstream about 2030. Cities will be less
   noisy because all new cars will run on electricity.</p> <p>Cities will
   have much cleaner air as well. (Can we start in Los Angeles,
   please?)</p> <p><strong>Electricity</strong> will become incredibly
   cheap and clean.&nbsp; Solar production has been on an exponential
   curve for 30 years, but you can now see the burgeoning impact.&nbsp;
   And it&rsquo;s just getting ramped up.</p> <p><strong>Fossil energy
   companies</strong> are desperately trying to limit access to the grid
   to prevent competition from home solar installations, but that simply
   cannot continue &ndash; technology will take care of that strategy.</p>
   <p><strong>Health:</strong> The Tricorder X price will be announced
   this year.&nbsp; There are companies who will build a medical device
   (called the &ldquo;Tricorder&rdquo; from Star Trek) that works with
   your phone, which takes your retina scan, your blood sample and you
   breathe into it.&nbsp; It then analyses 54 bio-markers that will
   identify nearly any Disease&nbsp; There are dozens of phone apps out
   there right now for health purposes.</p> <p><strong>WELCOME TO
   TOMORROW</strong> &ndash; it actually arrived a few years
   ago.</p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/diy-hanging-flower-planter/ Fri, 08 Feb 2019
   15:35:06 +0000 My Honeys Place Gardening
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60253 DIY Hanging Flower Planter. Spruce
   up your yard this spring... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/diy-hanging-flower-planter/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>DIY Hanging Flower Planter</strong>. Spruce up
   your yard this spring with a beautiful garden flower basket.&nbsp;A
   fresh plant can bring life to almost any space in your home. Whether
   you&rsquo;re introducing new foliage to the patio or living room, the
   right arrangement can make a big difference. Create a unique twist on
   standard hanging baskets by hanging them at different levels and in a
   creative pattern.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60254
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/DIY-Hanging-F
   lower-Planter.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="DIY Hanging Flower Planter. Spruce up your yard
   this spring with a beautiful garden flower basket.&nbsp;A fresh plant
   can bring life to almost any space in your home. Whether you&rsquo;re
   introducing new foliage to the patio or living room, the right
   arrangement can make a big difference. Create a unique twist on
   standard hanging baskets by hanging them at different levels and in a
   creative pattern."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/DIY-Hangin
   g-Flower-Planter.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/DIY-Hanging-Flower
   -Planter-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/DIY-Hanging-Flower
   -Planter-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>You will need:</strong></p> <p>A flower basket you can buy
   one at <a
   href="https://www.walmart.com/ip/Plastic-Hanging-Flower-Pot-Chain-Plant
   -Planter-Basket-for-Plants/572037520" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener">Walmart</a> and I have seen them at Dollar stores and <a
   href="https://www.homedepot.com/b/Outdoors-Garden-Center-Planters-Hangi
   ng-Baskets/N-5yc1vZbx7b" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Home
   Depot</a></p> <p>Potting soil</p> <p>A Garden trowel</p>
   <p><strong>Instructions:</strong><br> Fill the basket with potting
   soil.&nbsp;Before planting the basket, fill the container halfway with
   any premium potting soil.<br> Plant the flowers of your choice: Create
   three layers: low, medium and high.&nbsp;For the low layer, use&nbsp;<a
   href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lysimachia" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener"><i>Lysimachia</i></a>&nbsp;foliage to cascade over the
   basket edge.</p> <p>The next layer adds height, use&nbsp;<a
   href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barleria_cristata" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener"><i>Barleria</i>&nbsp;</a>for the center. Leave just
   enough space around it for the medium layer, which features plants that
   grow taller than the low-growing plants, but lower than the tallest
   plants.</p> <p>Add colors and&nbsp;<a
   href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heuchera" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener"><i>Heuchera</i></a>&nbsp;on either side of
   the&nbsp;Barleria, and sprinkle soil into any empty areas left in the
   basket.</p> <p><strong>For an easier way, just plant hardy flowers like
   <em>Petunias</em>. Plant them in light, well-drained soil in
   full&nbsp;sun&nbsp;after the last spring frost.</strong></p> <p>Give
   the basket a watering thoroughly, while still allowing the basket to
   dry out a little between watering.</p> <p>Before hanging, make sure the
   basket chain is hanging from a sturdy hook that&rsquo;s rated for the
   weight of the pot and is anchored in solid wood.&nbsp;To help keep the
   basket nutrient-rich, add an organic fertilizer every four months or
   so.</p> <p>Hanging baskets must always be located a site that receives
   the necessary sunlight conditions for the types of plants in the
   basket. Read on the label&rsquo;s of the plants you buy.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/gardening/" rel="">Gardening
   Ideas</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mini white chocolate
   chips</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">crushed Oreo cookies</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   strips of puff pastry and wrap them around a conical mold in an
   overlapping manner. Use water to stick the pieces into place.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   them on a cookie tray and bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   the horns are cooling, prepare the filling. In a mixing bowl, whip the
   cream cheese until fluffy.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   powdered sugar and vanilla extract and mix again.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   the whipped cream into the mixture until smooth and creamy.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   the white chocolate chips.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill a
   piping bag with this mixture and fill each horn with it.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60250-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the crushed Oreo cookies on top. (optional)</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">grated mozzarella
   cheese</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   potatoes and cover tops with olive oil. Salt and pepper to taste.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   350 degree F. for 45 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Slightly cool potatoes and slice 1/4 off the top of the potatoes
   with a sharp knife.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">With a
   spoon, scoop out center of each potato, scraping out as much as you
   can, leaving the skins intact. If you wish more topping on top, then
   leave more of the potatoes in the skins.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in large bowl and mash with the spoon.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs, diced ham, onion and parsley to the mashed potatoes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   well and pour into hollowed potatoes skins.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the filled potatoes in a large baking dish. Top with mozzarella
   cheese.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60243-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   back into oven for 10 to 15 minutes more.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy
   cream</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl combine Bisquick, milk and egg in a bowl using a fork. Mix
   until combined to create a dough ball.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl combine brown sugar, granulated sugar and cinnamon. Add 2
   T. melted butter to moisten. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Generously flour a rolling surface.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   dough out onto surface and start patting with hands into a rectangle
   shape. Use a rolling pin to thin dough to about 1/2 inch
   thickness.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   rolled out pour 3/4 cup melted butter over entire surface and spread
   evenly over dough.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle sugar over butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Start
   rolling dough from long end. Slice into 1 to 1/2 inch slices.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer to well greased 9 x 13 inch well greased baking
   pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   preheated 373 degree oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden
   brown.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the rolls are done allow them to cool for 10 minutes before
   glazing.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Glaze:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60236-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together all the ingredients and pour over warm rolls.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Pre-heat the Air fryer for about 5 minutes</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Coat
   the steak lightly with olive oil on both sides.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Season

   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div

   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Setthe

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After 3
   minutes, flip the steak on to it's other side.Basting lightly with the
   sauce mixture when you turn the meat over.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Setthe
   timer for another 3 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After 3
   minutes take the steak out of the Airfryer and place it onto a
   plate.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let it
   rest for another 3 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with more of the warmed sauce mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   immediately.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Sauce:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60223-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix all
   ingredients and baste on the steak when flipping steak. Pour remaining
   sauce on top of steak after warming it in the microwave for 1
   minute.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:

   class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg
   xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"

   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Oven Baked Prime Rib Roast</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh rosemary</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh thyme</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">finely chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">black pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">With a
   sharp knife, cut 6 small slits all over the prime rib. Insert the
   garlic cloves into the slits.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, mix the olive oil, fresh rosemary, fresh thyme, garlic
   powder, 2 teaspoons salt, and 1 teaspoon of ground black pepper.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the roast lightly with salt and ground black pepper
   before rubbing the herb/oil mixture. This is optional, however since we
   are cooking a large piece of meat a little extra seasoning is always
   good.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Rub the
   herb/oil mixture all over the roast. At this point, if you are
   seasoning your roast hours ahead or overnight, refrigerate the roast
   uncovered until ready to bake.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   refrigerated, take the rib roast from the refrigerator at least 30
   minutes before cooking. This will bring the meat to room temperature so
   it cooks more evenly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 450 degrees Fahrenheit.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the rib roast bone-side down in a roasting pan and place it in the
   pre-heated oven. Bake for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lower
   the oven temperature to 325 and cook until the internal temperature of
   the meat is 120 degrees to 160 degrees Fahrenheit, depending if you
   like it rare or well done. Make sure the thermometer is exactly in the
   center of the roast</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the rib roast from the oven and transfer it to a cutting board. Cover
   it tightly with aluminum foil and allow the meat to rest for 15
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60220-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the bones and slice.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60215-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Ina
   large bowl, beat the cake mix, butter and egg until crumbly. Press onto
   bottom of a greased 13x9-in. baking dish.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60215-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the sweet potatoes, cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and pie spice in a
   food processor; cover and process until blended. Spread over
   crust.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60215-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 until center is almost set, 20-25 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small
   bowl, combine sour cream, vanilla and remaining sugar. Spread over
   filling. Combine topping ingredients; sprinkle over top. Bake just
   until set, 5-8 minutes longer. Cool on a wire rack.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60215-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Cut into bars.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container

   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Makes 2 dozen
   bars.</span></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   class="continue-reading-link"

   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Grandma&rsquo;s Frosted Oatmeal
   Cookies</strong>. A special homemade dessert recipe that has been
   handed down from generations. A family favorite.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60210 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Grandmas-Fros
   ted-Oatmeal-Cookies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Grandma's Frosted Oatmeal Cookies. A special
   homemade dessert recipe that has been handed down from generations. A
   family favorite.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Grandmas-F
   rosted-Oatmeal-Cookies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Grandmas-Frosted-O
   atmeal-Cookies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Grandmas-Frosted-O
   atmeal-Cookies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <div id="wprm-recipe-container-60211"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="60211"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Grandma's Frosted Oatmeal Cookies</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cookies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">quick-cooking oats</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground allspice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raisins</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3 to 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">2% milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">White sprinkles</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cookies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60211-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cream
   butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs. In
   another bowl, whisk next seven ingredients; gradually beat into creamed
   mixture. Stir in raisins and, if desired, pecans. Divide dough in half.
   Shape each into a disk; cover. Refrigerate until firm enough to roll,
   about 1 hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60211-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. On a lightly floured surface, roll each portion of dough
   to 1/4-in. thickness. Cut dough with a floured 21/4-in. round cookie
   cutter. Place 2 in. apart on greased baking sheets. Bake until light
   brown, 7-9 minutes. Cool 2 minutes before removing to wire racks to
   cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60211-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   confectioners' sugar, butter and enough milk to reach spreading
   consistency. Spread over cookies. If desired, top with white
   sprinkles.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes about 4 dozen cookies</span></div></div>

   <html><body><p><strong>Recipe For A Richer Homemade
   Mayonnaise.</strong>&nbsp; Regular mayo is fine on a sandwich, but if
   you&rsquo;re making tartar sauce or you&rsquo;re in the market for
   something with a richer, more complex flavor. That&rsquo;s where
   homemade mayonnaise comes in. And you don&rsquo;t have to beat a whisk
   until your arm aches: Whipping up homemade mayo takes just a few
   minutes with a hand mixer. Or use a blender, if you&rsquo;d like.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60207 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Recipe-For-A-
   Richer-Homemade-Mayonnaise.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Recipe For A Richer Homemade Mayonnaise.&nbsp;
   Regular mayo is fine on a sandwich, but if you're making tartar sauce
   or you're in the market for something with a richer, more complex
   flavor. That's where homemade mayonnaise comes in. And you don't have
   to beat a whisk until your arm aches: Whipping up homemade mayo takes
   just a few minutes with a hand mixer. Or use a blender, if you'd like."

   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Recipe For A Richer Mayonnaise</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg yolk</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cider vinegar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dijon mustard</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Kosher salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">neutral-flavor vegetable oil</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">like canola or soybean oil or pure
   olive oil (not extra-virgin)</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Fresh lemon juice to taste</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium-small mixing bowl, combine the egg yolk with 1/2 tsp. of the
   vinegar, all of the mustard, and 1/4 tsp. kosher salt.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   with an electric hand mixer on medium-low speed until well combined.
   With the mixer running on medium-high or high speed, begin to very
   slowly drizzle in the oil. Start with just a few drops, then increase
   the speed at which you add the oil as the mixture becomes creamy
   looking and the emulsion takes hold.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   you've added about half the oil, add the remaining tsp. vinegar, then
   continue to add the remaining oil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   all of the oil is added, season with more salt to taste and a few drops
   of lemon juice, if using.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If the
   mayonnaise seems too thick, mix in a teaspoon or two of cold water to
   thin.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and refrigerate if not using right away.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60206-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   mayo will thicken as it chills, so you may want to thin it a little
   more than you would if using immediately.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Yields about 1 cup</span></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60200 10 Ways To Remove Stains. Stains can
   be remove with... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-ways-to-remove-stains/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>10 Ways To Remove Stains.</strong> Stains can be
   remove with these different products. How to remove red wine, makeup,
   blood, coffee, ink, lipstick, oil, sweat, grease and poop.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60201 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/10-Ways-To-Re
   move-Stains.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="10 Ways To Remove Stains. Stains can be remove
   with these different products. How to remove red wine, makeup, blood,
   coffee, ink, lipstick, oil, sweat, grease and poop."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/10-Ways-To
   -Remove-Stains.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/10-Ways-To-Remove-
   Stains-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/10-Ways-To-Remove-
   Stains-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>Red wine:</strong> Remove with white wine.</p>
   <p><strong>Makeup:</strong> Remove with shaving cream.</p>
   <p><strong>Blood:</strong> Remove with hydrogen peroxide</p>
   <p><strong>Coffee:</strong> Remove with baking soda</p>
   <p><strong>Ink:</strong> Remove with milk</p>
   <p><strong>Lipstick:</strong> Remove with baby wipes</p>
   <p><strong>Oil:</strong> Remove with chalk</p>
   <p><strong>Sweat:</strong> Remove with sliced lemon</p>
   <p><strong>Grease:</strong> Remove with soda</p>
   <p><strong>Poop:</strong> Remove with dish soap</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>For even more tips please visit our
   sister site <a href="https://tipsjust4u.com/" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener">Tips Just 4U</a></strong></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:
   (optional)</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped green
   onion</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oil in saucepan, and brown onions and garlic until well caramelized,
   then remove from heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fry the
   bacon.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375 degrees. Remove pie crust from freezer and allow to thaw
   until pliable.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   bowl, combine sage, mustard, paprika, salt, pepper, beer, breadcrumbs,
   and cooled onion mix. Use a wooden spoon to combine gently, but
   thoroughly. Mix in the fried bacon.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   flour a board and place a pie crust down. Taking half the sausage links
   and add the mixture, form a log about one inch in from the edge, across
   the entire width. Roll it over so the pastry encases the meat
   completely, and use a little of the eggs wash to seal the pastry
   together, allowing a 1/2 inch seam. There will be excess pastry, so
   just trim it away. Then, using a sharp knife, cut each log into 5-6
   pieces. Repeat with second pastry sheet and remaining pork.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   pieces onto a baking tray lined with parchment paper, brush the tops
   with remaining egg wash and place into the oven to bake 35-45 minutes
   until golden brown.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Creamy
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   heavy saucepan over a low heat, melt the butter with the garlic. Do not
   let it brown.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   cream cheese and stir slowly until it melts and blends with the butter
   and garlic.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   stir in the milk and salt, and continue heating on low for another 3
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the sauce over the cooked Sausage Rolls</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60195-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   diced cherry tomatoes and green onions on top (if desired)</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>See more <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/appetizers-favorite-re
   cipes/" rel="">Appetizer Recipe</a></strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Or <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/breakfast/"
   rel="">Breakfast Recipe</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">COLD butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dash of salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can Pillsbury Crescent
   Rolls</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Glaze:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">I like my glaze thicker, so if the
   glaze is too runny, just add more powdered sugar to get yours to the
   desired consistency.</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">softened butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 to 1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut in
   butter to sugars, cinnamon, and salt and flour to form crumbs.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On an
   ungreased cookie sheet, separate crescent roll dough into 8 triangles.
   Sprinkle crumbs on top. Roll into round shape with smaller end in
   center.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If you
   desire a crispier roll then do not roll them up. Delicious either
   way.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   400 degrees for 8-12 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Glaze:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   all ingredients together and drizzle over rolls</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60191-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After
   they were cooked and cooled you can cut them into smaller triangles but
   you can leave them big too!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   coconut</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60184-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   together sugar, oil and eggs. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Add
   carrots, pineapple, and coconut, and walnuts. Stir until combined. Pour
   into lightly greased 9x13 inch pan. . Bake at 350 for 40-45 min or till
   done.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Icing:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60184-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   together and beat with beaters until light and fluffy. Spread on well
   cooled carrot cake</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p
