   https://myhoneysplace.com/reasons-your-cake-fails/ Tue, 22 Jan 2019
   13:58:24 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Cooking Tips &
   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60179 Reasons Your
   Cake Fails. Tips for why your cake did... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/reasons-your-cake-fails/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Reasons Your Cake Fails.</strong> Tips for why
   your cake did not turn out right. How to make a perfect baked cake.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60180 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Reasons-Your-
   Cake-Fails.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Reasons Your Cake Fails. Tips for why your cake
   did not turn out right. How to make a perfect baked cake.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Reasons-Yo
   ur-Cake-Fails.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Reasons-Your-Cake-
   Fails-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Reasons-Your-Cake-
   Fails-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>Has a hump:</strong></p> <p>Your oven was overly hot when
   baking started.</p> <p>Too much flour was use.</p> <p><strong>Dark
   bottom:</strong></p> <p>Pan is too deep or large, which keeps the top
   from browning.</p> <p>Dark pans absorb more heat. Place on higher oven
   rack. Same with Pryrex.</p> <p>Pan was warped which causes uneven
   browning.</p> <p><strong>Has deep cracks:</strong></p> <p>Temperature
   was too high.</p> <p>Too much flour or baking powder.</p>
   <p><strong>Has fallen:</strong></p> <p>Temperature was too low.</p>
   <p>Cake peeked while baking.</p> <p>Removed from oven too early.</p>
   <p>Too much shortening, sugar, baking soda or baking powder.</p> <p>Not
   enough flour.</p> <p>The oven door has been opened before the cake has
   set.</p> <p>The cake didn&rsquo;t go in the oven as soon as the mixture
   was ready.</p> <p><strong>Course texture:</strong></p> <p>Temperature
   not high enough.</p> <p>Batter over mixed.</p> <p>Too much baking
   powder or flour.</p> <p><strong>Your cake is running over:</strong></p>
   <p>Temperature not high enough.</p> <p>Pan not large enough.</p> <p>Too
   much baking powder or sugar.</p> <p><strong>It&rsquo;s too
   tough:</strong></p> <p>Temperature too hot.</p> <p>Not enough
   shortening or sugar.</p> <p>Too much flour.</p> <p><strong>Doughy
   cake:</strong></p> <p>Temperature too low.</p> <p>Left in pan too long
   after removing from oven.</p> <p><strong>Too light in
   color:</strong></p> <p>Temperature too low.</p> <p>Another pan is too
   close while baking.</p> <p><strong>Browned edges:</strong></p> <p>Oven
   too full.</p> <p>Pans touching another one in your oven or side of
   oven.</p> <p><strong>Not large enough:</strong></p> <p>Temperature too
   high.</p> <p>Not enough baking powder.</p> <p>Over mixed batter.</p>
   <p>Over size pan.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more<a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/how-to-andtips/cooking-tips-tr
   icks/" rel=""> Cooking Tips and Tricks</a></strong></p></body></html>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   syrup</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60172-step-0-0"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   saucepan over medium heat, bring the water, butter and salt to a boil.
   Add the flour all at once and stir until a smooth ball forms.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60172-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Continue beating until the mixture is smooth and shiny. Remove
   from the heat; let stand for 5 minutes. Add the eggs, one at a time,
   beating well after each addition.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60172-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   into a greased 15x10x1-in. baking pan. Bake at 400 until crust is
   puffed and golden brown, 28-30 minutes. Cool crust completely on a wire
   rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60172-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>For the filling</strong>, in a large bowl, beat the cream
   cheese, milk and pudding mixes until smooth. Spread over the crust;
   refrigerate for 20 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60172-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   whipped topping over filling. Store in the refrigerator. Just before
   serving, drizzle with chocolate syrup.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=pudding+" rel="">Recipes Using
   Pudding</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   https://myhoneysplace.com/natural-remedies-to-relieve-hemorrhoid-pain/
   Sat, 19 Jan 2019 15:42:17 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY
   And Tips Health How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60158
   Natural Remedies To Relieve Hemorrhoid Pain. Ouch! Hemorrhoids (also
   called... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/natural-remedies-to-relieve-hemorrhoid-
   pain/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Natural Remedies To Relieve Hemorrhoid
   Pain.</strong> Ouch! Hemorrhoids (also called piles) can be very
   painful. Here are some tips to soothe the pain and help shrink
   them.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60159 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Natural-Remed
   ies-To-Relieve-Hemorrhoid-Pain.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Natural Remedies To Relieve Hemorrhoid Pain.
   Ouch! Hemorrhoids (also called piles) can be very painful. Here are
   some tips to soothe the pain and help shrink them."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Natural-Re
   medies-To-Relieve-Hemorrhoid-Pain.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Natural-Remedies-T
   o-Relieve-Hemorrhoid-Pain-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Natural-Remedies-T
   o-Relieve-Hemorrhoid-Pain-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p><strong>Cold compress:</strong><br> A cold
   compress will help the hemorrhoids to shrink and become small in size.
   It will reduce pain and provide instant relief from itching. It will be
   easier to pass stools once swelling is reduced. Wrap some ice in a
   clean cloth and apply it directly over the hemorrhoids. Doing this
   several times, a day will help to constrict the blood vessels and
   reduce hemorrhoids effectively. Also sitting on a cushion rather than a
   hard surface helps reduce the swelling of existing hemorrhoids and
   prevents the formation of new ones.</p>
   <p><strong>Hydration:</strong><br> Dryness may aggravate hemorrhoids
   and may cause excessive bleeding. Never use a dry tissue to wipe the
   affected area as it may cause unwanted scratches that can worsen the
   swollen vessels. Instead use a non-perfumed, non-medicated wet tissue
   to wipe off without drying out your skin. You may also place vitamin E
   capsules in the opening of the anus to soothe the area and re-hydrate
   it.</p> <p><strong>Take warm baths:</strong></p> <p>Soak in a bathtub
   filled with a few inches of warm water for about 15 minutes at a time.
   Do it two or three times a day and after every bowel movement. If you
   want to wash the area, too, use unscented soap and don&rsquo;t
   scrub.</p> <p><strong>Witch Hazel:</strong></p> <p>Witch hazel is
   reputed to reduce pain, itching and bleeding until hemorrhoids fade
   out. There isn&rsquo;t much scientific support for its use but it does
   contain tannins and oils that may help bring down inflammation and slow
   bleeding. Supporters say it tightens the skin as a natural
   anti-inflammatory.&nbsp;Witch hazel wipes (Tucks) are soothing and have
   no harmful effects.</p> <p><strong>Pure Aloe Vera:</strong></p> <p>The
   anti-inflammatory properties of aloe vera may help soothe inflammation
   of hemorrhoids.</p> <p><strong>Petroleum Jelly:</strong></p> <p>Put a
   little petroleum jelly just inside your rectum to make your bowel
   movements hurt less. Don&rsquo;t force it! Dab witch hazel
   on&nbsp;irritated&nbsp;hemorrhoids, or use over-the-counter creams or
   ointments made for hemorrhoid symptoms. A 1% hydrocortisone cream on
   the skin outside the rectum (not inside) can relieve&nbsp;itching,
   too.</p> <p><strong>Get more fiber:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Add more
   fiber to your diet from food, a fiber supplement (such as Metamucil,
   Citrucel, or Fiber Con), or both. Along with adequate fluid, fiber
   softens stools and makes them easier to pass, reducing pressure on
   hemorrhoids. High-fiber foods include broccoli, beans, wheat and oat
   bran, whole-grain foods, and fresh fruit.</p> <p><strong>OTC
   Meds:</strong></p> <p>Taking over-the-counter pain relievers such
   as&nbsp;acetaminophen&nbsp;<i class="eld i-exit-nih" aria-label="NIH
   external link"></i>,&nbsp;ibuprofen&nbsp;<i class="eld i-exit-nih"
   aria-label="NIH external link"></i>,&nbsp;naproxen&nbsp;<i class="eld
   i-exit-nih" aria-label="NIH external link"></i>, or aspirin will lessen
   the pain and reduce the swelling.</p> <p><em>Some hemorrhoids
   can&rsquo;t be managed with conservative treatments alone, either
   because symptoms persist or because an internal hemorrhoid has
   prolapsed. Contact your doctor if your hemorrhoids are severe or
   symptoms not relieved within a week.</em></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Check our more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=remedies+"
   rel="">Remedies</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">They

   id="wprm-recipe-60154-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with salt and cool for 2 mins or so to make them crisper.
   Serve immediately.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh shrimp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cleaned, peeled and
   deveined</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package of dried Italian
   Seasoning</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   shallow baking dish with aluminum foil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   melted butter in the pan and spread around.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slice
   lemon and layer it on top of the butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lay the
   shrimp in the baking pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle on the Italian Dressing evenly over the shrimp.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60150-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   oven at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-prevent-an-anxiety-attack/ Fri, 18 Jan
   2019 13:07:27 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How To
   and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60143 How To Prevent An Anxiety
   Attack. This is called Grounding... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-prevent-an-anxiety-attack/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>How To Prevent An Anxiety Attack</strong>. This
   is called Grounding and will help prevent a panic attack.&nbsp; It can
   help when feel like you have gone too far in your head and have lost
   all control of your surroundings.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-60145 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/How-To-Preven
   t-An-Anxiety-Attack.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="How To Prevent An Anxiety Attack. This is called
   Grounding and will help prevent a panic attack.&nbsp; It can help when
   feel like you have gone too far in your head and have lost all control
   of your surroundings.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/How-To-Pre
   vent-An-Anxiety-Attack.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/How-To-Prevent-An-
   Anxiety-Attack-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/How-To-Prevent-An-
   Anxiety-Attack-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>By recognizing that you&rsquo;re having an anxiety
   attack, instead of a heart attack, you can remind yourself that this is
   temporary, it will pass, and that you&rsquo;re OK.</p>
   <p><strong>Follow these steps:</strong></p> <p>Close your eyes and
   breath deeply in through your nose and out through your mouth.</p>
   <p>Then open your eyes and slowly look around you and find&hellip;</p>
   <ul><li>5 things that you can see</li> <li>4 things you can touch</li>
   <li>3 things you can hear</li> <li>2 things you can smell, or 2 smells
   you like</li> <li>1 emotion you feel</li> <li>Picture your self in a
   HAPPY place: On a mountain top, at the beach, etc.</li> <li>Keep
   some&nbsp;lavender essential oil&nbsp;on hand and put some on your
   forearms when you experience a panic attack. Breathe in the scent.</li>
   </ul><p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p></body></html> <div class='code-block

   half the dry mixture to the wet mixture and stir until just combined.

   for approximately 45-50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the
   center comes out almost clean . Remove from oven and allow to cool on a
   wire cooling rack .</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">with juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 to 3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">crushed
   pecans</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cake:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60135-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cake according to package directions. Cool. Then poke holes in the top
   with a fork.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Poke
   mixture:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60135-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Boil
   crushed pineapples and sugar. Then pour over cooled cake.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60135-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar. Mix well. Add
   vanilla and crushed pecans, mix well. Frost cooled cake.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">If you want a
   stacked cake then double the recipe.</span></div></div> </div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cookies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Strawberry jam or jam of your
   choice</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Icing:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">1/2 stick unsalted butter, room
   temp</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small lemon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1 tbsp juice+ zest</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">a few drops of yellow food
   coloring</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cookies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Sift
   the flour, baking powder and salt into a bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl using electric beaters or in a standing mixer, cream the
   butter and sugar for 3 minutes on medium to high speed until light and
   fluffy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   egg and vanilla to the butter mixture and beat until
   incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   the speed to low and slowly add the flour mixture until the dough comes
   together.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the dough onto a piece of plastic wrap, parchment paper or wax paper
   and flatten into a round shaped disk.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wrap
   the dough disk and chill in the refrigerator until firm, at least
   thirty minutes to overnight.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   chilled, preheat oven to 325 degrees.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   dough sit for about 10 minutes or until soft enough to roll out.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   lightly floured rolling pin, roll the dough out onto a lightly floured
   surface until 1/4 thick and even.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use a
   cookie cutter that has a heart shape and cut out cookies. On
   <strong>1/2 of the cookies</strong> use a spoon or a 1/2 teaspoon to
   place an indent in the center of the cookie.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use a
   spatula, transfer the cut-outs onto a cookie sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 6 to 8 minutes. Place jam on the indented cookies and return to
   oven for about 2 minutes longer or just until the jam melts and cookies
   have a golden brown edge.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-0-12" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   cookies on a rack.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Icing:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   the butter, powdered sugar, 1 tbsp lemon juice, zest from 1 small
   lemon, and vanilla until light and fluffy. Mix in a few drops of yellow
   food coloring until you get the desired light yellow color.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   the cookies are cool, cover with frosting leaving the indented centers
   unfrosted. Lightly frost the cookies not indented.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the cookies with one indented on top of the ones not indented.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60130-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   frosting will harden up within a half and hour, and then you can place
   them in an air tight container to store for a few weeks in the
   fridge.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/slow-cooker-italian-chicken/ Mon, 14 Jan 2019
   00:02:11 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60124 Italian Chicken Right In Your Slow
   Cooker. An easy recipe... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/slow-cooker-italian-chicken/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>Italian Chicken Right In Your Slow Cooker.
   </strong>An easy recipe that you can cook in your Crock Pot. Only 4
   ingredients required to serve for dinner.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60125 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Slow-Cooker-I
   talian-Chicken.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Italian Chicken Right In Your Slow Cooker. An
   easy recipe that you can cook in your Crock Pot. Only 4 ingredients
   required to serve for dinner.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Slow-Cooke
   r-Italian-Chicken.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Slow-Cooker-Italia
   n-Chicken-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Slow-Cooker-Italia
   n-Chicken-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 60126--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Slow Cooker Italian Chicken</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Slow-Cooker-I
   talian-Chicken-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>4 Chicken breast (cut
   into chunks)</li> <li>1 package Zesty Italian Dressing</li> <li>1 8 oz.
   package of cream cheese, softened</li> <li>2 cans of cream of chicken
   soup</li> <li>1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese (optional)</li>
   <li>Cooked pasta (optional)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Place first 4
   ingredients in your slow cooker.</li> <li>Cook on low for 4 hours. If
   sauce is too thick, add a little milk.</li> <li>Serve over cooked pasta
   and top with shredded mozzarella cheese if desired.</li> </ol></div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more our
   delicious <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Dish Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p></body></html> <div

   div> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60119-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>Brownies: </strong></div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60119-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325. Line a 9x9 baking pan with parchment paper, set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60119-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   butter, both cocoa powders and sugar in a large microwave-safe bowl and
   microwave for about 1 minute and 30 seconds, or until butter is melted.
   Mix everything together until smooth. Stir in eggs and vanilla until
   combined. Pour in the flour and mix until everything is completely
   combined. The batter will be very thick and glossy.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60119-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the batter into your prepared baking pan and smooth it out until level.
   Bake for 22-25 minutes or until a toothpick comes out slightly moist
   with a little bit of batter left on it - the top will not look so "wet"
   anymore when they are done. This is what makes them fudgy. Let them
   cool completely in the pan.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60119-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, melt the chocolate chips and shortening at 30 second
   increments in the microwave until completely smooth and pourable. Pour
   the chocolate on top the baked brownies and spread it out with a rubber
   spatula into a smooth and even layer. Place tray back into the
   refrigerator for 20 minutes to allow the top to set up properly. Take
   the pan out, allow the brownies to come back to room temperature for at
   least 10 minutes for smoother cutting lines.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Can be stored
   in an airtight container for up to 5 days.</span></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/what-it-is-like-to-have-an-autoimmune-disease
   / Fri, 11 Jan 2019 17:10:25 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Health How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60112 What It Is
   Like To Have An Autoimmune Disease. It... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/what-it-is-like-to-have-an-autoimmune-d
   isease/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>What It Is Like To Have An Autoimmune
   Disease.</strong> It can affect many parts of your body.
   A&nbsp;condition in which your immune system mistakenly attacks your
   body.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60113 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/What-It-Is-Li
   ke-To-Have-An-Autoimmune-Disease.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="What It Is Like To Have An Autoimmune Disease. It
   can affect many parts of your body. A&nbsp;condition in which your
   immune system mistakenly attacks your body."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/What-It-Is
   -Like-To-Have-An-Autoimmune-Disease.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/What-It-Is-Like-To
   -Have-An-Autoimmune-Disease-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/What-It-Is-Like-To
   -Have-An-Autoimmune-Disease-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>I just wish more people understood&hellip;what
   she has is not a cold or the flu. She will never get better.</p> <p>A
   nap won&rsquo;t help. She is not lazy but she is tired to the point of
   a lethargic state.</p> <p>She&rsquo;s on medications to try to make it
   easier to thrive and not merely survive. Many people say that
   she&rsquo;s faking it or that she will just have to push through it.
   Well sometimes she can push through the pain and live her life, but
   there are days where she can&rsquo;t even walk with out having to hold
   o<span class="text_exposed_show">n to something. </span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">Her joints hurt. Her body hurts. Her mood is
   varying and she is sad a lot. </span></p> <p><span
   class="text_exposed_show">She tries to control her mood swings and
   depression. She takes her meds everyday and lots of vitamins to help
   keep her up, but some days nothing works.</span></p> <div
   class="text_exposed_show"> <p>She has an autoimmune disease.</p>
   <p><strong>Most common autoimmune diseases:</strong></p> <p>Lupus</p>
   <p>Fibromyalgia</p> <p>Rheumatoid Arthritis</p> <p><span
   class="rRegJd">Multiple Sclerosis</span></p> <p>Celiac Disease</p>
   <p>Pernicious Anemia</p> <p>Graves Disease</p> <p>Psoriasis</p> <p>Type
   1 Diabetes</p> <div class="co8aDb gsrt" role="heading"
   aria-level="3"><b>Symptoms of a weaken immune&nbsp;system:</b></div>
   <div class="RqBzHd"> <ul class="i8Z77e"><li class="TrT0Xe">Frequent and
   recurrent pneumonia, bronchitis, sinus infections, ear infections,
   meningitis or skin infections.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Inflammation and
   infection of internal organs.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Blood disorders,
   such as low platelet counts or anemia.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Digestive problems, such as cramping, loss of appetite,
   nausea and diarrhea.</li> <li>fatigue</li> <li>achy muscles</li>
   <li>low-grade fever</li> <li>trouble concentrating</li> <li>numbness
   and tingling in the hands and feet</li> <li>hair loss</li> </ul><div>
   <article class="article-body css-osx908 e13ml3jd0"><div class="css-0">
   <p>Treatments include medicines to calm the overactive immune response
   and bring down inflammation in the body. Show support and love for
   these people. <strong>Do not judge they need you!!&nbsp;</strong></p>
   </div> </article></div> </div> </div></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div

   all ingredients. Whisk until combined.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   all chopped ingredients. Pour dressing over salad.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">7</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided use</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">2% milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plus 1/8 tsp. pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">17.3 oz. frozen puff pastry,
   thawed</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sliced deli ham</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1/4 in. thick</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded cheddar
   cheese</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">SAUSAGE
   GRAVY:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bulk pork sausage</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">envelope country gravy
   mix</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400. In a small bowl, whisk six eggs, milk, salt and 1/4 tsp.
   pepper until blended.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large nonstick skillet, heat the butter over medium heat. Pour in egg
   mixture; cook and stir just until eggs are thickened and no liquid egg
   remains. Remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, whisk remaining egg with water. On a lightly floured
   surface, unfold one sheet of puff pastry and roll into a 10-in. square.
   Transfer to a parchment paper-lined baking sheet. Arrange the the ham
   over the pastry to within 1 in. of edges; top with the scrambled eggs.
   Sprinkle with the shredded cheddar cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush
   beaten egg mixture over edges of pastry. Roll remaining puff pastry
   into a 10-in. square; place over filling. Press edges with a fork to
   seal; cut slits in top. Brush the top with additional egg mixture;
   sprinkle with remaining pepper. Bake pastry until golden brown, 20-25
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, in a skillet, cook the sausage over medium heat until
   it is no longer pink, breaking into crumbles, 6-8 minutes. Remove the
   sausage with a slotted spoon; drain on paper towels. Discard the
   drippings, wiping the skillet clean if necessary.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60091-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In same
   pan, prepare gravy mix according to package directions. Stir in the
   sausage. Serve with the pastry.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   starch</span></li></ul></div><div

   Cups:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li

   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Custard:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put 3
   cups of milk to a large pan on the stove. Bring to a boil. Add vanilla
   extract. Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl put in 1 cup milk, sugar. Mix in egg yolks until blended.
   Add in corn starch and mix. Pour in boiled milk mixture and mix.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Return
   mixture to heated stove (on low). Cook and whisk until thick. Pour into
   large bowl, cover and put in your refrigerator.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cookie Cups:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   butter, sugar, baking soda and eggs in large bowl and mix. Add in flour
   and mix until well blended.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   into cupcake pan and bake at 350 degrees F. for 10 to 12 minute.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   still slightly warm place a round small jar (like your vanilla extract
   jar) in the center of the cupcakes. pressing lightly to make a hole in
   the center of the cupcakes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   cupcakes and place custard mixture into the center.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   fruit of your choice to the top and sprinkle with powdered sugar.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60087-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until ready to serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/9-ways-to-make-your-food-last-longer/ Sun, 06
   Jan 2019 13:55:51 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Cooking
   Tips & Tricks DIY And Tips How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60060 9 Ways To Make Your Food Last
   Longer. Tips to... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/9-ways-to-make-your-food-last-longer/">
   Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>9 Ways To Make Your Food Last Longer.</strong>
   Tips to make meat, strawberries, bread, milk and bananas last longer.
   How to soften cookies and crisp up your lettuce.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-60081 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/9-Ways-To-Mak
   e-Your-Food-Last-Longer.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="9 Ways To Make Your Food Last Longer. Tips to
   make meat, strawberries, bread, milk and bananas last longer. How to
   soften cookies and crisp up your lettuce."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/9-Ways-To-
   Make-Your-Food-Last-Longer.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/9-Ways-To-Make-You
   r-Food-Last-Longer-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/9-Ways-To-Make-You
   r-Food-Last-Longer-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><strong>Meat:</strong> Place fresh meat into a zip lock
   bag leaving a small opening at the side of the bag. Then submerge in a
   bowl of water up to the top of the bag, and completely seal the top.
   Meat will be vacuum sealed ready to freeze.</p>
   <p><strong>Strawberries:</strong> Mix a bowl of 3 parts water with 1
   part apple cider vinegar. Take the strawberries that are still in the
   plastic container and dip them into the water mixture. Shake off excess
   water and store in the refrigerator. Days later your strawberries will
   still be fresh.</p> <p><strong>Bread:</strong> Add a celery stick to a
   fresh loaf of bread. This will help prevent moldy bread and keep it
   fresh longer.</p> <p><strong>To Soften Cookies:</strong> Place hard
   cookies in a resealable container. Add a slice of bread and reseal.
   Days later the cookies will soften.</p> <p><strong>Slow down milk from
   spoiling</strong>: When you open fresh milk add 1 teaspoon salt and
   shake the container. Several days later the milk will still be
   fresh.</p> <p><strong>Bananas:</strong> Wrap the top stems of a bunch
   of bananas with plastic wrap or aluminum foil. A week later they will
   still be fresh. This will slow down the browning process.</p>
   <p><strong>Potatoes:</strong> Place an apple in the bag of potatoes.
   The bag of potatoes will stay sprout free and firm for eight weeks.</p>
   <p><strong>Tomatoes:</strong> Store outside of the refrigerator with
   the stem side down. Will make your tomatoes last longer.</p>
   <p><strong>Wilted salad</strong>: Wrap the wilted salad in a clean
   kitchen towel. Store in an airtight plastic container. The kitchen
   towel will absorb the moisture and make your greens crisper. You can
   also place the wilted green in a bowl of ice water making them look
   fresh again.</p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   cheese</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 425F. Grease a 13 x 9 inch baking dish, or spray with
   nonstick cooking spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   the tortillas. Place paper towels on a work surface. Heat 1 teaspoon of
   the oil in a skillet over medium high heat, and cook the tortillas one
   at a time, for about 1 to 2 minutes on each side, or until just crisp
   and browned in spots (they should also start to smell nice and
   fragrant). As they are cooked, transfer them to paper towels. Add more
   oil, 1 teaspoon at a time as needed until all of the tortillas are
   cooked.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the enchilada sauce with the refried beans, cumin, garlic powder, and
   chili powder. Layer half the tortillas in the bottom of the prepared
   pan, overlapping them to cover the bottom of the pan. Drizzle over half
   of the enchilada sauce, then sprinkle over half of the cheese. Repeat
   layering the tortillas, enchilada sauce and cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use the
   a spoon and your fingers to create 8 evenly spaced little wells in the
   top of the casserole, breaking holes through the top layer of tortillas
   so that the eggs have enough room to sink into their indentations. Use
   the spoon and your fingers to create these wells, making them about 1
   inch deep. Crack the eggs carefully into the wells, and season them
   with salt and pepper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until the whites of the eggs are set, but the yolks are still loose and
   runny, about 25 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60077-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After
   taking out of oven sprinkle the diced tomatoes and shredded cheese over
   top. Or place in individual bowls and add the two toppings. Serve
   hot.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   flavor without the need for sugar.&nbsp;This is a coffee drink loaded
   with flavor, it&rsquo;s filling and satisfying.</p> <p>It keeps you
   feeling full.</p> <p>Speeds up your metabolism because it makes your
   system burn fat.</p> <p>It also keeps your energy level up all day
   because it enhances the effect of caffeine.</p> <p>Butter is digested
   faster than other fats, so it boosts energy and promotes weight
   loss.</p> <p>The butter turns off some of your food cravings and
   provides things the brain needs.</p> <p>Butter could slow the
   absorption of caffeine into the bloodstream. This would result in a
   prolonged energy boost rather than the peak and crash you might
   experience if you drank your coffee without the fat.</p> <p>You should
   drink this mix <strong>3 times a week</strong> at the most in order to
   feel your best.</p> <p><strong>Use unsalted
   butter.</strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   and peel potatoes. Slice into thin chip size slices. Place in a large
   bowl. Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cheese crackers into a zip lock bag and crush finely with rolling
   pin.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put
   cracker, oil and salt in the bowl with the potatoes. Coating the
   potatoes well.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   each coated potatoes on a cookie sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 degrees F. for 30 to 35 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60069-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Stuffing:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix all
   stuffing ingredients until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Set
   aside.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For Ground
   Beef:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix all
   ingredients well. Divide in half.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   loaf pan with parchment paper.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   1/2 of the ground meat in the pan. Smooth with your fingers, to line
   pan from bottom and up sides.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   stuffing mix and smooth with a spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the other half of the ground beef on top and smooth evenly over top of
   the stuffing.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   350 degree F. oven for 40 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take
   out of oven and place on cookie sheet. Coat top of meatloaf with 1 cup
   BBQ sauce or Ketchup.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   back in oven and bake for 5 minutes longer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-60065-step-1-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">46 oz. each white grape juice,
   chilled</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bottle</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">48 oz. cranberry juice,
   chilled</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">12 oz. each frozen lemonade
   concentrate, thawed</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bottle</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1 liter club soda,
   chilled</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon sherbet or
   sorbet</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh mozzarella
   balls</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh basil or
   spinach</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small cherry
   tomatoes</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 to 6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Balsamic vinegar
   glaze</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-60040-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large dish mix all ingredients together. Toss until well mixed.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-60040-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate and serve when ready.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/air-fryer-parmesan-potatoes/ Thu, 27 Dec 2018
   12:37:17 +0000 My Honeys Place Air Fryer Recipes Recipes Side Dishes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60034 &#160; Parmesan Potatoes In Your Air
   Fryer. This Recipe is... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/air-fryer-parmesan-potatoes/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Parmesan Potatoes In Your Air
   Fryer</strong>. This Recipe is so easy to get tender potatoes in 20
   minutes. You could even bake them in your oven.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-64707 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Air-Fryer-Par
   mesan-Potatoes-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Parmesan Potatoes In Your Air Fryer. This Recipe
   is so easy to get tender potatoes in 20 minutes. You could even bake
   them in your oven."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Air-Fryer-
   Parmesan-Potatoes-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Air-Fryer-Parmesan
   -Potatoes-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Air-Fryer-Parmesan
   -Potatoes-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 60035--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Air
   Fryer Parmesan Potatoes</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Air-Fryer-Par
   mesan-Potatoes-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>2 to 3 large potatoes
   (cleaned and sliced into french fry shape)</li> <li>1/4 cup olive
   oil</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon onion powder</li> <li>1/2 cup Parmesan
   cheese</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon garlic powder</li> <li>1 tablespoon butter
   (melted)</li> <li>Salt and black pepper to taste</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Wash potatoes, do
   not peel, slice into long strips.</li> <li>Mix all ingredients, except
   potatoes, into a large bowl.</li> <li>Add potatoes and mix until well
   coated.</li> <li>Place into your Air Fryer and cook on 400 degrees for
   about 20 minutes. Or until potatoes are tender, crisp and golden.</li>
   <li>****If you prefer oven method: Spray a shallow baking dish with
   cooking spray. Follow directions above then spread the potatoes evenly
   in your dish.&nbsp;Bake at 450 degrees for 25-30 minutes, or until
   potatoes are tender. Stir the potatoes once after about 15 minutes of
   baking so they brown on all sides.</li> </ol></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Be sure to check

   l/ Wed, 26 Dec 2018 11:04:12 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   DIY And Tips Gardening https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60030 Natural
   Fertilizers To Enrich Your Garden Soil NOW. You don&#8217;t... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/natural-fertilizers-to-enrich-your-gard
   en-soil/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60031 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Natural-Ferti
   lizers-To-Enrich-Your-Garden-Soil.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Natural Fertilizers To Enrich Your Garden Soil
   NOW. You don't have to wait for spring to get your soil ready for your
   garden. Awesome DIY ideas."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Natural-Fe
   rtilizers-To-Enrich-Your-Garden-Soil.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Natural-Fertilizer
   s-To-Enrich-Your-Garden-Soil-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Natural-Fertilizer
   s-To-Enrich-Your-Garden-Soil-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p><strong>Natural Fertilizers To Enrich Your
   Garden Soil NOW.</strong> You don&rsquo;t have to wait for spring to
   get your soil ready for your garden. Awesome DIY ideas.</p>
   <p><strong>Egg Shells:</strong> Use an empty milk bottle with a lid.
   Every time you use eggs, put the shells in the bottle. When almost full
   of egg shells fill it with water. Keep the lid on. After 6 months water
   it into the garden on a rainy day.</p> <p><strong>Use farm
   compost</strong>:&nbsp;&nbsp;<span data-ft='{"tn":"K"}'><span
   class="UFICommentBody">Poultry, ducks, chicken, rabbit, geese droppings
   are very good fertilizer.&nbsp;</span></span></p> <p>Throw all your
   <strong>vegetable scraps</strong> straight into the garden. Including
   avocado peels and pits, coffee grounds, used tea, sour milk, peanut
   shells.</p> <p><strong>Epson salt</strong>: Use on&nbsp;on tomatoes,
   peppers, and roses to&nbsp;grow&nbsp;stronger plants with more blossoms
   and sweeter tasting vegetables.</p> <p><strong>Coffee
   grounds:</strong>&nbsp;Add used&nbsp;coffee grounds&nbsp;directly to
   the soil in your garden. You can it into the top couple inches of soil,
   or just sprinkle the&nbsp;grounds&nbsp;on top and leave it
   alone.&nbsp;Coffee grounds&nbsp;encourage microbes to grow
   in&nbsp;the&nbsp;soil.&nbsp;Mix used coffee grounds with yard waste
   like dead leaves or dry straw and grass clippings to add nitrogen to
   the soil.</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dKgo346GTmw" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>You can also check out this <a
   href="https://www.almanac.com/content/vegetable-growing-guide"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vegetable Growing
   Guide</a></strong></p></body></html> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
