   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/messages-hidden-on-a-dollar-bill/ Wed, 26 Dec
   2018 11:01:52 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=60017 Messages Hidden On A Dollar Bill.
   What do those message... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/messages-hidden-on-a-dollar-bill/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60018 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Messages-Hidd
   en-On-A-Dollar-Bill.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Messages Hidden On A Dollar Bill. What do those
   message mean? Find out:"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Messages-H
   idden-On-A-Dollar-Bill.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Messages-Hidden-On
   -A-Dollar-Bill-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Messages-Hidden-On
   -A-Dollar-Bill-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>Messages Hidden On A Dollar Bill. What do those message
   mean? Find out:</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-60020"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-926397
   _960_720-400x168.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="251"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-926
   397_960_720-400x168.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-926397_960_
   720-768x322.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-926397_960_
   720-150x63.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-926397_960_
   720.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>On the front you will see a letter left of George
   Washington&rsquo;s face.</strong> It represents which federal reserve
   bank printed the bill.<br> Letters you may see are:</p>
   <p>&ldquo;A&rdquo; for Boston<br> &ldquo;B&rdquo; for New York<br>
   &ldquo;C&rdquo; for Philadelphia<br> &ldquo;D&rdquo; for Cleveland<br>
   &ldquo;E&rdquo; for Richmond<br> &ldquo;F&rdquo; or Atlanta<br>
   &ldquo;H&rdquo; for St. Louis<br> &ldquo;I&rdquo; for Minneapolis<br>
   &ldquo;J&rdquo; for Kansas City<br> &ldquo;K&rdquo; for Dallas<br>
   &ldquo;L&rdquo; for San Francisco</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-60019"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-103666
   9_960_720-400x170.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="254"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-103
   6669_960_720-400x170.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-1036669_960
   _720-768x326.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-1036669_960
   _720-150x64.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dollar-1036669_960
   _720.jpg 960w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><strong>On the back of the bill</strong> is and eagle is holding 13
   arrows and an olive branch with 13 leaves and 13 olives.<br> The
   eagle&rsquo;s shield has 13 vertical stripes and 13 horizontal stripes.
   The number 13 represents the<strong> <a
   href="https://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/namerica/usstates/co
   lonies.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">original 13
   colonies.</a></strong></p> <p>On the back at the <strong>bottom of the
   pyramid</strong> is a long series of roman numerals: MDCCLXXVI. The
   numerals stand for the number 1776, the year america declared
   independence.</p> <p><strong>Eye at the top of the pyramid</strong>.
   The eye represents the presence of God watching over America. Those who
   like conspiracy theories, believe that the &ldquo;all-seeing eye&rdquo;
   is a symbol of the Freemasonry. The <strong><a
   href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freemasonry"
   rel="">Freemasonry</a></strong> were once a secret fraternity, and many
   believe our Founding Fathers were members of the Freemasons. They are
   called Masons today.&nbsp;The all-seeing eye shaped like the top of the
   pyramid is an ancient symbol of divinity.</p> <p><strong>The hidden
   creature</strong> might just be too small for you to spot without
   taking out a magnifying glass. In the upper-right corner of the bill,
   just to the upper-left of the number &ldquo;1&rdquo;, there appears to
   be a teeny-tiny creature peeking out. There are several guesses as to
   what this is. Some say that this is the shape of an owl. Many believe
   it was put there as an anti-counterfeit measure. Others, however,
   don&rsquo;t see an owl at all; they see a spider. Some argue a hidden
   spider would make much more sense, given the &ldquo;web&rdquo; pattern
   behind the number &ldquo;1.&rdquo;</p> <p><strong>The 1 on the back
   side corners</strong>. The&nbsp;&nbsp;cross or windmill-like shape
   behind the number 1.&nbsp;Many believe that this symbol is the shape
   known as the Maltese cross.&nbsp; Some believe to be a hidden reference
   to the famed <strong><a
   href="https://www.orderofmalta.int/sovereign-order-of-malta/knights-of-
   malta/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Knights of
   Malta.</a></strong></p> <p><strong>The pyramid</strong> on the dollar
   bill represents strength and duration.</p> <p><strong>The
   Eagle</strong> on a dollar bill is a shield, which is unsupported to
   signify Americans should rely on their own virtue.</p> <p><strong>The
   balancing scales</strong> on the Department of Treasury seal represents
   a symbol of justice.</p> <p><strong>Latin phrases</strong> appear a few
   times on the dollar bill. Above the pyramid reads &ldquo;annuit
   coeptis,&rdquo; which means &ldquo;God has favored our undertaking.
   Under the pyramid is the phrase &ldquo;novus ordo seclorum,&rdquo;
   which is interpreted as &ldquo;a new order of the ages.&rdquo; On the
   banner the eagle holds, &ldquo;e pluribus unum,&rdquo; which means
   &ldquo;out of many, one.&rdquo;</p></body></html> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Cheesy-Egg
   -and-Bacon-Crescent-Rolls.jpg 600w,

   on-Crescent-Rolls-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p><strong>Cheesy Egg and Bacon Crescent Rolls</strong>.
   Compete breakfast recipe rolled into one and serves 8.&nbsp; Make these
   ahead of time and store in the refrigerator after baking and then
   microwave.&nbsp;You can also make these with breakfast sausage
   links&nbsp; split in half lengthwise.</p> <p>Print recipe and watch
   video below:</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 59994--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Cheesy Egg and Bacon Crescent
   Rolls</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Cheesy-Egg-an
   d-Bacon-Crescent-Rolls-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> </p><div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul><li>1 roll refrigerated
   crescent rolls</li> <li>4 large eggs (scrambled)</li> <li>8 slices
   bacon (cooked and cut in half or cooked sausage links)</li> <li>4
   slices American cheese (can also use shredded)</li> </ul></div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol><li>Unroll crescent roll
   dough and separate into triangles like you normally would.</li>
   <li>Place half a slice of cheese on the wide end, then a piece of
   scrambled egg, then a slice of bacon or sausage.</li> <li>Roll up,
   stretching the end tip as necessary to allow it to go on the bottom.
   Place onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350*F for 12-15
   minutes.</li> </ol></div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   <p>Makes 8 breakfast roll ups.</p> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59989-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl combine cool whip, sweetened condense milk, cherry pie
   filling and crushed pineapples. Mix until well combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59989-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold in
   mini marshmallows and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before
   serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </body></html> <div

   Cheesecake Recipe.&#160;Warning ! This cheesecake is... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"

   <html><body><p><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59985
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Instant-Pot-N
   ew-York-Cheesecake-Recipe.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"

   Recipe</strong>.&nbsp;Warning ! This cheesecake is extremely delicious,
   proceed with extreme caution! To make it sugar free, you could
   substitute the sugar for half the amount of Splenda.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong> Crust:</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">10 graham cracker sheets ( or about 1 full
   package )</p> <p style="text-align: center;">4 tbsp melted butter</p>
   <p style="text-align: center;">pinch of salt</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">2 tsp brown sugar</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Cheesecake batter:</strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">2/3 cup sugar</p> <p style="text-align: center;">2 tbsp corn
   starch</p> <p style="text-align: center;">2 pinches salt</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">16 oz cream cheese</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">1/2 cup sour cream</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">2 tsp vanilla</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">2 eggs</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Topping:</strong></p> <p style="text-align: center;">2
   &ldquo;big huge&rdquo; tbsp sour cream</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">2 tsp sugar</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>To
   make:</strong></p> <p style="text-align: center;">Pressure cook 26
   min</p> <p style="text-align: center;">rest 10 min</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">refrigerate at least 4 hours ~ even better
   overnight</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Watch cute video for instructions.
   *<strong>note</strong>: He&nbsp;meant to say that he used parchment
   paper in the video.<br><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CbJ8BAYn8VE" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span

   https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-and-easiest-ways-to-get-rid-of-fruit
   -flies/ Fri, 14 Dec 2018 15:37:49 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing
   Information DIY And Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59980 The Best
   And Easiest Ways To Get Rid Of Fruit... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-and-easiest-ways-to-get-rid-of
   -fruit-flies/">Continue reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59981
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/The-Best-And-
   Easiest-Ways-To-Get-Rid-Of-Fruit-Flies.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900" data-pin-description="The Best And Easiest Ways To Get Rid
   Of Fruit Flies. If you have problems with fruit flies try these
   ideas:&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/The-Best-A
   nd-Easiest-Ways-To-Get-Rid-Of-Fruit-Flies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/The-Best-And-Easie
   st-Ways-To-Get-Rid-Of-Fruit-Flies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/The-Best-And-Easie
   st-Ways-To-Get-Rid-Of-Fruit-Flies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"></strong></p> <p><strong>The Best And Easiest Ways
   To Get Rid Of Fruit Flies</strong>. If you have problems with fruit
   flies try these ideas:</p> <p>Fruit flies are small flies that&nbsp;lay
   their eggs near the surface of fermenting foods or other moist, organic
   materials. Fruit flies&nbsp;are especially attracted to
   ripened&nbsp;fruits&nbsp;and vegetables in the kitchen. But they also
   will breed in drains, garbage disposals, empty bottles and cans, trash
   containers, mops and cleaning rags.</p> <p><strong>The first step is to
   get rid of what is attracting them</strong>. Put all the apples,
   potatoes and onions in the fridge. Clean your sink, garbage disposal,
   trash can thoroughly. Make sure your trash can has a lid.&nbsp; Rinse
   your mops and cleaning rags with bleach water.</p> <p><strong>Pour hot
   water and bleach down your drains at night.</strong> Cover the drain
   with a bowl or dish. They breed in moist area&rsquo;s. Sink drains are
   a magnet for the pest.</p> <p><strong>Rinse out your beer/soda
   cans</strong> and wine bottles before throwing them away. This really
   attracts the monsters!</p> <p><strong>Get a bowl with sweet balsamic
   vinegar</strong> in it mixed with water say 1:5 vinegar and water. Put
   a squirt of dish soap in it, give it a stir. Leave it out. They will be
   attracted to the sweet vinegar but the soap breaks the surface tension
   of the liquid and they fall in.</p> <p><strong>Set out a glass of
   wine</strong> or something sweet and they will all collect in the
   drink.&nbsp;Take a bowl and place some wine into it, place saran wrap
   over it and pierce small holes into the wrap and place over the bowl.
   The gnats can get in but not out and drown in the fermenting wine.
   Works like a charm!</p> <p><strong>They could be from live inside
   plants</strong>. I went&nbsp; through that some time ago turned out it
   was the soil from the plants is where they were coming from I threw
   them all out problem solved.</p> <p><strong>Do a mix of all theses
   ideas?</strong> Find the room that has the most. I found its best to
   use a container that has a &ldquo;neck&rdquo; like water bottle, soap
   or beer bottle, etc to mix the solution. It can be anything that is
   going to smell strong, the soap is to stick&nbsp;to them, put 2 or 3 in
   room with most. Then 1 in each room. Pour stuff in drains. I had
   chemical pneumonia once from bleach so I use windex now in my drains.
   Take out all trash. Move plants out or put all in one room and close
   door. They will multiply very quickly, like in 1 day. My neighbor found
   her source by shutting doors to all rooms, bathrooms closet, then found
   they were all gone except 1 room so after hunting for source, Found
   them in unopened bag of dog food. But bag had a small rip in it and
   they loved it.</p></body></html> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59977-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make a
   double boiler by fitting a glass or ceramic bowl over a saucepan of
   water. Do not let the bottom of the bowl touch the actual water. Bring
   the water to the boil then turn it down to a simmer. Very slowly melt
   the cacao butter in the bowl of the double boiler. Take the cacao
   butter to no higher than 4045C/104113F. If you think it is getting too
   hot but hasnt all melted, take it off the heat to finish melting. It is
   important not to overheat it or the chocolate will taste grainy and be
   bloomed, with a white cloudy appearance. When the cacao butter has
   melted and is at around 4045C/104113F, add the rest of the ingredients.
   This should lower the temperature and we now want to bring it down to
   2830C/8286F; just above or below will be fine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59977-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   all the ingredients together with a hand-held blender to get rid of any
   cacao powder lumps and until velvety smooth and glossy. Do not
   over-blend or the chocolate will stiffen too much. If it is too stiff,
   place the bowl back over the hot water and stir gently for a minute or
   so then remove from the heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59977-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Keep
   stirring the chocolate gently to cool it then, when around 2830C/8286F,
   pour it into a silicon mold. Add your toppings. Then refrigerate until
   hard.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/iILl6evnDPw" width="450"

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">The Best Cheesy Beef Lasagna</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">&nbsp;</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">medium onion</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled and chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cloves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">finely minced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">15 oz. cans tomato
   sauce</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">15 oz. can water, you can use the
   tomato sauce can</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">12 oz can tomato
   paste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oregano</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">basil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">24</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mozzarella cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">grated</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">16</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cottage cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Parmesan cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 16</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">box of lasagna pasta</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">you will need
   15</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large pan, add olive oil, chopped onions and garlic. Saute for 3-4
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   ground beef and cook until completely browned, drain fat. Return to
   pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, oregano, basil, salt and
   pepper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   to a boil over medium heat, reduce heat to low, cover and cook for
   approximately 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   pasta according to package directions, rinse and set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   spray a 14 x 11 1/2 x 2 1/4 baking dish (or two smaller size baking
   dishes) with a non stick spray then add a small amount of meat mixture
   in the bottom of dish. Spread around.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   lasagna noodles (approximately 5, they will overlap onto each
   other).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   1/2 of the cottage cheese on top of pasta.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   1/3 meat mixture on top of cottage cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with 1/2 the Parmesan cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Next
   add 1/3 of the mozzarella cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-12" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   with another layer of pasta, cottage cheese, meat mixture, Parmesan
   cheese, mozzarella cheese.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-13" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Final
   layer is pasta, remaining meat mixture and remaining cheese.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59972-step-0-14"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   with foil, cook for approximately 50-60 minutes. Remove foil and cook
   for an additional 10 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/6-potluck-desserts/ Sun, 09 Dec 2018 13:48:10
   +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59948 6 Potluck Desserts. If you are going
   to a holiday... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/6-potluck-desserts/">Continue
   reading</a> <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
   <html><body><p><strong>6 Potluck Desserts.</strong> If you are going to
   a holiday potluck party then you will be a hit if you bring one of
   these delicious desserts.</p> <div id="attachment_59952" style="width:
   574px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59952" class="wp-image-59952
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-Dess
   ert-3.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705" data-pin-description="Yummy
   Dessert Recipes for A Potluck. Chocolate Coconut Bars or Lemon Pie. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-D
   essert-3.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-Dessert-3
   -320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-Dessert-3
   -120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw, 564px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59952" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Yummy
   Dessert Recipes for A Potluck. <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/out-of-the-ball-park-chocolate-coconut-
   bars/" rel="">Chocolate Coconut Bars</a> or <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/for-you-i-will-bake-a-lemon-pie/"
   rel="">Lemon Pie</a>. </strong></p></div> <div id="attachment_59950"
   style="width: 574px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59950" class="wp-image-59950
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-Dess
   ert-2.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="Delicious Potluck Desserts Recipes: Pecan Praline
   Cake and Easy Crispy Peach Turnovers. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-D
   essert-2.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Pot-Luck-Dessert-2
   -320x400.jpg 320w,

   564px"></figure></div> <p><strong>Easy</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Fondant
   Potatoes</strong>. Easy Crusty Potatoes Roasted with Butter and
   Stock.&nbsp;</p> <p><br>Learn how to make a Fondant Potatoes
   recipe!&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>You will need:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>2
   tbsp vegetable oil</p> <p>3 large russet potatoes (other varieties will
   not work as well)</p> <p>salt and pepper to taste</p> <p>a knob of
   butter (a 2 or 3 tablespoon size chunk)</p> <p>4 thyme sprigs</p>
   <p>1/2 cup chicken broth or stock, more if needed<br>*Roast at 425 F
   until tender, about 30 minutes</p> <p></p> <p><strong>Watch video below

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">each sliced fresh
   mushrooms</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sherry</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">half-and-half cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced fresh
   rosemary</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 tsp. salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded cheddar
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lbs.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">red potatoes</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thinly sliced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">paprika</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59912-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 350. In a large skillet, heat 1 Tbsp. butter over
   medium-high heat. Add the mushrooms; cook and stir until tender. If
   desired, stir in sherry and cook until sherry is evaporated, 1-2
   minutes longer. Remove mushrooms from pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59912-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In same
   pan, melt remaining butter over medium heat. Stir in flour until
   smooth;</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59912-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">gradually whisk in the cream. Bring to a boil, stirring
   constantly; cook and stir until thickened, about 2 minutes. Reduce heat
   to medium-low. Stir in the rosemary, salt and pepper. Gradually add in
   the cheese, stirring until melted. Remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59912-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Arrange
   the potatoes in an even layer in a greased 13x9-in. baking dish. Top
   with the mushrooms and sauce mixture; sprinkle with the paprika.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59912-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   potatoes, covered, for 40 minutes. Bake, uncovered, until golden brown
   and bubbly, 20-25 minutes longer. Let stand for 15 minutes before
   serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span
   id="more-59910"></span></p> <p><div id="attachment_59913" style="width:
   410px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59913" class="wp-image-59913
   size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-
   400x371.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="371" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflowe
   r1-400x371.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-768x7
   13.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-150x1
   39.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1.jpg
   978w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59913"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Cauliflower Au Gratin.</strong> Creamy
   dish that taste like mashed potatoes. Even your kids will love
   them.</p></div></p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59914"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="59914"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:
   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-
   150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflowe
   r1-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-450x4
   50.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-500x5
   00.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-50x50
   .jpg 50w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/cauliflower1-225x2
   25.jpg 225w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></div> </div> <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59914" style=""

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cauliflower Au Gratin</h2> <div

   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large heads cauliflower</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">broken into florets</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded Colby-Monterey Jack
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Montreal steak
   seasoning</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   crumbs</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59914-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Place cauliflower in a stockpot; add water to cover. Bring
   to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, until very tender, 10-12
   minutes. Drain; transfer to a large bowl. Mash cauliflower; stir in the
   two cheeses, cubed butter and seasonings. Transfer to a greased 3-qt.
   or 13x9-in. baking dish.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59914-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, mix bread crumbs and melted butter until evenly coated;
   sprinkle over cauliflower mixture. Bake, uncovered, until heated
   through and topping is golden brown, 40-50 minutes</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">FREEZE OPTION.
   Cool unbaked casserole; cover and freeze. To use, partially thaw in
   refrigerator overnight. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before
   baking. Preheat oven to 350. Bake casserole as directed, increasing
   time as necessary to heat through and fora thermometer inserted in
   center to read 165.</span></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><div

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
   Reduce the heat; simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, 8-10
   minutes. Meanwhile, crumble sausage into a large skillet; add onion.
   Cook over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain if
   necessary.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59916-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drain
   the potatoes; arrange them in an ungreased 13x9-in. baking dish.
   Drizzle with butter. Add sausage mixture and stir gently. Sprinkle with
   cheese.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59916-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake,
   uncovered, at 350 until cheese is melted, 5-7 minutes</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/19-simple-psychological-tricks-that-actually-
   work/ Thu, 06 Dec 2018 14:05:31 +0000 My Honeys Place Informative
   Videos https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59906 19 Simple psychological
   Tricks That Actually Work. Have you ever... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/19-simple-psychological-tricks-that-act
   ually-work/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br /> <html><body><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-59907 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/19-Simple-psy
   chological-Tricks-That-Actually-Work.jpg" alt="" width="600"
   height="900" data-pin-description="19 Simple psychological Tricks That
   Actually Work. This video offers a few psychological tricks you can use
   in everyday life to make it much easier and more exciting for you to
   reach your goals."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/19-Simple-
   psychological-Tricks-That-Actually-Work.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/19-Simple-psycholo
   gical-Tricks-That-Actually-Work-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/19-Simple-psycholo
   gical-Tricks-That-Actually-Work-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width:
   600px) 100vw, 600px"><strong>19 Simple psychological Tricks That
   Actually Work.</strong></p> <p>Have you ever had to use psychological
   tricks to get what you want? There are a lot of psychological tricks
   and neuro-linguistic programming tips and there are millions of books
   and articles written about them. Many of these tricks really help
   professionals manipulate people and avoid being tricked by others. But
   are there tips that non-professionals can use on a daily basis?</p>
   <p>Psychology is a science with certain laws one cannot ignore. Modern
   marketing specialists, entrepreneurs, and even swindlers realize that.
   This video offers a few psychological tricks you can use in everyday
   life to make it much easier and more exciting for you to reach your
   goals.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>This Video has been viewed over 19 million
   times.</p> <p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/l4tWdTmYZoM"
   width="450" height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark"
   style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden;
   line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>SUMMARY:</p> <p>Never start your request with the
   words &ldquo;Could you&hellip;&rdquo; It can cause the other person to
   subconsciously assume that this is a theoretical question</p> <p>If you
   ever want someone to feel uncomfortable, look at the middle of their
   forehead during the conversation.</p> <p>If someone you&rsquo;re
   talking to is trying to avoid answering a question, just make a pause
   in the conversation while still keeping eye contact.</p> <p>When asking
   a question that you want an affirmative answer to, try to nod subtly as
   you make your request. This trick is often used by restaurants
   employees to make guests buy more food, and it&rsquo;s pretty
   effective!</p> <p>If a person is really concentrated on a task
   (let&rsquo;s say they&rsquo;re in the middle of a serious phone
   conversation), you can extend your hand to them and get anything
   they&rsquo;re holding at the moment.</p> <p>If you want somebody to do
   something for you, casually say how they probably wouldn&rsquo;t even
   be able to do it. Most people will try really hard to prove someone
   wrong when it comes to doubting their capabilities.</p> <p>Here&rsquo;s
   a good one for negotiations. If you like a person&rsquo;s offer in
   general but would like to get better conditions, pretend to be a little
   bit disappointed.</p> <p>As soon as your alarm clock goes off, sit up,
   make two fists, and yell &ldquo;Yeah!&rdquo; as if you&rsquo;re a
   soccer player who&rsquo;s just scored a goal. It sounds bizarre, but it
   really does help you easily get out of bed feeling refreshed.</p> <p>If
   a person tries to pull you into an argument or some drama, say
   something nice to them. The ol&rsquo; &ldquo;kill &lsquo;em with
   kindness&rdquo; trick really does stop them in their tracks.</p> <p>If
   you have that one lazy person on your team that slows the whole work
   process down, don&rsquo;t give them tasks by saying &ldquo;Do
   this.&rdquo; It&rsquo;s better to say &ldquo;Start with
   this.&rdquo;</p> <p>If someone is staring at you in the subway (happens
   all-too often, right?), just look at their shoes. Don&rsquo;t give up,
   keep gazing! It&rsquo;ll drive them crazy!</p> <p>If someone has done
   something wrong, but you don&rsquo;t wanna sound too accusing, change
   the way you construct your sentences.</p> <p>If you didn&rsquo;t get a
   good night&rsquo;s sleep, tell yourself that you did. I know, it sounds
   like nonsense, but it does work 100% if you say it with meaning!</p>
   <p>People are better at remembering what happened at the beginning and
   end of the day. As for anything that went on in between, it gets
   blurry.</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59902 size-full"

   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   3-qt. slow cooker, combine all the sausages. In a small bowl, whisk
   barbecue sauce, marmalade, mustard and allspice. Pour over sausage
   mixture; stir to coat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59897-step-0-1"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and cook on high until heated through, 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Stir in
   pineapple. Serve with toothpicks.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced chives</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cubed part-skim mozzarella
   cheese</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59899-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine the first seven ingredients; add cheese cubes. Stir
   to coat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59899-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover;
   refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Serve with pretty party
   picks.</span></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3

   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name

   Cupcakes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 2/3 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 teaspoons ground
   ginger</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Garnish: gingersnap
   cookies</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">browned butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">how to brown butter
   below</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">7</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole buttermilk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cupcakes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Line 24 muffin cups with paper liners. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar at high speed with a mixer
   until creamy, approximately 3 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating
   well after each addition. Add maple syrup and vanilla, beating to
   combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, whisk together flour, ginger, baking powder, baking soda,
   salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, and cloves. Add flour mixture to butter mixture
   in thirds, alternating with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
   Divide batter evenly among prepared muffin cups.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until a wooden pick inserted in center of cupcakes comes out clean, 18
   to 20 minutes. Let cupcakes cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from
   pans, and let cool completely on a wire rack.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   browned butter maple cream frosting into a pastry bag fitted with a
   medium round tip. Pipe frosting on cupcakes in a circular motion.
   Garnish with gingersnap cookies, if desired. Store, covered, in
   refrigerator up to 3 days.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat browned butter at high speed with a mixer until
   smooth. Add extracts, beating until combined.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">To brown butter:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Graba
   wide heavy-bottomed pan and place it over medium-low heat.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add 16
   Tablespoons butter. As it melts, continuouslyswirl the butter around
   the pan. The butter will go from brown to burnt quickly, so stay
   close.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Keep
   swirling the butter over the heat until it is light brown in color and
   smells nutty.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59890-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   mixer speed to low. Gradually add confectioners' sugar, beating well
   after each addition. Add buttermilk as needed until frosting reaches a
   smooth, spreadable consistency. Add salt, beating well. Use
   immediately.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 2 dozen cupcakes</span></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p><span id="more-59888"></span></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>More yummy cupcake
   recipes:</strong></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/4-christmas-cupcakes-decorations/"
   rel=""><strong>4 Christmas Cupcakes Decorations</strong></a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mint-crush-chocolate-cupcakes/"
   rel=""><strong>Mint Crush Chocolate Cupcakes</strong></a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/pecan-pie-cupcakes-with-buttercream-fro
   sting/" rel=""><strong>Pecan Pie Cupcakes With Buttercream
   Frosting</strong></a></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-a-dome-on-your-cupcakes/"
   rel=""><strong>How To Make A Dome On Your Cupcakes</strong></a></p> <p

   https://myhoneysplace.com/20-diy-shoe-hacks/ Sun, 02 Dec 2018 16:41:30
   +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips Simple DIY
   Projects https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59878 20+ DIY Shoe Hacks. Have
   you ever wondered how to... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/20-diy-shoe-hacks/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59886 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/20-DIY-Shoe-H
   acks.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705" data-pin-description="20+ DIY
   Shoe Hacks. Have you ever wondered how to prevent blisters, prevent
   squeaky shoes, widen your boot shafts, get rid of stinky feet, when to
   buy shoes and much more.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/20-DIY-Sho
   e-Hacks.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/20-DIY-Shoe-Hacks-
   320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/20-DIY-Shoe-Hacks-
   120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw, 564px"></strong></p>
   <p><strong>20+ DIY Shoe Hacks.</strong> Have you ever wondered how to
   prevent blisters, prevent squeaky shoes, widen your boot shafts, get
   rid of stinky feet, when to buy shoes and much more.</p> <p><strong>To
   prevent blisters:</strong> Get a bit of clear gel deodorant, and rub
   the inner heel of your shoes.</p> <p><strong>Prevent squeaky
   shoes:</strong>&nbsp;Grab a bit of baby powder and put some underneath
   your inner shoe sole. It&rsquo;ll allow for better cohesion between
   both parts of the shoe.</p> <p><strong>How to widen your boot
   shafts</strong>:&nbsp;All you need is a couple of newspapers. Simply
   stuff the shafts with the papers, and pull them out when you want to
   use your boots. Simple as that!</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-59884 size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-5-
   150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks
   -5-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-5-450x4
   50.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-5-500x5
   00.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-5-50x50
   .jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><strong>Get rid of
   stinky shoes</strong>:&nbsp;Put unused tea bags in your shoes, as
   they&rsquo;re absolutely great at absorbing unpleasant scents.</p>
   <p><strong>Widen your shoe toes:</strong>&nbsp;Grab an airtight bag
   filled with a little bit of water, and stick it in the toe area. Let
   your shoes rest in the freezer overnight. Because water expands when it
   becomes ice, the shoe toes will be a little bit wider than before.</p>
   <p><strong>Get rid of water stains on leather shoes:</strong> Vinegar
   and toothbrush duo is all you need to keep these ugly stains away.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59882 size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-3-
   150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks
   -3-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-3-450x4
   50.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-3-50x50
   .jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><strong>Use Beeswax
   to waterproof your shoes:</strong> The beeswax won&rsquo;t even leave
   stains or change the color of your shoes.</p> <p><strong>When to buy
   shoes:</strong> Buy shoes in the evening&nbsp;because your feet have
   the tendency to swell throughout the day.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-59885 size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-6-
   150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks
   -6-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-6-450x4
   50.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-6-50x50
   .jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><strong>How to absorb
   sweat in your shoes:</strong> It may sound like a weird thought, but
   panty liners are great at absorbing sweat. Less sweat in your shoes
   equals less smelly odors, and it&rsquo;ll naturally keep your shoes
   fresher longer. Simply put them in the soles, and you&rsquo;re all
   done.</p> <p><strong>Chafing heals:</strong> Coat your heels with a
   layer of K-Y Jelly first to prevent chafing.</p> <p><strong>Fixing
   scuffs:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Apply some petroleum jelly on a cotton
   swab, and rub gently until the scuff is gone. Works best on a patent
   leather shoe.</p> <p><strong>How to get rid of moisture in wet
   shoes:</strong>&nbsp;Grab a couple of old newspaper pages (or paper
   towels) to keep your shoes nice and dry.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-59883 size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-4-
   150x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks
   -4-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-4-450x4
   50.jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-4-500x5
   00.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks-4-50x50
   .jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><strong>Warm your
   feet:</strong> Insert some wool fabric whenever you might think your
   feet need some warming up.</p> <p><strong>Keep your kicks looking
   new:</strong> use a magic erasers or simply by rubbing some white
   toothpaste all over it.</p> <p><strong>How to clean suede
   shoes:&nbsp;</strong>Instead of cloth, just use some bread to get rid
   of stains.&nbsp;Use can also use a nail file to loosen dirt from the
   suede and brush it away like it was never even there.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-59879 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Shoe-Pegs-464
   x645-288x400.jpg" alt="" width="288" height="400" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Shoe-Pegs-
   464x645-288x400.jpg 288w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Shoe-Pegs-464x645-
   108x150.jpg 108w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Shoe-Pegs-464x645.
   jpg 464w" sizes="(max-width: 288px) 100vw, 288px"></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Make your own DIY Shoe Organizer:
   Instructions <a
   href="https://sawdustgirl.com/shoe-organization-easy-diy-project/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">HERE</a></strong></p> <p><strong>How to
   fix the bottom of flip flops</strong>:&nbsp;Instead of throwing a
   broken flip-flop in the trash, grab a bread tag or a flat washer for an
   easy and quick fix.</p> <p><strong>To keep your heels from
   hurting:</strong>&nbsp;Try wearing your normal socks over a thinner
   pair of socks or nylons. The two socks will slide across one another
   and can reduce the amount of friction that occurs directly onto the
   skin of your heel.</p> <p><strong>Whiten the bottom sides of your
   sneakers:</strong> Use nail polish remover.</p> <p><strong>How to wash
   your sneakers</strong>:&nbsp;In your tub, mix two cups of vinegar with
   two gallons of water and submerge your dirty, smelly sneakers. Wash
   them as normal afterwards and find that the smell and hard stains are
   gone!</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59880 size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Baby-shoes-15
   0x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Baby-shoes
   -150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Baby-shoes-450x450
   .jpg 450w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Baby-shoes-500x500
   .jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Baby-shoes-50x50.j
   pg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Make your own baby shoes tutorial
   <a
   href="http://www.hopefulhoney.com/2015/02/lemon-drop-baby-booties-croch
   et-pattern.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HERE</a></strong></p>
   <p><strong>Use old boot for plants:&nbsp;<img class="wp-image-59881
   size-thumbnail aligncenter"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks1-1
   50x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/shoe-hacks

   pecans</span></li></ul></div></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59876-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. In another bowl,
   combine cranberry sauce and remaining water; add gelatin mixture and
   lemon juice. Pour into a 13x9-in. dish coated with cooking spray;
   refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59876-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat cream until stiff peaks form. In another bowl, beat
   cream cheese until smooth. Stir in /2 cup whipped cream; fold in
   remaining whipped cream. Spread over gelatin mixture; sprinkle with
   pecans. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Bourbon Chocolate Cake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bourbon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces dark
   chocolate</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped finely</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped coarsely</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cocoa powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 3/4 cups whipped
   cream</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59869-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F. Grease deep 9-inch round cake pan; line base and side
   with parchment paper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59869-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   bourbon and sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat, without
   boiling, until sugar dissolves. Blend or process chocolate and bourbon
   mixture until smooth. With motor operating, add butter, piece by piece,
   processing until combined. Add eggs, one at a time, processing until
   combined between additions. Pour mixture into pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59869-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   pan in a large baking dish. Pour enough boiling water into baking dish
   to come halfway up side of pan. Bake about 30 minutes or until edge is
   set (center will still be a little soft). Remove pan from dish; cool 10
   minutes. Cover; refrigerate for 4 hours (or overnight) until set.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59869-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Carefully turn cake out of pan onto serving plate; dust lightly
   with cocoa. Serve with whipped cream.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p><span id="more-59867"></span></p> <p

   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-heavenly-snickers-cake/"
   rel=""><strong>Easy Heavenly Snickers Cake</strong></a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/eggnog-apple-cake/"

   Frosting</strong></a></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/pumpkin-almond-christmas-fruitcake/"
   rel=""><strong>Pumpkin Almond Christmas Fruitcake</strong></a></p> <p

   ntinue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59864 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Diet-Plans-To
   -Help-You-Lose-Weight.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="Diet Plans To Help You&nbsp;Lose Weight. A guide
   to a healthy diet for your New Years Resolution."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Diet-Plans
   -To-Help-You-Lose-Weight.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Diet-Plans-To-Help
   -You-Lose-Weight-320x400.jpg 320w,
