   -You-Lose-Weight-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw,
   564px"><strong>Diet Plans To Help You&nbsp;</strong><strong>Lose
   Weight.</strong> A guide to a healthy diet for your New Years
   Resolution.</p> <p>I realize it very hard to lose. But you can do it
   with determination. One of my favorite diets is to just <strong>cut out
   bread</strong> and/or sweets from your diet. My daughter lost 10 pounds
   by just cutting out bread from her diet. Take the bread from your
   hamburger and just eat the meat. Make meals without bread. Eat soups
   instead of bread. Try these:</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/15-best-homemade-soup-recipes/"
   rel=""><strong>15 Best Homemade Soup Recipes&nbsp;</strong></a></p>
   <p><strong>Keto Diet</strong>:&nbsp;The ketogenic ( Keto for short)
   diet is a very low-carb, high-fat diet.&nbsp;It involves drastically
   reducing carbohydrate intake and replacing it with fat. Research shows
   that the ketogenic diet is far superior to the often
   recommended&nbsp;low-fat diet&nbsp;.What&rsquo;s more, the diet is so
   filling that you can&nbsp;lose weight&nbsp;without counting calories or
   tracking your food intake. Read more about a <a
   href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/ketogenic-diet-101#weight-lo
   ss" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Keto Diet</strong></a></p>
   <p><div id="attachment_59857" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59857"
   class="wp-image-59857"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Skinny-Bell-P
   epper-Nacho-1.jpg" alt="" width="450" height="609"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Skinny-Bel
   l-Pepper-Nacho-1.jpg 552w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Skinny-Bell-Pepper
   -Nacho-1-296x400.jpg 296w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Skinny-Bell-Pepper
   -Nacho-1-111x150.jpg 111w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59857" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Example
   of a Keto Diet: <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-best-keto-diet-recipes/" rel="">The
   Best Keto Diet Recipes </a></strong></p></div></p> <h3></h3>
   <h3>Details of a Paleo Diet:</h3> <p>Recommendations vary among
   commercial Paleo diets, and some diet plans have stricter guidelines
   than others. In general, a Paleo diet follows these guidelines.
   <strong>What to eat:</strong></p> <ul> <li style="list-style-type:
   none"> <ul> <li>Fruits</li> </ul> </li> </ul> <ul> <li
   style="list-style-type: none"> <ul> <li>Vegetables</li> </ul> </li>
   </ul> <ul> <li style="list-style-type: none"> <ul> <li>Nuts and
   seeds</li> </ul> </li> </ul> <ul> <li style="list-style-type: none">
   <ul> <li>Lean meats, especially grass-fed animals or wild game</li>
   </ul> </li> </ul> <ul> <li style="list-style-type: none"> <ul>
   <li>Fish, especially those rich in omega-3 fatty acids, such as salmon,
   mackerel and albacore tuna</li> </ul> </li> </ul> <ul> <li
   style="list-style-type: none"> <ul> <li>Oils from fruits and nuts, such
   as olive oil or walnut oil</li> </ul> </li> </ul> <ul> <li
   style="list-style-type: none"> <ul> <li>Read more about<strong> <a
   href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/healthy-lifestyle/nutrition-and-health
   y-eating/in-depth/paleo-diet/art-20111182" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener">Paleo diet&nbsp;</a></strong></li> </ul> </li> </ul>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div id="attachment_21312" style="width: 360px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-21312" class="wp-image-21312"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blueber
   ry-Lemon-Muffins.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="350"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blue
   berry-Lemon-Muffins.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blueberry-Le
   mon-Muffins-250x250.jpg 250w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blueberry-Le

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blueberry-Le

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Paleo-Blueberry-Le

   350px"><p id="caption-attachment-21312"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Try these Paleo <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/paleo-blueberry-lemon-muffins/"
   rel="">Blueberry Lemon&nbsp; Muffins</a></strong></p></div></p>
   <p><strong>The Atkins diet</strong>, or Atkins nutritional approach,
   focuses on controlling the levels of insulin in the body through a
   low-carbohydrate diet. If people consume large amounts of refined
   carbohydrates, their insulin levels rise and fall rapidly. Rising
   insulin levels trigger the body to store energy from the food that is
   consumed, making it less likely that the body will use stored fat as a
   source of energy. Therefore, people on the Atkins diet avoid
   carbohydrates but can eat as much protein and fat as they like.
   Although popular for some time, the Atkins Diet comes with certain
   risks. Individuals considering the Atkins Diet should speak with their
   doctor. <strong>Read more about the <a
   href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7379.php"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">Atkins Diet</a>.</strong></p> <p><div
   id="attachment_59861" style="width: 460px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59861"
   class="wp-image-59861"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/One-Skillet-C
   hicken-with-Lemon-Garlic-Cream-Sauce.jpg" alt="" width="450"
   height="633" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/One-Skille
   t-Chicken-with-Lemon-Garlic-Cream-Sauce.jpg 534w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/One-Skillet-Chicke
   n-with-Lemon-Garlic-Cream-Sauce-284x400.jpg 284w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/One-Skillet-Chicke
   n-with-Lemon-Garlic-Cream-Sauce-107x150.jpg 107w" sizes="(max-width:
   450px) 100vw, 450px"><p id="caption-attachment-59861"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Try these <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/delicious-low-carb-recipes-diet/"
   rel="">Delicious Low Carb Recipes</a></strong></p></div></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"> <p><strong>Vegetarian Diet:</strong></p>
   <p>The majority of vegetarians are lacto-ovo vegetarians, in other
   words, they do not eat animal-based foods, except for eggs, dairy, and
   honey. Studies over the last few years have shown that vegetarians have
   a lower body weight, suffer less from diseases, and typically have a
   longer life expectancy than people who eat meat.<strong> Read more
   about a <a href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/8749.php"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vegetarian Diet&nbsp;</a></strong></p>
   <p>6 High Protein Vegetarian Dinners<br /> <iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Sf0miHIujeI" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p> <p><strong>South Beach
   Diet:&nbsp;</strong>The South Beach Diet has three phases: The first
   aims to kick-start the weight loss process, the second takes the dieter
   to their target weight, and the third aims to maintain the&nbsp;ideal
   weight.&nbsp; They say that people who follow the Diet are better able
   to: Maintain an ideal body weight for the long term.
   Avoid&nbsp;diabetes, achieve normal&nbsp;cholesterol&nbsp;and blood fat
   levels, prevent&nbsp;hypertension. The South Beach Diet, they say,
   means that people enjoy better health and feel satisfied with the food
   they eat. The approach offers a lifestyle, rather than a diet.
   <strong>Read more about the <a
   href="https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/7501.php"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">South Beach Diet</a>.</strong></p>

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">How To Stuff A Turkey</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59826-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Stuffing should be fully cooked on its own before placing inside
   the turkey.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59826-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   cooked stuffing and raw turkey to room temperature before filling the
   birdand only stuff it right before it goes into the oven to avoid
   contamination.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59826-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Stuffing will expand as it heats up, so don't pack the cavityit
   may cause uneven cooking.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59826-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take
   the temperature of the meat and stuffing: A stuffed bird is cooked when
   the breast and stuffing each register 165, and thigh is 175.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><span id="more-59824"></span><br /> <strong>Check out these
   Stuffings and Holiday Recipes:</strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-bagel-stuffing/"
   rel=""><strong>Homemade Bagel Stuffing</strong></a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/cranberry-apple-stuffing/"
   rel=""><strong>Cranberry Apple Stuffing</strong></a></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/holiday-cornbread-stuffing/"

   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/the-perfect-christmas-dinner/"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   broth</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large day-old bagels</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into 1-in. cubes (about 8
   cups)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped fresh
   dill</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59822-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   sesame seeds, poppy seeds, 1 teaspoon garlic, dried onion, caraway
   seeds and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a small bowl. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59822-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375. Coat a 9x13-inch casserole dish with cooking spray. Melt
   butter in a large skillet over medium. Add red onion, celery and green
   onions; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 7 minutes.
   Add chives, 3 teaspoons garlic, pepper and remaining 1/2 tsp. salt;
   cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about 2 minutes. Remove from
   heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59822-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together eggs and broth in a large bowl. Fold in bagel cubes, , dill
   and onion-chives mixture. Pour mixture into prepared casserole dish;
   sprinkle with bagel seasoning. Bake until heated through and browned on
   top, about 30 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Serves:
   8</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display:
   block;">Active time: 30 minutes</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
   <span style="display: block;">Total time:1 hour</span></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/20-cooking-tips-from-professional-chiefs/
   Sun, 25 Nov 2018 15:16:16 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Cooking Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59805 20 Cooking Tips From Professional
   Chiefs.&#160;The best advice that professional... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/20-cooking-tips-from-professional-chief
   s/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong>20 Cooking Tips From Professional
   Chiefs.&nbsp;</strong>The best advice that professional chiefs use to
   make cooking easier and taste better.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-59807 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/20-Cooking-Ti
   ps-From-Professional-Chiefs.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="20 Cooking Tips From Professional
   Chiefs.&nbsp;The best advice that professional chiefs use to make
   cooking easier and taste better."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/20-Cooking
   -Tips-From-Professional-Chiefs.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/20-Cooking-Tips-Fr
   om-Professional-Chiefs-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/20-Cooking-Tips-Fr
   om-Professional-Chiefs-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px)
   100vw, 564px"></p> <ol> <li>Use milk or buttermilk to thaw
   <strong>frozen fish</strong>. It will take away the fishy taste and
   acts as a tenderizer.</li> </ol> <p>2. Add 1/2 teaspoon of cornstarch
   to the flour when making a <strong>pie crust</strong>. The crust will
   come out noticeably tastier and flakier.</p> <p><div
   id="attachment_59817" style="width: 342px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59817"
   class="wp-image-59817 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/afile00041692
   8271-332x400.jpg" alt="" width="332" height="400" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/afile00041
   6928271-332x400.jpg 332w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/afile000416928271-
   125x150.jpg 125w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/afile000416928271.
   jpg 515w" sizes="(max-width: 332px) 100vw, 332px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59817" class="wp-caption-text">Snow Ice
   Cream</p></div></p> <p>3. To make <strong>snow ice cream</strong>: Mix
   5 to 6 cups fresh snow, 1 cup milk, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon
   vanilla.</p> <p>4. When making <strong>biscuits</strong> cut out as
   many biscuits as possible from first roll of the dough. The more you
   roll out the dough the tougher the biscuits will be.</p> <p>5. To
   <strong>bake bacon</strong>: put it on aluminum foil, heat oven to 400
   degrees and bake for 12 minutes.</p> <p>6. If your recipe says to
   preheat <strong>oven</strong> to 400 degrees, you should put it to 425
   degrees and decrease to 400 degrees when you put your dish in. You lose
   oven heat when you open the door.</p> <p>7. Fresh
   <strong>celery</strong> will keep for weeks if you wrap the entire
   stalk in aluminum foil and put in the refrigerator.</p> <p><div
   id="attachment_54138" style="width: 330px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-54138"
   class="wp-image-54138 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/10-Best-Chris
   tmas-Cookies-320x400.jpg" alt="" width="320" height="400"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/10-Best-Ch
   ristmas-Cookies-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/10-Best-Christmas-
   Cookies-120x150.jpg 120w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/10-Best-Christmas-
   Cookies.jpg 564w" sizes="(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-54138" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Click <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-best-christmas-cookies/"
   rel="">HERE</a> for great cookie recipes </strong></p></div></p> <p>8.
   If you want <strong>cookies</strong> to remain chewy, don&rsquo;t over
   bake. Always bake the minimum amount of time.</p> <p>9. Running
   <strong>bacon</strong> under cold water before cooking will reduce
   shrinking by up to 50 percent.</p> <p>10.<strong> Potatoes</strong>
   should be mashed using warm milk only. Cold milk will make the potatoes
   turn grey.</p> <p>11. Cool<strong> cookies and cakes</strong> on a wire
   rack, because if you leave them in a pan, the heat from the pan will
   continue to the point where it is overdone.</p> <p>12. To make 8
   <strong>grilled cheese</strong> sandwiches at once, place them on a
   cookie sheet and put another cookie sheet on top.&nbsp; The sandwich
   bread comes out crispy and the cheese gooey.</p> <p>13. Don&rsquo;t
   throw away those over ripe <strong>bananas</strong>. Antioxidants
   increase in fruit the longer the ripen. Use in smoothies and banana
   bread.</p> <p>14. Cool <strong>cakes</strong> upside down on cooling
   rack. Once they are cooled you will have a flat surface to frost.</p>
   <p>15. To prevent <strong>pie crust</strong> from being tough, roll out
   dough on a surface dusted with confectioners sugar.</p> <p><div
   id="attachment_59811" style="width: 277px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59811"
   class="wp-image-59811 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-
   The-Perfect-Pie-Crust-267x400.jpg" alt="" width="267" height="400"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Ma
   ke-The-Perfect-Pie-Crust-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-The-P
   erfect-Pie-Crust-100x150.jpg 100w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-The-P
   erfect-Pie-Crust.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59811" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Click <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-the-perfect-pie-crust/"
   rel="">HERE</a> to make the perfect pie crust. </strong></p></div></p>
   <p>16. To bake more <strong>cupcakes</strong> at once: After putting
   the mix in a paper cup liner, use canning jar lids on a cookie sheet
   instead of muffin pans.</p> <p>17<strong>. Out of eggs</strong>? You
   can substitute 1 egg by using 1/4 cup applesauce or 1/4 cup mashed
   banana.</p> <p>18. When cooking<strong> steaks or meat</strong>, do not
   use a fork to turn the meat. Use cooking tong or spatula to keep the
   juices from leaking.</p> <p>19. Use a large muffin tin to bake<strong>
   stuffed pepper</strong>. It will keep them upright and in place.</p>
   <p><div id="attachment_59813" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59813"
   class="wp-image-59813 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-
   A-Cake-Taste-Like-It-Came-From-A-Bakery-400x247.png" alt="" width="400"
   height="247" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Ma
   ke-A-Cake-Taste-Like-It-Came-From-A-Bakery-400x247.png 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-A-Cak
   e-Taste-Like-It-Came-From-A-Bakery-150x93.png 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/aHow-To-Make-A-Cak
   e-Taste-Like-It-Came-From-A-Bakery.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 400px)
   100vw, 400px"><p id="caption-attachment-59813"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Click <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-make-a-cake-taste-like-it-came-f
   rom-a-bakery/" rel="">HERE</a> to print instructions.
   </strong></p></div></p> <p>20. To make a <strong>cake</strong> taste
   like it came from a <strong>bakery</strong>: Follow directions on the
   cake box, then add 1 or 2 more eggs, replace oil with melted butter and
   double the amount, replace the amount of water with equal amount of
   milk. Then mix and bake according to package directions.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>More:</strong></p> <p

   For Us Poor People</a></strong></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><a

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Almond Shortbread Cookies</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li

   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter at medium speed with a mixer for 2 to3 minutes.
   Add confectioners' sugar, beating until creamy. Add almond extract,
   beating to combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, sift together flour and salt. Add flour mixture to butter
   mixture, beating on low speed to incorporate. Increase speed to medium,
   beating to combine. Add 1/2 cup almonds and nutmeg, beating to combine.
   Shape dough into a disk. Wrap dough tightly in plastic wrap.
   Refrigerate until completely chilled, at least 1 hour.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Using a
   pizza cutter, cut dough into 2-inch rectangles, rerolling scraps only
   once. Place on prepared baking sheets. Refrigerate for 10 to 15
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly golden, 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool on pans for 5 minutes.
   Remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59798-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Working
   in batches, dip ends of cooled shortbread in melted chocolate. Place on
   wire racks. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup almonds. Let cool
   completely.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span
   id="more-59796"></span></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>More
   cookie recipes:</strong></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/cinnamon-swirl-cookies/"
   rel=""><strong>Cinnamon Swirl Cookies</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/spiced-chocolate-chunk-cookies/"
   rel=""><strong>Spiced Chocolate Chunk Cookies</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/pecan-praline-cookies/"
   rel=""><strong>Pecan Praline Cookies</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/honey-oatmeal-cookies/"
   rel=""><strong>Honey Oatmeal Cookies</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/shortbread-lemon-cookies/"
   rel=""><strong>Shortbread Lemon Cookies</strong></a></body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">20</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Oreo cookies</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cheesecake filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">8 ounce packages cream cheese, very
   soft</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Sour Cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups granulated
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pure vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs + 2 egg yolks</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy
   cream</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the lemon
   topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs PLUS 1 egg yolk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or bottled lemon
   juice</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted and cooled
   slightly</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Adjust
   the oven rack to the lower third position and preheat oven to 350F
   (175C).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   9-inch springform in the center of a large sheet of heavy duty aluminum
   foil (about 18 by 18-inches). Carefully wrap foil around sides of
   cheesecake pan, spray inside with non-stick spray.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   food processor or blender, pulse 20 Oreos to fine crumbs. In a medium
   mixing bowl stir together the Oreo crumbs and melted butter until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   mixture into an even layer in bottom of prepared springform pan. Bake
   in preheated oven 9 - 10 minutes then allow to cool as you prepare the
   filling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cheesecake filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl using a hand held mixer, beat the softened cream cheese and
   sour cream until completely smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sugar and vanilla; beat until smooth, scraping down the sides and
   bottom of bowl as needed. Add in the eggs and yolks; beat until smooth.
   Stir in the flour, mixing just until combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Quickly
   stir in the cream, mixing just until it's incorporated in the
   batter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   filling into prepared crust, and spread evenly and refrigerate.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the lemon topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   amicrowave-safe bowl, whisk together the sugar and eggs until smooth.
   Stir in lemon juice and butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook in
   the microwave, high power for 3-4 minutes at 1 minute intervals,
   stirring well after each minute, until the mixture is thick enough to
   coat the back of a metal spoon. (for 1 minute twice then 30 seconds and
   finally three times at 15 seconds). Pour into dish and cool.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59791-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   cool spread over prepared pie and place in refrigerator.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cup all purpose
   flour</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">apples pealed</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">corded, and thinly
   sliced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brown sugar firmly
   packed</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chilled butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into 1/2 inch
   squares</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 F. Line a 8 x 8 oven proof pan with parchment paper,
   leaving extra hanging over the ends, spray with cooking spray.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large mixing bowl, beat together the butter and sugar until light and
   fluffy, about 2-3 minutes. Add vanilla and mix until combined. Add
   flour and mix until combined and dough is crumbly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   dough evenly into bottom of prepared pan. Bake for 12-14 minutes, until
   dough is slightly puffed. Remove from oven and set aside, maintain oven
   temperature.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine apples, flour, cinnamon and sugar. Mix until apples
   are thoroughly coated. Arrange apples on baked crust.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, mix together first five ingredients. With a pastry blender
   or two knives, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Spread topping
   over apples in an even layer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59786-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   uncovered at 350 F for 45 minutes, or until topping is golden and apple
   mixture is bubbly. Let cool, lift apple crisp using the extra parchment
   paper at the ends as handles, and cut into bars.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span
   id="more-59785"></span></p> <p><strong>More recipes using
   Apples:</strong></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/eggnog-apple-cake/"
   rel=""><strong>Eggnog Apple Cake With Brown Butter
   Frosting</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-apple-meringue-pie/"
   rel=""><strong>Easy Apple Meringue Pie</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/apple-flatbread/" rel=""><strong>Apple
   Flatbread</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/apple-cups-served-with-maple-toffee-sau
   ce/" rel=""><strong>Apple Cups Served With Maple Toffee
   Sauce</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/crispy-apple-tart-and-pecan-toffee-shor
   tbread-recipes/" rel=""><strong>Crispy Apple Tart and Pecan Toffee
   Shortbread</strong></a></body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/its-not-just-for-dishes-anymore/ Wed, 21 Nov
   2018 23:15:28 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips
   Simple DIY Projects https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59770 It&#8217;s Not
   Just For Dishes Anymore. DIY ways to use... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/its-not-just-for-dishes-anymore/">Conti
   nue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59772 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Its-Not-Just-
   For-Dishes-Anymore.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="It's Not Just For Dishes Anymore. DIY ways to use
   Dawn Liquid Dish Soap. Pint it for a gift."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Its-Not-Ju
   st-For-Dishes-Anymore.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Its-Not-Just-For-D
   ishes-Anymore-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Its-Not-Just-For-D
   ishes-Anymore-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw,
   564px"></p> <p>It&rsquo;s Not Just For Dishes Anymore. DIY ways to use
   Dawn Liquid Dish Soap. Pint it <strong>(below) </strong>for a gift.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59778 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/swan-400x267.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/swan-400x2
   67.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/swan-768x512.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/swan-150x100.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/swan.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>Wild
   Life</strong><br /> Ever wonder why Dawn Dish washing Liquid is the
   wildlife cleaner of choice after an oil spill? According to the
   International Bird Rescue Research Center, Dawn effectively removes
   grease but does not cause harm to the skin of the birds. It&rsquo;s
   also biodegradable and contains no phosphates.</p>
   <p><strong>BUBBLES</strong><br /> Dawn dish washing liquid makes great
   homemade bubbles. Here is the Giant Bubble Recipe used in bubble makers
   at many children&rsquo;s museums: 1/2 cup Ultra Dawn 1/2 gallon warm
   water 1 tablespoon glycerin (available at any drug store) OR White Karo
   syrup works too! Stir gently. Skim the foam off the top of the solution
   (too much foam breaks down the bubbles). Dip bubble wand and get ready
   for some good, clean fun!</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59779
   size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/hair-400x277.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="277" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/hair-400x2
   77.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/hair-768x532.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/hair-150x104.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/hair.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>GREASY HAIR
   PROBLEMS</strong><br /> Kids get into the darnedest things! Like
   Vaseline and baby oil rubbed into their hair! Dawn is mild enough to
   use on their hair and strong enough to remove the most stubborn
   grease.</p> <p><strong>HAIR PRODUCT BUILDUP</strong><br /> Once a month
   use original Dawn as you would shampoo. It will remove excess oil from
   your hair and scalp and strip away any build-up of styling products
   without any damage. Perform this once a month and you won&rsquo;t have
   to buy expensive salon products that do the same thing.</p>
   <p><strong>MANICURE SECRET</strong><br /> Soak fingers in full-strength
   blue Dawn. It makes the cuticles soft and easy to work with. And it
   removes the natural oil from the fingernails, which allows the polish
   to adhere very well.</p> <p><strong>REPEL HOUSEPLANT
   INSECTS</strong><br /> A safe, effective way to repel insects from your
   houseplants, including aphids, spider mites and mealy bugs. Put a drop
   of Dawn Dish washing Liquid in a spray bottle, fill the rest of the
   bottle with water, shake well, and mist your household plants with the
   soapy water.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59776 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/window-400x25
   5.jpg" alt="" width="400" height="255" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/window-400
   x255.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/window-768x490.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/window-150x96.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/window.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>CLEAN YOUR
   WINDOWS&nbsp;</strong><br /> Try this recipe from Merry Maids: mix 3
   drops Dawn in 1 gallon water and fill a spray bottle with the solution.
   Spritz and wipe as you would with any window cleaner.</p>
   <p><strong>PETS AND PESTS</strong><br /> Use it to bathe the dogs. It
   kills fleas on contact and is much cheaper than expensive dog
   shampoos.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59775 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools-400x300
   .jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools-400x
   300.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools-768x576.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools-500x375.jpg
   500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools-150x113.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/tools.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>CLEAN AUTOMOTIVE
   TOOLS</strong><br /> After you have finished your automotive repair
   project, soak your dirty tools in Dawn before you put them away to
   remove all the oil and grime. Dawn also helps prevent rust from forming
   on the tools.</p> <p><strong>ICE PACK</strong><br /> Partially fill a
   strong zip-type sandwich bag with Dawn dish washing liquid, close and
   freeze. The liquid soap stays cold much longer and it can be re-frozen
   many times. It will conform to the place you need an ice pack.</p>
   <p><strong>TUB AND SHOWER CLEANER</strong><br /> Take a spray bottle
   and fill it halfway with white vinegar. Heat in the microwave. Fill the
   rest of the way with blue Dawn. Put lid on and shake to mix well. Spray
   on your tub and shower walls. Allow to sit for a few minutes and rinse
   away. It will totally melt all the gunk, slime, sludge and other stuff
   that builds up including a bathtub ring.</p> <p><div
   id="attachment_59777" style="width: 410px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-59777"
   class="wp-image-59777 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ants-400x268.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="268" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ants-400x2
   68.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ants-150x100.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ants.jpg
   620w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-59777"
   class="wp-caption-text">&nbsp;</p></div></p> <p><strong>REPEL
   ANTS</strong><br /> Spray counter-tops, cupboards and any other area
   where you see ants with a solution of Dawn and water. Wipe dry. The
   slight residue of Dawn that remains will not be a problem at all for
   kids or pets, but ants hate it. Should you see a trail of ants, go
   ahead and hit them with the Dawn spray.</p> <p><strong>STRIPPING CLOTH
   DIAPERS</strong><br /> Add a squirt or two of original Dawn dish soap
   to your washer and run a hot wash, then rinse until there are no more
   bubbles. Dawn is a degreasing agent and helps stripping by removing
   oily residue. Be sure to rinse, rinse, rinse until the water runs
   clear.</p> <p><strong>UNCLOGGING TOILETS</strong><br /> A cup of Dawn
   detergent poured into a clogged toilet allowed to sit for 15 minutes
   and then followed with a bucket of hot water poured from waist height
   will clear out the toilet.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-59780 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/rash-400x267.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="267" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/rash-400x2
   67.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/rash-768x512.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/rash-150x100.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/rash.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>POISON
   IVY</strong><br /> Poison ivy spreads through the spread of the oil
   within the blisters. Washing the affected area with Dawn, especially on
   children who keep scratching the blister&rsquo;s open, helps dry up the
   fluid, AND keep it from spreading.</p> <p><strong>DRIVEWAY
   CLEANER</strong><br /> If you have gasoline or motor oil stains on your
   driveway, you can use the kitty litter method to clean up the excess
   oil and then use a scrub broom and a solution of biodegradable Dawn
   dish washing detergent and warm water to safely and effectively remove
   excess motor oil from the pavement.</p> <p><strong>OILY
   SKIN</strong><br /> Dawn makes a great facial cleanser for oily skin. A
   drop or two combined with warm water will do the trick.</p>
   <p><strong>PAINT OR GREASE REMOVER FOR HANDS</strong><br /> Dawn
   combined with corn oil makes for the perfect paint or grease remover.
   Simply combine a little bit of both in your hands then rub it over
   affected areas. The corn oil and the dish washing liquid both help to
   dissolve the grease and paint &ndash; yet leave skin soft, unlike
   harsher paint removers.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59783
   size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool-400x300.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="300" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool-400x3
   00.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool-768x576.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool-500x375.jpg
   500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool-150x113.jpg
   150w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/pool.jpg
   960w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"><strong>CLEANING THE
   KIDDIE POOL</strong><br /> Plastic wading pools can get very gunky,
   very fast. Dump the water, then scrub the pool with Dawn and a sponge.
   More potent cleaners like bleach will weaken and dry out the plastic in
   the sun.</p> <p><strong>MULTIPURPOSE CLEANER</strong><br /> Merry Maids
   recommends using a drop of Dawn in water to clean ceramic tile and
   no-wax/linoleum floors. You can also use the spray on:<br /> &bull;
   Bathroom and kitchen counters and sinks.<br /> &bull; Woodwork, e.g.,
   baseboards, shelves, and wainscoting. (Dry as you go&ndash;wood
   doesn&rsquo;t like prolonged contact with water.)<br /> &bull; Tubs and
   toilet seats.</p> <p><strong>LAUNDRY PRE-TREATER FOR OILY
   STAINS</strong><br /> For oil-based stains such as lipstick, grease,
   butter, motor oil, cooking oil, and some pen inks, simply apply some
   Dawn dish washing liquid directly to the stain and scrub with a small
   brush or toothbrush until the oil is removed, and then launder as
   usual.</p> <p><strong>NON-TOXIC LUBRICANT</strong><br /> Sliding glass
   doors, door knobs, hinges etc. It lasts much longer than any aerosol
   type spray that I have tried. And Its non-toxic! It does a great job of
   cleaning the parts that its lubricating as well!</p>
   <p><strong>SIDEWALK DE-ICER</strong><br /> For icy steps and sidewalks
   in freezing temperatures, mix 1 teaspoon of Dawn dish washing liquid, 1
   tablespoon of rubbing alcohol, and 1/2 gallon hot/warm water and pour
   over walkways. They won&rsquo;t refreeze. No more salt eating at the
   concrete in your sidewalks</p> <p><strong>POOL CLEANING</strong><br />
   Squirt Dawn down the middle of the pool and all of the dirt, suntan
   lotion, etc. will move to the edges of the pool for easy clean up! AND
   it makes the pools sparkle.</p> <p><strong>EYEGLASS
   DEFOGGER</strong><br /> Simply rub a small drop of Dawn on eyeglass
   lenses, and wipe clean. It will leave a very thin film that will
   prevent them from fogging up.</p> <p><strong>SHOWER FLOORS</strong><br
   /> Cover greasy footprints on shower floors with a coating of Dawn; let
   sit overnight. Scrub away the gunk in the morning with a stiff
   brush.</p> <p><strong>APHID CONTROL ON FRUIT TREES</strong><br /> Mix
   two tablespoons Dawn to a gallon of water and put in your sprayer. Try
   to get spray both sides of the leaves, branches and the tree trunks.
   Let sit for about 15 minutes and then rinse the trees THOROUGHLY!</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59782 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/gift-400x262.
   jpg" alt="" width="400" height="262" data-pin-nopin="true"

   this post and include it with a bottle of Blue Dawn!</p> <p><div

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">It's Not Just For Dishes Anymore</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Wild
   Life</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Ever
   wonder why Dawn Dish washing Liquid is the wildlife cleaner of choice
   after an oil spill? According to the International Bird Rescue Research
   Center, Dawn effectively removes grease but does not cause harm to the
   skin of the birds. Its also biodegradable and contains no
   phosphates.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">BUBBLES</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dawn
   dish washing liquid makes great homemade bubbles. Here is the Giant
   Bubble Recipe used in bubble makers at many childrens museums: 1/2 cup
   Ultra Dawn 1/2 gallon warm water 1 tablespoon glycerin (available at
   any drug store) OR White Karo syrup works too! Stir gently. Skim the
   foam off the top of the solution (too much foam breaks down the
   bubbles). Dip bubble wand and get ready for some good, clean fun!</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">GREASY HAIR PROBLEMS</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Kids
   get into the darnedest things! Like Vaseline and baby oil rubbed into
   their hair! Dawn is mild enough to use on their hair and strong enough
   to remove the most stubborn grease.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">HAIR PRODUCT
   BUILDUP</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-3-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once a
   month use original Dawn as you would shampoo. It will remove excess oil
   from your hair and scalp and strip away any build-up of styling
   products without any damage. Perform this once a month and you wont
   have to buy expensive salon products that do the same thing.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">MANICURE SECRET</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-4-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Soak
   fingers in full-strength blue Dawn. It makes the cuticles soft and easy
   to work with. And it removes the natural oil from the fingernails,
   which allows the polish to adhere very well.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">REPEL
   HOUSEPLANT INSECTS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-5-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">A safe,
   effective way to repel insects from your houseplants, including aphids,
   spider mites and mealy bugs. Put a drop of Dawn Dish washing Liquid in
   a spray bottle, fill the rest of the bottle with water, shake well, and
   mist your household plants with the soapy water.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">CLEAN YOUR WINDOWS</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-6-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Try
   this recipe from Merry Maids: mix 3 drops Dawn in 1 gallon water and
   fill a spray bottle with the solution. Spritz and wipe as you would
   with any window cleaner.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">PETS AND
   PESTS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-7-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use it
   to bathe the dogs. It kills fleas on contact and is much cheaper than
   expensive dog shampoos.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CLEAN
   AUTOMOTIVE TOOLS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-8-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After
   you have finished your automotive repair project, soak your dirty tools
   in Dawn before you put them away to remove all the oil and grime. Dawn
   also helps prevent rust from forming on the tools.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">ICE PACK</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-9-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Partially fill a strong zip-type sandwich bag with Dawn dish
   washing liquid, close and freeze. The liquid soap stays cold much
   longer and it can be re-frozen many times. It will conform to the place
   you need an ice pack.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">TUB AND SHOWER
   CLEANER</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-10-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take a
   spray bottle and fill it halfway with white vinegar. Heat in the
   microwave. Fill the rest of the way with blue Dawn. Put lid on and
   shake to mix well. Spray on your tub and shower walls. Allow to sit for
   a few minutes and rinse away. It will totally melt all the gunk, slime,
   sludge and other stuff that builds up including a bathtub ring.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">REPEL ANTS</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-11-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spray
   counter-tops, cupboards and any other area where you see ants with a
   solution of Dawn and water. Wipe dry. The slight residue of Dawn that
   remains will not be a problem at all for kids or pets, but ants hate
   it. Should you see a trail of ants, go ahead and hit them with the Dawn
   spray.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">STRIPPING
   CLOTH DIAPERS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-12-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add a
   squirt or two of original Dawn dish soap to your washer and run a hot
   wash, then rinse until there are no more bubbles. Dawn is a degreasing
   agent and helps stripping by removing oily residue. Be sure to rinse,
   rinse, rinse until the water runs clear.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">UNCLOGGING
   TOILETS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-13-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">A cup
   of Dawn detergent poured into a clogged toilet allowed to sit for 15
   minutes and then followed with a bucket of hot water poured from waist
   height will clear out the toilet.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">POISON
   IVY</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-14-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Poison
   ivy spreads through the spread of the oil within the blisters. Washing
   the affected area with Dawn, especially on children who keep scratching
   the blisters open, helps dry up the fluid, AND keep it from
   spreading.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">DRIVEWAY
   CLEANER</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-15-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If you
   have gasoline or motor oil stains on your driveway, you can use the
   kitty litter method to clean up the excess oil and then use a scrub
   broom and a solution of biodegradable Dawn dish washing detergent and
   warm water to safely and effectively remove excess motor oil from the
   pavement.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">OILY
   SKIN</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-16-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dawn
   makes a great facial cleanser for oily skin. A drop or two combined
   with warm water will do the trick.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">PAINT OR
   GREASE REMOVER FOR HANDS</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-17-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dawn
   combined with corn oil makes for the perfect paint or grease remover.
   Simply combine a little bit of both in your hands then rub it over
   affected areas. The corn oil and the dish washing liquid both help to
   dissolve the grease and paint  yet leave skin soft, unlike harsher
   paint removers.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CLEANING THE
   KIDDIE POOL</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-18-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Plastic
   wading pools can get very gunky, very fast. Dump the water, then scrub
   the pool with Dawn and a sponge. More potent cleaners like bleach will
   weaken and dry out the plastic in the sun.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">MULTIPURPOSE
   CLEANER</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Merry Maids
   recommends using a drop of Dawn in water to clean ceramic tile and
   no-wax/linoleum floors. You can also use the spray on:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-20-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">
   Bathroom and kitchen counters and sinks.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-20-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">
   Woodwork, e.g., baseboards, shelves, and wainscoting. (Dry as you
   gowood doesnt like prolonged contact with water.)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-20-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px"> Tubs
   and toilet seats.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">LAUNDRY
   PRE-TREATER FOR OILY STAINS</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-21-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">For
   oil-based stains such as lipstick, grease, butter, motor oil, cooking
   oil, and some pen inks, simply apply some Dawn dish washing liquid
   directly to the stain and scrub with a small brush or toothbrush until
   the oil is removed, and then launder as usual.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">NON-TOXIC LUBRICANT</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-22-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Sliding
   glass doors, door knobs, hinges etc. It lasts much longer than any
   aerosol type spray that I have tried. And Its non-toxic! It does a
   great job of cleaning the parts that its lubricating as well!</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">SIDEWALK DE-ICER</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-23-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">For icy
   steps and sidewalks in freezing temperatures, mix 1 teaspoon of Dawn
   dish washing liquid, 1 tablespoon of rubbing alcohol, and 1/2 gallon
   hot/warm water and pour over walkways. They wont refreeze. No more salt
   eating at the concrete in your sidewalks</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">POOL
   CLEANING</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-24-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Squirt
   Dawn down the middle of the pool and all of the dirt, suntan lotion,
   etc. will move to the edges of the pool for easy clean up! AND it makes
   the pools sparkle.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">EYEGLASS
   DEFOGGER</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-25-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Simply
   rub a small drop of Dawn on eyeglass lenses, and wipe clean. It will
   leave a very thin film that will prevent them from fogging up.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">SHOWER FLOORS</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-26-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   greasy footprints on shower floors with a coating of Dawn; let sit
   overnight. Scrub away the gunk in the morning with a stiff brush.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">APHID CONTROL ON FRUIT TREES</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-27-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix two
   tablespoons Dawn to a gallon of water and put in your sprayer. Try to
   get spray both sides of the leaves, branches and the tree trunks. Let
   sit for about 15 minutes and then rinse the trees THOROUGHLY!</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-27-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px"><strong>AND FINALLY</strong>..</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59771-step-27-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heres a
   brilliant idea! Need a hostess gift when visiting friends and
   family?Print off this post and include it with a bottle of Blue
   Dawn!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59754-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In your
   crock pot layer pork chops on bottom.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59754-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   cream of chicken soup and sprinkle the dry dressing mix over the
   top.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59754-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and cook for high for 4 hours or low for 6 hours.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span
   id="more-59753"></span></p> <p><strong>More Crockpot
   recipes:</strong></p> <p><a
