   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ham And Mashed Potatoes Casserole</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">potatoes</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled and diced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">8 oz. salted butter, cut into
   1/2-in. cubes, softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 3/4 tsp. kosher salt</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">aged white Cheddar cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">shredded (about 2 cups),
   divided</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg yolks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cooking spray</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">country ham</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thinly sliced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">thinly sliced green onions</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">about
   4</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Place potatoes in a large stockpot. Add water to
   completely cover potatoes and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to a boil over
   high. Reduce to medium-low heat, and simmer until potatoes are tender
   when pierced with a fork, about 10 minutes. Drain and return potatoes
   to pot. Mash potatoes to desired consistency.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   butter, sour cream, remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup of the
   cheese; stir just until smooth</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">and
   incorporated. Let stand 10 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add egg
   yolks, and stir just until incorporated.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Coat a
   2-quart broiler-safe baking dish with cooking spray. Transfer
   mashed-potato mixture to dish, and smooth top with a rubber spatula.
   Top evenly with remaining 1 cup cheese. Bake in preheated oven until
   potatoes are heated through and cheese has melted, about 20
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, heat a small skillet over medium high. Add ham, and
   cook until ham is brown and crisp, about 4 minutes per side. Transfer
   to a plate lined with paper towels to drain; let cool 10 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Increase oven temperature to high broil; broil potatoes until the
   cheese is bubbly and top is brown and golden, about 2 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59750-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   mashed potatoes from oven. Crumble crispy ham on top, and sprinkle with
   green onions. Serve hot.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Tip: Bake the mashed potatoes early in the day,
   then transfer them to a slow cooker and set on "low". They will stay
   warm and creamy and will free up your oven.</span></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p><span id="more-59748"></span></p> <p><strong>More
   Casserole Recipes:</strong></p> <p><a

   rel=""><strong>Crunchy Corn Casserole</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/kiss-my-grits-casserole/"
   rel=""><strong>Kiss My Grits Casserole</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-cheesy-chicken-biscuit-casserole/"
   rel=""><strong>Easy Cheesy Chicken &amp; Biscuit
   Casserole</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/taco-hamburger-casserole/"
   rel=""><strong>Taco Hamburger Casserole</strong></a></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/scalloped-potato-and-cheese-casserole/"
   rel=""><strong>Scalloped Potato and Cheese
   Casserole</strong></a></body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/12-uses-for-aluminum-foil-that-are-not-for-ba
   king/ Sun, 18 Nov 2018 14:56:53 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing
   Information DIY And Tips Simple DIY Projects
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59743 12 Uses For Aluminum Foil That Are
   Not For Baking.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/12-uses-for-aluminum-foil-that-are-not-
   for-baking/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD
   HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59745 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/12-Uses-For-A
   luminum-Foil-That-Are-Not-For-Baking.jpg" alt="" width="564"
   height="705" data-pin-description="12 Uses For Aluminum Foil That Are
   Not For Baking. Of course aluminum foil has great uses for baking in
   your kitchen. But bet you never heard of these 12 awesome uses."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/12-Uses-Fo
   r-Aluminum-Foil-That-Are-Not-For-Baking.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/12-Uses-For-Alumin
   um-Foil-That-Are-Not-For-Baking-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/12-Uses-For-Alumin
   um-Foil-That-Are-Not-For-Baking-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width:
   564px) 100vw, 564px"></strong></p> <p><strong>12 Uses For Aluminum Foil
   That Are Not For Baking.</strong> Of course aluminum foil has great
   uses for baking in your kitchen. But bet you never heard of these 12
   awesome uses:</p> <p><strong>Remove rust:</strong> All you have to do
   is soak the foil in water and scrub on rushed chrome. The rust will
   melt away.</p> <p><strong>Throw away grease:</strong> After you fry
   food. Pour your unwanted grease in a cup lined with aluminum foil. Wait
   until it hardens then throw it in the trash.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-59744 size-medium"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/bana-267x400.
   jpg" alt="" width="267" height="400"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/bana-267x4
   00.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/bana-100x150.jpg
   100w, https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/bana.jpg
   500w" sizes="(max-width: 267px) 100vw, 267px"><strong>Keep
   banana&rsquo;s fresher:</strong> Just wrap foil around the ends of a
   banana and it will keep them from getting brown too fast.</p>
   <p><strong>Burned pans:</strong> Use some dawn dish soap and a ball of
   aluminum foil and easily scrub it off.</p> <p><strong>Iron your
   clothes:</strong>&nbsp;Place a piece of tinfoil under the ironing board
   cover. This will reflect the iron&rsquo;s heat back up to the bottom of
   the clothes, allowing you to iron both sides at the same time.</p>
   <p><strong>Make a beautiful frame:</strong>&nbsp;Make a cheap wooden
   frame unique and beautiful! Simply paint the wooden frame with art
   glue, and adhere aluminum foil to the front of the frame. For best
   results, fold foil around the edges of the frame. It&rsquo;s OK if the
   foil is wrinkled &ndash; that adds to the rustic look! Once the glue
   dries, lightly sponge on metallic paint to create a rusted metal
   appearance.</p> <p><strong>Sharpen Scissors:</strong>&nbsp;Fold foil in
   quarters to create four layers. Then, cut foil with scissors &ndash; it
   will sharpen the blades.</p> <p><strong>Use as a funnel:</strong> Form
   a funnel out of foil. Easy clean up after, as you can simply throw out
   the dirty foil.</p> <p><strong>Use in your clothes
   dryer:</strong>&nbsp;By tossing a ball of wadded-up foil into the dryer
   with a load of clothes you can avoid static cling.</p> <p><strong>Keep
   your oven cleaner</strong>:&nbsp;Place a sheet of foil in the bottom
   rack to prevent any drips or crumbs falling to the bottom. Make sure to
   replace regularly to avoid any damage to the oven.</p> <p><strong>Move
   heavy furniture:</strong> Place aluminum foil under the legs of
   furniture and it will glide with ease.</p> <p><strong>Cover while
   painting.</strong> Cover door handles with foil and it will protect
   those areas from unwanted pain.</p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59740 size-full"

   Bars-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw,
   564px"><strong>Pumpkin Maple Pie Bars</strong>. The best and easiest
   recipe for a yummy pumpkin dessert bar. Recipe includes cream cheese,
   maple syrup, a cake mix, instant pudding and a whipped topping for a
   Holiday treat.<br /> To make this recipe even more delicious you can
   make your own<strong>&nbsp;<a

   Cream&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-59741" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="59741"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img
   style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;"
   width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Pumpkin-Maple
   -Pie-Bars-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""

   ple-Pie-Bars-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Pumpkin-Maple-Pie-

   wprm-block-text-bold">Pumpkin Maple Pie Bars</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">2-layer size yellow cake
   mix</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter or margarine</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">8 oz. Cream Cheese,
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">15 oz. pumpkin</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">3.4 oz. JELL-O Pumpkin Spice Flavor
   Instant Pudding</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">envelope Whipped Topping
   Mix</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground
   cinnamon</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oven to 350F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   13x9-inch pan with Aluminum Foil, with ends of foil extending over
   sides; spray with cooking spray. Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter until
   blended; press onto bottom of prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese, pumpkin, sugar, dry pudding mix and remaining eggs with
   mixer until blended; pour over crust.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 40
   min. or until center is almost set; cool 10 min. Use foil handles to
   transfer dessert to wire rack; cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, beat whipped topping mix, milk and syrup in large bowl
   with mixer on low speed until blended. Beat on high speed 4 min. or
   until mixture forms stiff peaks. Refrigerate until ready to use.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59741-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   whipped topping mixture onto dessert just before serving; sprinkle with
   cinnamon.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Orange Cranberry Cheesecake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-author-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container wprm-recipe-block-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">24</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">square shortbread cookies</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">finely crushed (about 1 and 1/4
   cups)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">8 oz. each Cream Cheese,
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">4 oz.White Chocolate,
   melted</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">zest and 1/2 cup juice from 2 large
   oranges</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups fresh
   cranberries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oven to 325F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   cookie crumbs and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch springform pan.
   Bake 10 min.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in large bowl with mixer until
   blended. Add chocolate; mix well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low
   speed after each until just blended. Pour over crust.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 1
   hour to 1 hour 5 min. or until center is almost set. Run knife around
   rim of pan to loosen cake; cool before removing rim. Refrigerate
   cheesecake 4 hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, mix cornstarch and 1 tbsp. orange juice until blended.
   Bring cranberries, remaining orange juice and remaining sugar to boil
   in saucepan on medium-high heat; simmer on low heat 6 min. or until
   cranberries are softened, stirring frequently. Stir in cornstarch
   mixture; bring to boil, stirring constantly. Cook and stir 1 min. or
   until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in orange zest. Cool.
   Refrigerate until ready to use.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59736-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   cranberry glaze over cheesecake just before serving.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><span

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59705 Easy Heavenly Snickers Cake. Recipe
   for an easy, delicious, poke... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/easy-heavenly-snickers-cake/">Continue

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-59706 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Heavenly-Snic
   kers-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="Easy Heavenly Snickers Cake. Recipe for an easy,
   delicious, poke cake. Made with a cake mix, whip cream, then topped
   with snickers bars and caramel.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Heavenly-S
   nickers-Cake.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Heavenly-Snickers-
   Cake-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Heavenly-Snickers-
   Cake-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw,
   564px"><strong>Easy Heavenly Snickers Cake</strong>. Recipe for an
   easy, delicious, poke cake. Made with a cake mix, whip cream, then
   topped with snickers bars and caramel.</p> <p><strong>For an even
   better taste use this recipe for&nbsp;&nbsp;<a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/make-homemade-whipped-cream/"
   rel="">Homemade Whip Cream</a></strong></p> <p><div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-59707" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="59707"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">

   wprm-block-text-normal"><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label
   wprm-block-text-bold wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package devil's food chocolate cake
   or German chocolate cake mix</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">One 14 oz. can sweetened condensed
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">jar caramel topping</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">One 8 oz. tub cool
   whip</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 to5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">snickers
   bar</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59707-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the cake according to directions in 9x13 inch pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59707-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   for 5 minutes, using the handle of a wooden spoon poke holes into cake,
   then let cake cool for about an 1/2 hour until warm.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59707-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   pour sweetened milk over cake, letting it soak into holes, then drizzle
   caramel over the cake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59707-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cake cool completely (you may refrigerate it to cool faster just cover
   well). Top cake with cool whip, decorate with candy and drizzle with
   caramel!!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-details-label wprm-block-text-bold
   wprm-recipe-author-label">Author </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-details wprm-recipe-author
   wprm-block-text-normal">My Honeys Place</span></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small green apples</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled, chopped
   finely</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brandy</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">11</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces cream cheese</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 additional cups
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">additional teaspoon ground
   nutmeg</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">additional cup butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups confectioners'
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325F. Grease a 8-inch round cake pan; line base and side with
   parchment paper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   apple, brandy and sugar in a large saucepan; cook, stirring, over
   medium heat until sugar dissolves. Reduce heat to low; cook, uncovered,
   stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes or until apple is tender.
   Cool.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter, cream cheese, additional sugar and extract in a medium bowl
   with an electric mixer until pale and creamy. Beat in eggs, one at a
   time, until just combined. Add sifted flour, baking powder, nutmeg and
   salt; stir until just combined. Fold apple through cake mixture. Spoon
   mixture into pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cake for 1 hour 35 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the center
   comes out clean. Stand cake in pan for 15 minutes before turning,
   top-side down, onto a parchment paper-covered wire rack to cool.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make
   Brown Butter frosting.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   frosting on cooled cake. Drizzle with reserved browned butter; dust
   with additional nutmeg.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   butter in a small frying pan over medium heat; cook for 2 minutes or
   until butter is nut brown. Cool slightly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   additional butter in a small bowl with an electric mixer until pale and
   creamy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sifted confectioners' sugar, in three batches, beating until light and
   fluffy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   extract and 2 tablespoons of the browned butter; beat until
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59702-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reserve
   remaining browned butter to drizzle on top of cake.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Tip: It is best
   to pour the remaining brown butter over cake just before serving or it
   will set on the frosting.</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span
   style="display: block;">Unfrosted cake can be made a day ahead. Store
   in an airtight container at room temperature.</span></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=59690 The Perfect Christmas Dinner. Recipe

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">separated</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/3 cups self-rising
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/3 cups ground
   walnuts</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">slightly warmed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">walnut halves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">roasted</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the center
   and topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">instant coffee
   granules</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">hot
   water</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325"F. Grease deep 8-inch round cake pan; line base and side
   with parchment paper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter and sugar in a small bowl with an electric mixer until light and
   fluffy. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time, until combined. Transfer
   mixture to a large bowl; stir in sifted flour, ground walnuts and milk,
   in two batches.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   egg whites in a small bowl with an electric mixer until soft peaks
   form. Fold egg white into cake mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   mixture into pan. Bake about 50 minutes. Stand cake in pan 5 minutes
   before turning, top-side up, onto a wire rack to cool.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the center and topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   cream cheese and whipping cream until well mixed. Add the confectioners
   sugar. Mix.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Dissolve the coffee in the hot water in a small cup.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   into mixture. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Put it together:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   serrated knife, split cake into two layers. Place bottom layer on a
   serving plate, spread with half the cream mix; top with remaining
   layer.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59688-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Warm
   the honey slightly. Spread top of cake with remaining topping, sprinkle
   with walnut halves and drizzle with honey.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">To make ground walnuts, process roasted walnuts
   until very fine.</span></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/mudslide-and-brownie-trifle/ Sat, 10 Nov 2018
   12:16:59 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=2674 &#160;Mudslide and Brownie Trifle is
   a delicious alcohol drink! A... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mudslide-and-brownie-trifle/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <h2>&nbsp;<strong>Mudslide and Brownie Trifle is a
   delicious alcohol drink! </strong></h2> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mudslide-and-brownie-trifle/mudslide-an
   d-brownie-trifle_bakers-royale-11-2/" rel="attachment wp-att-6688"><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-6688 size-full" style="margin: 5px 20px;"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-
   Brownie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111.jpg" alt="" width="465" height="698"
   data-pin-description="Mudslide Brownie Truffle. A recipe with chocolate
   Pudding with Kahlua Layer. Yummy dessert for any holiday party. "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-a
   nd-Brownie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111.jpg 465w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-Brown
   ie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-233x350.jpg 233w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-Brown
   ie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-266x400.jpg 266w" sizes="(max-width: 465px)
   100vw, 465px"></a></p> <p><strong>A few notes:</strong></p> <ul>
   <li><strong>If booze in desserts is not your thing, skip
   it.</strong></li> <li><strong>Too short cut this recipe, you can use
   boxed pudding. I find boxed pudding to be overly sweet and&nbsp;keep in
   mind this recipe hasn&rsquo;t been tested&nbsp;with it so pour your
   alcohol slowly and mix along the way.</strong></li> <li><strong>If you
   want something slightly lighter in texture change out the pudding for
   mousse. I chose the pudding for its denser texture as I wanted the
   broken brownies and roasted almonds to be contrasted against something
   more full bodied like pudding versus the lighter-airy texture of
   &nbsp;mousse that would disappear too quickly in my mouth against those
   components.</strong></li> </ul> <h3><strong>Mudslide and Brownie
   Trifles</strong></h3> <p><strong>Serves 7-8 (in 6.5oz
   glasses)</strong></p> <p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p>
   <p><strong>Chocolate Pudding with Kahlua Layer:</strong></p> <ul>
   <li><strong>1/3 cup cornstarch</strong></li> <li><strong>1/2 cup
   granulated sugar</strong></li> <li><strong>Pinch of salt</strong></li>
   <li><strong>3 cups cold whole milk</strong></li> <li><strong>3/4 cups
   dark chocolate, chopped</strong></li> <li><strong>1/2 cup plus 4
   tablespoon of &nbsp;Kahlua</strong></li> <li><strong>1 tablespoon
   vanilla extract</strong></li> </ul> <p><strong>Vanilla Pudding with
   Bailey&rsquo;s Irish Cream Layer:</strong></p> <ul> <li><strong>1/3 cup
   plus 1 tablespoon cornstarch</strong></li> <li><strong>1/2 cup
   granulated sugar</strong></li> <li><strong>Pinch of salt</strong></li>
   <li><strong>3 cups cold whole milk</strong></li> <li><strong>1/2 cup
   plus 4 tablespoons of Bailey&rsquo;s Irish Cream</strong></li>
   <li><strong>2 tablespoon vanilla extract</strong></li> </ul>
   <p><strong>Brownie and&nbsp; Almond Layer:</strong></p> <ul>
   <li><strong>1 1/2 cup of crushed brownie crumb</strong></li>
   <li><strong>3/4 cup of finely chopped almonds</strong></li> </ul>
   <p><strong> Instructions:</strong></p> <p><strong>Chocolate Pudding
   with Kahlua Layer:</strong></p> <p><strong>1. Combine cornstarch,
   sugar, salt and milk in a blender or food processor and pulse until
   well blended. Alternatively, combine all ingredients in a bowl and
   whisk vigorously. Transfer mixture to a heat proof bowl and place over
   (not on) simmering water for approximately 15-20 minutes, stirring
   occasionally. Pudding is ready when mixture coats the back of the
   spoon. &nbsp;Add Kahlua and stir to combine. Add vanilla and stir to
   combine.</strong></p> <p><strong>Vanilla Pudding with Bailey&rsquo;s
   Irish Cream Layer:</strong></p> <ol> <li><strong>Combine cornstarch,
   sugar, salt and milk in a blender or food processor and pulse until
   well blended. Alternatively, combine all ingredients in a bowl and
   whisk vigorously. Transfer mixture to a heat proof bowl and place over
   (not on) simmering water for approximately 15-20 minutes, stirring
   occasionally. Pudding is ready when mixture coats the back of the
   spoon. Add Bailey&rsquo;s Irish Cream stir to combine. Add vanilla and
   stir to combine.</strong></li> </ol> <p><strong>Assembly:</strong></p>
   <ol> <li><strong>Fill pastry bags with each flavor of
   pudding.</strong></li> <li><strong>Pipe a&nbsp;chocolate layer onto
   bottom of glass.</strong></li> <li><strong>Sprinkle&nbsp;crushed
   brownie&nbsp;and&nbsp;finely chopped&nbsp;roasted almonds&nbsp;on top
   of chocolate&nbsp;layer.</strong></li> <li><strong>Pipe vanilla pudding
   on top of&nbsp;brownie and almond layer.</strong></li>
   <li><strong>Continue layering by repeating steps 2-4.</strong></li>
   </ol> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-54233"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="54233"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:
   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-
   Brownie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-225x225.jpg" class="attachment-150x150
   size-150x150" alt="Mudslide Brownie Trifle"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-a
   nd-Brownie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-225x225.jpg 225w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-Brown
   ie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-250x250.jpg 250w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Mudslide-and-Brown
   ie-Trifle_Bakers-Royale-111-350x350.jpg 350w" sizes="(max-width: 150px)
   100vw, 150px" /></div> </div> <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/54233" style=""
   class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode
   wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe-id="54233" target="_blank"
   rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon
   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Mudslide Brownie Trifle</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div

   Almond Layer</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of crushed brownie
   crumb</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of finely chopped
   almonds</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate
   Pudding with Kahlua Layer</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">1.
   Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk in a blender or food processor
   and pulse until well blended. Alternatively, combine all ingredients in
   a bowl and whisk vigorously. Transfer mixture to a heat proof bowl and
   place over (not on) simmering water for approximately 15-20 minutes,
   stirring occasionally. Pudding is ready when mixture coats the back of
   the spoon. Add Kahlua and stir to combine. Add vanilla and stir to
   combine.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Vanilla
   Pudding with Baileys Irish Cream Layer</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   cornstarch, sugar, salt and milk in a blender or food processor and
   pulse until well blended. Alternatively, combine all ingredients in a
   bowl and whisk vigorously. Transfer mixture to a heat proof bowl and
   place over (not on) simmering water for approximately 15-20 minutes,
   stirring occasionally. Pudding is ready when mixture coats the back of
   the spoon. Add Baileys Irish Cream stir to combine. Add vanilla and
   stir to combine.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Assembly</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill
   pastry bags with each flavor of pudding.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pipe a
   chocolate layer onto bottom of glass.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle crushed brownie and finely chopped roasted almonds on top
   of chocolate layer.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pipe
   vanilla pudding on top of brownie and almond layer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54233-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Continue layering by repeating steps 2-4.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">applesauce</span></li></ul></div></
   div> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 150.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   medium bowl, combine cinnamon, cloves &amp; nutmeg. Add applesauce,
   stir to combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Work
   the dough with your hands for 3 or 4 minutes until dough is smooth and
   ingredients are thoroughly mixed.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If the
   dough is a little crumbly, add a tablespoon of applesauce at a time to
   it until it is smooth and a bit sticky.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   out dough to 1/3 inch thickness. It will be sticky, so be careful with
   it. You can use cinnamon like flour on your pin and rolling surface to
   stop it from sticking.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   dough with cookie cutters. Simple shapes like hearts, bells, trees and
   ginger men are easier to work with than cutters with complicated
   shapes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using
   straw make small hole in top of ornament.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake on
   an ungreased cookie sheet at 150 degrees for 2 1/2 hours</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from the cookie sheet and cool on a wire rack.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59669-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Loop a
   ribbon through the top.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">This recipe m<span
   class="text_exposed_show">akes 12 to 14 medium sized Cinnamon
   Applesauce Ornaments</span></span></div></div>

   How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=54197 Top Natural Pain
   Killers. Have an earache, heartburn, toothache, arthritis... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/top-natural-pain-killers/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-54198 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Top-Natural-P
   ain-Killers.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705"
   data-pin-description="Top Natural Pain Killers. Have an earache,
   heartburn, toothache, arthritis pain, gas pain or nausea? Simple DIY
   remedies.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Top-Natura
   l-Pain-Killers.jpg 564w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Top-Natural-Pain-K
   illers-320x400.jpg 320w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Top-Natural-Pain-K
   illers-120x150.jpg 120w" sizes="(max-width: 564px) 100vw,
   564px"><strong>Top Natural Pain Killers</strong>. Have an earache,
   heartburn, toothache, arthritis pain, gas pain or nausea? Simple DIY
   remedies.</p> <p><strong>Earache</strong>:&nbsp;Whenever you suffer
   from an annoying and painful headache or earache,
   <strong>garlic</strong> can help relieve your misery. Just put a few
   drops of garlic oil on a cotton ball (or take a peeled clove of
   garlic), and gently place it in the opening of your ear.</p>
   <p><strong>Heartburn:</strong>&nbsp;Mix <strong>baking soda</strong>
   with water. You might have a&nbsp;heartburn&nbsp;remedy at hand in your
   kitchen without even knowing it. Baking soda can calm some episodes
   of&nbsp;heartburn&nbsp;by neutralizing your stomach acid.
   To&nbsp;do&nbsp;this, dissolve a teaspoon of baking soda in a glass of
   water and drink it slowly. <strong>You can also read <a
   href="https://www.everydayhealth.com/gerd/preventing.aspx"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">10 Ways To Prevent GERD</a></strong></p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-54199"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/lavender-150x
   150.jpg" alt="" width="260" height="173" data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/lavender-4
   00x267.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/lavender-150x100.j
   pg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/lavender.jpg 750w"
   sizes="(max-width: 260px) 100vw, 260px"><strong>Arthritis
   pain:</strong> Take a sniff of <strong>Lavender</strong>. Lavender can
   alter the perception of pain.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a pain-soothing
   aromatherapy treatment, add to a teaspoon to a quarter-cup of vegetable
   oil. Take a whiff frequently. Check out our <strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/aroma-therapy-hacks/" rel="">Aroma
   Therapy Hacks</a>.</strong></p>
   <p><strong>Toothache:</strong>&nbsp;<strong>Salt water</strong> is a
   natural disinfectant, and it can help loosen food particles and debris
   that may be stuck in between your teeth. Treating a toothache
   with&nbsp;salt water&nbsp;can also help reduce inflammation and heal
   any oral wounds. Mix 1/2 teaspoon of salt into a glass of warm water
   and use it as a mouthwash. If your symptoms persist for more than a day
   or two, see your dentist.</p> <p><strong>Gas Pain</strong>:&nbsp;The
   easiest way to avoid these gas pain is to simply <strong>let out the
   gas</strong>. Don&rsquo;t drinking through a straw it can causes you to
   swallow air. Drinking directly from a bottle can have the same effect,
   depending on the bottle&rsquo;s size and shape. <strong>Avoid
   carbonated drinks</strong>, such as sparkling water and sodas, they
   send a lot of gas to the stomach. This can cause bloating and pain.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-54201"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/emotiguy-1654
   864_960_720-150x150.png" alt="" width="250" height="167"
   data-pin-nopin="true"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/emotiguy-1
   654864_960_720-400x267.png 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/emotiguy-1654864_9
   60_720-768x512.png 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/emotiguy-1654864_9
   60_720-150x100.png 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/emotiguy-1654864_9
   60_720.png 960w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw,
   250px"><strong>Nausea:</strong>&nbsp;Chewing raw ginger or drinking
   <strong>ginger tea</strong> is a common home remedy for nausea
   during&nbsp;cancer&nbsp;treatment.&nbsp;Measure 1/4 teaspoon
   of&nbsp;<b>ground ginger</b>&nbsp;into a heat proof mug or glass and
   pour 1 cup of boiling water over it. Cover with a saucer and let sit
   until cool enough to drink before straining. (You can line a fine mesh
   strainer with a coffee filter to&nbsp;do&nbsp;so.) Sweeten with honey
   or sugar as desired.</p> <p><strong>Urinary Tract
   Infections:</strong>&nbsp;Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of raw, unfiltered
   <strong>Apple Cider Vinegar</strong> to a glass of unsweetened
   cranberry juice. Cranberry juice is the most commonly used natural
   treatment for&nbsp;UTI&rsquo;s. Although clinical trials suggest that
   cranberries can&rsquo;t treat or cure a&nbsp;UTI, cranberries may help
   prevent&nbsp;UTIs&nbsp;in women with frequently recurring&nbsp;<a
   href="https://www.webmd.com/women/guide/your-guide-urinary-tract-infect
   ions#1" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>infections</b>.&nbsp;</a></p>
   <p>If any pain last more than 24 hours, please see your
   doctor.</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">boiling water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">almond extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pkg.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cut-up candied cherries or chopped
   pecans</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">drop red or green food coloring -
   optional</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54171-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   dry frosting mix, corn syrup, water and almond extract in small mixer
   bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54171-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat on
   high speed until stiff peaks form; about 5 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54171-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer to large mixer bowl; blend in sugar gradually on low
   speed or by hand.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54171-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   cherries or chopped pecans and food coloring if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54171-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using
   piping bag to make swirls and drop onto waxed paper. When candies feel
   firm, turn and dry at least 12 hours. Store in airtight
   container.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 5 to 6 dozen candies.</span><div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display: block;">Can be frozen
   in airtight container up to 2 months.</span></div></div>

   strawberries you will LOVE this recipe. Two layers of cake then topped
   off with a sweet jello strawberry topping. Easy to make for a Holiday
   favorite."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Jello-Stra
   wberry-Dessert.jpg 564w,

   564px"><strong>Jello Strawberry Dessert.</strong>&nbsp;If you like

   off with a sweet jello strawberry topping. Easy to make for a Holiday
   favorite.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-54167"

   /></div> </div> <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/54167"

   wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal"
   data-recipe-id="54167" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg
   xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
