   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Jello Strawberry Dessert</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sticksunsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">largeeggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large package strawberry jello
   mix.</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups fresh or frozen
   strawberries.</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   and flour two 8 inch square pans.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl whisk the flour and baking powder to combine, set aside
   for later.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cream
   the butter with the paddle attachment in your mixer, gradually add the
   sugar and beat until light and fluffy 2 to 3 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs one at a time blending after each to incorporate.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   vanilla to the l cup of milk. Add the flour mixture alternately with
   the milk to the butter, sugar, egg mixture. Begin and end with the dry
   ingredients. Add the dry 3 times and milk twice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 degrees for about 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out
   clean.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   cakes completely</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   strawberry jello according to package directions. Place in refrigerator
   for about 30 minutes or until almost set. Remove from refrigerator and
   stir in strawberries. Return to refrigerator until completely
   set.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54167-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cooled cakes on top of each other and then spread the jello mixture on
   top. Refrigerate until ready to serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   Peppermint Shortbread Cookies are the perfect addition to your holiday

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">One refrigerated pie crust</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened as directed on
   package.</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold"> For the
   Filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">medium apples</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">pealed and cut into thin
   slices</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon
   juice</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Meringue:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg whites</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream of tartar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oven to 425F. Place 1 pie crust in ungreased 9-inch glass pie plate.
   Press firmly against side and bottom.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   large bowl, gently mix filling ingredients; spoon into crust-lined pie
   plate.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 30
   to 40 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is golden
   brown.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool on
   cooling rack at least 1 hour.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">To make the
   Meringue:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   eggs from the refrigerator and separate, as they will separate best
   cold.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   egg whites to reach room temperature to allow them to whip to their
   fullest.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   eggs whites into a spotlessly-clean bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whip
   the egg whites until they are glossy and smooth, then add the cream of
   tartar to help the egg whites hold their form.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add the sugar to the egg whites.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54119-step-2-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   meringue on top of cooled pie, place about 4 inches under the heat and
   bake for about 10 minutes, until golden.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:
   #ff0000;"><strong>You might also enjoy these mini pies:
   </strong></span></p> <p><div id="attachment_54122" style="width: 610px"

   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Mini-Bourbon-
   Vanilla-Sweet-Potato-Pies.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Mini-Bourb
   on-Vanilla-Sweet-Potato-Pies.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Mini-Bourbon-Vanil
   la-Sweet-Potato-Pies-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Mini-Bourbon-Vanil
   la-Sweet-Potato-Pies-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><p id="caption-attachment-54122"
   class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Mini Bourbon Vanilla Sweet Potato
   Pies</strong>. Recipe <strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/mini-bourbon-vanilla-sweet-potato-pies/

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">One large orange with the insides
   scraped out.</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   candle:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Leftover unscented candles with
   some wax still left around the sides or bottom</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">New wicks from a craft
   store</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">A microwave safe container that you
   are comfortable tossing or using just for candles</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">A
   spoon</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut the
   orange in half and scrape the insides out with a spoon. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   spoon, dig out all of the wax from each candle.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Microwave wax in a microwave-safe dish in 1-minute increments at
   about 60% power. It will take about 4 minutes to melt down.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   wick in the sliced and scraped oranges.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   the wax is melted, hold on to the wick with one hand and slowly pour
   the wax into the orange with the other hand.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54114-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in the refrigerator for 10 minutes or until the wax has hardened.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54090-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   an 8 X 8 inch square pan generously. Grease it well or it will
   stick.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54090-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   medium bowl, stir together brown sugar, flour and <strong>finely
   crushed</strong> pecans.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54090-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl, beat the butter and eggs together. Stir in dry
   ingredients just until combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54090-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 15 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick placed in the center comes
   out clean. The time depends on how gooey you want the bars. The less
   time the more gooey.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div

   frozen</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For Orange
   Glaze:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh orange
   juice</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">orange
   zest</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Loaves:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Spray 2 (9x5-inch) loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray.
   Dust each pan with 1 tablespoon sugar. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until creamy.
   Gradually add remaining 2 and 1/4 cups sugar, beating until light and
   fluffy. Add eggs, one at time, beating well after each addition. Add
   vanilla, beating to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   another bowl, sift together 2 cups flour, cornmeal, baking powder,
   cinnamon, salt, and nutmeg. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating
   just until combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Toss
   cranberries with remaining 2 tablespoons flour. Gently fold into
   batter. Spread batter in prepared pans, smoothing top.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 1 hour. (Do not open oven door while loaves are baking.) Let cool
   in pans for 10 minutes. Invert onto a wire rack, and let cool
   completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   Orange Glaze over each loaf, and sprinkle with orange zest.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For Orange Glaze:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54077-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, whisk together confectioners' sugar and orange juice until
   smooth.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 2 (9x5 inch loaves)</span></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mixed dried fruit</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dark corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sweet sherry wine</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">beaten lightly</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">self-rising flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pumpkin pie spice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">blanched almonds</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">additional cup sweet sherry
   wine</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54042-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   dried fruit under cold water; drain well. Place fruit in a medium
   saucepan with butter, syrup, sugar and sherry; stir over medium heat,
   without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Remove from
   heat; stir in soda. Cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54042-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 300F. Grease a deep 8-inch round cake pan; line base and side
   with parchment paper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54042-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   or process cooled fruit mixture, in several batches, until smooth;
   transfer to a large bowl. Stir in eggs, sifted flours and spice. Pour
   mixture into pan; smooth surface. Decorate cake with nuts.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54042-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cake for 2 hours. Brush hot cake with additional sherry, cover with
   foil; leave cake in pan to cool.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">This cake will keep in an airtight container at
   room temperature for up to 10 days. Freeze for up to 3
   months.</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display:
   block;">You can make this eggless if you like; omit the eggs, and
   increase the corn syrup to 1/3 cup. The cake doesn't keep quite as well
   without eggs, about 5 days, but it will freeze for 3
   months.</span></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Christmas Chocolate Cake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">9</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces frozen seeded
   cherries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">self-rising flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground hazelnuts</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">buttermilk</span></li></ul></div><d
   iv class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the Hazelnut Ganache:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces milk
   chocolate</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Nutella</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chocolate hazelnut
   spread</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">hazelnut-flavored
   liqueur</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping
   cream</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Hazelnut Paraline:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">roasted
   hazelnuts</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">To make the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Working
   quickly, cut frozen cherries in half; return to freezer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   butter and eggs to room temperature.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 340F. Grease deep 9-inch round cake pan; line base and side
   with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above side.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter and sugar in small bowl with electric mixer until light and
   fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Mixture will curdle at this stage,
   but will come together later. Transfer mixture to large bowl; stir in
   sifted flours, ground hazelnuts, buttermilk and cherries. Spread
   mixture into pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cake about 2 hours. Let cake stand in pan 10 minutes before turning,
   top-side up, onto wire rack to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make
   Chocolate Hazelnut Ganache and Hazelnut Praline.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   cold cake with ganache; sprinkle with praline.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">To make the Chocolate Hazelnut Ganache:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Break
   chocolate into medium heatproof bowl; add Nutella and liqueur. Bring
   cream to a boil in small saucepan; pour hot cream over Nutella mixture,
   stir until smooth. Cover; refrigerate about 2 hours or until thick.
   Beat ganache with electric mixer until spreadable.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">To make the Hazelnut Paraline:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54038-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   sugar and the water in small saucepan over high heat, without boiling,
   until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil; boil, uncovered, without
   stirring, about 5 minutes or until caramel in color. Meanwhile,
   coarsely chop nuts. Add nuts to toffee, pour onto oven tray; stand at
   room temperature until set. Chop praline finely.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Makes 10
   servings.</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display:
   block;">Cake will keep in an airtight container, in the fridge, for up
   to 1 week. Freeze unfrosted cake for up to 3 months.</span></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   both;'> <script async

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Apple Cups Served With Maple Toffee Sauce</h2>
   <div class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Apple
   Cups:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Braeburn apples</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled, cored, and
   diced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Golden Delicious apples</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled, cored, and
   diced</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">17.3-ounce package frozen puff
   pastry, thawed</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Maple Toffee
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sweetened condensed
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple
   flavoring</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Apple
   Cups:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add apples, sugar,
   cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves. Cook, stirring often, until apples are
   tender, approximately 5 minutes. Add flour, stirring until thickened.
   Remove from heat, and let cool for 15 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375. Spray a 12-cup muffin pan with nonstick cooking
   spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, unroll 1 sheet puff pastry. With a rolling
   pin, smooth any seams. Using a 3 and 1/2-inch round cutter, cut 6
   rounds per sheet. Repeat with remaining puff pastry. Press rounds into
   bottoms and up sides of muffin cups.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until puffed and golden, approximately 6 minutes. Remove from oven.
   Using the back of a spoon, press down puffed bottoms of cups. Spoon
   apple mixture into cups.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until golden brown, approximately 6 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes
   before removing from pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   with Maple-Toffee Sauce.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Maple Toffee
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54014-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Add brown sugar, corn
   syrup, condensed milk, and 1 tablespoon water, stirring to combine.
   Bring to a simmer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add maple
   flavoring, stirring to combine. Serve warm or at room temperature.
   Refrigerate up to 3 days.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 12 Apple Cups and 2 cups maple toffee
   sauce.<br /> If you can't find Braeburn or Golden Delicious Apples
   others will taste almost as good.</span></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/christmas-rum-sponge-cake/ Tue, 23 Oct 2018

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53999 Christmas Rum Sponge Cake. Homemade
   dessert or appetizer recipe for... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/christmas-rum-sponge-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-54000 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Rum-Sponge-Ca
   ke.jpg" alt="" width="564" height="705" data-pin-description="Christmas
   Rum Sponge Cake. Homemade dessert or appetizer recipe for any Holiday.
   Serve in fancy glasses for a special treat for your adult guest.&nbsp;"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Rum-Sponge
   -Cake.jpg 564w,

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Christmas Rum Sponge Cake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Sponge
   Cakes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">active dry yeast</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raw sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 3/4 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raisins</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Rum
   Syrup:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">superfine sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla bean</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon sticks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">slices</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of a lime</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">slices</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of an orange</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dark
   rum</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Sponge
   Cakes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Warm
   milk in a small saucepan. Whisk yeast, warmed milk and sugar in a large
   bowl until combined. Cover; let stand in a warm place about 10 minutes
   or until frothy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sifted flour and eggs to yeast mixture; mix to a soft dough. Knead
   dough on a floured surface about 10 minutes or until smooth and
   elastic. Place in a lightly greased large bowl, cover; stand in a warm
   place about 1 hour or until doubled in size.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   four 12-hole, 1-tablespoon mini muffin pans.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   butter and raisins into dough; knead on a floured surface until
   combined. Roll 1 rounded teaspoon of dough into a ball and place each
   in a pan hole. Cover pans; stand in a warm place for about 1 hour or
   until doubled in size.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   cakes for 20 minutes or until browned lightly; cool in pans.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, make Rum Syrup. Instructions below.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cakes in a large heatproof bowl; pour over hot syrup. Let stand at room
   temperature 1 hour for syrup to soak in; refrigerate 1 hour before
   serving.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Rum
   Syrup:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54001-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   the water, sugar, vanilla bean, cinnamon sticks, lime and orange in a
   large saucepan over medium heat, without boiling, until sugar
   dissolves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, without
   stirring, 8 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in rum.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Makes 48 sponge
   cakes.</span></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">self-rising flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cocoa powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground
   almonds</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">24</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">creme de menthe baking
   chips</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">DARK CHOCOLATE
   GANACHE:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces dark
   chocolate</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 340F. Line 12-hole, 1/3-cup muffin pan with paper liners.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   chocolate and the water in a small saucepan over low heat until
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter, sugar and eggs in a small bowl with an electric mixer until
   light and fluffy. Stir in sifted flour and cocoa, then ground almonds
   and warm chocolate mixture. Drop 1/4 cups of mixture into paper
   liners.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 25 minutes. Stand cakes in pan for 5 minutes before turning,
   top-side up, onto a wire rack to cool. Make Dark Chocolate
   Ganache.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   mint baking chips in a small plastic resealable bag. Using rolling pin,
   gently tap baking chips to crush slightly. Spread cold cakes with Dark
   Chocolate Ganache; top with crushed chips.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">TO MAKE DARK
   CHOCOLATE GANACHE:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53997-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   cream to a boil in a small saucepan; remove from heat. Break chocolate
   into pan with hot cream; stir until smooth. Cool mixture to room
   temperature before beating or whipping to the desired
   consistency.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Cupcakes can be made 2 days ahead; store in an
   airtight container in a cool dry place.<br /> Decorate with crushed
   mint chips just before serving.<br /> Makes 12
   cupcakes.</span></div></div> </div></div></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   cutting board place the pie crust and cut a square. Slice each square
   into 1 inch long slices. Prick each slice with a fork. Set aside.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Sauce:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large sauce pan over medium heat, add the apples, butter, powdered
   sugar, cream cheese.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook,
   stirring occasionally for about 10-12 minutes or until apples slightly
   tender.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   white chocolate until melted. Set aside.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the dry ingredients in a bowl and stir together.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   pastry cutter, cut in the butter and then use your hands to finish
   mixing until well mixed.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   sauce on top of pie crust. Place topping and bake at 375 degrees for
   20-25 minutes or until golden and bubbling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53989-step-2-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">After
   baking sprinkle with extra sugar on top while warm if desired.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">crushed almonds</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CHEESECAKE
   FILLING:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unflavored gelatin</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups heavy whipping
   cream</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CRUST AND
   TOPPING:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 425F. Grease a 101/2-inch springform pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roast
   walnuts and pistachios on an oven tray for 5 minutes. Sprinkle nuts
   with pie spice; roast for 1 minute longer. Cool. Process spiced nuts
   with cookies until chopped finely; transfer to a medium bowl, stir in
   almonds.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reserve
   one-third of the nut mixture in a small bowl. Stir butter into
   remaining nut mixture. Press mixture evenly over base of tin;
   refrigerate for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, make Cheesecake Filling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   Cheesecake Filling into tin; top with reserved nut mixture. Cover;
   refrigerate overnight.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CHEESECAKE
   FILLING:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle gelatin over the water in a small heatproof measuring
   cup; stand cup in a small saucepan of simmering water.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   until gelatin dissolves; cool for 5 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53979-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese, sugar and honey in a medium bowl with an electric mixer
   until smooth; beat in cream, then stir in gelatin mixture.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-notes-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Cheesecake can
   be made a day ahead; keep covered in the refrigerator. Makes 16
   slices,</span></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><div
   id="attachment_53982" style="width: 610px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-53982"

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cherry and White Chocolate Cheesecake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-tags-container
   wprm-recipe-details-container wprm-recipe-details-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal" style=""><div class="wprm-recipe-tag-container
   wprm-recipe-keyword-container wprm-recipe-block-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container-columns wprm-block-text-normal"

   wprm-recipe-tag-label wprm-recipe-keyword-label">Keyword </span><span
