   recipe</span></div></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">12</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces chocolate graham
   crackers</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces white
   chocolate</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CHERRY
   SYRUP:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">9</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces frozen seeded
   cherries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 tablespoons
   butter</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   the cream cheese to room temperature.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 300F. Grease deep 8-inch round closed springform pan; line side
   with parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above side.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   butter. Process crackers until fine; add butter, process until
   combined. Press cracker mixture firmly over base of pan; refrigerate 30
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Break
   chocolate into small saucepan, add cream; stir over low heat until
   smooth. Cool completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese, sugar and egg in a small bowl with an electric mixer
   until smooth. Stir in cooled chocolate mixture. Pour mixture into pan;
   smooth surface.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the cheesecake about 1 hour. Cool in oven with the door ajar.
   Refrigerate cheesecake overnight.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make
   Cherry Syrup.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   cheesecake with Cherry Syrup.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">TO MAKE CHERRY
   SYRUP:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53983-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   ingredients in a medium saucepan over medium heat until mixture boils
   and thickens slightly. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, about 2 minutes.
   Cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 12 slices.</span></div></div>

   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Christmas Lemon Meringue Pie Shots</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-tags-container
   wprm-recipe-details-container wprm-recipe-details-container-columns
   wprm-block-text-normal" style=""><div class="wprm-recipe-tag-container
   wprm-recipe-keyword-container wprm-recipe-block-container
   wprm-recipe-block-container-columns wprm-block-text-normal"
   style=""><span class="wprm-recipe-details-label wprm-block-text-bold
   wprm-recipe-tag-label wprm-recipe-keyword-label">Keyword </span><span
   class="wprm-recipe-keyword wprm-block-text-normal">dessert, pie
   shots</span></div></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">gingersnap cookies</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">13</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 ounces store-bought lemon
   curd</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg whites</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53972-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Process
   cookies until fine crumbs form. Divide crumbs between twelve 1/3-cup
   shot glasses. Spoon curd into a pastry bag; pipe curd into
   glasses.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53972-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   egg whites and sugar constantly in a small saucepan over low heat for 2
   minutes or until mixture reaches 125"F. Transfer to a small bowl; beat
   or whisk with an electric mixer on high speed for 10 minutes or until
   firm peaks form and sugar is dissolved. (See Notes).</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53972-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   meringue into a clean pastry bag fitted with a 1/2-inch plain round
   tip. Pipe meringue on top of the curd. Using a kitchen torch, lightly
   toast meringue until golden.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">This recipe can be made up to 2 days ahead;
   refrigerate until needed.<br /> To test if sugar has dissolved in the
   meringue, rub a small amount of meringue between your thumb and finger;
   you will be able to feel if there are any undissolved sugar grains.
   Heating the meringue mixture stabilizes it and prevents the meringue
   from weeping after standing.</span><div class="wprm-spacer"></div>
   <span style="display: block;">Yields 12.</span></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">slices</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Canadian bacon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">English muffins</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">split and toasted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">poached</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Hollandaise
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg yolks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 to 3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dash of salt and
   pepper</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped green onion for
   garnish</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   brown Canadian bacon in a skillet. Remove from pan and set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Split
   and toast the English Muffins.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">To poach the
   eggs:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill a
   saucepanwith several inches of water. Heat the water on high until it
   reaches a boil and then lower the heat until the water is at a bare
   simmer.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Crack
   eggs into a small bowl. Working with the eggs one at a time, crack the
   egg into a small bowl or cup. Place the bowl close to the surface of
   the hot water and gently slip the egg into the water.Turn off the heat
   and cover the pan. Set atimer for 4 minutes. At this point the egg
   whites should be completely cooked, while the egg yolks are still
   runny.Gently lift the poached eggs out of the pan with a slotted spoon
   and place on top of the English Muffin and Canadian Ham.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the Hollandasie Sauce:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the butter in a small pan and melt it over a low heat. (Don't allow the
   butter to brown and turn off the heat as soon as the butter is just
   melted.) Addthe egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and pepper.Blend the egg
   yolk mixture for a minute with a blender. Slowly pour over the hot
   melted butter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   over the Muffin, ham and eggs.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53945-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with chopped green onions if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Yields 4.</span></div></div> </div></div> </p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/4 cups all-purpose

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">frozen blueberries</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thawed</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, sift together flour, salt, baking</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">powder
   and sugar.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, beat together egg and milk.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   milk and egg into flour mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix in
   the butter and fold in the blueberries.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Set
   aside for 1 hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat a
   lightly oiled frying pan over mediumhigh heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour or
   scoop the batter into the pan, usingapproximately 1/4 cup for each
   pancake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brown
   on both sides and serve hot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53965-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   you favorite syrup over top.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">roasted
   pistachios</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53916-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   two 31/4-inch x 101/2-inch bar cake pans; line base and sides with
   parchment paper, extending the paper 2 inches above long sides.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53916-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   chocolate in a medium heatproof bowl over a medium saucepan of
   simmering water (don't let water touch the base of bowl); stir until
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53916-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   marshmallows, coconut, Turkish delight and nuts in a large bowl.
   Working quickly, stir in the melted chocolate; spread mixture into
   pans, pressing down to flatten.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53916-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until set, then cut into slices.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53916-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Rocky
   road can be made up to 1 week ahead; keep refrigerated in an airtight
   container.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">If you're making the rocky road for children,
   swap the Turkish delight for raspberry jubes; instead of almonds and
   pistachios, use the same quantity of red and green M&amp;Ms.</span><div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display: block;">Yields 36
   slices</span></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53892-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 450. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53892-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, cinnamon,
   and baking soda. Add buttermilk and melted butter to flour mixture,
   stirring to remove any large lumps. Add raisins, stirring to combine.
   Drop dough onto prepared baking sheet in 1/4 cupfuls.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53892-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool completely on
   pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53892-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, whisk together confectioners' sugar and cream. Drizzle over
   cooled biscuits</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   pistachios and orange zest</span></li></ul></div></div> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53885-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large saucepan, bring milk, rice, coconut milk, sugar, cardamom, orange
   zest, and salt to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring frequently
   (see notes). Reduce heat; simmer over medium-low heat, stirring
   occasionally, until rice is tender and mixture is thick and creamy,
   approximately 50 minutes. Stir in butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53885-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   pudding among four small serving dishes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53885-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Garnish
   with pistachios and orange zest, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53885-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   warm or seal in small mason jars.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">While rice mixture is coming to a boil, keep an
   eye on it because it can boil over very quickly.</span><div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <span style="display: block;">Yields 4
   servings.</span></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

   large bowl, combine flours, baking soda, and salt. Make a well in
   center of dry ingredients. Add cereal mixture to flour mixture,
   stirring just until moistened. Fold in pecans. Spoon batter into
   prepared muffin cups, filling three-fourths full.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53858-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 18 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.</div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/diy-home-remedies-for-spiders/ Wed, 10 Oct
   2018 14:08:42 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips
   Simple DIY Projects https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53845 DIY Home
   Remedies For Spiders. Most spiders will not bite... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/diy-home-remedies-for-spiders/">Continu
   e reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53846 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/DIY-Home-Reme
   dies-For-Spiders.jpg" alt="DIY Home Remedies For Spiders. Most spiders
   will not bite you and most spiders are not poisonous. But most of us do
   not want them in our home. Here are a few natural ways to get rid of
   them." width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/DIY-Home-R
   emedies-For-Spiders.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/DIY-Home-Remedies-
   For-Spiders-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/DIY-Home-Remedies-
   For-Spiders-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>DIY Home Remedies For Spiders</strong>. Most spiders
   will not bite you and most spiders are not poisonous. But most of us do
   not want them in our home. Here are a few natural ways to get rid of
   them.</p> <p>Fill a standard spray bottle with water and mix in 15 to
   20 drops of <strong>peppermint oil</strong>. Spray down all the cracks
   and corners of your house. They will run in the opposite direction.</p>
   <p>Mix equal parts <strong>white vinegar</strong> and water in a spray
   bottle. Apply it to any area in which spiders gather and spray it
   directly on any spider you see. Vinegar contains acetic acid, which is
   thought to burn and kill spiders upon contact.</p> <h4>Natural
   (Aggressive) Spider Repellent Spray Recipe</h4> <ul> <li>1 cup apple
   cider vinegar</li> <li>one teaspoon oil</li> <li>one cup pepper</li>
   <li>one teaspoon liquid dish soap.</li> </ul> <p><strong>Get a
   cat.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;Cats will chase anything that moves, making
   them natural spider repellents.</p> <p>Place <strong>Chestnuts</strong>
   along the baseboards in your home and along the window sills to prevent
   spiders from coming in.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Symptoms of a spider bite:</strong></p> <ol
   class="X5LH0c"> <li class="TrT0Xe">itching or rash.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">pain around the area of the bite.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">muscle pain or cramping.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">blister
   that&rsquo;s red or purple in color.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">sweating.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">difficulty
   breathing.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">headache.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">nausea and vomiting.</li> </ol> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>What to do if you are bitten by a spider:</strong></p>
   <ul> <li>Clean the wound. Use mild soap and water and apply an
   antibiotic ointment.</li> <li>Apply a cool compress. Use a cloth
   dampened with cold water or filled with ice. This helps reduce pain and
   swelling. If the bite is on an arm or leg, elevate it.</li> <li>Take an
   over-the-counter pain medication if needed. If the wound is itchy, an
   antihistamine (Benadryl, Chlor-Trimeton, others) may help.</li> <li>Get
   immediate medical attention if you have severe pain, abdominal cramping
   or a growing ulcer at the bite site. Or the person who was bitten
   isn&rsquo;t breathing.</li> </ul> <p><strong>Check out this <a
   href="https://www.termite.com/spider-identification.html"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">Spider Identification Guide</a>, with
   pictures of high risk spider and low risk
   spiders.</strong></body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole
   milk</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, combine brown sugar and cinnamon. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and sugar at medium speed with a mixer until
   creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add
   vanilla, stirring well to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt.
   Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating until blended.
   Shape dough into a disk, wrap in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at
   least 2 hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough to a 1/4-inch thickness. Trim to
   form a rectangular shape. Transfer dough to a piece of parchment paper.
   Sprinkle brown sugar mixture on dough to cover, and lightly press in
   place. Roll dough into a log, jelly roll style. Wrap log in plastic
   wrap, and refrigerate for 2 hours.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Unwrap
   dough. Cut into 1/4-inch-thick slices. Place 2 inches apart on prepared
   baking sheets.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until golden, 10 to 12 minutes per batch. Let cool on pans for 5
   minutes. Remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53868-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, combine confectioners' sugar and milk, stirring until
   smooth. Drizzle on cooled cookies.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Makes 36 cookies.</span></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of chicken broth</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Red Peppers</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">roasted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small jar
   Artichokes</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For Green
   Beans:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   2-3 tablespoons of olive oil in the pan and melt 3-4 tablespoons of
   butter over medium high heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wait
   for all the butter to melt and look foamy.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   chopped garlic.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let the
   garlic cook for 2 minutes and then add the green beans.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   them around and get them as flat as possible in the pan. Cooking them
   until they turn bright green.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   salt and pepper to taste.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   for a couple more minutes, stirring occasionally.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   chicken broth to cover them and stir. Let come to a rapid boil.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   them and turn the heat to medium low, venting the pan so steam can
   escape. Cook for 15-20 minutes or until most of the chicken broth has
   cooked out.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">To Roast Red
   Pepper:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   your oven to 450 degrees.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   the peppers and then cut them in half lengthwise.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut off
   the stem with a paring knife and scoop out all the seeds and
   membranes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the peppers cut side down on a rimmed baking sheet that has been lined
   with parchment paper.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roast
   the peppers in the pre-heated 450 degree oven for about 25 minutes; or
   until the skins are completely wrinkled and the peppers are charred,
   rotating the sheet if necessary for them to cook evenly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let the
   peppers cool for a minute or two, and then remove them from the baking
   sheet and place them in the back into the bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   the bowl with foil or a plate, and let cool for about 30 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the peppers are cool enough to handle, peel off the skins and discard
   them, dropping the peppers back into the green beans.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53870-step-1-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   jar of artichokes and simmer until everything is warm. Serve warm</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>More ways to cook Green
   Beans:</strong></span></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-roasted-green-beans-with-speci
   al-sauce/">Homemade Roasted Green Beans with Special
   Sauce</a>&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/crock-pot-ham-green-beans-and-potatoes/
   ">Crock Pot Ham, Green Beans and Potatoes</a></strong></p>
   <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/toasted-almond-green-beans/">Toasted
   Almonds Green Beans</a></strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/crispy-baked-green-bean-fries/">Crispy
   Bakes Green Bean Fries</a></strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/garlic-sauteed-green-beans/">Garlic
   Sauteed Green Beans</a></strong></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53879-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Flip
   each one over when well browned.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53879-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   each popper on a paper towel lined tray to drain excess grease.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53879-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with powdered sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53879-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   with maple syrup over top if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   An easy, delicious, low calorie... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/baked-cabbage-steaks/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Healthy Baked Cabbage
   Steaks</strong>. An easy, delicious, low calorie and crispy recipe.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64688 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Baked-Cabbage
   -Steaks-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Healthy Baked Cabbage Steaks. An easy, delicious,
   low calorie and crispy recipe."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Baked-Cabb
   age-Steaks-1.jpg 600w,

   ks-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,

   degrees</p> <p>Wash and remove outer leaves, trim stem off , cut 1 to 1
   1/2 inch steaks</p> <p>Brush both sides with olive oil</p> <p>Add
   garlic salt and pepper to both sides</p> <p>Bake 30 to 40 minutes.</p>
   <p>40 min if you want the edges to turn brown.</p>

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53803 size-full"

   -100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>Sh..T On A Shingle</strong>.</p> <p>The best gravy
   recipe to put on biscuits, french toast or bread for breakfast.</p>
   <p>Also called SOS.</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-53896"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="53896"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:
   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sh..T-On-A-Sh
   ingle-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sh..T-On-A
   -Shingle-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Sh..T-On-A-Shingle
   -450x450.jpg 450w,

   wprm-block-text-bold">Sh..T On A Shingle</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-recipe-summary
   wprm-block-text-normal">Gray for biscuits, mashed potatoes or
   hashbrowns</div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">All Purpose Flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Whole Milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Black Pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4.5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dried Beef</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat a
   skillet over medium heat. Add butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the butter is melted and begins to bubble add the flour and mix to
   combine. This makes a smooth paste.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Simmer
   the smooth paste for 2-3 minutes to cook away the raw flour
   taste.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   milk and stir or whisk to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   black pepper and the chipped beef to the white sauce and simmer 3-5
   minutes, stirring constantly, until thickened.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53896-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   over toasted bread, biscuits, or hashbrowns.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butterscotch morsels</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped
   walnuts</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53905-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Spray an8-inch square baking pan withnonstick baking spray
   with flour. Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53905-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, whisk togethermelted butter and brown sugar untilsmooth.
   Whisk in eggs and vanilla.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53905-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   another medium bowl, whisktogether flour, baking powder,and salt.
   Gradually add egg mixtureto flour mixture, stirring to combine.Gently
   stir in butterscotch and walnuts.Spread batter in prepared pan,
   smoothing top with an offset spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53905-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until golden brown anda wooden pick inserted in centercomes out clean,
   approximately20 minutes. Let cool completelyin pan on wire rack.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>More recipes using
   Butterscotch:&nbsp;</strong></span></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/butterscotch-swirl-cheesecake-bars/"><s
   trong>Butterscotch Swirl Cheesecake
   Bars&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></a><strong>A delicious blend
   of&nbsp;HERSHEY&rsquo;S Butterscotch Chips, cream cheese and walnuts on
   a graham cracker crust.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/butterscotch-apple-dip-printable-recipe
   -2/">Butterscotch Apple Dip</a>&nbsp;A recipe so simple yet so
   delicious.</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/butterscotch-haystacks-printable-recipe
   /">Butterscotch Haystacks</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;To enjoy in a snap, make them
   the microwave way.</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/butterscotch-pie-printable-recipe/">But
   terscotch Pie</a>&nbsp;It has a smooth, creamy filling made from real
   butterscotch that never goes out of style.</strong></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packages cream cheese</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 8-</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">container sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 4-</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bars white chocolate</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted and cooled</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 teaspoons vanilla
   extract</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canned pumpkin pure</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground ginger</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cumin</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon and nutmeg
   mixed</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pumpkin pie
   spice</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 300. Spray a 10-inch springform pan with nonstick baking spray
   with flour. Line bottom of part with parchment paper; spray again. Wrap
   bottom of pan tightly in aluminum foil. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans, toffee bits, and
   melted butter. Press into the bottom of prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar at medium-high speed with a
   mixer until smooth and creamy, about 5 minutes. Add eggs, one a time,
   beating just until combined after each addition. Add sour cream, white
   chocolate, and vanilla, mixing to combine. Reserve 1 and 1/2 cups
   batter. Pour remaining batter into prepared pan. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine 1 cup reserved batter, pumpkin, ginger, cumin,
   cinnamon - nutmeg mixture, and pumpkin pie spice. Pour over batter in
   pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drop
   remaining 1/2 cup batter by tablespoonfuls over pumpkin batter. Using a
   knife, create a swirl pattern in batter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cheesecake in a roasting pan, and place roasting pan in oven. Fill
   roasting pan with enough water to come halfway up sides of foil-wrapped
   springform pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 1 and 1/2 hours. Turn oven off. Leave cheesecake in oven with door
   closed for 2 hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   cheesecake from oven. Refrigerate for 24 hours.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53909-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Gently
   run a knife around the edge of pan to release cheesecake. Invert onto a
   cutting board. Remove parchment paper, and invert cheesecake onto a
   serving platter.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">quick-cooking oats</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">not instant</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped pistachios</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53935-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter, shortening, and sugar at medium speed with a
   mixer until creamy. Add vanilla, mixing well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53935-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl, combine flour, oats, 1/2 cup pistachios, and salt.
   Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well. Cover and refrigerate for
   1 hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53935-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53935-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   dough into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in remaining 1/2 cup pistachios to
   coat. Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53935-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until edges are lightly browned, 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer to wire
   racks, and let cool completely. Store in airtight containers at room
   temperature up to 5 days.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded cheddar
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt &amp; pepper to
   taste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Honey or maple syrup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 400.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   spray a muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Flatten
   and slightly stretch each biscuit so its large enough to be pressed
   into the muffin tin. Make sure to press the biscuit all the way up the
   sides of each muffin cup so that theres room for the egg without
   spillage.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Crack
   an egg into each biscuit and sprinkle with salt and pepper.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the cheese on top.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top off
   with bacon bits.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If you
   wish you can LIGHTLY scramble your eggs first.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 18-20 minutes. Start checking it at the 13-15 minute mark. When the
   whites are set, youre good.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-53954-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   with honey or maple syrup on top.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Yields 8</span></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground allspice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed dark brown sugar</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">You can substituted light brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">freshly grated orange zest</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">freshly grated lemon zest</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canola oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canned pure pumpkin
   puree</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">toasted pecans or walnuts,
   optional</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the Pumpkin
   Butter Cream Frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canned pure pumpkin
   puree</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">half &amp; half or
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4 to 1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans or walnuts</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional, for sprinkling on
   top</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Bread:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Position your oven rack in the middle of the oven, and preheat
   oven to 325 degrees. Grease and flour a 9 x 5 loaf pan; set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt, nutmeg, and allspice
   in a medium bowl and whisk until thoroughly combined; set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   another bowl, or bowl of an electric mixer, beat eggs on medium-high
   speed for two minutes or until lightened in color. Add the brown sugar,
   mixing for about 2 minutes, then the granulated sugar, mixing for about
   1 minute. Add the orange and lemon zests, if using, and beat for
   another minute. Scrape down the bowl as needed.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   in the canola oil with beater on medium-low. Reduce speed to low and
   add the pumpkin puree. Mix until thoroughly combined. Add the dry
   ingredients in two additions and blend for 10-15 seconds just until
   incorporated. Fold in the pecans using a rubber spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   the batter into your prepared loaf pan and bake for 60-65 minutes or
   until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool loaf in pan
   for 10 to 15 minutes, then remove and cool completely on a wire
   rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***If
   youre going to frost the loaf, you can make the frosting while the loaf
   is cooling</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Pumpkin Buttercream Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cream
   the butter, pumpkin puree, cinnamon, and vanilla, blending well. Add
   powdered sugar a cup at a time, blending well after each addition. Add
   half &amp; half or milk and blend well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***NOTE: This makes a very thick butter cream frosting. If you
   want a thinner, creamier frosting, add more half &amp; half or milk
   until you get the desired consistency.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-54211-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***After frosting the cooled pumpkin loaf, sprinkle with chopped
   pecans or walnuts if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53657 size-full"

   made to be served warm but can be refrigerated and served cold."
   width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/The-Best-G
   erman-Potato-Salad.jpg 600w,

   erman-Potato-Salad-150x150.jpg 150w,

   class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg
   xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
