   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pounds</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">red potatoes</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">used when boiling
   potatoes</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">12</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bacon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">apple cider vinegar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dijon mustard</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Freshly ground black
   pepper</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced fresh garlic</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped fresh
   parsley</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Mayonnaise</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Paprika to taste</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59649-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scrub
   potatoes and cut in fourths so that all potatoes are of approximately
   equal size. Place potatoes in a large pot and cover with cold water.
   Bring to a boil and stir in 1 teaspoon of salt. Reduce heat and simmer
   potatoes for 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender when stabbed
   with a fork. Drain water. Leaving potatoes in pot, return pot to
   still-hot and turn off burner. Leave lid off of pot and allow potatoes
   to steam dry for a few minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59649-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Set a
   large pot over medium heat and use kitchen shears over pot to cut bacon
   strips into approximately 1-inch pieces. Cook bacon, stirring
   occasionally, until crispy. Set aside. Once bacon is done, remove pot
   from stove and use a slotted spoon to remove bacon to a bowl while
   leaving bacon grease in the pot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59649-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To the
   bacon grease, slowly and carefully add vinegar, sugar, Dijon, salt, and
   pepper. Place pot back on burner, bring mixture to a simmer, and stir
   for a couple of minutes. Stir the minced garlic into the mixture and
   cook for 30 seconds to 1 minute, or until garlic starts to turn a light
   golden.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59649-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   pot from heat and toss in the sliced potatoes, gently mixing until
   potatoes have absorbed all of the liquid. Carefully fold in the cooked
   bacon pieces and chopped parsley. Add the mayonnaise and
   blend.&nbsp;Top with paprika if desired. Transfer potato salad to a
   serving dish and serve hot.&nbsp;Refrigerate if not serving
   immediately.&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script

   https://myhoneysplace.com/hamburger-steaks-with-onion-gravy/ Sat, 22
   Sep 2018 23:40:39 +0000 My Honeys Place Main Dishes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53646 Hamburger Steaks With Onion Gravy.
   This recipe is the very... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/hamburger-steaks-with-onion-gravy/">Con
   tinue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53648 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Hamburger-Ste
   aks-With-Onion-Gravy2.jpg" alt="Hamburger Steaks With Onion Gravy. This
   recipe is the very best tasting and so easy to make. You can even use
   the gravy over mashed potatoes.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Smothered Grown Beef Steaks With Onion Gravy.
   Easy and tasty recipe for a dinner meal "
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Hamburger-
   Steaks-With-Onion-Gravy2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Hamburger-Steaks-W
   ith-Onion-Gravy2-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Hamburger-Steaks-W
   ith-Onion-Gravy2-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>Hamburger Steaks With Onion Gravy.</strong> This recipe
   is the very best tasting and so easy to make. You can even use the
   gravy over mashed potatoes.</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 59645--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Hamburger Steaks With Onion
   Gravy</h2> <p> <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Hamburger-Ste
   aks-With-Onion-Gravy2-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul> <li>1 lb. ground
   beef</li> <li>1 egg</li> <li>1/3 cup bread crumbs</li> <li>1/2 tsp.
   black pepper</li> <li>1 tsp. salt</li> <li>1/2 tsp. onion powder</li>
   <li>1 clove garlic minced</li> <li>1 tsp. Worcestershire sauce</li>
   <li>1 Tbsp. oil</li> <li>1 1/2 cup thinly sliced onion</li> <li>2 Tbsp.
   all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 cup beef broth</li> <li>1/2 tsp. salt</li>
   </ul> </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol>
   <li>In a large bowl, mix together the ground beef, egg, bread crumbs,
   pepper, salt, onion powder, garlic, and Worcestershire sauce.</li>
   <li>Form into thick patties.</li> <li>Heat the oil in a large skillet
   over medium heat.</li> <li>Fry the patties and onion in the oil until
   patties are nicely browned.</li> <li>Remove the beef patties to a
   plate, and keep warm.</li> <li>Sprinkle flour over the onions and
   drippings in the skillet. Stir in flour with a fork, scraping bits of
   beef off of the bottom as you stir.</li> <li>Gradually mix in the beef
   broth. Season with seasoned salt. Simmer and stir over medium-low heat
   for about 5 minutes, until the gravy thickens. Turn heat to low, return
   patties to the gravy, cover, and simmer for another 15 minutes.</li>
   </ol> </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Check out more of <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/main-dishes/"
   rel="">Main Meal Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   wprm-block-text-bold">Greek Yogurt Cucumber Sauce</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Greek Yogurt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">juice of one lemon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic clove</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">medium cucumbers</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">seeded and diced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt for salting
   cucumbers</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped fresh
   dill</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Kosher salt and fresh ground black
   pepper to taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59641-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Peel
   cucumbers, then cut in half lengthwise and take a small spoon and
   scrape out seeds. Discard seeds. Slice cucumbers, then put in a
   colander, sprinkle on 1 Tablespoon salt, and let stand for 30 minutes
   to draw out water. Drain well and wipe dry with paper towel.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59641-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   food processor add cucumbers, garlic, lemon juice, dill, and a few
   grinds of black pepper. Process until well blended, then stir this
   mixture into the yogurt. Taste before adding any extra salt, then salt
   if needed.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59641-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in refrigerator for at least two hours before serving so flavors can
   blend.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59641-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">This
   will keep for a few days o</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59641-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">more in
   the refrigerator, but you will need to drain off any water and stir
   each time you use it.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg
   xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">How To Make The Perfect Pie Crust</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For a single
   pie shell or one 8 inch double pie crust:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups sifted all purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shortening</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 to 5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cold
   water</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For one 9 or 10
   inch double crust pie or one 8 or 9 inch lattice top pie:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sifted all purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shortening</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5 to 7</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cold
   water</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Sift
   together flour and salt. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or
   blending fork until pieces are the size of small peas.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   pastry extra tender and flaky, divide shortening in half. Cut in first
   half until mixture looks like corn meal. Then cut in remaining half
   until looks like small peas.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle 1 Tablespoon of the water over part of the flour mixture.
   Gently toss with a fork; push to one side of bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle next Tablespoon water over dry part; mix lightly; push to
   moistened part at side. Repeat until all is moistened. Gather up with
   fingers; form into ball. ( For two crust pie, divide dough for upper
   and lower crust. Form each in ball.)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface; flatten ball sightly and roll 1/8 inch thick.
   If edges split, pinch together. Always roll dough from center to edge.
   Using light strokes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To
   transfer pastry, roll it over rolling pin; unroll pastry over pie
   plate, fitting loosely onto bottom and sides. Trim 1/2 to 1 inch beyond
   edge; fold under and flute.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   baked pie shell is needed, prick bottom and sides well with a fork.
   Bake in very hot oven (450 degrees F.) 10 to 12 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   filling and crust are to be baked together, do NOT prick pastry. Pour
   in filling and bake as directed in pie recipe.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wrap
   any extra dough in aluminum foil or several thicknesses of waxed paper;
   store in refrigerator until needed.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59639-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   double crust pie:Prepare pastry as directed above. Fit the lower crust
   in pie plate. Slash upper crust with your own design. Trim lower crust
   even with the rim of the pie plate, moisten the edges. Add your
   filling, then add top crust; trim 1/2 inch beyond edge; tuck it under
   edge of the lower crust (this seals in the juice). Crimp edge. Bake as
   directed in your pie recipe.&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canned pumpkin puree</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter - melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Honey</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59637-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 450. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59637-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg,
   and cinnamon. Add pumpkin and melted butter, stirring well.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59637-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead 6 to 8 times until
   dough is smooth. Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Using a 2-inch round
   cutter dipped in flour, cut dough, rerolling scraps once. Place
   biscuits on prepared baking sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59637-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly golden, 10 to 12 minutes. Serve warm with honey, if
   desired.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59637-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">**Makes
   approximately 1 dozen biscuits.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/12-signs-of-an-unhealthy-relationship/ Sun,
   16 Sep 2018 13:52:00 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53572 12 Signs Of An Unhealthy
   Relationship. Good tips to know... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/12-signs-of-an-unhealthy-relationship/"
   >Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53574 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/12-Signs-Of-A
   n-Unhealthy-Relationship.jpg" alt="12 Signs Of An Unhealthy
   Relationship. Good tips to know that you might be in an unhealthy
   relationship.&nbsp;I&rsquo;m not referring to small arguments that
   resolve reasonably quickly with a compromise." width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/12-Signs-O
   f-An-Unhealthy-Relationship.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/12-Signs-Of-An-Unh
   ealthy-Relationship-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/12-Signs-Of-An-Unh
   ealthy-Relationship-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></strong></p> <p><strong>12 Signs Of An Unhealthy
   Relationship</strong>. Good tips to know that you might be in an
   unhealthy relationship.&nbsp;I&rsquo;m not referring to small arguments
   that resolve reasonably quickly with a compromise.</p> <p><strong>If
   you feel afraid of your partner:</strong>&nbsp; No one should feel
   afraid of the other person that they are close to. Fear is not only
   afraid of physical fear, but fear of falling apart, fear of
   abandonment, being hurt emotionally, loss of control of your
   relationship or chronic fear of insecurity.</p> <p><strong>Any Physical
   or VERBAL abuse:</strong> We all get into arguments from time to time.
   Sometimes we lose our cool and yell. It&rsquo;s all part of being
   human. But verbal abuse isn&rsquo;t normal, it can wear you down over
   time. Never accept physical or verbal abuse.&nbsp;When someone
   repeatedly uses words to demean, frighten, or control someone,
   it&rsquo;s considered verbal abuse.&nbsp;If you&rsquo;re being verbally
   abused, know that it&rsquo;s not your fault. Continue reading to learn
   more, including how to recognize it and what you can do next.</p>
   <p><strong>Acting strange:</strong>&nbsp;When your partner acts
   differently with you versus how they act when you&rsquo;re not around.
   Examples can be lying to you, purposely leaving you out or not telling
   you things, being two-faced, acting differently around friends, or
   cheating while in a relationship with you.</p> <p><strong>They make
   excuses for their behavior</strong>. Examples can be blaming you, other
   people or past experiences for their actions, using alcohol or drugs as
   an excuse, using mental health issues or past experiences (like a
   cheating ex or divorced parents) as a reason for unhealthy
   behavior.</p> <p><strong>Too much pressure:</strong> Making you feel
   responsible for their happiness, making you feel like everything is
   your fault, threatening to hurt themselves or others if you don&rsquo;t
   do as they say or stay with them, pressuring you to do anything sexual
   you&rsquo;re not comfortable with. Telling you what to wear, who to
   talk to, what you can or can not do, or&nbsp;making you miss work,
   school or practice.</p> <p><strong>Making you feel bad about
   yourself.</strong>&nbsp;They can be calling you names, making rude
   remarks about who you hang out with, your family or what you look like,
   and making fun of you &ndash; even if it&rsquo;s played off as just a
   joke.</p> <p><strong>Keeping you away from friends, family, or other
   people:</strong>&nbsp;When your partner makes you choose between them
   and your friends, insisting you spend all your time with them, making
   you question your own judgement of friends and family, and making you
   feel dependent on them for money, love or acceptance.</p>
   <p><strong>Fighting or arguing too much:</strong> We all argue with our
   partner. But when you see that your are arguing more than normal then
   you might be in an unhealthy relationship. When the arguments get
   overwhelming and too intense.</p> <p><strong>Sending you mixed
   messages:</strong> One minute they say &ldquo;I love you&rdquo; and
   then later say &ldquo;I hate you.&rdquo; Or do something trivially
   hateful to you and apologize later. Doing this more and more often.</p>
   <p><strong>Not attentive to your needs:</strong> Does not help you with
   the household chores, help take care of the children, or does not
   listen to you about how you are feeling.</p> <p><strong>Makes repeated
   threats to break up:</strong> When an argument gets too intense, just
   walk away. Take a break. If your partner is making threats to break up,
   take it seriously. It is usually a sign that they really mean it. It
   might be sooner or even later.</p> <p><strong>You find you are doing
   more things apart than you are doing together.</strong>&nbsp;Remember
   when you use to go to the movies together? Try to get your partner to
   be the same person you met. Go places together, play games together.
   Sit down and have a talk, talk about things that happened today, what
   you did, what the children did or anything you are feeling.</p>
   <p><strong>Trust your instincts. Don&rsquo;t live in a relationship
   that is full of fear. There is a life after breaking
   up.&nbsp;</strong></body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53558 3 Easy Microwave Treats. Recipes
   includes a carrot cake, a... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/3-easy-microwave-treats/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53559 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/3-Easy-Microw
   ave-Treats.jpg" alt="3 Easy Microwave Treats. Recipes includes a carrot
   cake, a sweet treat, and a chocolate marshmallow peanut butter treat.
   The best desserts for a perfect party." width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/3-Easy-Mic
   rowave-Treats.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/3-Easy-Microwave-T
   reats-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/3-Easy-Microwave-T
   reats-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></strong></p> <p><strong>3 Easy Microwave Treats</strong>.</p>
   <p>Recipes includes a carrot cake, a sweet treat, and a chocolate
   marshmallow peanut butter treat. The best desserts for a perfect
   party.</p> <p><div id="attachment_53561" style="width: 416px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-53561" class="wp-image-53561
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture4.jpg"
   alt="" width="406" height="279"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture4.j
   pg 406w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture4-400x275.j
   pg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture4-150x103.j
   pg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 406px) 100vw, 406px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-53561" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Carrot
   Cake</strong>: 2 cups grated carrots, 1 cup self rising flour, 3/4 cup
   brown sugar, 2 Tablespoons ground cinnamon, 1/2 cup vegetable oil, and
   2 eggs. Mix well and place in glass square bowl. Microwave 8 minutes on
   medium heat. Top with your favorite frosting.</p></div></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div id="attachment_53563" style="width: 477px"
   class="wp-caption aligncenter"><img
   aria-describedby="caption-attachment-53563" class="wp-image-53563
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture5.jpg"
   alt="" width="467" height="273"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture5.j
   pg 467w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture5-400x234.j
   pg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture5-150x88.jp
   g 150w" sizes="(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-53563" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Sweet
   treat:</strong> 1 cup salted butter, 1 can condensed milk, 1 cup brown
   sugar, 4 cups sugar. Mix and microwave for 8 minutes (in 2 minute
   bursts). Add 1 Tablespoon vanilla extract. Pour on cookie sheet covered
   with waxed paper. Chill.</p></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div
   id="attachment_53564" style="width: 491px" class="wp-caption
   aligncenter"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-53564"
   class="wp-image-53564 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture7.jpg"
   alt="" width="481" height="368"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture7.j
   pg 481w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture7-400x306.j
   pg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Capture7-150x115.j
   pg 150w" sizes="(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px"><p
   id="caption-attachment-53564" class="wp-caption-text"><strong>Chocolate
   Marshmallow Peanut Butter Treat:</strong> 5 cups chocolate chips, 1 cup
   peanut butter. Mix and microwave in 30 second burst until melted. Add
   1/2 cup peanuts, 1 cup mini marshmallows, 1/2 cup broken graham
   crackers. Pour into square dish and chill.</p></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Low Calorie Mashed Cauliflower</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Parmesan cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Greek yogurt cream cheese or low
   fat cream cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">or to
   taste</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Optional for
   garnish:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dried parsley or 1 chopped green
   onion</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59633-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut the
   cauliflower into florets and place into a large pot. Add enough water
   to the pot to cover the florets. Bring the water to a boil over high
   heat, then reduce the heat and simmer, covered, for about 10-15
   minutes, or until a fork can easily pierce cauliflower. Once the
   cauliflower is tender, strain in a colander.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59633-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile, add the onion and garlic to a small pan. Saute over
   medium heat until golden brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59633-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   onion and garlic mixture to the large pot used to cook cauliflower,
   along with the cream cheese and parmesan. Use a handheld mixer to whip
   the garlic, onions, cream cheese, and parmesan together. Add
   cauliflower to the pot and mix with mixer until everything is well
   combined and smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59633-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use
   parsley or chopped green onion to garnish if desired.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plus 2 tablespoons confectioners'
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plus 1 Tablespoon unsweetened
   natural cocoa powder</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59631-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   work bowl of a food processor, combine flour, confectioners' sugar,
   cocoa, cinnamon, and salt. Pulse until combined. Add butter and
   vanilla, pulsing until smooth. Shape mixture into a disk; wrap in
   plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 2 hours.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59631-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven. to 350. On a lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4-inch.
   thickness. Using a 61/2-inch round cutter, cut rounds from dough. Press
   dough into bottom and up sides of 6 (41/2-inch) removable- bottom tart
   pans, trimming dough, if necessary.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59631-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   square piece of parchment paper in each shell, letting corners hang
   over sides. Fill each shell with pie weights.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59631-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for approximately 15 minutes. Remove pie weights and parchment paper.
   Let cool for approximately 15 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   light brown sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped crystallized
   ginger</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59629-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375. Spray a 13x9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking
   spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59629-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine 3 Tablespoons flour and sugar. Add pears and
   raspberries, tossing to coat. Pour into prepared baking dish.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59629-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, remaining 1/2 cup flour,
   ginger, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Using a pastry blender or your fingers,
   work butter into mixture until crumbly with pea-size pieces of butter
   remaining. Sprinkle over fruit.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59629-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packages cream cheese</span> <span

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher
   salt</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59627-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Spray 3 (9-inch) round cake pans with nonstick baking
   spray with flour. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59627-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and sugar at medium-high speed with a mixer
   until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add molasses, and beat until
   mixture is combined. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
   addition.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59627-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, whisk together flour, ground pecans, cinnamon, allspice,
   baking soda, nutmeg, and salt. Add flour mixture to butter mixture in
   thirds, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
   Add vanilla and ginger. Spoon batter evenly into prepared pans.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59627-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until layers are firm to the touch and a wooden pick inserted in center
   comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Let cool in pans for 10 minutes.
   Remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks. Spread Spice
   Cake Icing between layers and on top and sides of cake. Press chopped
   pecans up sides of cake as desired.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For Spice Cake
   Icing:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59627-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and cream cheese at medium high speed with a
   mixture until fluffy, approximately 5 minutes. Reduce speed to low. Add
   confectioners' sugar, vanilla, and salt, beating until mixture is well
   combined, approximately 6 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Spiced Cookies With Orange Marmalade</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">orange zest</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">prepared orange
   marmalade</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter, confectioners' sugar, orange zest, and vanilla
   at medium speed with a mixer until creamy.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, whisk together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, and salt.
   Slowly add flour mixture to butter mixture beating until combined.
   Divide dough in half, and wrap each portion in plastic wrap.
   Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Remove dough from refrigerator 15
   mint, before using.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll 1 dough portion to 1/4-inch thickness.
   Cut with a 2-inch fluted square cutter. Repeat process with remaining
   dough, rerolling scraps only once. Using a 3/4 - inch fluted round
   cutter, cut a circle in the center of half of cookies.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   2-inch squares on one prepared baking sheet, approximately 1 inch
   apart. Place 2-inch squares with cutouts on another prepared baking
   sheet. Sprinkle cookies evenly with sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until edges of cookies are lightly browned, 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool
   on pans for 1 minute. Transfer to wire racks, and cool
   completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   cookies have cooled, dust cookie with cutouts with confectioners'
   sugar. Spread approximately 1 teaspoon preserves on flat side of whole
   cookies. Top preserves with cookies with cutouts. Store in an airtight
   container up to 5 days.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59625-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Makes
   approximately 16 sandwich cookies&nbsp;</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">CINNAMON CHOCOLATE SWIRL POUND CAKE</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 4-</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bar semi sweet chocolate</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">and 1/2 cups butter-flavored
   shortening</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole buttermilk</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spray a
   10-inch tube pan with nonstick baking spray with flour. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, place chocolate. In a small saucepan, bring cream,
   confectioners sugar, butter, and corn syrup to a boil over medium-high
   heat. Pour hot cream mixture over chopped chocolate, whisking until
   melted and smooth. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, sift together flour, salt, and baking powder. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   another large bowl, beat shortening, sugar, and cinnamon at high speed
   with a mixer until light and fluffy, approximately 6 minutes. Reduce
   mixer speed to medium. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
   addition. Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, combine buttermilk and vanilla.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   flour mixture to shortening mixture in thirds, alternating with
   buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Pour half
   of batter into prepared pan. Pour chocolate mixture over batter. Using
   a butter knife, swirl chocolate mixture through batter. Pour remaining
   batter over chocolate mixture. Tap pan against counter to release any
   trapped air bubbles.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 45 minutes. Loosely cover cake with aluminum foil, and continue
   baking until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean,
   approximately 45 minutes more. Let cool in pan for 20 minutes. Remove
   from pan, and let cool completely on a wire rack.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59623-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   tightly covered at room temperature.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped toasted
   pecans</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375 degrees, Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, whisk together flour, cinnamon, ginger, baking soda,
   allspice, and cloves.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small skillet, melt 10 tablespoons butter over medium-high heat. Cook
   until butter is golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes. Transfer to a large
   bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   remaining 4 tablespoons butter, and stir until melted.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sugars, vanilla, and salt to butter, stirring to combine. Add egg and
   egg yolk, whisking until well combined, 3 to 4 minutes. Add flour
   mixture to butter mixture, stirring with a wooden spoon until well
   combined. Add chocolate and pecans, stirring just until combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scoop
   dough by heaping table- spoonfuls, and roll with hands to form balls.
   Place dough at least 2 Inches apart on prepared baking sheets.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59621-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until edges are golden brown and cookies are puffy, 8 to 14 minutes.
   Remove from pans, and let cool completely on a wire rack.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59613-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350. Spray 4 to 6 (2-cup) individual baking dishes with
   nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59613-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, toss apple slices with lemon juice. In a small bowl,
   combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Add brown sugar
   mixture to apples, tossing to combine. Divide apple mixture evenly
   among prepared baking dishes, mounding, if necessary. Dot tops of
   apples with butter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59613-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 25 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59613-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine flour, oats, brown sugar, walnuts, and salt for
   topping. Add melted butter, stirring until incorporated. Crumble
   topping evenly over baked apples.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59613-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Increase oven temperature to 375. Return apples to oven, and bake
   until top is browned and apples are bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.
   Remove from oven, and let cool slightly on a wire rack. Drizzle with
   maple syrup just before serving.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53425 Aroma Therapy Hacks. DIY tips that
   you can use daily... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/aroma-therapy-hacks/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53426 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Aroma-Therapy
   -Hacks.jpg" alt="Aroma Therapy Hacks. DIY tips that you can use daily
   in your home. Want your home to smell good?" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Aroma-Ther
   apy-Hacks.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Aroma-Therapy-Hack
   s-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Aroma-Therapy-Hack
   s-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></strong><br /> <strong>Aroma Therapy Hacks.</strong> DIY tips
   that you can use daily in your home.</p> <p>Listen to post:<br />
   <iframe
   src="https://anchor.fm/gone-now/embed/episodes/Aroma-Therapy-Hacks-e25o
   46" width="400px" height="102px" frameborder="0"
   scrolling="no"></iframe></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Want your home to smell good? </strong></p> <p>Grab
   some lemon, vanilla extract, and rosemary. Throw them in your crock
   pot. Add a little water, then turn it on low. Your home will smell
   fantastic, but not overpowering.</p> <p>Place vanilla scented tea light
   in bowl of coffee beans. The warmth of the candles will heat up the
   coffee bean and make your home smell like french vanilla coffee.</p>
   <p>Spices and savory candles scents match well in the kitchen, like
   cinnamon, clove, or cardamom.</p> <p>Make your house smell like spring.
   Take 2 lemons (sliced), 3 to 4 sprigs of thyme, 1/2 teaspoon mint
   extract, and 1 teaspoon vanilla extract. Fill a pot on your stove with
   water and simmer.</p> <p>Use lemon-Scented Pledge. It can be used on
   wood and stainless steel, so try wiping down your furniture and
   appliances with this product before visitors arrive. Makes your home
   smell so delicious.</p> <p>Placing fresh flowers around your home will
   give the whole house a fresh smell.</p> <p>Make your won aroma
   beads.<strong> Instructions <a
   href="http://www.bittercreeksouth.com/aroma_beads_instructions.htm"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">HERE&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p>Cooking
   cabbage and stinking up the house? Add a bay leaf. This will reduce the
   smell during cooking and give it a subtle flavor.</p> <p>Run half a
   lemon through the garbage disposal once a week. It lubricates the
   blades while giving the sink and kitchen a fresh, lemony scent.</p>
   <p>Fresh-baked cookies or BREAD makes your home smell warm and
   inviting. So cook away before guest arrive.</p> <p>To create a homey
   atmosphere, put some cinnamon spice in a pot with water and boil.
   Or&nbsp;cinnamon and orange peels simmering on the stove!</p> <p>Use
   cinnamon or vanilla beans in a pot of simmering water or a small crock
   pot. The scent lasts as long as the water does, so make sure you keep
   adding a little water every few hours. And they are not as overpowering
   as some of the candles people burn. When the scent is too strong,turn
   it off.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Want to relax?
   </strong></p> <p>Citrus scents, especially orange essential oil, will
   help you relax. Just rub a few drops on the palm of your hand and take
   a deep breath. Stress be gone!</p> <p>Use aroma therapy with your bath.
   Add coconut and rose water to a warm bath. Soak for 20 minutes. Not
   only will it help you relax but will make your skin feel softer and
   smell luscious.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Want to
   sleep better at night? </strong></p> <p>Place a few drops of lavender
   oil on a tissue and place it inside your pillow case before going to
   bed. You will drift off to sleep with sweet dreams!</p> <p>Use calming,
   sleep inducing scents in the bedroom. Use a vanilla candle. Other
   recommendations for a bedroom include eucalyptus mint scented candle,
   lavender, jasmine, sandalwood or chamomile.</body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole buttermilk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 15</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can pumpkin puree</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 14</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">can sweetened condensed
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground
   ginger</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line 2
   (9 inch) pie platters with piecrust. Fold edges under, and crimp as
   desired. Set aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, beat sugar, butter, and flour together until fluffy. Add 2
   eggs, buttermilk, and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla, beating well to combine.
   Pour into prepared crust.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine pumpkin, condense milk, remaining 2 eggs,
   remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla, cloves, nutmeg, and ginger, stirring
   until blended. Pour over cooked buttermilk layer.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 35 minutes or until set. Let cool completely on wire racks.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59609-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with ice cream or whipping cream if desired.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2 15</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cans pumpkin puree</span></li><li

   cream</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
