   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground coriander</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cardamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Frozen nondairy whipping
   topping</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thawed</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   work bowl of a food processor, combine graham cracker, sugar, chili
   powder, and salt. Pulse until mixture is finely ground. Add melted
   butter and egg white, pulsing until crumbly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   mixture into bottom and up sides of a 10 inch deep dish pie plate, or
   removable bottom tart pan. Line crust with parchment paper; add pie
   weights.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 15 minutes. Remove from oven, and let cool. Remove pie weights and
   parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, beat pumpkin and marshmallow cream at medium high speed
   with a mixer until smooth, approximately 3 minutes. Add confectioners'
   sugar, coconut milk, orange zest, pumpkin pie spice, vanilla,
   coriander, cardamon and salt, beating to combine. Pour mixture into
   prepared crust.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until set, approximately 1 hour. Transfer to a wire rack, and let cool
   for at least 1 hour. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving. Top with
   whipped topping.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59619-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   Makes 1 (10 inch) deep dish pie</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/what-your-tongue-might-be-telling-you-about-y
   our-health/ Tue, 04 Sep 2018 13:21:42 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing
   Information Health How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53375
   What Your Tongue Might Be Telling You About Your Health.... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/what-your-tongue-might-be-telling-you-a
   bout-your-health/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC
   "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN"
   "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br /> <html><body><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53376 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-Your-Ton
   gue-Might-Be-Telling-You-About-Your-Health.jpg" alt="What Your Tongue
   Might Be Telling You About Your Health. Let's take a look at what your
   tongue is telling you.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-Your-
   Tongue-Might-Be-Telling-You-About-Your-Health.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-Your-Tongue-M
   ight-Be-Telling-You-About-Your-Health-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/What-Your-Tongue-M
   ight-Be-Telling-You-About-Your-Health-100x150.jpg 100w"
   sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><strong>What Your Tongue Might
   Be Telling You About Your Health.</strong> Let&rsquo;s take a look at
   what your tongue is telling you.</p> <p><strong>A&nbsp;healthy
   tongue</strong>&nbsp;should be pink and covered with small nodules
   (papillae). Any deviation from your&nbsp;tongue&rsquo;s
   normal&nbsp;appearance, or any pain, may be cause for concern.
   A&nbsp;number of diseases can show up on your tongue.</p>
   <p><strong>Bright Red Tongue:</strong></p> <p>Could mean you have a
   vitamin deficiency. A glossy, bright red tongue may be a sign your body
   is lacking iron or B12.</p> <p><strong>Brown or Black
   Tongue:</strong></p> <p>Could mean you don&rsquo;t have the best oral
   hygiene or tongue health. May look nasty but not really a health
   concern. But can cause bad breath or taste abnormalities. Removing the
   offending cause, like smoking, and brushing the tongue or using a
   tongue scraper, may be all you need.</p> <p><strong>Lumpy White Coated
   Tongue:</strong></p> <p>Could mean you have a yeast infection. Also
   called&nbsp;Thrush, which might cause taste disturbances or a bit of
   pain, can also occur in those with weakened immune systems. Usually
   happens after taking an antibiotic.&nbsp;A salt water rinse to help
   ease the symptoms of the yeast infection and clean out the
   mouth.&nbsp;If you suspect you might have thrush, see your doctor.</p>
   <p><strong>Wrinkles On Your Tongue:</strong></p> <p>As we get older we
   many get wrinkles in our tongue, which is natural.&nbsp;Fissures and
   cracks in the tongue are typically harmless, but problems can arise if
   poor dental hygiene leads to infection within the crevices.</p>
   <p><strong>Small White Patches:</strong></p> <p>It may mean something
   is irritating your mouth. If they don&rsquo;t go away in a week or two,
   it&rsquo;s extremely important to see your dentist, who might recommend
   a biopsy.</p> <p><strong>Burning Sensation:&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>It
   may mean you are in&nbsp;postmenopausal, or using the wrong toothpaste.
   Try toothpaste like Sensodyne.</p> <p><strong>Painful
   Sores:</strong></p> <p>May mean your are stressed. Also called canker
   sores usually subside and eventually disappear within two
   weeks.&nbsp;They&rsquo;re not contagious. Just make sure it&rsquo;s not
   a <strong>cold sore</strong>, which is an extremely contagious sore
   (caused by the herpes simplex virus) that typically appears on the
   lips.&nbsp;Canker sores&nbsp;appear on the soft tissues inside the
   mouth, while a&nbsp;cold sore&nbsp;usually shows up on the outside of
   the mouth. A&nbsp;canker sore&nbsp;is an ulcer and a&nbsp;cold
   sore&nbsp;is a blister.</p> <p><strong>Red Lesions&nbsp; or
   patches.</strong><br /> It could mean you have tongue cancer. Be sure
   to read:&nbsp; <a
   href="https://www.rd.com/health/conditions/oral-cancer-symptoms/1/"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">13 Silent Signs of Oral Cancer You
   Shouldn&rsquo;t Ignore</a></p> <p>Always check with your doctor or
   dentist if you have problems with your tongue. While most problems can
   be solved over time some can mean very severe
   problems.</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   <div class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pumpkin pie spice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground ginger</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">canned pumpkin
   puree</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mildly sweet chocolate
   morsels</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">such as Hersey's Special
   Dark</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">natural unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F. Line 18 muffin cups with paper liners.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until creamy. Add
   sugars, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
   addition.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, sift together flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda,
   baking powder, salt and ginger. Gradually add to butter mixture,
   beating to combine. Add pumpkin, beating well. Divide batter among
   prepared cups.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean, 18 to 20
   minutes. Let cool in pans for 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from pans, and let
   cool completely on a wire rack.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pipe or
   spread chocolate frosting onto cooled cupcakes.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until
   creamy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   microwavable bowl, microwave chocolate morsels on High, in 30 second
   intervals, stirring between each, until melted, approximately 1 minute
   total. Add chocolate to butter, beating well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Gradually add confectioners' sugar and cream to butter mixture.
   Add cocoa powder, beating well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59607-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Makes about 18 cupcakes</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground ginger</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cloves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59605-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59605-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a 10
   inch cast iron skillet, place apple slices for filling, sprinkle with
   flour and salt. Drizzle with apple and lemon juice, tossing to combine.
   Scatter diced butter over apple mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59605-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon, ginger,
   clovers and salt for topping, add butter. Blend with fingertips until
   mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over apple mixture.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59605-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until oat mixture is lightly browned and filling is bubbly,
   approximately 30 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes before
   serving.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59605-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   Makes approximately 4 servings.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners' sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely chopped
   peacans</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">semisweet chocolate morsels</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chocolate covered toffee
   bits</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until
   creamy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine flour, confectioners' sugar and corn starch. Add
   flour mixture, cream, vanilla, and pecans to butter, beating until well
   combined. Wrap dough in plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 2
   hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness. Using a 2
   inch square cutter, cut out dough, rerolling scraps twice. Place 1 inch
   apart on prepared baking sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly browned, 12 to 14 minutes. Let cool on pans for 2
   minutes. Remove from pans, and let cool completely on wire racks.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   half of each cookie in melted chocolate, and place on baking sheet
   lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle toffee bits on top of chocolate.
   Let stand until chocolate is set, approximately 1 hour. Store in
   airtight container up to 5 days.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59617-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-treat-brain-fog/ Sun, 02 Sep 2018
   12:03:25 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips Health
   How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53357 How To Treat Brain
   Fog. Do you have brain fog?... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-treat-brain-fog/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53358 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/How-To-Treat-
   Brain-Fog.jpg" alt="How To Treat Brain Fog. Do you have brain fog? Tips
   to treat your brain fog." width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/How-To-Tre
   at-Brain-Fog.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/How-To-Treat-Brain
   -Fog-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/How-To-Treat-Brain
   -Fog-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>How To Treat Brain Fog. </strong></p> <p>Do you have
   brain fog? Tips to treat your brain fog.</p> <p>Brain fog is not a
   medical condition. It is a symptom of other possible medical
   conditions. You may have memory problems, difficulty concentrating,
   mental confusion or unable to focus on the task at hand.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>Some of the causes might
   be:</strong></p> <p><strong>Menopause</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Treatment:&nbsp;Hormone supplements and
   other types of medication may help.</p>
   <p><strong>Depression</strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Treatment:&nbsp;Treatment for your depression, which includes
   medication and talk therapy, should help get you back on
   track.&nbsp;Trying something new alters the levels of dopamine, which
   is associated with pleasure, enjoyment, and learning.&nbsp;Plan things
   you used to enjoy, even if they feel like a chore.</p> <p><strong>Lack
   of sleep </strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Treatment:&nbsp;Sleep 7 to 9 hours a night.&nbsp;Try
   repeatedly tensing and releasing your toes to the count of 10. Avoid
   caffeine and alcohol before bedtime. Have a night time snack before
   going to bed. Cheese, omega-3-rich fish like tuna, sardines, or
   mackerel can get the job done, too. Or low fat milk, whole grain
   crackers, bananas and cherries.</p> <p><strong>Stress</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Treatment: Know your limitations of your
   stress level. Avoid excessive alcohol and caffeine.&nbsp; Natural
   remedies include passionflower, massage, mediation, exercise and B
   vitamins.</p> <p><strong>Hormonal changes</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Treatment: Blood test. Most hormones can be
   detected in the blood. A doctor can use a blood test to check your
   thyroid, estrogen, testosterone, and cortisol levels then possibly
   prescribe medications such as low dose estrogen therapy.</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Your diet</strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Treatment:&nbsp; increasing your intake of protein, fruits,
   vegetables, and healthy fats.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Foods that may cause your brain fog:</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Processed Meat.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Dairy. Many people are sensitive to dairy products like milk,
   cheese, and yogurt.</p> <p style="text-align: center;">MSG.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Alcohol.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Artificial Sweeteners.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>Foods that may help:</strong></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Nutritional Yeast.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Turmeric.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Spinach.</p> <p style="text-align: center;">Avocado.</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;">Eggs.</p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Celery.</p> <p style="text-align: center;">Rosemary.</p>
   <p><strong>Medications you take</strong></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;">Treatment: Some kinds of drugs ,over-the-counter and
   prescribed, can cause brain fog. If you take medicine and notice that
   your thinking isn&rsquo;t as clear as it should be or you suddenly
   can&rsquo;t remember things, call your doctor. Be sure to let him know
   all the medications you take.</p> <p><strong>Medical
   conditions</strong> associated with inflammation, fatigue, or changes
   in blood glucose level can also cause brain fog. This can include:
   chronic fatigue syndrome, anemia and depression.&nbsp;You should let
   your doctor know about other symptoms you might have.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Easy Chocolate Mayonnaise Cake</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of mayonnaise</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cocoa</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of
   water</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   two cake pans (9 x 1  ) and heat oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl mixed together the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and
   baking soda).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add in
   the mayonnaise and stir to combine. Slowly stir in the water.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Finally
   add in the vanilla extract and stir until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   mixtures equally into both pans.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 30 minutes or until you can insert a toothpick and have it come out
   clean. Remove from oven and allow to to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Finish
   with your favorite chocolate icing.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59603-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn
   syrup</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Crust:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 9 inch square baking pan with a piece of
   parchment paper large enough to slightly hang over sides of pan. Spray
   parchment paper with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, beat shortening, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with a
   mixer until light and fluffy, approximately 3 minutes. Add flour and
   salt, beating until combined. Press dough into bottom of prepared
   pan</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until light golden brown, approximately 25 minutes. Let cool
   completely.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">White caramel
   center:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan, bring butter, sugar, and corn syrup to a boil over
   high heat , stirring constantly. Boil until thickened, 8 to 10 minutes.
   Stir in salt and vanilla. Use immediately.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   caramel sauce over crust. Let cool until set, approximately 2
   hours.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate
   ganache:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, place chocolate. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small sauce pan, bring cream, butter, and corn syrup to a boil over
   high heat. Remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   hot cream mixture over chocolate, whisking until melted and smooth. Use
   immediately over cooled crust and caramel center. Refrigerate for 2
   hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   into bars. Garnish with sea salt, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate in a air tight container for up to 5 days.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59601-step-2-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   https://myhoneysplace.com/what-your-snot-can-tell-you/ Wed, 29 Aug 2018
   12:13:31 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How To and
   Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53344 What Your Snot Can Tell You.
   Ever wonder what the... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/what-your-snot-can-tell-you/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53345 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/What-Your-Sno
   t-Can-Tell-You.jpg" alt="What Your Snot Can Tell You. Ever wonder what
   the color of your snot means. It can tell you a lot of things.&nbsp;"
   width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/What-Your-
   Snot-Can-Tell-You.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/What-Your-Snot-Can
   -Tell-You-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/What-Your-Snot-Can
   -Tell-You-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></strong></p> <p><strong>What Your Snot Can Tell You</strong>.
   Ever wonder what the color of your snot means. It can tell you a lot of
   things.</p> <p>Snot is mucus from your nose.&nbsp;Typically, mucus is
   clear and thin and not noticeable at all. When someone gets sick with a
   cold or an infection, the mucus can become thickened and changes
   color.</p> <p><strong>Clear snot</strong> is normal. It consists of
   water, salts, antibodies and other immune system cells. After being
   produced in the respiratory tract, most of it goes down the back of the
   throat and is swallowed.&nbsp;Thin and watery snot is usually normal
   and indicates a healthy respiratory tract.</p> <p><strong>Brown
   snot</strong> may indicate possible bleeding, and if so, is likely to
   be caused by bleeding that happened a while ago. Bright red or pink
   phlegm means the bleeding has happened more recently.</p>
   <p><strong>Black snot</strong> may indicate the presence of a fungal
   infection. Someone who has black snot should contact their doctor
   immediately, especially if they have a weakened immune system.</p>
   <p><strong>White snot</strong> signals nasal congestion. When the nasal
   cavity is congested, the tissues are swollen and inflamed, which slows
   the passage of mucus through the respiratory tract. When this happens,
   the snot becomes thicker and cloudy or white.</p> <p><strong>Yellow
   snot</strong> suggests that immune cells are starting to work at the
   site of the infection or another type of inflammatory insult.&nbsp;You
   might have heard that&nbsp;yellow&nbsp;or green snot&nbsp;is a clear
   sign that you have an infection, but despite that common misconception,
   the&nbsp;yellow&nbsp;or green hue isn&rsquo;t due to bacteria. When you
   have a cold, your immune system sends white blood cells called
   neutrophils rushing to the area. So that can be a good sign.</p>
   <p><strong>Thick Green snot</strong>&nbsp;can point to an
   infection,&nbsp;antibiotics&nbsp;are&nbsp;not always needed. Most
   infections that lead to green phlegm are viral and usually resolve
   without treatment within a few weeks.&nbsp;A <strong>thick</strong>
   and&nbsp;dark yellow snot&nbsp;may be a sign of a viral or bacterial
   infection, sinus infection, or lower respiratory tract infection.</p>
   <p><strong>A</strong>&nbsp;<b>sinus infection</b>&nbsp;may be
   accompanied by other symptoms like:</p> <ul>
   <li>post-nasal&nbsp;drip,</li> <li>green (or
   yellow)&nbsp;nasal&nbsp;discharge,</li> <li>aching in your teeth,</li>
   <li>fever,</li> <li>bad breath,</li> <li>sinus pressure or a headache
   that worsens&nbsp;when you&nbsp;lean forward or lie down.</li> </ul> <p
   data-spx-slot="1"><strong>Pink and frothy snot</strong> can mean that
   someone is experiencing severe left-sided&nbsp;heart failure,
   especially when combined with any of the following symptoms:</p> <ul>
   <li>shortness of breath</li> <li>sweating</li> <li>chest pain</li>
   </ul> <p>Anyone experiencing these symptoms should head to their local
   emergency room immediately.</p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   0x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>Nuts
   are good sources of fat, fiber and&nbsp;protein. Most of the fat in
   nuts is monounsaturated fat, as well as omega-6 and omega-3
   polyunsaturated fat. However, they do contain some saturated fat.</p>

   magnesium and vitamin E.</p> <p>Besides Nuts make recipes taste

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Fried Pecan Pies</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cold butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5 to 7</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ice water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Garnish:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">natural unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   work bowl of a food processor, combine flour and salt, pulse 2 times.
   Add shortening and butter; pulse until crumbly, 4 to 5 times. Transfer
   mixture to a large bowl. Sprinkle ice water, 1 Tablespoon at a time,
   over dry ingredients, tossing with a fork just until moistened. Place
   dough on a slightly floured surface; gently knead until combined, 2 to
   3 times. Shape into a disk, and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate for
   30 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium sauce pan, bring brown sugar, corn syrup, 3 Tablespoons water,
   butter, and salt to a boil over medium high heat. Reduce heat to low;
   simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in pecans and vanilla. Let
   cool for 15 to 20 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough to approximately 1/8 inch
   thickness. Using a 3 1/2 inch round cutter, cut dough into 12 rounds,
   rerolling as necessary. Using a pastry brush, moisten edges of dough
   with water. Spoon 2 teaspoons pecan mixture into center of dough. Fold
   dough over; press edges with a fork dipped in flour to seal.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill a
   large deep cast-iron skillet halfway up with canola oil, Heat over
   medium high heat until a deep-fry thermometer reaches 350
   degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Gently
   place pies in hot oil. Fry in batches, turning occasionally, until
   golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes per batch. Adjust heat to maintain
   temperature at 350 degrees if necessary. Remove pies with a slotted
   spoon; drain on several layers of paper towels. Let cool for 10
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with sugar. Sift cocoa over pies, if desired.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59599-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Makes 1 dozen pies.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped sweetened dried
   cranberries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 425 degree F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   15x10 inch jelly roll pan with heavy aluminum foil. Spray foil with
   nonstick cooking spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Arrange
   saltines in an even layer on prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan, bring butter and brown sugar to a boil over medium
   high heat. Cook for 2 minutes. Remove from heat, and stir in condensed
   milk. Pour mixture over crackers.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with chopped white chocolate. Let stand for 1
   to 2 minutes to soften. Using a small offset spatula, spread softened
   chocolate evenly over baked toffee. Sprinkle with pecans and
   cranberries . Let cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Break
   toffee into cracker size pieces. Store in an airtight container for up
   to 5 days.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59615-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen pieces.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-53330 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Maple-Spiced-
   Walnuts.jpg" alt="Maple-Spiced Walnuts. Perfect snack appetizer for a
   holiday party or just sitting in front of your fireplace. " width="600"
   height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Maple-Spic
   ed-Walnuts.jpg 600w,

   ts-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Maple-Spiced-Walnu
   ts-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59635" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="59635"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Maple Spiced Walnuts</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground ginger</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 9-</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">inch</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sprig rosemary</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into thirds</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">walnuts</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium sauce pan, bring maple syrup, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, salt and
   rosemary to a boil over medium high heat. Add walnuts and cook,
   stirring constantly, until most of the liquid is evaporated,
   approximately 3 minutes. Discard rosemary.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   mixture onto prepared baking sheet. Using a large spoon, spread walnuts
   in an even layer, smoothing out any clusters.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake,
   stirring twice, until golden brown and bubbling, approximately 15
   minutes. Let cool on a wire rack until walnuts are dry and cool to the
   touch, approximately 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Break
   into cluster. Store in airtight container up to 1 week.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59635-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Makes about 3 cups</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   cloves</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mini
   marshmallows</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   work bowl of a food processor, combing pecans, graham cracker crumbs,
   brown sugar, and cinnamon for crust. Pulse until mixture is crumbly.
   Add melted butter, pulsing just until mixture is moistened. Press
   mixture into bottom and up sides of 5 (4 1/2 inch) removable bottom
   tart pans or 1 (9 inch) removable bottom tart pan. Place on baking
   sheet.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 10 minutes. Let cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine sweet potato, eggs, brown sugar, melted butter,
   cream, honey, cinnamon, nutmeg, and cloves for filling. Beat at medium
   speed with a mixer until combined. Divide mixture evenly among cooled
   crusts.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until filling sets, approximately 25 minutes for individual tarts or 35
   minutes for 9 inch tart. Remove from oven, and let cool on wire rack
   for 15 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Increase oven to broil. Arrange marshmallows on tarts. Broil,
   watching carefully, until lightly toasted, 1 to 2 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59597-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   Makes 5 (4 1/2 inch) tarts or 1 (9 inch) tart.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p><strong>How To cook sweet
   potatoes:</strong><br /> The humble sweet potato is packed with
   nutrition; is simple to bake in an oven, microwave, or cook on a grill;
   and can be seasoned with a variety of your favorite toppings as well as
   paired with other vegetables.</p> <p>Step 1: Select potatoes<br />
   Select fresh, firm, smooth, and plump sweet potatoes and wash them as
   you would other vegetables.</p> <p>Tip<br /> Cook sweet potatoes whole
   to benefit from nutrients found next to the skin.</p> <p>Step 2:
   Pierce<br /> Pierce your dry sweet potatoes a few times with a fork
   before baking or microwaving.</p> <p>Step 3: Place on pan and bake<br
   /> Place the sweet potatoes on a rimmed pan and bake at 375 degrees for
   about 45 minutes or until they are tender.</p> <p>Step 4: Quick-cook<br
   /> Quick-cook sweet potatoes by placing two clean, pierced potatoes in
   a microwave oven for five to nine minutes, or four sweet potatoes for
   10 to 13 minutes.</p> <p>Tip<br /> Sweet potatoes rank high among the
   healthiest of vegetables, providing vitamins A and C, potassium, and
   fiber.</p> <p>Step 5: Grill<br /> Grill sweet potatoes by first boiling
   them, letting them cool, and then slicing them lengthwise into eighths,
   oiling the slices, and grilling all sides until they&rsquo;re golden
   brown.</p> <p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QLlLnAZKl8Q"
   width="450" height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span data-mce-type="bookmark"
   style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden;
   line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></body></html></p>
   <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto;
   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/caramel-layer-cake/ Sun, 26 Aug 2018 12:11:33
   +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Holiday Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53319 Caramel Layer Cake. Delicious
   homemade 3 layer dessert cake recipe.... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/caramel-layer-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong>Caramel Layer Cake. </strong>Delicious homemade 3
   layer dessert cake recipe. Topped with a creamy caramel frosting, then
   garnished with pecans. Perfect for the Holidays.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53322 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-Layer
   -Cake.jpg" alt="Caramel Layer Cake. A 3 layer delicious dessert cake
   recipe. Topped with a caramel frosting and garnished with pecans.
   Perfect for the Holidays.&nbsp;&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Caramel Layer Cake. Delicious homemade 3 layer
   dessert cake recipe. Topped with a creamy caramel frosting, then
   garnished with pecans. Perfect for the Holidays."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-La
   yer-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-Layer-Cake
   -267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-Layer-Cake
   -100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>Caramel Layer Cake Recipe:</strong></p> <p><strong>For
   the people who would like to take a phone snap shot of the
   recipe:</strong></p> <div class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-color-header"></div> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 56828--></p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Caramel Layer Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-Layer
   -Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul> <li>Cake: 1 cup butter
   softened (2 cups sugar, 4 large eggs, 3 cups self-rising flour, 1 cup
   whole buttermilk, 1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract Caramel Frosting: 2
   cups sugar, 1/4 cup water, 2 Tablespoons light corn syrup, 1/2 cup cold
   butter- cubed, 1 cup hot heavy whipping cream (see note), 1 cup butter
   -softened, 6 cups confectioners sugar- sifted Garnish: toasted pecan
   halves)</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol>
   <li><strong>Cake:</strong> Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray 3 (9
   inch) round pans with nonstick cooking spray with flour. Line bottoms
   of pans with parchment paper; lightly spray again. In a large bowl,
   beat butter and sugar at medium speed with a mixer until fluffy,
   stopping occasionally to scrap sites of bowl. Add eggs, one at a time,
   beating well after each addition. Add flour to butter mixture in
   thirds, alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour
   mixture. Stir in vanilla. Divide batter evenly among prepared pans,
   smoothing tops with a spatula. Bake until a wooden pick inserted into
   center of layers comes out clean, 20 to 30 minutes. Let layers cool in
   pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans, discard parchment paper, and let
   cool completely on wire racks. Spread caramel frosting between layers
   and on top and sides of cake. Drizzle with reserved 1/3 cup of caramel
   from caramel frosting. Garnish with pecans, if desired.</li>
   <li><strong>Caramel Frosting:</strong> In a large heavy bottomed
   saucepan, place sugar. In a small bowl, whisk together 1/4 cup water
   and corn syrup. Pour over sugar, stirring just until sugar is
   moistened. Cook, without stirring, over medium high heat until mixture
   is golden brown. (While caramel cooks, brush any sugar crystals on side
   of pan with a pastry brush dipped in water.) Remove from heat. Using a
   long handed wooden spoon, add cold butter. Stir until butter melts.
   (Mixture will foam.) Slowly add hot cream, stirring until smooth. (If
   mixture does not get smooth, cook over low heat, stirring until
   smooth.) Set aside, and let mixture cool until slightly warm,
   approximately 1 hour, stirring occasional. Reserve 1/3 cup caramel to
   drizzle over assembled cake. Pour caramel mixture into a large bowl;
   add softened butter. Beat at medium speed with a mixture until smooth.
   With mixer on low, gradually add confectioners sugar, beating just
   until smooth. Place piece of plastic wrap on surface of frosting. Let
   stand until frosting has reached a spreadable consistency, about 10
   minutes.</li> <li><strong>Note:</strong>To keep caramelized sugar from
   hardening or seizing in step 2 of Caramel Frosting, microwave heavy
   cream until it&rsquo;s hot but not boiling, 60 to 90 seconds, before
   you add it to the caramel.</li> </ol> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <div class="easyrecipeWrapper mceNonEditable"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name"></div>
   </div> </div> </div> <div class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container"> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"> <div></div> </div>
   <div><strong>Or print recipe:</strong></div> </div> </div> </div>
   <p><!--WPRM Recipe 59595--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Caramel Layer Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Caramel-Layer
   -Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ul> <li>1 cup
   butter (softened)</li> <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>4 large eggs</li>
   <li>3 cups self-rising flour</li> <li>1 cup whole buttermilk</li> <li>1
   1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> </ul> <h4>Caramel Frosting:</h4> <ul>
   <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>1/4 cup water</li> <li>2 Tablespoons light
   corn syrup</li> <li>1/2 cup cold butter (cubed)</li> <li>1 cup hot
   heavy whipping cream (see note)</li> <li>1 cup butter (softened)</li>
   <li>6 cups confectioners sugar (sifted)</li> </ul> <h4>Garnish:</h4>
   <ul> <li>toasted pecan halves</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol>
   <li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.</li> <li>Spray 3 (9 inch) round pans
   with nonstick cooking spray with flour. Line bottoms of pans with
   parchment paper; lightly spray again.</li> <li>In a large bowl, beat
   butter and sugar at medium speed with a mixer until fluffy, stopping
   occasionally to scrap sites of bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating
   well after each addition. Add flour to butter mixture in thirds,
   alternating with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
   Stir in vanilla. Divide batter evenly among prepared pans, smoothing
   tops with a spatula.</li> <li>Bake until a wooden pick inserted into
   center of layers comes out clean, 20 to 30 minutes. Let layers cool in
   pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans, discard parchment paper, and let
   cool completely on wire racks.</li> <li>Spread caramel frosting between
   layers and on top and sides of cake.</li> <li>Drizzle with reserved 1/3
   cup of caramel from caramel frosting.</li> <li>Garnish with pecans, if
   desired.</li> </ol> <h4>Caramel Frosting:</h4> <ol> <li>In a large
   heavy bottomed saucepan, place sugar. In a small bowl, whisk together
   1/4 cup water and corn syrup. Pour over sugar, stirring just until
   sugar is moistened. Cook, without stirring, over medium high heat until
   mixture is golden brown. (While caramel cooks, brush any sugar crystals
   on side of pan with a pastry brush dipped in water.) Remove from
   heat.</li> <li>Using a long handed wooden spoon, add cold butter. Stir
   until butter melts. (Mixture will foam.) Slowly add hot cream, stirring
   until smooth. (If mixture does not get smooth, cook over low heat,
   stirring until smooth.) Set aside, and let mixture cool until slightly
   warm, approximately 1 hour, stirring occasional. Reserve 1/3 cup
   caramel to drizzle over assembled cake.</li> <li>Pour caramel mixture
   into a large bowl; add softened butter. Beat at medium speed with a
   mixture until smooth. With mixer on low, gradually add confectioners
   sugar, beating just until smooth. Place piece of plastic wrap on
   surface of frosting. Let stand until frosting has reached a spreadable
   consistency, about 10 minutes.</li> </ol> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> <p>To keep caramelized sugar from
   hardening or seizing in step 2 of Caramel Frosting, microwave heavy
   cream until it&rsquo;s hot but not boiling, 60 to 90 seconds, before
   you add it to the caramel.</p> </p></div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>See
   more of our yummy <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake+"
   rel="">Cake Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">15 oz sloppy Joe
   sauce</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded cheddar
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted butter for
   brushing</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   beef over medium high heat until browned.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div

   5px">Drain.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sauce to the ground beef. Mix well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Layout
   biscuits on board.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   1/3 of mixture into center of biscuits.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with 1 Tablespoon cheese</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   dough in half over filling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   edges of dough with a fork to seal.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div

   on ungreased cookie sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush
   top with melted butter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59593-step-0-11"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   350 degrees F. for 9 to 14 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
