   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-check-your-heath-with-your-ear-wax/
   Thu, 23 Aug 2018 11:45:51 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY
   And Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53311 How To Check Your Heath
   With Your Ear Wax. With... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-check-your-heath-with-your-ear-w
   ax/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br
   /> <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53312 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Check-
   Your-Heath-With-Your-Ear-Wax.jpg" alt="How To Check Your Heath With
   Your Ear Wax.&nbsp;With the help of a Q-tip, you can check the color of
   your ear wax and understand what it means." width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Che
   ck-Your-Heath-With-Your-Ear-Wax.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Check-Your-
   Heath-With-Your-Ear-Wax-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Check-Your-
   Heath-With-Your-Ear-Wax-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"><strong>How To Check Your Heath With Your Ear
   Wax.</strong></p> <p>With the help of a Q-tip, you can check the color
   of your ear wax and understand what it means.</p> <p>Ear wax is not a
   body waste to get rid of regularly, quite the contrary &ndash;
   it&rsquo;s a kind of protection.</p> <p>It keeps the ear canal
   lubricated, therefore, prevents the ears from itching. Moreover, it
   prevents different pollutants from entering the inner ear.</p> <p>Even
   more surprisingly, this substance has antibacterial properties. Our
   body is a clever mechanism. Did you know that when we chew, the
   movement pushes ear wax to the outer part of the ear? This way, your
   ears self-clean!</p> <p>If your ears tend to produce a big amount of
   ear wax creating a build-up, you can take some preventive measures
   yourself. &ndash; It&rsquo;s effective to use agents softening the wax.
   They can be mineral or baby oil, or ear drops. It is enough to put a
   few drops of these substances into your ear once a week to soften the
   ear wax and help it to come out faster and with ease.</p> <p>Salt water
   is one of the best ear wax removal solution that can be used at home.
   It softens the wax accumulated inside the ear making it&nbsp;easy to
   clean. Mix a teaspoon of salt in half a cup of warm water until
   the&nbsp;salt&nbsp;gets completely dissolved. Soak a cotton ball in the
   solution. Tilt the affected ear upwards towards the sky. Squeeze the
   cotton ball to put a few drops of the saline water into the ear and
   stay in the same position for three to five minutes. Next, tilt your
   head in the opposite direction to allow the saline water to drain out.
   Clean the outer part of your ear with a clean cloth to remove the
   softened wax.</p> <p><strong>Q-tips aren&rsquo;t for cleaning your
   ear&rsquo;s.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Another way to take care of your
   ears is to buy a special at-home kit for their irrigation. Follow the
   instruction precisely step by step.</p> <p>Watch video for the 8 ear
   wax tips as to what your ear wax might mean:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/a2-6F2zOk30" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></body></html></p>

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   id="wprm-recipe-59591-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"

   100vw, 150px" /></div> </div> <a

   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"

   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Pecan Pie Cupcakes With Buttercream Frosting</h2>
   <div class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed dark brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole milk</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">at room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">toasted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Drizzle:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">semisweet chocolate morsels</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted and
   cooled.</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Buttercream
   Frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">firmly packed dark brown
   sugar</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plus 2 Tablespoons butter</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened and divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 to 3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole
   milk</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Pecan Topped
   Pastry Rounds:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4 14.1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package refrigerated
   piecrust</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1/2 sheet</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dark corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">12</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pecan
   halves</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line 12
   muffin cups with pager liners, set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, and salt. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar at medium high speed with a
   mixer until light and fluffy, approximately 5 minutes. Reduce speed to
   low. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition and
   scraping down sides of bowl as necessary.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   flour mixture to butter mixture in thirds, alternating with milk,
   beginning and ending with flour mixture. Fold in pecans and vanilla.
   Divide batter evenly among muffin cups. Tap pan against counter to
   release bubbles.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 18 to 20 minutes.
   Let cool in pan for 5 minutes. Remove from pan, and let cool completely
   on a wire rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   brown sugar buttercream frosting evenly on cupcakes. (Recipe
   below)</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   melted chocolate drizzle into a heavy duty resealable bag. Cut a small
   hole in corner of bag and drizzle on frosted cupcakes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Just
   before serving, top cupcakes with Pecan Topped Pastry Rounds. ( Recipe
   below).</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Buttercream
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small saucepan, bring brown sugar, 2 Tablespoon water and salt to a
   boil over medium high heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until sugar is
   dissolved, approximately 1 minute. Remove from heat, stir in 2
   Tablespoons butter. Let cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, beat cooled brown sugar mixture and remaining 1/2 cup
   butter at medium speed with a mixture until creamy, Add confectioners
   sugar and enough milk to achieve a spreadable consistency.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Pecan Topped Pastry Rounds:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   dough on a lightly floured surface. Using a 1 1/4 inch fluted cutter,
   cut 12 rounds. Reserve scraps for another use.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, combine corn syrup, melted butter, and salt; lightly brush
   over dough rounds. Gently press 1 pecan half into each dough round.
   Lightly brush pecans with butter mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until dough is golden brown, 6 to 8 minutes. Let cool completely.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59589-step-2-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   in a resealable plastic bag until ready to place on top of
   cupcakes.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />
   </body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin:
   8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole buttermilk</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chilled</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raisins</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">confectioners sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping
   cream</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 450 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, cinnamon,
   and baking soda.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   buttermilk and melted butter to the mixture, stirring to remove any
   large lumps.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   raisins, stirring to combine..</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drop
   dough onto prepared baking sheet in 1/4 cupfuls.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly golden, 10 to 12 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cool completely on pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   large bowl, whisk together confectioners sugar and cream.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   over cooled biscuits.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59587-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   Makes approximately 16 biscuits.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/chocolate-coca-cola-cake/ Mon, 20 Aug 2018
   13:40:38 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53291 &#160; From Scratch Chocolate Coca
   Cola Cake. OMG delicious. The... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/chocolate-coca-cola-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>From Scratch Chocolate Coca
   Cola Cake. </strong>OMG delicious. The best and most amazing dessert
   cake recipe you will ever eat. Moist inside and topped with an easy
   chocolate buttercream frosting.&nbsp; If you like chocolate you will
   love this recipe.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64629
   size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/From-Scratch-
   Chocolate-Coca-Cola-Cake.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="From Scratch Chocolate Coca Cola Cake. OMG
   delicious. The best and most amazing dessert cake recipe you will ever
   eat. Moist inside and topped with an easy chocolate buttercream
   frosting.&nbsp; If you like chocolate you will love this recipe."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/From-Scrat
   ch-Chocolate-Coca-Cola-Cake.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/From-Scratch-Choco
   late-Coca-Cola-Cake-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/From-Scratch-Choco
   late-Coca-Cola-Cake-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><!--WPRM Recipe 59585--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe">
   <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Chocolate Coca Cola Cake</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Chocolate-Coc
   a-Cola-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>Cake:</h4> <ul>
   <li>1 cup Coca Cola</li> <li>1/2 cup oil</li> <li>1 stick butter</li>
   <li>3 Tablespoon cocoa</li> <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>2 cups flour</li>
   <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li> <li>2 eggs</li> <li>1/2 cup buttermilk</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla</li> </ul>
   <h4>Frosting:</h4> <ul> <li>1 stick butter</li> <li>3 Tablespoon
   cocoa</li> <li>6 Tablesppons of cream or milk</li> <li>1 teaspoon
   vanilla extract</li> <li>3 3/4 cups confectioner&rsquo;s sugar</li>
   </ul> </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions">
   <h4>Cake:</h4> <ol> <li>In a saucepan, mix Coca Cola, oil, butter and
   cocoa and bring to a boil.</li> <li>In another bowl, combine the sugar,
   flour and salt.</li> <li>Pour the boiling Cola mixture over the flour
   mixture and beat well.</li> <li>Add the eggs, buttermilk, soda and
   vanilla and beat well.</li> <li>Pour mixture into a greased and floured
   13 x 9 inch baking pan and bake at 350 degrees or 20 to 25
   minutes.</li> <li>Remove pan. Cool for about 10 minutes before
   frosting.</li> </ol> <h4>Frosting:</h4> <ol> <li>In a saucepan, combine
   the butter, cocoa, and milk. Heat until the butter melts.</li> <li>Beat
   in the remaining ingredients and spread on the cake while it&rsquo;s
   still warm.</li> </ol> </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes">
   </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our yummy <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cake" rel="">Cake
   Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-freeze-corn-on-the-cob/ Mon, 20 Aug
   2018 12:29:16 +0000 My Honeys Place Cooking Tips & Tricks How To and
   Tips Recipes Side Dishes https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53288 How To
   Freeze Corn On The Cob. Can I freeze... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-freeze-corn-on-the-cob/">Continu
   e reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53289 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Freeze
   -Corn-On-The-Cob.jpg" alt="How To Freeze Corn On The Cob.&nbsp;Can I
   freeze corn on the cob whole, or should I scrape the corn off of the
   cob before I freeze it?" width="600" height="900"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Fre
   eze-Corn-On-The-Cob.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Freeze-Corn
   -On-The-Cob-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/How-To-Freeze-Corn
   -On-The-Cob-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>How To Freeze Corn On The Cob</strong>.</p>
   <p><strong>Can I freeze corn on the cob whole, or should I scrape the
   corn off of the cob before I freeze it?</strong></p> <p>On the Cob
   works great. I put some in the freezer a few days ago.</p> <p>Just cut
   the kernels off the cob as close to the cob as you can without getting
   any of the cob with it. You will get the feel of it once you get
   going.</p> <p>Freeze it whole uncooked wrapped in news paper when
   thawed just boil as usual. Delish!</p> <p>You can freeze it&nbsp;with
   the innermost layer of the husk still on it. Always turns out
   great.</p> <p>Don&rsquo;t wash it. Just shuck it, brush off the silks,
   and put it in freezer bags, get all the air you can out of the bags
   before zipping them.</p> <p>Both ways. My mom scraped so it
   didn&rsquo;t take up as much room.</p> <p>As you can see, either way is
   ok!!!</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   baking sheet with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   bread dough into 5 even portions. Divide each portion into 3
   pieces.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   each piece to approximately 5 inches.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Braid
   three pieces, securing ends.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   on prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly golden, 14 to 17 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine almonds and sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush
   braids on both sides with melted butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   braids in almond mixture, turning to coat both sides.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59583-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   Makes 5 servings</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>You
   might also enjoy this recipe: <strong>Breakfast Bombs</strong></p>
   <p>You will need:</p> <div class="ingredients col md-col-4 xs-mx2
   xs-mt2 md-mt0 xs-flex-order-2 md-flex-order-1"> <div
   class="ingredients__section xs-mt1 xs-mb3"> <ul class="list-unstyled
   xs-text-3"> <li class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">4 slices bacon, roughly
   chopped</li> <li class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">2 cloves garlic, minced</li> <li
   class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">9 large eggs, divided</li> <li class="xs-mb1
   xs-mt0"> <section class="measurement us-measurement
   xs-inline-block">&frac14; cup scallions, chopped</section> </li> <li
   class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">salt, to taste</li> <li class="xs-mb1
   xs-mt0">pepper, to taste</li> <li class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">6 yellow
   potatoes, peeled, grated, excess moisture squeezed out</li> <li
   class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0"> <section class="measurement us-measurement
   xs-inline-block">&frac34; cup all-purpose flour</section> </li> <li
   class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0"> <section class="measurement us-measurement
   xs-inline-block">1 cup shredded cheddar cheese, divided</section> </li>
   <li class="xs-mb1 xs-mt0">1 egg, beaten</li> <li class="xs-mb1
   xs-mt0">fresh parsley, chopped, for garnish</li> </ul> <p>Watch video
   for instructions:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/TjA1_WL8XGk" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> </div> </div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/upside-down-pumpkin-cake/ Sun, 19 Aug 2018
   12:22:55 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Holiday Recipes Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53278 &#160; Pumpkin Upside Down Cake. The
   best dessert cake recipe.... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/upside-down-pumpkin-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Pumpkin Upside Down Cake.
   </strong>The best dessert cake recipe. Homemade with cranberries,
   walnuts, pumpkin puree, and spices. Perfect for the Holidays.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64614 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Upside-Down-P
   umpkin-Cake-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Pumpkin Upside Down Cake. The best dessert cake
   recipe. Homemade with cranberries, walnuts, pumpkin puree, and spices.
   Perfect for the Holidays."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Upside-Dow
   n-Pumpkin-Cake-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Upside-Down-Pumpki
   n-Cake-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Upside-Down-Pumpki
   n-Cake-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe 59581--> </p> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Upside Down Pumpkin Cake</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Upside-Down-P
   umpkin-Cake-1-150x150.jpg"></p> <p
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul> <li>1 cup firmly packed
   light brown sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup unsalted butter</li> <li>1
   Tablespoon water</li> <li>2/3 cup chopped toasted walnuts</li> <li>1/2
   cup dried cranberries</li> <li>1 cup canned pumpkin puree</li> <li>3/4
   cup sugar</li> <li>1/3 cup vegetable oil</li> <li>2 large eggs</li>
   <li>1 1/2 cups all purpose flour</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoon baking
   powder</li> <li>1 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon ground
   ginger</li> <li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li> <li>1/8 teaspoon ground
   cloves</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol> <li>Preheat oven to 350
   degrees F.</li> <li>Line an 8 inch square baking dish with parchment
   paper. Spray with nonstick baking spray with flour. Set aside.</li>
   <li>In a small sauce pan, cook brown sugar, butter, and water over
   medium high heat until mixture bubbles, approximately 4 minutes.</li>
   <li>Pour sugar mixture into bottom of prepared dish, sprinkle with
   walnuts and cranberries. Set aside.</li> <li>In a medium bowl, combine
   pumpkin, sugar, oil, and eggs, whisking until well blended. Set
   aside.</li> <li>In a large, sift together flour, baking powder,
   cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves. Add pumpkin mixture, stirring to
   combine. Spoon batter into prepared pan, and smooth with a
   spatula.</li> <li>Bake until wooden pick inserted into the center comes
   out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.</li> <li>Let cool in pan for 5
   minutes.</li> <li>Invert pan into a serving platter. Remove parchment
   paper. Serve warm.</li> </ol> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>You should enjoy this video also:&nbsp;<b>Roasted
   Pumpkin Soup</b></p> <p>You will need:</p> <p>2.2 pounds Pumpkin<br />
   2 Tablespoon Oil<br /> Salt &amp; Pepper<br /> 1 Onion<br /> 3 Cloves
   Garlic<br /> 1 Tablespoon Ground Coriander Seeds<br /> 3 Cups Vegetable
   Stock</p> <p>Watch video for instruction:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/RPGBMkN-_Ys" width="450"
   height="340" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more of our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/recipes/holiday-recipes/"
   rel="">Holiday Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul

   until tender, approximately 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool
   completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   oven temperature to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   9 inch deep dish pie plate with pie crust; prick with a fork. Fold
   edges under, and crimp as desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   piece of parchment paper in bottom of pie crust, letting ends extend
   over edge. Add pie weights.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 12 minutes. Carefully remove parchment paper and pie weights, bake
   until lightly browned, approximately 8 minutes more. Let cook on a wire
   rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile peel potatoes. In the work bowl of a food processor,
   place pulp, pulse until completely smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, combine 4 cups sweet potato puree, eggs, egg yolk, brown
   sugar, cream, butter, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Beat at
   medium speed with a mixer until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   filling into pie crust.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-11"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with Pecan Crumble:</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-12"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***For
   Pecan crumble: In a medium bowl combine flour, pecans, brown sugar,
   cinnamon and salt.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-13"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 30 minutes. Cover pie loosely with foil to prevent excessive
   browning, and bake for an additional 30 minutes. Remove from
   oven,</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-14"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cool on a wire rack for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-15" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59579-step-0-16" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   in refrigerator up to 5 days.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/honey-oatmeal-cookies/ Sat, 18 Aug 2018
   11:01:53 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53264 &#160; Raisin Pecan Honey Oatmeal
   Cookies. Easy homemade dessert recipe&#160;... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/honey-oatmeal-cookies/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Raisin Pecan Honey Oatmeal
   Cookies. </strong>Easy homemade dessert recipe&nbsp; that is healthy
   and chewy.&nbsp; Made healthy with whole wheat flour, oats, raisins and
   honey.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64610 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Honey-Oatmeal
   -Cookies-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900"
   data-pin-description="Raisin Pecan Honey Oatmeal Cookies. Easy homemade
   dessert recipe&nbsp; that is healthy and chewy.&nbsp; Made healthy with
   whole wheat flour, oats, raisins and honey."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Honey-Oatm
   eal-Cookies-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Honey-Oatmeal-Cook
   ies-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Honey-Oatmeal-Cook
   ies-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><!--WPRM Recipe 59577--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe">
   <h2 class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Honey Oatmeal Cookies</h2> <p>
   <img class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Honey-Oatmeal
   -Cookies-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary">
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <ul> <li>1 1/2 cups
   whole wheat flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>1/2 teaspoon
   ground cinnamon</li> <li>1 cup unsalted butter (softened)</li> <li>1
   cup honey</li> <li>2 large eggs</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla
   extract</li> <li>3 cups old fashioned oats</li> <li>1 cup raisins</li>
   <li>1 cup pecans pieces</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <ol> <li>Preheat oven to 350
   degrees F.</li> <li>Line 3 baking sheets with parchment paper. Set
   aside.</li> <li>In a large bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and
   cinnamon.</li> <li>In another large bowl, beat butter, honey, eggs and
   vanilla at medium speed with a mixture until well combined.</li>
   <li>Slowly add flour mixture, beating well.</li> <li>Add oats, raisins,
   and pecans. Mix well</li> <li>Drop dough by Tablespoonfuls onto
   prepared baking sheet, approximately 2 inches apart.</li> <li>Bake
   until barely golden around bottom edges, 10 to 12 minutes.</li>
   <li>Remove from pans, and let cool completely on a wire rack.</li>
   <li>***Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen cookies.</li> </ol> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>You might also enjoy this <strong>video</strong>
   recipe:&nbsp; <strong>How to Make M&amp;M Cookies</strong></p>
   <p><strong>Ingredients:&nbsp;</strong></p> <ul id="lst_ingredients_1"
   class="checklist dropdownwrapper list-ingredients-1"> <li
   class="checkList__line"><label class="checkList__item" title="1 cup
   packed brown sugar"><span class="recipe-ingred_txt added"
   data-id="1525" data-nameid="1525">1 cup packed brown
   sugar</span></label></li> <li class="checkList__line"><label
   class="checkList__item" title="1/2 cup white sugar"><span
   class="recipe-ingred_txt added" data-id="1526" data-nameid="1526">1/2
   cup white sugar</span></label></li> <li class="checkList__line">1 cup
   shortening</li> <li>2 eggs</li> <li>1 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
   <li>2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
   <li><span class="recipe-ingred_txt added" data-id="16421"
   data-nameid="16421">1 teaspoon salt</span></li> <li>1 1/2 cups
   candy-coated milk chocolate pieces (such as M&amp;M&rsquo;s&reg;)</li>
   </ul> <p>Instructions:</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0iRt6Ups8HA" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p

   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   several baking sheets with parchment paper. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl beat butter and sugars at medium high speed with a mixer
   until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
   Stir in vanilla.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add
   flour mixture to butter mixture, beating at low speed until smooth. Add
   cream, beating to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Shape
   dough into a disk, and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate at least 1
   hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough into 1/4 inch thickness. Using a 2
   inch fluted round cutter, cut as many cookies as possible, rerolling
   scraps no more than twice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until edges are lightly browned, approximately 10 minutes. Let cookies
   cool on pan for 2 minutes. Remove from pans, and let cool completely on
   wire racks.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small saucepan, cook caramel bits and 1/4 cup water, whisking often,
   over medium heat until bits are melted and mixture is smooth. Let cool
   to room temperature.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   approximately 1/2 teaspoon caramel mixture on the center of each
   cookie. Press a praline pecan onto caramel.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle with sea salt, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   cookies on parchment paper to dry, approximately 1 hour.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59573-step-0-12"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">****Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>Thought you would enjoy this
   recipe too. <strong>How To Make French Macarons.</strong><br /> Watch
   video below for instructions.</p> <p>Ingredients: 1 cup powdered sugar
   3/4 cup almond flour 2 egg whites room temperature 1/4 cup granulated
   sugar food coloring (optional)</p> <p>For Honey Buttercream Filling: 2
   egg yolks 1/4 cup granulated sugar 3 1/2 tsp milk 7 tbsp softened
   unsalted butter 3 tbsp honey.</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0JeTgZGt-p8" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">wooden ice pop
   sticks</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">apples</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   crushed candy bars and peanuts in separate bowls.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   large microwaveable bowl, combine caramels and 1 Tablespoon water.
   Microwave on high, in 30 second intervals, stirring between each, until
   melted, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   sticks in center of apples.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   bottom halves of apples in melted caramel, allowing excess to drip
   off.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   apples in crushed candy bars or peanuts.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   on waxed paper. Let cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   in refrigerator up to 2 days.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59571-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Makes 5
   Caramel Apples.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>You
   might also enjoy this&nbsp;<strong>Apple Turnovers Recipe</strong></p>
   <p style="font-weight: 400;">Ingredients for 4 Apple Hand Pies:</p> <p
   style="font-weight: 400;">about 1 pound pie dough, divided into 4</p>
   <p style="font-weight: 400;">egg wash (1 egg beaten with 2 tsp
   milk)</p> <p style="font-weight: 400;">granulated sugar as needed</p>
   <p style="font-weight: 400;">For the apple filling:</p> <p
   style="font-weight: 400;">2 tbsp butter, browned</p> <p
   style="font-weight: 400;">2 or 3 green apples</p> <p
   style="font-weight: 400;">1/4 tsp salt</p> <p style="font-weight:
   400;">1/4 cup white sugar</p> <p style="font-weight: 400;">2 tbsp brown
   sugar</p> <p style="font-weight: 400;">1 1/2 tsp cinnamon, or to
   taste<br /> 1 or 2 tsp&nbsp;of water if needed</p> <p>Watch video for

   https://myhoneysplace.com/southern-apple-cake/ Wed, 15 Aug 2018
   11:05:29 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53247 &#160; The Best Southern Apple Cake.
   Dessert recipe that has... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/southern-apple-cake/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>The Best Southern Apple
   Cake.</strong></p> <p>Dessert recipe that has an apple cake topped with
   a caramel topping and pecans.</p> <p>The best cake you will ever
   eat.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-64599 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Southern-Appl
   e-Cake-1.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="900" data-pin-description="The
   Best Southern Apple Cake. Dessert recipe that has an apple cake topped
   with a caramel topping and pecans. The best cake you will ever eat."
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Southern-A
   pple-Cake-1.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Southern-Apple-Cak
   e-1-267x400.jpg 267w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Southern-Apple-Cak
   e-1-100x150.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><!--WPRM
   Recipe 59569--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Southern Apple Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Southern-Appl
   e-Cake-150x150.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the cake:</h4> <ul>
   <li>2 cups sugar</li> <li>4 large eggs</li> <li>1 cup vegetable
   oil</li> <li>3 cups all purpose flour</li> <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li> <li>3 cups thinly sliced apple</li>
   <li>1 cup chopped pecans or walnuts</li> </ul> <h4>For the caramel
   topping:</h4> <ul> <li>1/2 cup sugar</li> <li>1/2 cup firmly packed
   light brown sugar</li> <li>4 Tablespoons butter</li> <li>1/4 cup
   evaporated milk</li> <li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li> </ul>
   <h4>Garnish:</h4> <ul> <li>Pecan halves</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the cake:</h4> <ol>
   <li>Do NOT preheat oven.</li> <li>Spray a 13&times;9 inch pan with
   nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.</li> <li>In a large bowl, beat
   sugar, eggs, and oil at medium speed with a mixer until smooth.</li>
   <li>In a separate bowl, sift together flour, salt, and baking
   soda.</li> <li>Stir flour mixture into egg mixture until thoroughly
   combined.</li> <li>Add apple and nuts. Gently stir until incorporated.
   Spread batter in prepared pan.</li> <li>Place pan in a cold oven. Bake
   at 325 degrees F. for 50 to 55 minutes. Let cool in pan.</li> <li>Pour
   warm Caramel topping over cake in pan. Instructions below.</li> <li>Cut
   into squares, and garnish with pecan halves, if desired.</li> </ol>
   <h4>For the caramel topping:</h4> <ol> <li>In a small saucepan, bring
   sugars, butter, and evaporated milk to a boil over medium high
   heat.</li> <li>Cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes.</li> <li>Stir
   in vanilla,</li> <li>***Yield approximately 16 serving.</li> </ol>
   </div> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div>
   <p><!--End WPRM Recipe--></p> <p>You also might enjoy this
   cake:&nbsp;<strong>How to Make the Most Amazing Chocolate
   Cake</strong></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dsJtgmAhFF4" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p><strong>Recipe
   for Amazing Chocolate Cake:</strong></p> <p><!--WPRM Recipe
   59575--></p> <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe"> <h2
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-name">Amazing Chocolate Cake</h2> <p> <img
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-image"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Capture-150x1
   50.jpg"></p> <p class="wprm-fallback-recipe-summary"> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-ingredients"> <h4>For the cake:</h4> <ul>
   <li>butter and flour for coating and dusting the cake pan</li> <li>3
   cups all-purpose flour</li> <li>3 cups granulated sugar</li>
   <li>1&frac12; cups unsweetened cocoa powder</li> <li>1 tablespoon
   baking soda</li> <li>1&frac12; teaspoons baking powder</li>
   <li>1&frac12; teaspoons salt</li> <li>4 large eggs</li> <li>1&frac12;
   cups buttermilk</li> <li>1&frac12; cups warm water</li> <li>&frac12;
   cup vegetable oil</li> <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li> </ul>
   <h4>Chocolate Cream Cheese Buttercream Frosting:</h4> <ul>
   <li>1&frac12; cups butter (softened)</li> <li>8 oz cream cheese
   (softened)</li> <li>1&frac12; cups unsweetened cocoa powder</li> <li>3
   teaspoons vanilla extract</li> <li>7-8 cups powdered sugar</li>
   <li>about &frac14; cup milk (as needed)</li> </ul> </div> <div
   class="wprm-fallback-recipe-instructions"> <h4>For the cake:</h4> <ol>
   <li>Preheat oven to 350 degrees.</li> <li>Butter three 9-inch cake
   rounds. Dust with flour and tap out the excess. (see cooking lesson
   below)</li> <li>Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking
   powder, and salt in a stand mixer using a low speed until
   combined.</li> <li>Add eggs, buttermilk, warm water, oil, and vanilla.
   Beat on a medium speed until smooth. This should take just a couple of
   minutes.</li> <li>Divide batter among the three pans. I found that it
   took just over 3 cups of the batter to divide it evenly.</li> <li>Bake
   for 30-35 minutes until the cake meets the toothpick test (stick a
   toothpick in and it comes out clean).</li> <li>Cool on wire racks for
   15 minutes and then turn out the cakes onto the racks and allow to cool
   completely.</li> <li>Frost with your favorite frosting and enjoy!</li>
   <li>**Notes: The better quality cocoa powder you use the better the
   cake will taste.</li> </ol> <h4>Chocolate Cream Cheese Buttercream
   Frosting:</h4> <ol> <li>In a large bowl, beat together butter and cream
   cheese until fluffy. Use a hand mixer or stand mixer for best
   results</li> <li>Add in cocoa powder and vanilla extract. Beat until
   combined.</li> <li>Beat in powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time. Add milk as
   necessary to make a spreadable consistency. The frosting should be very
   thick and will thicken even more if refrigerated.</li> </ol> </div>
   <div class="wprm-fallback-recipe-notes"> </div> </div> <p><!--End WPRM
   Recipe--></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><span
   style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>More Cake Recipes:</strong></span></p>
   <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/pumpkin-swirl-cheesecake/">Pumpkin
   Swirl Cheesecake</a>&nbsp;Delicious dessert recipe made with graham
   cracker crust, toasted pecans, cream cheese, sour cream, pumpkin puree
   and white chocolate.</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/caramel-layer-cake/">Caramel Layer Cake
   &nbsp;</a>A 3 layer delicious dessert cake recipe. Topped with a
   caramel frosting and garnished with pecans.</strong></p> <p><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/chocolate-coca-cola-cake/"><strong>Choc
   olate Coca Cola Cake&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></a><strong>If you like
   chocolate you will love this recipe.</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/upside-down-pumpkin-cake/">Upside Down
   Pumpkin Cake</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;This dessert recipe will be the best
   pumpkin cake you ever baked.</strong></p> <p><strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-lemon-cake-and-frosting/">Home
   made Lemon Cake and Frosting</a>&nbsp;A moist and fluffy lemon layer
   cake with homemade lemon cream cheese
   frosting</strong></body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   </div> <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59567" style=""

   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cherry Apricot Crumb Bars</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">quick cooking oats</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">not instant</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can cherry pie filling</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">21 ounce</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped dried
   apricots</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degree F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line a
   13x9 inch baking pan with aluminium foil, extending edges of foil over
   edges of pan approximately 2 inches.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine oats, flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
   Add melted butter, tossing to combine. Reserve 1 cup crumble
   mixture.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   remaining mixture into bottom of prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until set, 12 to 14 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, combine pie filling and apricots. Gently spread cheery
   mixture over crust. Sprinkle with reserved 1 cup crumble mixture.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until lightly browned and bubbly, 30 to 35 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cool completely on a wire rack. Remove from pan by lifting foil
   edges.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut
   into squares and serve.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59567-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Makes 1
   dozen bars.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>See more recipes using <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cherries+">Cherries</a></strong></p>
   <p>Cherry Clafoutis Recipe:</p> <p><iframe

   height="450" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
   <p><strong>Ingredients:</strong></p> <p>Makes about 6-8 servings</p>
   <p>20 oz (600 g) fresh sweet cherries, stemmed and pitted</p> <p>2 tbsp
   (30 g) butter, melted</p> <p>4 eggs</p> <p>1 cup (240 ml) milk</p>
   <p>3/4 cup (100g) flour</p> <p>1/4 tsp salt</p> <p>1/2 cup (100 g)
   sugar</p> <p>1/2 tsp almond extract (or 3 drops of almond essence)</p>
   <p>1/2 tsp vanilla extract</p> <p>For Dusting powdered
   sugar</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cold butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">diced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5 to 6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ice
   water</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For The
   Filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">almond paste</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">crumbled</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small to medium ripe but firm
   pears. Peeled</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">corded and sliced. (about 2
   pounds)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground ginger</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
