   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">turbinado
   sugar</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Garnish:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">toasted sliced
   almonds</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In the
   bowl of a food processor, pulse together flour sugar and salt for
   crust. Add butter, pulsing until mixture resembles course crumbs,
   approximately 6 times. Spoon flour mixture into large bowl. Sprinkle
   ice water over flour mixture, 1 Tablespoon at a time, tossing with a
   fork until all dry ingredients are moistened.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   dough on a lightly floured surface. Kneading just until dough is
   combined. 2 to 3 times. Shape dough into 6 inch disk. Wrap dough in
   plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 375 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">On a
   lightly floured surface, roll dough into 12 inch circle. Transfer dough
   to prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle almond paste for filling over dough,
   leaving a 2 inch border.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, combine pears, sugar, flour, ginger and salt. Sprinkle
   lemon juice over pears, tossing to combine. Arrange pear mixture over
   almond paste. Gently folding edges of dough over filling. (Dough will
   not completely cover filling)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, whisk together egg and 1 teaspoon water. Brush over edges
   of dough then sprinkle with turbinado sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly, approximately 40
   minutes. Let cool on pan or a wire rack for 20 minutes before
   serving.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Garnish
   with honey and sliced almonds, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Yields
   approximately 6 servings.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59565-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>You might
   also enjoy this: <strong>Quick N&rsquo; Easy Pear Cobbler</strong></p>

   12:11:21 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips Simple
   DIY Projects https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53187 8 Free Airplane Perks.
   There are still free things you... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/8-free-airplane-perks/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53197 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/8-Free-Airpla
   ne-Perks.jpg" alt="8 Free Airplane Perks. There are still free things
   you can get on your airplane trip. All you have to do is ask."
   width="600" height="900" data-id="53197"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/8-Free-Air
   plane-Perks.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/8-Free-Airplane-Pe
   rks-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><strong>8
   Free Airplane Perks.</strong> There are still free things you can get
   on your airplane trip. All you have to do is ask.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53189"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/airplane1.jpg
   " alt="" width="350" height="233" data-id="53189"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/airplane1.
   jpg 960w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/airplane1-400x267.
   jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/airplane1-768x512.
   jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Tours of the
   cockpit:</strong><br /> Most pilots will allow you to take a peek of
   the cockpit. Ask them after the flight when time is not so important.
   Just ask.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53190"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks.jpg"
   alt="" width="350" height="263" data-id="53190"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks.jpg
   3264w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks-400x300.jpg
   400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks-768x576.jpg
   768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks-1024x768.jp
   g 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks-65x50.jpg
   65w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/snacks-500x375.jpg
   500w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Extra
   snacks:</strong></p> <p>Airlines often have a good supply of snacks.
   After snacks have been given out and you are still hungry just ask your
   fight attendant if they have any extra. On the most basic level, you
   can ask for unlimited refills and snacks from the refreshment cart, but
   if you have a reason (like a delayed flight or faulty seat), ask for a
   comped glass of wine or a cocktail. Most will gladly oblige.</p>
   <p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-53191"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/First-Aid-sup
   ples.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" data-id="53191"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/First-Aid-
   supples.jpg 300w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/First-Aid-supples-
   150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/First-Aid-supples-
   50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"><strong>First
   aid supplies:</strong></p> <p>Have a headache, a small boo-boo, or an
   upset stomach? Airplanes are stocked with basic first aid supplies.
   Just ask.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53192"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wipes.jpg"
   alt="" width="350" height="231" data-id="53192"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wipes.jpg
   700w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wipes-400x264.jpg
   400w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Small packages of
   sanitizing wipes:</strong><br /> You never know how many germs are on
   your food tray or seat belt. Ask your flight attendant for a wipe and
   scrub away.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53193"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-attend
   ant.jpg" alt="" width="350" height="197" data-id="53193"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-att
   endant.jpg 1920w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-attendant-4
   00x225.jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-attendant-7
   68x432.jpg 768w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-attendant-1
   024x576.jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/flight-attendant-4
   80x270.jpg 480w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Keep
   an eye on your young child:</strong><br /> When you have to use the
   rest room and are unable to take your child with you, just ask your
   friendly flight attendant&nbsp; to keep an eye out on your child. Most
   will gladly help. Just pick a time they are not too busy.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53194"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/magazines.jpg
   " alt="" width="350" height="184" data-id="53194"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/magazines.
   jpg 1024w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/magazines-400x210.
   jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/magazines-768x404.
   jpg 768w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Free
   magazines:</strong></p> <p>The magazines on airplanes are free to take
   with you. Most of them are left by other passengers.</p> <p><img
   class="aligncenter wp-image-53195"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wings.jpg"
   alt="" width="350" height="180" data-id="53195"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wings.jpg
   679w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wings-400x206.jpg
   400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wings-290x150.jpg
   290w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Airline
   wings:</strong></p> <p>We have all heard of &ldquo;the mile high
   club&rdquo; but don&rsquo;t do it. If you are traveling with children
   ask your flight attendant for a set of wings. Not all airlines will
   have them, but does not hurt to ask.</p> <p><img class="aligncenter
   wp-image-53196"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/toys.jpg"
   alt="" width="350" height="263" data-id="53196"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/toys.jpg
   1396w,

   65w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/toys-500x375.jpg
   500w" sizes="(max-width: 350px) 100vw, 350px"><strong>Toys:</strong><br
   /> Some airlines offer kids&rsquo; packs and toys as a way to help keep
   the younger set occupied during the trip. Just ask if your plane flight
   might have some available. But be sure to bring your own just in
   case.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><iframe style="border: none;

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Spinach Cream Soup</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped onion</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of fresh spinach</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chicken bullion base</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">10</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large sauce pan, saute onions in butter.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   spinach and water and cook spinach until spinach is wilted and
   soft.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   flour and cook for about 1 minute.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add milk and stir until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   chicken base and continue stirring constantly until soup comes to a
   boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">With a
   hand blender, puree soup until spinach is well blended.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If you
   would like your soup a little thicker, in a separate small bowl mix
   together 3 Tablespoons of corn starch to 4 Tablespoons of cold
   water.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59561-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add cornstarch mixture as needed to boiling soup stirring constantly
   until soup is thickened to desired consistency.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:

   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oil in a pot over medium heat to 350</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   bowl, mix together the ground beef, salt, pepper, and garlic
   powder.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Peel
   and slice the onion into 1-centimeter rings, and detach the rings from
   each other.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take a
   spoonful of the beef mixture and press it into the bottom of a
   ring.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Push a
   cheddar square into the center of the beef.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Seal
   the top with another spoonful of the beef, pressing it flat.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   with the rest of the rings.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the flour, eggs, and bread crumbs into three separate bowls.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip a
   ring into the flour, shaking off excess, then into the egg, the bread
   crumbs, then back to the eggs, and one last time into the
   breadcrumbs.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   with the remaining rings.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fry the
   rings for 5-6 minutes, until deep golden-brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59559-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drain
   on a paper towel, then serve with ketchup!</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   div> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   butter, sugar, raisins, spices, salt and water to a medium boil for 3
   minutes on top of the stove.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from stove and let cool.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   vanilla extract.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together the flour, baking soda and baking powder in a large
   bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour in
   cooled ingredients and mix until ingredients are all wet.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   eggs and fold in nuts.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   a 99 baking pan, by lightly oiling it or lining it with parchment
   paper and bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 50 to 55 minutes or
   until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out
   clean.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle more raisins on top of cake.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59557-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">You can
   add your favorite frosting or a glaze. Or just sprinkle on some
   powdered sugar top.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the bottom
   layer:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Press
   the pie crust into a pie pan, crimping the edges.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   according to directions or until lightly browned.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the middle layer:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   heavy whip cream and vanilla with a mixer until thicken. About 5 to 10
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold in
   1/3 cups of sugar. Do not over mix after sugar is added.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">****You
   could also use cool whip instead of making your own whipped
   topping.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the Top
   layer:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Take
   stems off fresh strawberries and cut up into small pieces. Place in
   bowl and put 1/3 cup sugar on top, stir and let set about 1/2 hour.
   This will give you the sweet juice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drain
   off most of the juice.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59555-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Layer
   strawberries on top.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">

   wprm-block-text-bold">Healthy Honey Garlic Shrimp</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">soy sauce</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced garlic</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced fresh ginger -
   optional</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">medium uncooked shrimp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">peeled &amp;
   deveined</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive
   oil</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   the honey, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger (if using) together in a
   medium bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   shrimp in a large zipped-top bag.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   1/2 of the marinade mixture on top, give it all a shake or stir, then
   allow shrimp to marinate in the refrigerator for 15 minutes or for up
   to 8-12 hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and refrigerate the rest of the marinade if marinating shrimp more than
   1/2 hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Discard
   used marinade.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   shrimp in the skillet.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   shrimp on one side until pink-- about 45 seconds-- then flip shrimp
   over.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour in
   remaining marinade and cook it all until shrimp is cooked through,
   about 1 minute more.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   shrimp with cooked marinade sauce and a garnish of green onion.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59553-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   sauce is excellent on brown rice and steamed veggies on the side.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><strong>More <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/favorite-recipes/main-dishes/"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vegetable oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">packed brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy whipping cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped
   pecans</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pre
   Heat oven to 350 F. Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   large microwavable bowl, microwave 2 tablespoons butter, 2 tablespoons
   brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped pecans uncovered on High 1 minute or
   until mixture is bubbling and hot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   another large bowl, beat cake mix, sour cream, vegetable oil and eggs
   with electric mixer on low speed 1 minute, then on medium speed 2
   minutes. Stir in pecan mixture. Pour into pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 30
   to 36 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
   Cool completely in pan on cooling rack, about 1 hour.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   2-quart heavy saucepan, heat 1/2 cup butter, 2 cups brown sugar and the
   whipping cream to boiling, stirring frequently.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Boil
   and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   2 cups pecans.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool 10
   to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until frosting begins to
   thicken.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   frosting over cake.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59549-step-1-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   before cutting.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">not the liquid. Start with a drop
   or two and then work up to the color you
   want.</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   softened butter into your stand mixer or bowl</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter on medium to high in stand mixer or with a hand mixer for 3
   minutes until fluffy</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Just
   before the end of 3 minutes add vanilla and 3 tablespoons milk to
   butter, keep beating</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   to medium low or medium</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   pour in powdered sugar and continue beating for a total of 3 more
   minutes on medium moving up to high speed as sugar is
   incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If you
   want to add in food coloring, add in while it is beating that last 3
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   frosting is too stiff add in more milk 1 tsp at a time and beat until
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   on cake or cookies,</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To
   store place butter cream in an airtight container and store in
   refrigerator for 2-3 days.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59547-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   to room temp prior to frosting.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53123 How To Get Spilled Flour Off Your
   Couch. A DIY... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-get-spilled-flour-off-your-couch

   Maybe your child or your dog made a mess with flour on your couch. This
   tip will work also on your carpet.</p> <p>Let the flour dry real good
   first. Add some baking soda to help dry it out. &nbsp;<span
   data-ft='{"tn":"K"}'><span class="UFICommentBody">Don&rsquo;t vacuum
   right away, it will make a cloudy haze/smoke and will spread! Gently
   sweep the excessive into small piles and scoop up. Then take damp cloth
   to wipe the rest- try to get up as much as you can
   .&nbsp;</span></span><strong>Vacuum real good when dry</strong> and
   shampoo if needed. T<span data-ft='{"tn":"K"}'><span
   class="UFICommentBody">hen Steam clean the sofa and
   carpet.&nbsp;</span></span>But getting it dried out is #1. I just went
   through this 2 weeks ago. Good luck.</p> <p style="text-align:

   tricks/">Household Tips and Tricks</a></strong></p>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/10-reasons-to-use-an-air-fryer/ Tue, 31 Jul
   2018 12:46:26 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53119 10 Reasons To Use An Air Fryer. I
   have an... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-reasons-to-use-an-air-fryer/">Contin
   ue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53121 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Reasons-To
   -Use-An-Air-Fryer2.jpg" alt="10 Reasons To Use An Air Fryer. I have an
   air fryer and use it daily. So convenient and easy to use. I have lots
   of recipes for my air fryer.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   data-id="53121"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Reasons
   -To-Use-An-Air-Fryer2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Reasons-To-Use-
   An-Air-Fryer2-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>10 Reasons To Use An Air Fryer.</strong> I have an air
   fryer and use it daily. So convenient and easy to use. I have lots of
   recipes for my air fryer.</p> <p>An air fryer has mechanical fan
   circulates the hot&nbsp;air&nbsp;around the food at high speed, cooking
   the food and producing a crispy layer.&nbsp; Counter-top&nbsp;air
   fryers&nbsp;are a healthy alternative to the traditional way of frying
   food in a pot of oil.</p> <p><strong>Healthier than frying</strong>.
   You can cook all sorts of things in an air fryer. Using less than a
   tablespoon of oil or a couple of spray of canola cooking spray, you can
   fry beef, chicken, fish, frozen food and vegetables. A&nbsp;healthier
   way with up to 75% less fat.</p> <p><strong>Cooking frozen
   food</strong> in the air fryer is very efficient and they are super
   crispy and taste delicious. Pop in your favorite potato delights in the
   baskets and you will have crispy fries in a fraction of the time and in
   a much healthier style.</p> <p>It makes <strong>cleaning up a
   breeze</strong>. Just cook and wipe out the inside after most
   cooking.</p> <p>Be sure to clean your air fryer weekly or regularly,
   depending on how often you use it. But give it a good cleaning once a
   week.</p> <ul> <li>Take out the tray and pans and rinse out the
   leftover oils and food.</li> <li>Soak them in warm soapy water for an
   hour.</li> <li>Scrub them with a gentle cleansing brush. Rinse and dry
   with a kitchen towel.</li> <li>Or place trays and the pan in the
   dishwasher.</li> </ul> <p><strong>The air fryer is quiet</strong>. It
   is powerful, but doesn&rsquo;t make a lot of fuss.</p> <p>It also
   <strong>saves tons of cooking time</strong>. Most food will cooking in
   less than 1/2 the time of a regular oven.</p> <p>Your<strong> kitchen
   does not get hot</strong> as with a regular oven.</p> <p>Compared to
   deep-frying, using an&nbsp;<strong>air fryer&nbsp;can reduce the amount
   of fa</strong>t, calories and potentially harmful compounds in your
   food.</p> <p><strong>Air fryers are actually more gentle and suitable
   for baked goods</strong>.&nbsp;The heat generated from it is pulled up
   with the fan, so there is no direct heat source on the food. It&rsquo;s
   dispersed on the outside of the chamber, and then ascends from the open
   bottom to heat the baked goods from all around.</p> <p>Air fryers are
   <strong>smaller than convection ovens</strong>. Which makes them
   efficient for daily family meals.</p> <p>An air fryer&nbsp;spares you
   from that <strong>unwanted aroma</strong> of&nbsp;fried&nbsp;foods in
   your home.</p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Check out our <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/favorite-recipes/air-fryer-rec
   ipes/">Air Fryer Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>
   <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Strawberry
   juice:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mash
   strawberries until very fine pieces.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   strawberries and sugar together and let set for about 1/2 hour or until
   you have 3/4 cup strawberry juice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Separate juice from strawberries. So you have correct juice
   measurement.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Ice
   cream:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Blend
   all ingredients in strong blender or food processor until
   whipped.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   mixture is too runny, add 1/4 cup ice and process further.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59545-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To look
   more like a creamy whip, transfer mixture to piping bag with star tip
   and pipe into cups or ice cream cones.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar or less if your raspberries
   are sweet.</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh lemon
   juice</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Chocolate
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 F | 175C. Lightly grease an 8-inch round cake pan with non
   stick cooking oil spraying.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
   Whisk thoroughly to combine well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   oil, egg, vanilla and milk to the flour mixture and beat well to
   combine. Pour in the boiling water (with the coffee), and mix until
   glossy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   Raspberry ingredients together and stir 1/2 of the mixture into the
   cake batter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the cake batter into the prepared pan. Press the other half or the
   Raspberry mixture on top of cake. Bake for about 40 - 45 minutes, until
   a toothpick inserted in the center of the chocolate cake comes out
   semi-clean with small amount of cake (not runny batter) on it due to
   the fudgy texture.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59543-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from oven and allow to cool for 20 minutes. Transfer cake from the pan
   to a wire rack and cool completely.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   optional</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large mixing bowl, mix the butter into the mashed bananas.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix in
   the sugar, egg and vanilla.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   baking soda and salt and stir to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   flour and mix until just incorporated.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold in
   the chopped walnuts. The less you stir the mixture at this time, the
   fluffier the muffins will be when baked.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   mixture into prepared muffin pan lined with cupcake liners or greased
   with butter or vegetable oil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   25-30 minutes until golden brown and once a knife inserted into the
   center of the muffin comes out clean.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   sprinkles on top - optional</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59541-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   to cool on a cooling rack.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/30-day-no-spending-challenge/ Sun, 29 Jul
   2018 14:34:49 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And Tips
   Household Tips & Tricks How To and Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53097 30 Day No Spending Challenge. A DIY
   project to save... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/30-day-no-spending-challenge/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53099 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/30-Day-No-Spe
   nding-Challenge.jpg" alt="30 Day No Spending Challenge. A DIY project
   to save money. You will be surprised how much money you can save in 30
   days." width="600" height="900" data-id="53099"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/30-Day-No-
   Spending-Challenge.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/30-Day-No-Spending
   -Challenge-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px">30
   Day No Spending Challenge.</strong> A DIY project to save money. You
   will be surprised how much money you can save in 30 days.</p>
   <p><strong>Step 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;Take a peak at your checking account.
   </strong></p> <p>Pick one <strong>non- essential thing</strong> where
   you spend your money. Non- essential expenses are not essential to meet
   your needs.&nbsp;You may want these things because you like or enjoy
   them but they are not necessary for your survival.</p> <p>It might be
   for entertainment or eating out.</p> <p>Maybe you could cancel
   your&nbsp;memberships, and magazine subscriptions.</p> <p>Drive your
   car less.&nbsp;Consider using public transportation, walking or riding
   a bike to and from work.</p> <p>Raise the deductible on your insurance
   policies to lower your monthly premiums. Be prepared to pay the
   deductible though, if an emergency does happen.</p> <p>Skip restaurant
   lunches and pack your lunch&mdash;every day.</p> <p>Use netflix instead
   of going to the movies.</p> <p>Make your morning coffee instead of
   buying.</p> <p>Do not use your credit card for one month. Pay with
   cash.</p> <p>Cut down on your electric bill. In the summer, close
   blinds, use fans and turn air conditioner down while you are not
   home.</p> <p><strong>Use the 30 day rule</strong>. It is a simple
   method to control impulse spending. Here&rsquo;s how it works: Whenever
   you feel the urge to splurge &mdash; whether it&rsquo;s for new shoes,
   a new video game, or a new car &mdash; force yourself to stop. If
   you&rsquo;re already holding the item, put it back and leave the
   store.&nbsp; For the next thirty days, think whether you really want
   the item, but do not buy it.&nbsp; If, at the end of a month, the urge
   is still there, then consider purchasing it. (But&nbsp;<i>do not use
   credit to do so</i>.)</p> <p><strong>Step 2:&nbsp;Pick a
   goal.</strong></p> <p>Pick a goal that is right for you and your
   family.</p> <p>You may want to take a vacation at the end of the
   year.</p> <p>You may want to pay off your credit cards.</p> <p>You may
   want to build up your saving account. Money for your children&rsquo;s
   college.</p> <p>Save money for a down payment on a house.</p> <p>Money
   for retirement.</p> <p><strong>Think of your goal every time you save
   money.</strong> This will help you meet your goal.</p> <p><strong>Step
   3:</strong></p> <p>Remember no spending does not mean NO fun. Pick
   things that you feel are non-essential for you.</body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   temperature</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">+ 3 Tablespoons all-purpose
   flour</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Brownies:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   chocolate chips and butter in a medium microwave safe bowl in 20 second
   increments, stirring after each, in the microwave. Remove from the
   heat, pour into a large mixing bowl, and allow to slightly cool for 10
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Adjust
   the oven rack to the lower third position and preheat oven to 350F
   degrees. Line the bottom and sides of a 9x13 baking pan with aluminum
   foil or parchment paper, leaving an overhang on all sides. Set
   aside.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   the granulated and brown sugars into the cooled chocolate/butter
   mixture.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   eggs, one at a time, whisking until smooth after each addition.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   in the vanilla.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Gently
   fold in the salt, flour, and cocoa powder.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   batter into the prepared baking pan and bake for 35-36 minutes or until
   the brownies begin to pull away from the edges of the pan. A toothpick
   inserted in the center should come out with only a few moist crumbs
   when the brownies are done. All ovens are different, so keep an eye on
   them after 30 minutes and use the toothpick test to see when yours are
   finished. Allow the brownies to cool completely in the pan set on a
   wire rack.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   completely cooled, lift the foil out of the pan using the overhang on
   the sides.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the whole thing on a baking sheet as you make the frosting.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Do not
   cut into squares yet.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Top and Bottom
   layer:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt in
   a medium microwave safe bowl in 20 second increments, stirring after
   each, in the microwave.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   melted gently spread 1/2 of the chocolate chip mixture evenly in a
   bottom of a 9x13 inch pan with a knife.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in refrigerator for 1/2 hour to set the chocolate.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the middle area:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl using a handheld or stand mixer fitted with a paddle
   attachment, beat the butter on medium speed until smooth and creamy,
   about 2 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   confectioners sugar and milk. Beat for 2 minutes on low speed, then
   increase to high speed and beat for 1 additional minute.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   on top of chocolate chip mixture, then place cooked brownies on
   top.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with other 1/2 of chocolate chip mixture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59539-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate until ready to serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>More <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=brownies">Brownie
   Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   https://myhoneysplace.com/10-home-remedies-for-chiggers-bites/ Sat, 28
   Jul 2018 11:34:18 +0000 My Honeys Place DIY And Tips
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53077 10 Home Remedies For Chigger Bites.
   Chiggers are a&#160;juvenile forms... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-home-remedies-for-chiggers-bites/">C
   ontinue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53083 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Home-Remed
   ies-For-Chiggers-Bites.jpg" alt="10 Home Remedies For Chigger Bites.
   The best DIY tips to relieve that terrible itching from chigger bites."
   width="600" height="900" data-id="53083"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Home-Re
   medies-For-Chiggers-Bites.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Home-Remedies-F
   or-Chiggers-Bites-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"><strong>10 Home Remedies For Chigger Bites.</strong></p>
   <p>Chiggers are a&nbsp;juvenile forms of a mite. Chiggers are only
   barely visible to the naked eye. Juvenile forms are red in color and
   have 6 legs.&nbsp;Adult chiggers don&rsquo;t bite. It&rsquo;s the
   babies, called larvae, that you have to watch out for. They&rsquo;re
   red, orange, yellow, or straw-colored, and no more than 0.3 millimeters
   long.</p> <p>They&nbsp;live in all parts of the world. They are most
   commonly found in:</p> <ul> <li>forests,</li> <li>grassy fields,</li>
   <li>parks, gardens, and</li> <li>in moist areas around lakes or
   rivers.</li> <li><strong>Symptoms</strong> of chigger bites include
   intense itching, and flat or raised red&nbsp;bumps&nbsp;on the skin.
   They sometimes have an appearance of a blister.</li> </ul> <p>The only
   effective treatments are anti-itch creams and medications, such as
   Benadryl.&nbsp; Both&nbsp;calamine&nbsp;lotion and corticosteroid
   creams may be useful in reducing the itching of chigger bites. Home
   remedies to relieve itching, such as cool showers or baths, colloidal
   oatmeal baths, or cool compresses may bring some relief.</p>
   <p><strong>Home Remedies:</strong></p> <p><strong>1.</strong> Take a
   <strong>Dobie pad</strong> ( for washing dishes) and scrub in the
   shower. It will get seed ticks, chiggers, and exfoliate your skin at
   the same time. When you get out, use baby oil or a itch cream.</p>
   <p><strong>2</strong>. Apply <strong>clear nail polish</strong> to the
   area.</p> <p><strong>3. Vicks vaporub</strong> may stop the itching
   itching.</p> <p><strong>4.</strong> This is an old recipe for chiggers
   on your body. Put a small amount of <strong>salt</strong> in the palm
   of your hand. Add a drop or two of water to make a paste, rub it on the
   chigger bite. In just a little while you will see a red dot appear.
   That&rsquo;s the chigger. If all over your body, set in a tub of
   <strong>epsom salt</strong> water.</p> <p><strong>5. Baking
   soda</strong> add water and enough to make a paste and rub it on
   it.</p> <p><strong>6. Alcohol</strong> on cotton balls. Wipe the area.
   It also get rid of the remaining chiggers.</p> <p><strong>7.</strong>
   Put an <strong>ice pack</strong> on the place where you have been
   bitten for a quick relief from itching. You can also put a topical
   cream, like Neosprin.</p> <p><strong>8.</strong> In order to reduce the
   excessive itchiness, wrap the area with an <strong>ace
   bandage</strong>. This will interrupt the air supply and reduce
   itching.</p> <p><strong>9.</strong> After washing the affected area
   with soap and water, soak a cotton ball in some <strong>Listerine
   mouthwash</strong> and apply it to the chigger rash.</p>
   <p><strong>10.</strong> Massage some <strong>castor oil</strong> on the
   affected skin to get relief from the itchiness and
   irritation</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   sugar</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-0"

   5px">Pre-heat the oven to 425F.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using
   cooking spray coat the muffin pan. Make sure that the whole top is
   covered, not just the part that the batter goes into.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   paper muffin/cupcake liners into the muffin pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   dry ingredients in a medium bowl and mix with a whisk so that
   everything is well combined. Stir in 1 3/4 cups of the chocolate
   chips.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl combine all the wet ingredients, making sure the eggs are
   well incorporated as well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the wet ingredients into the dry and stir until just combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scoop
   out the batter evenly into each section of the muffin pan.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the tops of the batter with the remaining chocolate chips
   and the coarse sugar.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   the oven for 7 minutes at 425F then reduce the heat to 375F and bake
   for 15-20 min.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59537-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   the muffins are finished baking cool in the muffin pan for 5-10
   minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>More Muffin <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=muffins+">Recipes</a></strong></p>

   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=chocolate+">Chocolate

   600px"><strong>Crispy Peach Turnovers</strong>.</p> <p>An easy dessert
   recipe made with fresh peaches covered in a crispy crunchy&nbsp;
   crust.</p> <p>Then sugar sprinkled on top.</p> <p><div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-59531" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="59531"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img
   style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;"

   wprm-block-text-bold">Crispy Peach Turnovers</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sheet puff pastry</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">thawed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh peaches</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">raw sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg whites for brushing top of
   turnovers</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar for
   sprinkling</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash,
   peel, and finely dice peaches. Mix together with sugar and cornstarch.
   Heat the peach mixture on medium-low and simmer until thickened, 5 to 7
   minutes. Set aside to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   the puff pastry. Cut the pastry into 8 equal squares for mini
   turnovers, or 6 squares for larger turnovers.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 425.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the peach mixture has cooled, spoon 1-2 tablespoons of peaches onto the
   puff pastry squares, off center. Fold the pastry over the filling to
   make a square and seal the perimeter by pinching the edges or pressing
   the tines of a fork into the dough.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the turnovers on a baking sheet and brush with the egg white.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   until the dough is crispy and golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59531-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">As soon
   as removing from oven sprinkle the sugar over the top.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p style="text-align:
   center;"><b>More Recipes&nbsp;using </b><a style="font-weight: bold;"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=peaches+">Peaches</a></p>
