   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-remove-bad-smells-from-your-carpet/
   Tue, 24 Jul 2018 13:40:19 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY
   And Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53039 How To Remove Bad Smells
   From Your Carpet. DIY tips... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-remove-bad-smells-from-your-carp
   et/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br
   /> <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53040 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/How-To-Remove
   -Bad-Smells-From-Your-Carpet.jpg" alt="How To Remove Bad Smells From
   Your Carpet. DIY tips for removing a stinky carpet smell and
   stains.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900" data-id="53040"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/How-To-Rem
   ove-Bad-Smells-From-Your-Carpet.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/How-To-Remove-Bad-
   Smells-From-Your-Carpet-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"><strong>How To Remove Bad Smells From Your
   Carpet</strong>.</p> <p>DIY tips for removing a stinky carpet smell and
   stains:</p> <p><strong>1.</strong>&nbsp;Your&nbsp;carpet&nbsp;is one of
   the key smell-trappers of your home. But there&rsquo;s an even easier
   way to eliminate&nbsp;carpet&nbsp;odors,&nbsp;using<b>
   Febreze</b>&nbsp;<strong>Fabric Refresher</strong>! Application
   couldn&rsquo;t be easier; just spray&nbsp;Febreze&nbsp;all over until
   it&rsquo;s damp! Let it dry and the uninvited smells are gone.</p>
   <p><strong>2.</strong> 50/50 <strong>vinegar/baking soda
   mixture</strong>, let sit, wipe, dry &amp; vacuum.</p> <p><strong>3.
   Detergent solution:</strong> Mix 1/4 teaspoon of a translucent liquid
   dish washing detergent, such as Dawn or Joy, into one cup of lukewarm
   water.&nbsp;Dip a white cloth into these solutions and apply to the
   stain. Never pour the solutions directly onto carpeting.</p>
   <p><strong>4.</strong> Sprinkle <strong>baking soda</strong> over your
   carpet! Let it set for about 20 minutes and then vacuum up. It works
   great and it&rsquo;s a very cheap way to refresh your carpet.</p>
   <p><strong>5. DRY coffee grounds</strong> work wonders. Sprinkle them
   on let them sit, vacuum them up. Use them on anything and everything
   that needs odor removed. Or for a stinky drawer put a tablespoon fresh
   coffee grounds in a coffee filter rubber banded and throw in each
   drawer and will suck the smell right out.</p> <p><strong>6. Steam
   clean</strong> with a bit of <strong>bleach</strong> in with the
   cleaning solution. It works great.</p> <p><strong>7.</strong> Spray
   lots of <strong>straight white vinegar</strong> on it! I use it all the
   time on almost everything. Smell goes away!</p> <p><strong>8. Baking
   soda and borax</strong>:&nbsp;The ingredients that you will need to
   make the deodorizer include half a cup of baking soda, half a cup of
   borax and one teaspoon of ground spices. <strong>Cinnamon</strong> is a
   great option to try in this recipe. Mix these ingredients well and
   store in a dry, well-ventilated place. Sprinkle the mix on a carpet
   that smells bad and leave it on for at least 30 minutes. Vacuum clean
   and you should be left solely with the enticing scent of the ground
   spices.</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   the cavities with the cheese filling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59529-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   with the mozzarella.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59529-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the mushroom caps onto a Power Air Fryer Oven tray.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59529-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   370 for 12 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p
   style="text-align: center;"><strong>More <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/favorite-recipes/air-fryer-rec
   ipes/">Air Fryer Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p>

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Homemade Lemon Boozy Ice Cream</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream double
   cream</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">full fat milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Lemon peel from 1
   lemon</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg yolks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">+ 1 tbsp sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Limoncello
   liqueur</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   cream, milk and lemon peel to a sauce pan and bring to a boil.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Meanwhile whisk the egg yolks and sugar together in a bowl until
   light and fluffy.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">**Tip:
   When the milk and cream comes to a boil turn off the heat to avoid it
   overflowing and set it aside for 1 minute before continuing with the
   next step.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the lemon zest from the milk and discard.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Very
   slow, gradually add the hot milk mixture to the beaten eggs and sugar
   whilst constantly whisking. Continue until the mixture is completely
   incorporated.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   mixture back to the saucepan and heat on a low heat whilst stirring
   with a wooden spoon. It'll take about 10 minutes for the mixture to
   thicken enough to coat the back of the wooden spoon.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   thickened, remove from the heat for 10 minutes then add the Limoncello
   and stir. Set aside to cool for around 20-30 minutes before using the
   ice cream machine.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Churn the
   mixture according to your ice cream mixer directions.</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Or:</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   the freezer bowl out of the freezer and place into the machine, add the
   paddle and the top then turn it on.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   machine MUST be on and turning before adding the ice cream mixture.
   Pour the mixture into the machine and leave it to churn for 25-30
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Youll
   have very soft ice cream at this point.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59527-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   the mixture into a freezer proof container and freeze for a few hours
   or overnight to stiffen.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=ice+cream+">Ice Cream
   Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div

   Mon, 23 Jul 2018 13:23:03 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY
   And Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=53014 Best Kept Secret To Keep
   Your Teeth Healthy. A better... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/best-kept-secret-to-keep-your-teeth-hea
   lthy/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br
   /> <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53015 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Best-Kept-Sec
   ret-To-Keep-Your-Teeth-Healthy.jpg" alt="Best Kept Secret To Keep Your
   Teeth Healthy. A better way to clean your teeth. A lot cheaper, easier
   and less messy than an expensive WaterPik.&nbsp;" width="600"
   height="900" data-id="53015"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Best-Kept-
   Secret-To-Keep-Your-Teeth-Healthy.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Best-Kept-Secret-T
   o-Keep-Your-Teeth-Healthy-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"><strong>Best Kept Secret To Keep Your Teeth
   Healthy</strong>.</p> <p>A better way to clean your teeth. A lot
   cheaper, easier and less messy than an expensive WaterPik. You can buy
   them a Walmart or any drug store.</p> <p><strong>Ways to clean your
   teeth:</strong></p> <p><strong>First you need to brush your
   teeth</strong></p> <ul> <li>Place your toothbrush at a 45-degree angle
   to the gums.</li> <li>Gently move the brush back and forth in short
   (tooth-wide) strokes.</li> <li>Brush the outer surfaces, the inner
   surfaces, and the chewing surfaces of the teeth.</li> <li>To clean the
   inside surfaces of the front teeth, tilt the brush vertically and make
   several up-and-down strokes. Watch video <strong><a
   href="https://www.mouthhealthy.org/en/az-topics/b/brushing-your-teeth"
   target="_blank" rel="noopener">HERE</a></strong></li> </ul>
   <p><strong>Then floss your teeth</strong>: Watch video<strong><a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/proper-way-to-floss-your-teeth-video/">
   Here</a></strong></p> <p><strong>The Secret</strong>: Instead of buying
   an expensive waterpik you can use a syringe. Like the one pictured
   above. Not messy like a waterpik.</p> <ul> <li>Fill the syringe with
   warm water.</li> <li>Place the tip at the <strong>gum line</strong> of
   each tooth. Cup your mouth tightly around the tip of the syringe and
   push a small amount of the water from the syringe. Pull out the syringe
   from your mouth then you can then swallow the warm water without
   opening your mouth.&nbsp; Repeat this process between each tooth.</li>
   </ul> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53012 size-full"

   <p>A yummy dessert recipe filled with a lemon filling, blueberry sauce
   and all wrapped in homemade crepes.</p> <p>Topped with a powered sugar
   topping.</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59525"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="59525"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:
   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Homemade-Blue
   berry-Crepes-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150"
   alt=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Homemade-B

   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Homemade Blueberry Crepes</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Crepes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbs.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Maple Syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">melted coconut
   oil</span></li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Lemon filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">finely grated fresh lemon
   zest</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">stick 6 tablespoons unsalted
   butter</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into
   bits</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Blueberry
   sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen organic
   blueberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Pure Maple Syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Water adjust water amount according
   to preferred sauce consistency. Start with 1/4 Cup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cornstarch adjust amount as needed
   to attain the preferred sauce consistency. Start with 2 Tablespoons and
   work up to 3 Tablespoons if you want it almost
   jam-like.</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">margarine or butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">softened</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3 to 4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk or
   half-and-half</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Crepes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make
   the batter in your blender or whisk the ingredients in a mixing
   bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let the
   batter sit if you prefer, an hour or up to overnight in the
   fridge.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Or
   immediately pour 1/4 Cup of the batter into the center of a heated non
   stick 8 inch frying pan with just a teeny bit of coconut oil or butter
   melted in the pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Immediately pick up the pan and swirl the batter so it covers the
   bottom of the pan evenly and return to burner.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let
   cook briefly until the edges firm and lighten.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Flip
   the crepe over with a spatula.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   very quickly until just done and remove to serving plate. Repeat until
   the batter is gone.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Lemon
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together juice, zest, sugar, and eggs in a 2-quart heavy
   saucepan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   butter and cook over moderately low heat, whisking frequently, until
   filling is thick enough to hold the marks of the whisk. Do Not
   Boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the first bubble appears on surface, about 6 minutes; remove from heat
   immediately.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer lemon topping to a covered bowl and chill until cold, at
   least 1 hour.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Blueberry
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   blueberries and maple syrup in a 2 quart sauce pan on medium
   heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together the cornstarch and water.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-2-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the cornstarch water into the blueberries and stir until its
   mixed.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-2-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   the berries until they boil. Stir it on a low boil for about a minute
   until the cornstarch turns clear and the sauce thickens.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-2-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat. Cool it to room temperature.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-3-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In
   medium bowl, combine all ingredients until smooth, adding enough milk
   for desired glaze consistency.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Put it
   together:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59525-step-4-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   the lemon filling on the cooled crepes. Add the blueberry sauce. Wrap
   the crepes and pour topping across top.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>More <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=blueberry+">Blueberry
   Recipes&nbsp;</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lemon juice</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">King Arthur Pie Filling
   Enhancer**</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">*If using frozen peaches</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">be sure they're thawed and at room
   temperature before proceeding.</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">**Don't have Pie Filling Enhancer?
   See tips</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">below.</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">TOPPING:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Pastry Flour Blend or King Arthur
   Unbleached All-Purpose Flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 to 1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">enough to make a cohesive
   dough</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 to 2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk or melted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for brushing on top</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">coarse white sparkling sugar</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for sprinkling on top,
   optional</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 350F. Lightly grease a 9" round pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   the filling: Combine all the filling ingredients, and spoon the peaches
   into the prepared pan.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   the topping: Whisk or sift together the flour, salt, baking powder, and
   sugar.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   enough heavy cream to moisten the dough thoroughly. You'll probably use
   about 1 cup in the summer, 1 1/4 cups in the winter, and 1 cup + 2
   tablespoons at the turn of the seasons. You want to be able to gather
   the dough together, squeeze it, and have it hang together, without dry
   bits falling off.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pat the
   dough into a lightly greased 9" round pan. Use a 2" round biscuit
   cutter to cut as many biscuits as you can, leaving them in the pan.
   Turn the pan over onto a lightly greased or lightly floured surface,
   rapping it a few times to make the dough fall out. Lift off the pan,
   pick up the cut biscuits, and space them atop the peach filling. You'll
   have leftover biscuit dough; shape it into additional biscuits to bake
   separately, if desired.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush
   the biscuits with milk or butter, and sprinkle with coarse white
   sparkling sugar, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the cobbler for 45 to 50 minutes, until the filling is bubbly and the
   biscuits are golden brown.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the cobbler from the oven, and let it rest at room temperature for
   about 20 to 30 minutes before serving; this allows the filling to set
   somewhat. Don't worry, it'll still be warm when you serve it.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scoop
   the cobbler into serving dishes, including a biscuit with each serving.
   Top with vanilla ice cream, if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59523-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Yield:
   about 12 servings.</div> </li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Notes</h3><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span
   style="display: block;">Pie Filling Enhancer, a combination of
   extra-fine sugar, thickener, and ascorbic acid, improves both the
   flavor of the fruit, and provides the necessary thickening. Replace it
   with 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with the sugar before adding to the
   fruit, if desired. If you make this substitution, increase the sugar in
   the recipe to 3/4 cup</span></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>Recipe
   courtesy and reprinted with permission of&nbsp;<a
   href="http://www.kingarthurflour.com/" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener">King Arthur Flour</a></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   https://myhoneysplace.com/13-reasons-to-use-a-cast-iron-skillet/ Thu,
   19 Jul 2018 22:33:41 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And
   Tips Simple DIY Projects https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52998 13 Reasons
   To Use A Cast Iron Skillet. Included is... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/13-reasons-to-use-a-cast-iron-skillet/"
   >Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><strong><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52999 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/13-Reasons-To
   -Use-A-Cast-Iron-Skillet.jpg" alt='13 Reasons To Use A Cast Iron
   Skillet. Included is how to "season" and care for an iron skillet. I
   love my iron skillet and have had it for over 40 years. Still in
   perfect shape.' width="600" height="900" data-id="52999"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/13-Reasons
   -To-Use-A-Cast-Iron-Skillet.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/13-Reasons-To-Use-
   A-Cast-Iron-Skillet-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></strong></p> <p><strong>13 Reasons To Use A Cast Iron
   Skillet.</strong></p> <p>Included is how to &ldquo;season&rdquo; and
   care for an iron skillet.</p> <p>I love my iron skillet and have had it
   for over 40 years. Still in perfect shape.</p> <ol> <li>Has been used
   for thousands of years.</li> <li>No toxic fumes when you cook.</li>
   <li>Can take high heat, even in your oven</li> <li>It is non
   stick.</li> <li>It is inexpensive.</li> <li>Beautifully brown
   food.</li> <li>Has better heat distribution.</li> <li>Can be used a
   grill.</li> <li>Usable over a campfire.</li> <li>It can cook multi
   foods at once.</li> <li>Will boost your iron intake.</li> <li>Cleans up
   easily.</li> <li><strong>And in a pinch you can use it as a
   weapon.&nbsp;</strong></li> </ol> <p><strong>How to season an iron
   skillet:</strong></p> <p>Traditional&nbsp;cast-iron
   skillets&nbsp;don&rsquo;t emerge from the box with a nonstick surface.
   That comes with&nbsp;seasoning, or coating the&nbsp;skillet&nbsp;with
   cooking oil.</p> <ol class="X5LH0c"> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">Scrub&nbsp;skillet&nbsp;well in hot soapy water.</li>
   <li class="TrT0Xe">Dry thoroughly.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Spread a
   thin layer of melted shortening or vegetable oil over
   the&nbsp;skillet.</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Place it upside down on a
   middle oven rack at 375&deg;. (Place foil on a lower rack to catch
   drips.)</li> <li class="TrT0Xe">Bake 1 hour; let cool in the oven.</li>
   </ol> <p>It won&rsquo;t take on that shiny black patina just yet, but
   once&nbsp;you&nbsp;dry it with paper towels, it will be ready to
   use.</p> <h4 class="title style-scope
   ytd-video-primary-info-renderer">Easy Trick To Clean Cast Iron:</h4>
   <p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/a5NbQwzwUTw" width="350"
   height="350" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></body></html></p>

   pieces</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   candies</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut horizontally in
   half</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59521-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   pudding mix and milk in large bowl with whisk 2 min.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59521-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   COOL WHIP.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59521-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Layer
   7-1/2 grahams and half the COOL WHIP mixture in 13x9-inch pan, breaking
   grahams as necessary to fit; repeat layers. Top with remaining
   grahams.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59521-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Microwave frosting in small microwaveable bowl on HIGH 20 to 30
   sec. or until softened but not melted. (Do not overheat). Stir; spread
   over grahams.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59521-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerate 4 hours. Cut into squares. Decorate with remaining
   ingredients to resemble photo just before serving.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Increase heat to med-high and bring mixture to a rolling
   boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59519-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   frequently mashing the strawberries as you stir, continuing to boil,

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer jam to a jar and let cool to room temperature.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59519-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Seal
   jars and store in refrigerator for about 10 days (or freeze)</div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg yolks</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">The cookie
   dough:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vegetable oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mini chocolate
   chips</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">The Ice
   cream:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan over low heat, heat the heavy cream, milk, chocolate,
   and 1/4 cup of the sugar. Heat until mixture begins to steam and is
   scalding, but isn't boiling.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   separate bowl, whisk together the remaining sugar, egg yolks, and cocoa
   powder. Using a ladle, whisk in 1 cup of the heated cream mixture.
   Then, whisk the entire thing back into the main saucepan.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Continue to stir the mixture gently for around 5 minutes, until
   the mixture thickens and fully coats the back of a spoon. Remove from
   heat, stir in vanilla extract and salt, then place saucepan in an ice
   bath to cool for 5 minutes. Transfer mixture to a quart-sized zip lock
   bag and place in the fridge to cool completely, about 4 hours.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">The cookie dough:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   the cookie dough, combine the butter and sugars in a medium bowl. Stir
   until combined, then add in the flour, oil, and chocolate chips.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   with plastic wrap and place dough in fridge to cool for 30 minutes.
   After 30 minutes, remove from fridge and roll into centimeter-sized
   balls. Place back in fridge to harden.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   the ice cream has cooled for 4 hours, churn in ice cream maker
   according to manufacturer's instructions. Remove from mixer, fold in
   cookie dough pieces by hand, and scoop the entire thing into a large
   freezer-safe container.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59517-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   with plastic wrap and freeze for at least 8 hours, preferably
   overnight.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />
   </body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin:
   8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script
   async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">corn starch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cake flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pinch</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 </span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg yolk slightly
   beaten</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Zest of 2 lemons very finely
   chopped</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Juice of 2 lemons</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   meringue:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg whites</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream of tarter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Pinch</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla
   extract</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   food processor or a pastry blender cut cold butter into flour and salt
   until mixture resembles a coarse meal. Small pieces of butter should
   still be visible.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   cold water over the mixture and work in by tossing with a fork until
   dough begins to form. Use your hands as little as possible and work the
   dough as little as possible.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   dough into 2 balls, flatten into 2 rounds, wrap in plastic wrap and
   place in the refrigerator to rest for a minimum of 20 minutes. You can
   freeze the second round for another time.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">You can
   make your dough the previous day but make sure you take it out of the
   fridge for 10 minutes to warm slightly before rolling out.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   the dough into a 12 inch round and place in the bottom of a 10 inch pie
   plate.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Trim
   and flute the edges as desired. Poke a few holes in the bottom of the
   pastry shell, rest in the refrigerator for an additional 20 minutes
   before baking at 400 degrees F for 12  15 minutes or until golden
   brown.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cool
   completely before adding the filling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan, combine corn starch, cake flour, sugar and salt. Pour
   in water and stir constantly over medium low heat until mixture comes
   to a slow boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   the pan from the heat and reduce the flame to low.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   about a cup of this mixture onto the slightly beaten egg yolks while
   whisking constantly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the egg mixture back into the rest of the other mixture in the pot,
   whisking constantly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Return
   to the stove and cook for an additional 3 minutes stirring
   constantly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat and stir in lemon juice and lemon rind.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Finally
   whisk in your butter one tbsp at a time.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-1-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the filling into the baked and cooled shell. Let stand for a few
   minutes while preparing the meringue.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   meringue:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whip
   egg whites, vanilla, salt and cream of tarter to soft peaks.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Very
   gradually add the sugar while continuing to beat the egg whites.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Dollop in heaping tablespoonfuls onto pie. Gently
   spread over the filling, making sure that the meringue touches the
   crust all the way around the pie. This will help to prevent the
   meringue from shrinking.</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-3-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake in
   a 325 degree F oven for about 20 to 25 minutes or until the meringue is
   well browned. Cool pie thoroughly in the refrigerator before
   serving.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59513-step-3-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Keep
   refrigerated.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />
   </body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin:
   8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script

   Blue Moon Smoothie. A blueberry, banana, high protein smoothie drink...
   <a class="continue-reading-link"

   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52950 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-Smo
   othie.jpg" alt="Blue Moon Smoothie. A blueberry, banana, high protein
   smoothie drink recipe. Perfect for breakfast or an anytime
   snack.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900" data-id="52950"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-
   Smoothie.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-Smoothie
   -267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"><strong>Blue
   Moon Smoothie. </strong></p> <p>A blueberry, banana, high protein
   smoothie drink recipe.</p> <p>Perfect for breakfast or an anytime
   snack.</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59509"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="59509"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:
   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-Smo
   othie-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-
   Smoothie-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-Smoothie
   -500x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Blue-Moon-Smoothie
   -50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></div> </div>
   <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59509" style=""
   class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode
   wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe-id="59509" target="_blank"
   rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon
   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Blue Moon Smoothie</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen unsweetened
   blueberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">medium banana</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced and frozen</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plain nonfat Greek
   yogurt</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened vanilla almond
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ice
   cubes</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59509-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add all
   of the ingredients to a blender in the order listed, and blend until
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59509-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   immediately.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">whole chicken</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">onions</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">celery</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cloves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of garlic</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">of carrots</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped into coins</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen peas</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">bay leaves</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dried thyme</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dried parsley flakes</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Water</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">as needed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Additional salt and pepper</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put
   your chicken into a large pot and cover with water.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add a
   little salt and bring to a boil. Once it comes to a good rolling boil
   for a few minutes, lower the heat to between LOW and MEDIUM. Put the
   lid on and let it cook for about 1 hour on the stove.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Open
   the pot and check to see how the chicken is doing. When the meat is
   more tender and JUST STARTS to come off the chicken it's time for the
   next step.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using
   tongs or another kitchen tool to remove the chicken from the pot and
   set on a cookie sheet or large plate. The only thing that should be
   left in the pot is the liquid.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   the chicken cools for a couple minutes so you can work with it easier,
   skim off some of the fat that's accumulated on the surface of the pot.
   You don't have to remove it all since it does give the soup a great
   flavor but if there's a lot you should try to remove some. The amount
   of fat you have on the top depends on the chicken itself  some are
   fattier than others.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Using a
   fork and knife, remove as much meat as possible from the chicken and
   drop it into the pot. Cut the meat into chunks.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make
   sure that you add the leg bones to the pot along with the meat. The
   bones are extremely important in making the soup taste perfect.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Once
   all the meat is removed from the chicken you can discard the unused
   parts.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Now add
   the vegetables, garlic and herbs to the pot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   some water to the pot until the veggies, etc are covered.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bring
   to a rolling boil once more for a couple minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-11" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lower
   the heat to about between LOW and MEDIUM, cover and let it cook for 1
   more hour.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-12"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   the soup a couple times while it cooks.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-13" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">At the
   end of cooking give the soup a taste and add a little more salt and
   pepper to taste.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-14"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let it
   cook for a couple more minutes and remove the leg bones and bay
   leaves.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59507-step-0-15"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***
   serve hot or refrigerate to warm up later.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Easiest Way To Clean Your Coffee Pot</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white vinegar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Make a
   mixture of 3 cups white vinegar to 6 cups water-- enough to fill the
   pot.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put a
   filter in your coffee maker, as usual.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the mixture into the coffee maker where you would normally add
   water.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   the coffee maker on and let the mixture run completely through.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Discard
   the filter and mixture.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let the
   coffee maker sit and cool for 15 minutes while it's off.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Rinse
   the coffee pot.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59505-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Repeat
   all of the above a second time, but this time with plain cold water.
   This will make sure all of the vinegar and water solution is completely
   gone.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div> </p>
   <p></body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>
