   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsweetened cocoa
   powder</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg whites</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">preferably at room
   temperature</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream of tartar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Sugar</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the Caramel
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heavy cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">to taste</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For The
   Cookies:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the egg whites in a large mixing bowl, and add the cream of tartar.
   Whip the egg whites, on medium-high speed, until fluffy. Slowly add in
   the sugar, while whipping. When all the sugar has been added, turn the
   speed up to high and continue to whip until stiff.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   cocoa mixture, all at once, and fold until the mixture drops
   firmly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the batter onto parchment-lined baking sheets, in 1 1/2-inch circles.
   Set them out to dry for 45 minutes to an hour, or until a thin, dry
   membrane has formed on the surface of the macarons.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the macarons in the hot oven. Turn the oven temperature down to 300
   degrees F, and bake for 18 minutes (do not brown). Allow the macarons
   to cool completely on the baking sheets.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For The
   Caramel Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small pot, gently heat the cream, butter, and salt until the butter has
   melted and the salt has completely dissolved. Remove from heat and add
   the vanilla.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   larger pot, combine the sugar, corn syrup, and water. Heat over a
   medium high flame, swirling the pot occasionally to distribute the heat
   evenly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Continue to boil the sugar mixture until the bubbles begin to get
   smaller and it becomes amber-colored.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   the heat to low, and pour in the warm cream mixture, whisking
   constantly to avoid lumps or crystals.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Immediately transfer the hot mixture to a heat-safe vessel and
   cool completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59503-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">***Place cooled caramel sauce between cooled cookies.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52923 size-full"

   they were young.&nbsp; Works fantastic.</p> <p><strong>Apply Vapor Rub
   to the bottom of you or your child&rsquo;s feet and put on socks. Works
   100% of the time and has proven to be more effective than prescription
   drugs.&nbsp;</strong></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>More
   uses for Vapor Rub:</strong></p> <p><b>Decongestant For Your
   Chest&nbsp;</b><br /> The most common use of Vapo rub is a decongestant
   for your chest and throat area. When applied to the upper chest, it
   provides excellent relief of cough and congestion symptoms.</p>
   <p><b>&nbsp;Achy Muscles</b><br /> Vapo Rub relieves sore, overworked
   muscles. It increases circulation and provides almost instant aid. Use
   a generous portion and apply it all over the aching area.</p>
   <p><strong>Sinuses&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Put in boiling water for
   sinuses. Boil for about 30 minutes.</p> <p><strong>Prevent
   Infection</strong></p> <p>To prevent infection and speed up healing
   time, dab a small amount of Vapo Rub on any small cut or splinter.</p>
   <p><strong>Keep Insects away</strong></p> <p>Rub VapoRub on your neck,
   behind your ears, inner knees and elbows. Insects be gone! You could
   also open a jar and place it on your picnic table to keep bugs
   away.</p> <p><b>&nbsp;Nail Fungus</b><br /> Rub VapoRub on your
   toenails if you suspect you have a fungus. Within days, the nail will
   turn dark&mdash;this means the Vicks is killing the fungus. As your
   toenail grows out, the dark part will grow off and you will have
   fungus-free feet. Keep applying the ointment over a period of two weeks
   to fully cleanse nail beds of any remaining bacteria.</p> <p><b>Stop
   Your Cat from Scratching&nbsp;</b><br /> Cats are notorious for
   scratching every hard surface they get their claws on. To prevent your
   kitty from ruining your doors, walls, and windows, apply a small amount
   of VapoRub to these areas. Cats detest the smell and will steer clear.
   Vicks can also be applied to your arms and legs if your kitty is prone
   to scratching you.</p> <p><strong>Treat cracked heels</strong></p>
   <p>Apply to heels and cover with socks at bedtime. The next morning
   wash your feet with warm water. Exfoliate the skin with a pumice stone.
   This will keep your feet healthy and smooth.</p>
   <p><b>Headaches&nbsp;</b><br /> Rub a small amount of VapoRub on your
   temples and forehead to help relieve headaches. The mentholated scent
   will release pressure in your head and instantly relieve
   pain.</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:
   both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   spray a 9x13-inch pan with cooking spray. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp, stirring
   occasionally.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   pan from heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   bacon with a slotted spoon; drain on paper towels and chop.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large saucepan, add chicken stock, and Ranch dressing mix; bring to a
   boil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   stir in grits.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   heat to medium-low; cook, covered, 5 to 7 minutes or until thickened,
   stirring occasionally. Remove from heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   Velveeta cheese and butter; stir until melted. Stir in milk. Slowly
   stir in eggs until blended. Stir in half of cooked bacon.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-9"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Transfer grits to prepared dish. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and
   remaining bacon.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59501-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake,
   uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   your oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   your pan with foil and cooking spray and set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix the
   first 4 ingredients in a bowl until combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   decent portions of the chicken mixture into your tortillas. Add a
   liberal pile of cheese and spinach.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   the left and right sides of the tortillas into the middle and then fold
   the bottom flap over the two sides and roll it away from you to close
   the burrito (you'll be rolling it onto the remaining top flap to close
   it).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   each burrito onto your pan and sprinkle each one with a bit of cheese
   if desired.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59499-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 20 minutes and enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br
   /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ketchup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">beef bouillon cube</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">crumbled</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Worcestershire sauce</span></li><li

   powder</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Gravy</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">minced</span></li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">finely chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mushrooms</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">plain flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">beef stock</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dijon mustard</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Worcestershire sauce</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt and
   pepper</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Steaks</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   breadcrumbs in a bowl. Use a box grater and grate the onion over the
   breadcrumbs. Mix with fingers, leave to soak for a few minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   remaining Salisbury Steak ingredients into the large bowl. Use your
   hands to mix until just combined - don't over mix.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   into 5 and pat into oval patties around 3/4" / 1 2/3 cm thick.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cooking and Gravy</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oil in a skillet over high heat. Add the steaks and cook the first side
   for 1 minute or until browned, then flip and brown the other side (they
   will still be raw inside). Remove onto plate.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If
   skillet is looking dry, add a touch more oil. Add chopped onion and
   garlic and cook for 2 minute until onions are a bit translucent.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   mushrooms into the skillet and cook for 2 - 3 minutes until
   golden.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   heat down to medium. Add butter. Once melted, add flour and cook for 30
   seconds, stirring constantly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Gradually add in beef broth, stirring as you go. Once mostly lump
   free, whisk in remaining Gravy ingredients.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   steaks along with the juices on the plate. Cook for 5 - 7 minutes, or
   until gravy is thickened, stirring occasionally around the steaks. If
   the gravy thickens too quickly, add more water.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   steaks onto a plate. Taste gravy and adjust salt and pepper to
   taste.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59497-step-1-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   steaks topped with the mushroom gravy - over mashed potato is ideal!
   Sprinkle with a bit of parsley if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   <div class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shredded unsweetened
   coconut</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">coconut oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">t.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chocolate chips - I like dark
   chocolate</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Warm
   coconut oil until it is liquid.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   everything except the chocolate chips in a blender and blend on high
   until smooth. (This will take about 5 minutes or so.)</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   into a 9x5 plastic container.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Freeze
   for about 15 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   coconut mixture is freezing, melt chocolate chips.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cut the
   coconut mixture into bite size bars.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   into the melted chocolate chips and place each in clean dish.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Return
   to freezer for about 15 more minutes or until firm.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59495-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Store
   leftovers in refrigerator.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">lite soy sauce</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1-2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cloves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced
   garlic</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   all sauce ingredients into a gallon size zip lock bag and seal. Squeeze
   gently to combine ingredients, then add salmon fillets.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Seal
   and refrigerate for 1 to 3 hours to allow flavors to penetrate the
   fish.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   grill to medium high heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">For
   each salmon fillet, take a piece of heavy duty aluminum foil and fold
   around the fish with sides, to handle the foil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   salmon fillet into each foil with skin side down. Add a little of the
   sauce on top and place the entire foil on the grill.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grill
   for 18-20 minutes with the lid closed.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   foil and place the salmon onto the grill to sear the top, about 1-2
   minutes each side.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59493-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Carefully scrape off the skin (it should lift right off) and
   serve.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52862 size-full"

   topped with buttercream frosting then plop a fresh strawberry on
   top.</p> <p>Yummy!</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59491"

   strawberries</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees and prepare a cupcake pan with cupcake
   liners.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   butter and sugar until light in color and fluffy, about 2-3
   minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   sour cream and strawberry extract and mix until well combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add egg
   whites in two batches, mixing until well combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   dry ingredients in another bowl, then combine milk and strawberry puree
   in another bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   half of the dry ingredients to the batter and mix until well combined.
   Add the milk mixture and mix until well combined. Add remaining dry
   ingredients and mix until well combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   pink color.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill
   cupcake liners about halfway. Bake for 15-17 minutes, or until a
   toothpick inserted comes out with a few crumbs.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">While
   cupcakes cool, make the frosting.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese and butter until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   half of the powdered sugar and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   vanilla extract and remaining powdered sugar and mix until
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59491-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Frost
   the cooled cupcakes and top with a fresh strawberry,</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   wprm-block-text-bold">Catch Me If You Can Shrimp and Broccoli</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg whites</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mayonnaise</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large shrimp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">18-20 count, peeled and
   deveined</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sweetened condensed
   milk</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped Broccoli</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vegetable oil for
   frying</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   the egg whites until they are foamy then add cornstarch and continue
   whisking until combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   shrimp to the batter one at a time using a fork.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pick up
   1 shrimp at a time allowing it to drip off so that the shrimp has a
   thin coating and maintains it's shape.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   your oil in a medium sized pot on medium high (350 degrees) and fry
   until light golden brown, 4-5 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">To make
   the sauce, add the honey, mayonnaise and sweetened condensed milk and
   whisk to combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   sauce to the frying pan and then add the broccoli.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   until broccoli is tender. About 2-3 more minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59489-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   immediately with steamed rice if desired.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   together all of the ingredients in a microwavable mug.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Microwave for 70 seconds.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   to cool before adding frosting on top.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   frosting:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Its
   easiest to mix in a stand mixer, but you may also do it by hand.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cream
   butter until smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add in
   vanilla.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Gradually beat in confectioners sugar and cocoa.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   milk. You may add more or less milk to get it to the consistency youre
   looking for.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   frosting on top of cooled mug of cake,</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drizzle
   with caramel sauce if desired.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59487-step-1-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   frosting makes enough to frost a 9 x 11 cake. So save the extra
   frosting for your next cup of cake.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   beaten</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F. Line an 8x8 baking pan with aluminum foil and spray
   lightly with nonstick spray. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the graham cracker crumbs, butter, and sugar in a medium bowl. Stir
   until the mixture resembles wet sand. Press it into the bottom of the
   prepared pan and bake for 5 minutes. Cool completely while making the
   filling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   the oven temperature to 300F.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   cream cheese in a mixing bowl until smooth and creamy. Beat in the
   sugar until well combined. Add the lemon zest, lemon juice, and
   vanilla. Beat until combined. Using a spatula, gently fold the egg into
   the batter until fully incorporated.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   over prepared crust and bake for 30-35 minutes or until the edges of
   the filling feels firm but the center remains jiggly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Leave
   cheesecake in pan to cool completely then refrigerate for at least 8
   hours.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59485-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">The
   cheesecake will keep for up to 5 days stored in an airtight container
   in the refrigerator. They can be frozen for up to 2 months. Thaw
   overnight in the refrigerator.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   https://myhoneysplace.com/life-changing-tips-for-the-elderly/ Wed, 04
   Jul 2018 23:12:27 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information DIY And
   Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52821 Life Changing Tips For The
   Elderly. Listen to Podcast: As... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/life-changing-tips-for-the-elderly/">Co
   ntinue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52823 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Life-Changing
   -Tips-For-The-Elderly.jpg" alt="Life Changing Tips For The Elderly. As
   we get older some adjustments need to be made. Here are some ideal tips
   to make it a much smoother ride." width="600" height="900"
   data-id="52823"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Life-Chang
   ing-Tips-For-The-Elderly.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Life-Changing-Tips
   -For-The-Elderly-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Life Changing Tips
   For The Elderly.</strong></p> <p><strong>Listen to
   Podcast:</strong></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://anchor.fm/gone-now/embed/episodes/Life-Changing-Tips-For-T
   he-Elderly-e1oh3u" width="400px" height="102px" frameborder="0"
   scrolling="no"></iframe></p> <p>As we get older some adjustments need
   to be made. Here are some ideal tips to make it a much smoother
   ride.</p> <p><strong>How to get down stairs if your elevator is not
   working.</strong> A lot of the elderly live in apartments. If the
   elevators are not working or in case of a fire and you can not use your
   elevator getting down the steps could be very difficult. If you are
   unable to walk down the stairs, then sit down on the first step. Place
   your feet firmly on the second or third step, and scoot yourself
   down.</p> <p><strong>How to get up from the floor or ground without
   help:</strong></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/d_nqwkMNXVU" width="350"
   height="350" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></p> <p><strong>If you
   fall in your home and unable to get up</strong>.</p> <ul> <li>If you
   feel you are not injured, most cites have emergency personal that will
   assist you. You can dial 311. This is a free service.</li> <li>You
   could also purchase a Medical Alert System. They are reasonably priced.
   My Mother had one and used it many times. Most state Medicaid plans
   will furnish one for the elderly. These can be a lifesaver.</li> <li>If
   you do not have a medical alert system, keep your mobile phone with at
   all time. Have speed dial set up so only one button needs to be
   pushed.</li> <li>If really strapped for money then purchase a
   &ldquo;throw away&rdquo; phone with very little time on the phone and
   use it for emergency only.</li> </ul> <p><strong>How to get in and out
   of a car</strong>.</p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/tmkfrJnTA9o" width="350"
   height="350" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
   <p><strong>Tips:</strong></p> <p><img class="alignleft wp-image-52822
   size-thumbnail"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Jar-opener-15
   0x150.jpg" alt="" width="150" height="150" data-id="52822"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Jar-opener
   -150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Jar-opener-400x400
   .jpg 400w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Jar-opener-50x50.j
   pg 50w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Jar-opener.jpg
   500w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"><br /> Purchase a non
   slip rubber jar opener. I bought one at the 99 cent store and it sure
   comes in handy to open jars.</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Put
   most used items at waist level in your kitchen and bedroom dresser
   drawers.</p> <p>Use a 10 point mirror to apply makeup or just to check
   for face cleanness.</p> <p>If you are hard of hearing ask people to
   talk to you by talking slowly, clearly and facing you. Politely ask the
   person<strong> NOT</strong> to shout. Shouting does not help.</p>
   <p>When you bathe use a 2 in one shampoo. It will take less time.</p>
   <p>For minor muscle aches and pains I use &ldquo;Zim&rsquo;s Max
   Freeze&rdquo;. It is an OTC ointment that is 100 per-cent natural
   menthol. Works very well and is inexpensive.</p> <p>Use a microwave or
   crock pot for most of your cooking.</p> <p>Buy reading glasses at the
   99 cent store. Will save you money and work just as well as expensive
   ones.</p> <p>If you sleep in a bedroom and your family is in another
   bedroom, place a bell or whistle beside your bed. Your family is more
   likely to hear you if you need them.</p> <p>Use a weekly pill box for
   your medications. You are more likely to remember if you took them or
   not.</p> <p>If you need a walker to ambulate, then USE it.</p>
   <p><strong>To help prevent falls in the home:&nbsp;</strong></p> <ul>
   <li>Clean up clutter around the areas you walk.</li> <li>Install grab
   bars and handrails. In the shower and beside steps.</li> <li>Avoid
   wearing loose clothing that can cause you to trip over baggy
   pants.</li> <li>Install brighter light bulbs where needed, particularly
   in stairways and narrow hallways.</li> <li>Wear shoes or non-slip
   socks.</li> <li>Put non-slip mats in your shower.</li> <li>Pause after
   going from lying down to sitting and from sitting to standing.</li>
   <li>Do not use area rugs in your home. They are too easy to trip
   over.</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   5px">Microwave on high for 60 more seconds. Stir well again.</div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">If the

   chopped walnuts (if using) and stir completely.</div> </li><li

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Refrigerated for 1/2 hour then sprinkle chocolate chips over top
   and return to refrigerator for another hour.</div> </li><li

   foil out of pan and cut into squares.</div> </li></ul></div></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour

   https://myhoneysplace.com/10-signs-your-heart-is-not-working-properly/
   Mon, 02 Jul 2018 12:22:16 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information
   Health How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52798 10 Signs Your
   Heart Is Not Working Properly. Listen to... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-signs-your-heart-is-not-working-prop
   erly/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br
   /> <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52800 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Signs-Your
   -Heart-Is-Not-Working-Properly.jpg" alt="10 Signs Your Heart Is Not
   Working Properly. Your body gives you warning signs early on so that
   you can catch an illness in its early stages or even prevent it
   altogether and save your life. Here are 10 of the most common red flags
   that indicate bad heart health:" width="600" height="900"
   data-id="52800"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Signs-Y
   our-Heart-Is-Not-Working-Properly.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/10-Signs-Your-Hear
   t-Is-Not-Working-Properly-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"><strong>10 Signs Your Heart Is Not Working
   Properly.</strong></p> <p>Listen to post:<br /> <iframe
   src="https://anchor.fm/gone-now/embed/episodes/10-Signs-Your-Heart-Is-N
   ot-Working-Properly-e1o6lm" width="400px" height="102px"
   frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>Your body
   gives you warning signs early on so that you can catch an illness in
   its early stages or even prevent it altogether and save your life. Here
   are 10 of the most common red flags that indicate bad heart health:</p>
   <p><strong>A cough that won&rsquo;t quit.</strong> A persistent cough
   can be a symptom of all kinds of health issues, and cardiovascular
   disease is one of them. For instance, a chronic cough that produces a
   pinkish bloody liquid is very common in people with heart failure.
   Despite what it sounds like, heart failure doesn&rsquo;t mean that the
   heart completely stops beating. It just means that a person&rsquo;s
   heart isn&rsquo;t pumping blood as well as it should be. As a result,
   the body doesn&rsquo;t get enough oxygen since it&rsquo;s carried to
   all the tissues by the blood.</p> <p><strong>Nausea and loss of
   appetite</strong>. A lot of heart disease patients show a lack of
   appetite, nausea, or both, even if they&rsquo;ve had just a couple
   bites of food. The reason for that is built-up fluid around the liver
   and intestines that interferes with proper digestion. These symptoms
   are usually accompanied by abdominal pain, upset stomach, or feeling
   bloated. In fact, abdominal cramps that come and go in short spurts are
   extremely common right before a heart attack.</p> <p><strong>Your skin
   becomes paler or takes on a bluish tint.</strong> Being naturally pale
   doesn&rsquo;t necessarily mean you have a heart condition. But sudden
   paleness can be a result of reduced blood flow due to a heart
   that&rsquo;s not pumping blood as effectively as it should be. Shock,
   which can be caused by any condition that prevents the blood in your
   body from circulating properly, is the main reason why people who are
   suffering from a heart attack or heart failure turn pale all of a
   sudden.</p> <p><strong>Chronic or sudden fatigue.</strong> Fatigue can
   be one of the main symptoms indicating an impending heart attack. Women
   are more likely to experience heart-related fatigue than men, with 70%
   of female heart attack patients reporting that they&rsquo;d felt
   extremely tired before their episode. Physical or mental activity
   isn&rsquo;t the reason for such exhaustion, and it increases by the end
   of the day if it&rsquo;s due to a failing heart. It&rsquo;s really hard
   for this symptom to go unnoticed. Sometimes it&rsquo;s exhausting just
   to perform even the simplest tasks, like making the bed or taking a
   shower.</p> <p><strong>Pain that spreads to the arm.</strong>&nbsp;If
   their heart isn&rsquo;t working properly, a lot of men feel pain in
   their left arm, while women experience the same pain in either or both
   arms.</p> <p><strong>Swollen legs, ankles, and feet.</strong>&nbsp;When
   your heart isn&rsquo;t pumping enough blood through the body, fluid
   from your blood vessels leaks into surrounding tissues. Your lower
   extremities are the most affected simply due to gravity.</p>
   <p><strong>Extreme levels of anxiety.</strong>&nbsp;People who suffer
   from extreme anxiety from a very early age or most of their life are
   more prone to developing coronary heart disease.</p> <p><strong>Light
   headness or fainting</strong>.&nbsp;Feeling lightheaded and
   experiencing temporary loss of consciousness, also known in the
   scientific community as &ldquo;syncope&rdquo;, is super common among
   heart patients.</p> <p><strong>Skin rashes or unusual
   spots.</strong>&nbsp;People with eczema were found to have a 48% chance
   of suffering from high blood pressure and a 29% possibility of having
   high cholesterol.</p> <p><strong>Increased
   perspiration.</strong>&nbsp;People experience flu-like symptoms, have
   clammy skin, and sweat regardless of the air temperature or physical
   exertion.</p> <p>Talk to your physician if you have any of these
   symptoms.</p> <p>Watch Video:</p> <p><iframe width="890" height="501"
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/tWSBCiZY-Mo?feature=oembed"
   frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media;
   gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
   allowfullscreen></iframe></body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Hazel&rsquo;s Homemade Apple
   Pie.</strong></p> <p>Turn up your sound and listen to auto of

   foolproof. Apple pie filling with a flaky crust.</p> <p><div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-59477" class="wprm-recipe-container"
   data-recipe-id="59477"><div class="wprm-recipe
   wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div class="wprm-container-float-left">
   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img
   style="border-width: 0px;border-style: solid;border-color: #666666;"
   width="150" height="150"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Hazels-Apple-
   Pies-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Hazels-App

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Hazels-Apple-Pies-
   500x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Hazels-Apple-Pies-
   50x50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></div> </div>
   <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59477" style=""
   class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode
   wprm-block-text-normal" data-recipe-id="59477" target="_blank"
   rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon
   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Hazel's Homemade Apple Pie</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Flaky pie
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">unsalted butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cold and cut into
   cubes</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4 to 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ice cold water</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">as needed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">**1/4 cup melted butter for pie
   crust topping</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">**1/4 cup sugar for pie crust
   topping</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">7-8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small granny smith apples.
   Peeled</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">sliced, and cored.</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6 to 8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ice waters</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">stick butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">heaping tsp cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">nutmeg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Flaky Pie
   crust:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the flour, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add the cubed butter and toss to
   coat. Dump the mixture out onto a clean surface and use a rolling pin
   to roll the butter into thin sheets, combining it with the flour. Use a
   bench scraper to scrape the rolling pin and to bring the mixture back
   into a pile as necessary. Continue until all of the butter is
   incorporated into the flour. Mixture will be very flaky.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Return
   mixture to the bowl and place in the freezer for 10 minutes to chill
   the butter.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from freezer and add 1/4 cup of the ice cold water. Use a spoon and
   then your hands to stir the mixture until it comes together into a
   ball. If mixture is too dry, add additional water a tablespoon at a
   time.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Divide
   the dough in two and flatten into disks. Wrap each disk in plastic wrap
   and chill in the fridge for at least 1 hour and up to 5 days. Dough can
   also be frozen (double-wrapped) for up to 2 months.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   ready to roll out, let the dough rest at room temperature for five
   minutes. On a lightly floured surface, use a rolling pin to roll out
   the dough into a rough 13 inch circle. Dough should be about 1/4 inch
   thick. Transfer dough to 9-inch pie dish. Fill pie with below filling.
   Repeat with the second disk of dough.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   the filling completely, cutting a few vents with a sharp knife.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold
   the edges of the top and bottom crusts together and use your index
   fingers and thumb to pinch into a pattern. Brush with melted butter and
   sprinkle with sugar.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Filling:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the peeled, cored, and sliced apples in a large bowl. Set aside.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 425F.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium sauce pan, melt butter over medium heat. Add the 3 tbsp of flour
   and mix well, forming a paste. Add the water, sugars, cinnamon, nutmeg,
   and vanilla and mix well. Bring to a boil for 1 minute, then reduce
   heat to a simmer for an additional minute.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat and add remaining filling to apples. Toss well.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   apples into prepared pie crust, mounding slightly. Top with second pie
   crust. Cut off edges around the pie. Crimp edges. Brush top lightly
   with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   the pie loosely with aluminum foil. Lightly spray the foil so it does
   not stick to the pie. Place the pie on top of a cookie sheet (to catch
   any drips) and bake at 425F for 10-12 minutes. Reduce the heat to 350F
   and bake for another 50 minutes (remove the foil the last 10 minutes to
   let the crust brown), or until done. The pie is done when the crust is
   golden-brown and the apples are soft when pierced with a fork.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59477-step-1-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   the pie to cool before serving. Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   drained</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   drained</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Small Cans Chopped Black
   Olives</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Small Can Chopped Green
   Chilies</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Can Rotell Cooked &amp; Diced
   Tomatoes or Tomatoes with Chili Peppers</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Jalapeo - chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Small Red Onion -
   chopped</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 to 4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Bunches of Green Onions -
   chopped</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tb</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Garlic - chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Small Bunch Cilantro -
   chopped</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4 to 6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Plum Tomatoes - seeded &amp;
   chopped</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 - 16</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Bottle Italian
   Dressing</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59475-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   all ingredients in a large bowl and pour dressing over top.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59475-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Can be
   served immediately, but marinating overnight is recommended.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59475-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   with tortilla chips.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
