   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">maple syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li></ul></div></div
   > <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   your oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat a
   medium-sized skillet up over medium high heat. Add 1 cup sliced almonds
   to the pan. Let them get nice and golden brown. Should take about 3-4
   minutes. Be sure to stir them frequently so they don't burn. Once they
   have changed color and are fragrant and delicious remove the pan from
   the heat and set it aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium-sized mixing bowl place rolled oats. Add the dried fruit,
   cinnamon, brown sugar,the toasted almonds and a dash of salt. Give it
   all a nice stir to combine.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl or glass measuring cup place honey, canola oil, maple syrup
   and vanilla. Stir it around to combine. Don't get worried if everything
   doesn't combine perfectly. Just do the best you can to mix it
   together.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the wet (sticky!) ingredients into the oat mixture. Stir it well making
   sure all of the dry ingredients are coated.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   the mixture out onto a large cookie sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the pan into the oven and bake for about 30 minutes or until golden
   brown. You'll want to take the pan out of the oven once or twice and
   stir the granola during the baking time, just to make sure it cooks
   evenly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59473-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Let it
   cool and come to room temperature. Store leftovers in an airtight
   bowl.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Scouring pads 1 synthetic non
   scratch type</span> <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1 metal coil type</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dishcloth</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Baking soda</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Steel wool</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Dawn dish
   soap</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Copper-Bottom Pan:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">white vinegar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   the stainless steel pots and pans in Dawn dish soap and hot
   water.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Rinse
   the cookware in plain, warm water to remove soap and to assure a wet
   surface. Shake baking soda over the bottom of the pot.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Scour
   the stainless steel pot bottom with a synthetic scrubbing pad to remove
   black marks and prevent scratches.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Polish
   the bottoms of stainless steel pots and pans with a clean dry
   dishcloth.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   Copper-Bottom Pans:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix 1
   tbs. flour, 1 tbsp. white vinegar and 1 tbsp. salt to create a polish
   for pot bottoms. Apply the mixture to the pot bottoms with a sponge or
   non-scratch pad and rub the mixture all over the surface to remove
   discolorations.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Wash
   the pans in hot soapy water. Rinse with plain warm water.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   stubborn hard water spots from cookware by rubbing a dab of toothpaste
   on the spots. Rinse thoroughly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59471-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Polish
   the pots with a clean, dry dishtowel.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream of tartar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount"></span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li></ul></div></div>
   <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   eggs from the refrigerator and separate, as they will separate best
   cold.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   egg whites to reach room temperature to allow them to whip to their
   fullest.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   eggs whites into a spotlessly-clean bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whip
   the egg whites until they have stiff peaks and are glossy and
   smooth.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Then
   add the cream of tartar to help the egg whites hold their form.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add the sugar to the egg whites.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use a
   melon baller or a tablespoon measuring spoon to scoop on to top of
   pie.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59469-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   in oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large eggs</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room
   temperature</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">strawberries - sliced with stems
   removed</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Crust:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 325F (163C). Grease a 913 pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   the crust ingredients in a small bowl. Press the mixture into the
   bottom of the prepared pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the crust for 10 minutes, then set aside to cool.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Reduce
   the oven temperature to 300F</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Cheesecake
   filling:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   large bowl, blend the cream cheese, sugar and flour on low speed until
   well completely combined and smooth. Be sure to use low speed to reduce
   the amount of air added to the batter, which can cause cracks. Scrape
   down the sides of the bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   sour cream and vanilla extract mix on low speed until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   eggs one at a time, mixing slowly to combine. Scrape down the sides of
   the bowl as needed to make sure everything is well combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the batter into the pan with the crust and spread evenly.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   the cheesecake for 30 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Turn
   off the oven and leave the cheesecake in the oven with the door closed
   for 20 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Crack
   the door of the oven, with the cheesecake inside, for 15 minutes. This
   slow cooling process helps prevent the cheesecake from cracking.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-1-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   cheesecake in the fridge to cool completely, 3-4 hours.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Topping:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-2-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   stems from strawberries. Slice in haves and place on top of pie.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59467-step-2-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">***If
   your strawberries are not very sweet, put them in a bowl and add 1/2
   cup sugar and let them set for 1/2 hour.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div class='code-block
   code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display:
   block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">baking powder</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vegetable oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li

   water</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">powdered
   sugar</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Cake:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F (176C) and prepare a 913 inch cake pan with non-stick
   baking spray.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt to a large
   mixer bowl and combine. Set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   milk, vegetable oil, vanilla extract and eggs to a medium sized bowl
   and combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and beat until well
   combined.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Slowly
   add the hot water to the batter and mix on low speed until well
   combined. Scrape down the sides of the bowl as needed to make sure
   everything is well combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   the batter into the prepared cake pan and bake for 25 To 30 minutes, or
   until a toothpick comes out with a few moist crumbs.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   cake from oven and allow to cool.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   Topping:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59465-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Sprinkle the powdered sugar evenly over the cake.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Easy-Chocolat
   e-Banana-Cream-Pie-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150"

   ana-Cream-Pie-500x500.jpg 500w,

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   both chocolate and banana pudding according to package directions</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59463-step-0-1"

   your heavy whipping cream and powdered sugar on high speed with a hand

   id="wprm-recipe-59463-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"

   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   second layer with the banana pudding</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59463-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   whipping cream on top</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59463-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div

   you are done!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   types of herbs and spices. Paella rice is not fattening, provided you
   include it as part of a balanced diet. I used regular rice in my recipe
   but you can buy and use Paella rice.&nbsp;" width="600" height="900"
   data-id="52684"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Spanish-Pa
   ella.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Spanish-Paella-267
   x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p> <p>Spanish
   Paella is a Spanish dish recipe which is accompanied by any combination
   of seafood, chicken, pork and various types of herbs and spices. Paella
   rice is not fattening, provided you include it as part of a balanced
   diet. I used regular rice in my recipe but you can buy and use Paella
   rice.</p> <p><div id="wprm-recipe-container-59457"
   class="wprm-recipe-container" data-recipe-id="59457"><div
   class="wprm-recipe wprm-recipe-template-basic"><div
   class="wprm-container-float-left"> <div class="wprm-recipe-image
   wprm-block-image-normal"><img style="border-width: 0px;border-style:

   a-150x150.jpg" class="attachment-150x150 size-150x150" alt=""

   ella-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Spanish-Paella-500
   x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Spanish-Paella-50x
   50.jpg 50w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px" /></div> </div> <a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59457" style=""
   class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode

   wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"

   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Spanish Paella</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sausage spicy</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into small
   slices</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chicken breasts</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">cut into small cubed
   pieces</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">red bell pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">green bell pepper</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">pound</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shrimp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">20-30 shrimp, deveined and peeled,
   with tails still on</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">green onions</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">smoked paprika</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">start with 1 teaspoon and add more
   if desired</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">red chili powder</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">add more, if desired, - depends on
   how spicy you want it</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">turmeric</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">for color</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">rice or Paella rice</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">uncooked</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chicken
   stock</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat 3
   tablespoons of olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add
   sliced sausage, sliced chicken and cook for about 5 minutes,
   covered.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   chopped red bell pepper and green bell pepper, stir in with sausage and
   chicken, cover, and continue cooking for about 5 more minutes, on
   medium heat.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   shrimp and cook until shrimp just turns red. Add chopped green
   onions.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   spices (sweet smoked paprika and red chili powder), add just a touch of
   turmeric for color. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from heat and
   keep the skillet covered. The shrimp and green onions will continue
   cooking slightly when covered and off heat  without overcooking.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook 2
   cups of rice in a sauce pan according to package instructions.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   cooked rice into the skillet with shrimp, chicken and sausage. Mix
   everything well, so that olive oil, juices from spicy sausages, and
   other cooking juices and spices coat orzo or rice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   some chicken stock or water to make paella more juicy vs. dry. Keep
   adding more chicken stock or water to achieve the desired consistency
   of your paella  I think the juicier it is, the better. Add more salt
   and pepper if needed.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59457-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Dough :</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2.5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">granulated sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fine salt 1 tbsp dry
   yeast</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">warm milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">beaten. Keep 2 tbsp for later
   use.</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">room temperature</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Extra flour as
   needed</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Garlic
   Butter:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter/margarine</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">soft at room temperature (not
   melted)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fine salt</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">table salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">minced green onion</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic powder / minced
   garlic</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Garlic
   butter:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put
   butter, salt, green onion in a small bowl, mix until combined. Add
   garlic powder/minced garlic into the mix and continue mixing until well
   blended. Keep in the fridge until ready to use.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Make the dough :</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   mixing bowl put flour, make 3 wells. Add into each well : sugar, salt,
   yeast. Stir sugar and yeast first then stir together using a wooden
   spoon.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   warm milk and beaten egg (minus 2 tbsp). Stir until combined.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   soft butter, continue stirring until well blended into a smooth sticky
   dough.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Put the
   dough into greased bowl. Cover with cling wrap and put in warm place
   for about an hour. An hour later the dough will be very soft and
   hollow. When you pull the dough, it will show the hollows all around.
   Sprinkle with extra flour and start folding with fingertips (not
   kneading). Sprinkle more flour as needed but not too much.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dust
   work table with flour before put the dough. Flatten the dough with
   hand. Cut into 16 pieces. 6. Shape the dough into balls. Sprinkle with
   flour to prevent sticking.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Flatten
   or press the dough with fingers, spread with 1/2 tsp of garlic butter.
   Fold into a half-moon then gather both corners creating a flower petal.
   Repeat the method until finished.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-6" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Arrange
   on greased a round baking pan ( I used inverted pie pan). Cover with
   loose cling wrap for 30 minutes. Let rise.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Brush
   beaten egg on top. Bake at 175C pre-heated oven, for 30 minutes until
   golden brown and blooming. Let stay in the pan for 10 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59455-step-1-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   with hot soup or just enjoy the way it is.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/cRTMiISTWGM" width="450"
   height="450" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"><span
   data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px;
   overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;"
   class="mce_SELRES_start">&#65279;</span></iframe></body></html></p>

   text-align: center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">recipe follows</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">freshly grated lemon peel</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Heat
   oven to 400F. Grease and flour cookie sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   together sugar, flour and cocoa in small bowl. Add egg whites and
   butter; beat until smooth. Drop teaspoons of mixture onto prepared
   cookie sheet and spread out thinly in 5-inch circles.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake 6
   to 7 minutes or until set. Immediately remove from cookie sheet; place
   top side down, over bottom of inverted juice glasses. Mold to give wavy
   edges (if chocolate cup cracks, gently press together with fingers).
   Let stand until hard and completely cool, about 30 minutes.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   about 2 teaspoons CHOCOLATE COATING into each cup; use pastry brush or
   spoon to coat inside. Refrigerate 20 minutes or until coating is set.
   Meanwhile, prepare LEMON CREAM. Spoon scant 1/2 cup cream filling into
   each cup. Garnish with shredded lemon peel, if desired. About 6
   cups.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">CHOCOLATE
   COATING:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   3/4 cup HERSHEY'S SPECIAL DARK Chocolate Chips or HERSHEY'S Semi-Sweet
   Chips and 1 teaspoon shortening (do not use butter, margarine, spread
   or oil) in small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave at MEDIUM (50%) 45
   seconds or until smooth when stirred.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">LEMON
   CREAM:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59453-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   1 package (4- serving size) instant lemon pudding and pie filling mix,
   1 cup milk and 1/8 teaspoon lemon extract in medium bowl. Beat with
   whisk or on low speed of mixer 2 minutes. Fold in 1-1/2 cups thawed
   non-dairy whipped topping; refrigerate 30 minutes or until set. About
   2-1/2 cups.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name

   potatoes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">russet potatoes peeled washed and

   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">strips bacon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped green onion</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4-1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">milk</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Chopped fresh parsley for garnish
   optional</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the
   gravy:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">water</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">beef or turkey
   bouillon</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">all-purpose flour</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">onion</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">chopped</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and pepper to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For the mash
   potatoes:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59441-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook
   potatoes in a pot of boiling lightly salted water until fork tender.
   (About 15-20 minutes) While potatoes are cooking fry bacon until
   crispy, cool slightly then crumble or chop, set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59441-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Drain
   potatoes, add in half of the bacon, green onions, cream cheese and 1/4
   cup milk. Mash with potato masher or use a hand mixer until you reach
   desired consistency. If your potatoes seem a little stiff add in more
   milk. Taste for salt and pepper and adjust accordingly.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59441-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Garnish
   with reserved bacon and chopped parsley, if desired.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">For the gravy:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59441-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   water, bouillon, flour, onion, salt, pepper and butter in a small
   saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat and cook until thickened.
   Thats it!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>
   <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p> <div class='code-block code-block-2'
   style='margin: 8px auto; text-align: center; display: block; clear:

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla extract</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sour cream</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Lemon zest from 1
   lemon</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Filling</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">peach jam</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">reserved cookie
   crumbs</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">For
   decoration</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2/3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Peach liqueur</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">divided</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">red food coloring</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">yellow food coloring</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fine sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">green
   leaves</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350F .</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Line
   two baking sheets with parchment paper and set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   cookie dough. In a large bowl mix butter with sugar and lemon zest
   until creamy. Add egg and mix until well combined. Mix in vanilla
   extract and sour cream.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium bowl whisk together flour, baking powder and salt.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">With
   mixer on low incorporate flour mixture to butter mixture.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   your hands with softened butter or oil. Scoop about 1 tbsp of dough and
   shape into balls. Place the balls on the prepared baking sheets.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Flatten
   the balls slightly .</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 13-15 minutes until bottoms are lightly golden brown.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   form the oven and let cool completely.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   cookies are cooled use a small sharp knife to remove the cookie center
   crumb and place it in a bowl as it will be used for the filling.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-10"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Prepare
   the filling. Break the reserved cookie centers into crumbs. Add peach
   jam and ground pecans or walnuts over the reserved cookie crumbs and
   stir to combine.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-11"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the filling into a piping bag fitted with a plain tip (Ive used a 9 mm
   tip).</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-12"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill
   the cookies and match two cookies together.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-13" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Decorate cookies. Add about  cup peach liqueur into a small bowl.
   Ad yellow food coloring. Add another  cup peach liqueur into another
   bowl and add red food coloring. In another bowl add a bit of fine
   sugar.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-14"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Dip
   about a half of each sandwiched cookie into the yellow liqueur and then
   into the red one. Let it drain a bit and then roll into sugar to coat
   evenly.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59439-step-0-15"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the peach cookies onto a serving platter and decorate with green leaves
   if desired. Enjoy!</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br />

   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z
   M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z
   M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18
   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Homemade Roasted Green Beans with Special
   Sauce</h2> <div class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Roasted Green
   Beans:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">lb.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen green
   beans</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">grated parmesan
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">panko bread crumbs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">kosher
   salt</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Special
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cloves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic minced</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cups</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">half and half a mixture of milk and
   cream; available in dairy section</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Tablespoons</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cornstarch</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">ground black pepper</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Italian seasoning</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">teaspoon</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">dried oregano</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">grated Parmesan
   cheese</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Roasted Green
   Beans:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; toss to coat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   green beans on a large rimmed baking sheet.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roast
   for 15-20 minutes; stirring halfway through.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Special
   Sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   minced garlic and saute until golden.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   mixing bowl, whisk together half and half, cornstarch, salt, pepper,
   Italian seasoning and oregano. Add mixture to sauted garlic.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook,
   stirring often until thick.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   Parmesan cheese and stir well.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59437-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat and serve over the green beans or pasta.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>&nbsp;</body></html></p>

   solid;border-color: #666666;" width="150" height="150"

   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Caramel-Ch
   ocolate-Pecan-Turtles-150x150.jpg 150w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Caramel-Chocolate-
   Pecan-Turtles-500x500.jpg 500w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Caramel-Chocolate-

   /></div> </div> <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/wprm_print/59435"

   wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal"
   data-recipe-id="59435" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg
   xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
   xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px"
   height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#333333"
   d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.56
   9,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0
   ,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z

   .552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print</a> <div class="wprm-spacer"
   style="height: 5px"></div> <h2 class="wprm-recipe-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Caramel Chocolate Pecan Turtles</h2> <div
   class="wprm-spacer" style="height: 5px"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2 1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">pecans</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salted butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">light corn syrup</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">7</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounces</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sweetened condensed milk</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">1/2 of a 14 ounce
   can</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">t</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">vanilla</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1 12</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">package milk chocolate
   chips</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">t</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">shortening</span></li></ul></div></
   div> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place 2
   1/2 cups of pecans into a large skillet. Toast them over medium high
   heat, stirring occasionally, until they have darkened. Should only take
   a few minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Use 2
   large cookie sheets. Line them with parchment paper and spray it with
   cooking spray. Arrange your pecans into clusters, three to a group
   works well. You want to leave some space (about an inch) between each
   cluster. You can also skip the cluster step, as I did and put the
   pecans on the top.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Make your
   caramel sauce and chocolate:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   1/2 C butter into a medium-sized sauce pan. Melt it over medium high
   heat. Add 1 C brown sugar, 1/2 C light corn syrup and 7 ounces
   sweetened condensed milk to the pan. Increase the heat just a bit and
   stir it continually. Cook and stir until it reaches 235-240 degrees. It
   will continue to rise in temperature just a bit even without the direct
   heat, making the caramel just the right texture.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   1/2 teaspoon vanilla.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Put it
   together:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-2-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom:
   5px">Carefully drizzle about 1 1/2 teaspoons of caramel over each nut
   cluster. You'll want to work quickly, as the caramel will begin to set
   up. Be sure there is caramel touching all of the nuts in your cluster.
   The caramel works like glue, sticking the nuts together.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-2-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   microwave safe bowl pour 12 ounces of milk chocolate chips. Heat in the
   microwave for 30 seconds at a time, stirring after each cooking
   interval.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-2-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add 1/2
   teaspoon of shortening to the melted chocolate. Allow it to sit for a
   minute or two (so it can melt and make the chocolate chips more
   spreadable). Stir it all together.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-2-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spoon
   about 1 1/2 teaspoons of melted chocolate over the top of the caramel
   and nuts. Swirl it around along the top making a swoop with your
   spoon.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59435-step-2-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   the chocolate to set up. Once it has hardened and cooled you can serve
   them immediately, or transfer them to an air tight container.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async

   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   Wed, 06 Jun 2018 13:28:38 +0000 My Honeys Place Desserts Recipes
   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52553 Apple Cupcakes with Caramel Topping.
   This homemade dessert recipe will... <a class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/homemade-apple-cupcakes-with-caramel-to
   pping/">Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML
   4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br
   /> <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52555 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Homemade-Appl
   e-Cupcakes-With-Caramel-Topping.jpg" alt="Apple Cupcakes with Caramel
   Topping. This homemade dessert recipe will be a family favorite.&nbsp;"
   width="600" height="900" data-id="52555"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Homemade-A
   pple-Cupcakes-With-Caramel-Topping.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Homemade-Apple-Cup
   cakes-With-Caramel-Topping-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px)
   100vw, 600px"></p> <p>Apple Cupcakes with Caramel Topping. This
   homemade dessert recipe will be a family favorite.</p> <p><div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
