   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">+ 2 tbsp caramel
   sauce</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Cupcakes:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 350 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Whisk
   together flour, sugars, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg
   in a large mixing bowl.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add egg
   whites, vanilla extract, sour cream, milk and butter and mix on medium
   speed just until smooth. Do not over mix.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir in
   chopped apples</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fill
   cupcake liners about 3/4 full.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   17-19 minutes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   to cool for 1-2 minutes, then remove to cooling rack to finish
   cooling.</div> </li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Frosting:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   butter and shortening and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add 4
   cups of powdered sugar and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-1-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   caramel sauce and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-1-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   remaining powdered sugar and mix until smooth.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59433-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Top
   cupcakes with icing and a drizzle of caramel.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div><br /> </body></html></p> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-clean-your-bbq-grill/ Tue, 05 Jun 2018
   12:33:33 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Camping and Outdoors
   DIY And Tips How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52534 How to
   clean your BBQ grill. The best way to... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-clean-your-bbq-grill/">Continue
   reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52536 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/How-To-Clean-
   Your-BBQ-Grill2.jpg" alt="How to clean your BBQ grill. The best way to
   clean your charcoal and gas grill." width="600" height="900"
   data-id="52536"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/How-To-Cle
   an-Your-BBQ-Grill2.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/How-To-Clean-Your-
   BBQ-Grill2-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>How to clean your BBQ grill. The best way to clean your
   charcoal and gas grill.</p> <p><b>Safety:&nbsp;</b>When cleaning grills
   with bristle brushes, always thoroughly wipe down the cleaned area
   afterwards in order to remove any bristles that may have come off
   during the cleaning process and stuck to the grill. Also, cleaning
   while the grilling surface is warm can make the job easier, but
   remember to wait until the surface has cooled enough that it will not
   burn you.</p> <p><strong>To clean a charcoal grill you will
   need:</strong></p> <ul class="list list--type-plain u__text-align--left
   "> <li class="list__item list__item--padding-none ">Long-handled
   stiff-wire grill brush</li> <li class="list__item
   list__item--padding-none ">Paper towels</li> <li class="list__item
   list__item--padding-none ">Dawn Dish detergent</li> <li
   class="list__item list__item--padding-none ">Vegetable oil</li> <li
   class="list__item list__item--padding-none ">Rags</li> <li>Watch video
   below for instructions</li> </ul> <p><strong>Instruction to clean a gas
   grill:</strong></p> <ul class="list u__text-align--left "> <li
   class="list__item ">Pre-heat the grill for 15 minutes on high heat then
   turn off the grill. &bull; Turn the gas off &ndash; either on the
   propane tank or the gas line.</li> <li class="list__item ">Clean the
   grill using a stiff wire brush dipped in water. Do not lean over the
   grill while cleaning, as this should create plenty of steam.</li> <li
   class="list__item ">For tough grease spots, add Dawn dish soap to the
   water or a grill cleaner.</li> <li class="list__item ">Once the surface
   has cooled, wipe the grate with a damp cloth to remove residue or brush
   bristles.</li> <li class="list__item ">Remove burners from the gas
   supply line and remove blockages to the burner&rsquo;s gas ports using
   a dry wire brush. Clean the ports by brushing side-to-side instead of
   up-and-down, as the vertical motion may push debris into the
   ports.</li> <li class="list__item ">Clean the burner valve with soapy
   water and run water through the inside of the valve.</li> <li
   class="list__item ">Clean the inside of of the grill using a wire brush
   and warm soapy water and rinse with water. Towel dry the burners and
   reinstall.</li> <li class="list__item ">When washing the outside of a
   stainless steel grill, use a specially formulated stainless steel
   cleaner and micro fiber cloth. Ceramic, porcelain and painted steel
   surfaces can be cleaned using soap and water.</li> <li
   class="list__item ">If you have a propane grill, you can store it
   outside with the propane tank attached. If storing inside, remove the
   propane tank and keep outside away from direct sunlight.</li> <li
   class="list__item ">Keep the grill protected with a grill cover.</li>
   <li class="list__item ">Replace your grill brush annually.</li> </ul>
   <p><iframe width="890" height="501"
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jII9940XrYc?feature=oembed"
   frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media;
   gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe></p> <p><iframe
   src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xmIQVDvkvZs?rel=0" width="560"
   height="315" frameborder="0"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cream cheese
   softened</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">large egg</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/8</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">fresh or frozen
   strawberries</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">Cup</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped pecans</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">optional</span></li></ul></div></di
   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59431-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the oven to 325 degrees.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59431-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, mix the cake mix, jello, egg, cream cheese , butter,
   strawberries and pecans until it is all well combined.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59431-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Roll
   the dough into about 24 balls. Place them on a cookie sheet and gently
   press down on the top of the balls to slightly flatten them.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59431-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake at
   325 degrees for 11-13 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59431-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Move
   the cookies to a wire rack to cool.</div> </li></ul></div></div>
   </div></div></p> <p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Check out more
   of our <a href="https://myhoneysplace.com/?s=cookies">Cookie
   Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div class='code-block

   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Peanut-Butter-Cup-
   Stuffed-Monkey-Bread-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>Peanut Butter Cup Stuffed Monkey Bread.&nbsp;No napkins
   needed with this easy and delicious Reese&rsquo;s monkey bread dessert
   recipe! It&rsquo;s finger lickin&rsquo; good!</p> <p><div
   id="wprm-recipe-container-59427" class="wprm-recipe-container"

   <div class="wprm-recipe-image wprm-block-image-normal"><img

   class="wprm-spacer"></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-ingredients-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Ingredients</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">3 - 7.5</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">ounce</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cans refrigerated biscuit
   dough</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cinnamon</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">c.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">brown sugar</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp.</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">honey</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">30</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Reese's Peanut Butter Cups</span>
   <span class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">unwrapped</span></li></ul></div></d
   iv> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   oven to 400.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Grease
   a bundt pan well, and set aside.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   cinnamon and sugar in a large zip top bag.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Open
   the cans of biscuit dough.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place a
   Reese's in the center of each piece of dough and roll each one into a
   ball. You'll have 30 biscuit total, so you'll need 30 Reese's
   unwrapped.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the dough balls into the zip top bag, and shake to coat the dough. Add
   5-8 at a time. Repeat until all of the pieces of dough are coated in
   cinnamon sugar.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Place
   the coated dough balls in the bundt pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-7" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   small bowl, microwave the butter, brown sugar, and honey for 1
   minute.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-8"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Stir
   well to dissolve the sugar.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-9" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Pour
   over the dough balls in the bundt pan.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-10" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Bake
   for 20-25 minutes, until dough appears to be firm &amp; set.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59427-step-0-11"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Allow
   to stand for 5 minutes and then invert onto a plate.</div>
   </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p>Watch video for

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Tbl Sugar for sprinkling the
   lemons</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">4</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">C</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">Cold Water plus Ice
   Cubes</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Simple
   syrup: combine 1 Cup Sugar and 1 Cup Water in a small saucepan over
   medium heat. Boil for 5 minutes until sugar is dissolved. Cool
   completely.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   a grill pan or grill until very hot. Oil lightly to prevent any
   sticking.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Halve
   the lemons and sprinkle the cut sides with a small amount of sugar.
   Place cut side down on the grill pan and cook for 2-3 minutes and
   remove to a plate until cool enough to handle. Squeeze the juice from
   them while still warm into a strainer over a measuring cup. You'll need
   1 full of Cup of lemon juice.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Also,
   make thick slices from another lemon (or two) and sprinkle both sides
   with sugar. Grill until marks appear, repeat on the other side. Set
   aside for garnish.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-4"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add the
   lemon juice to a pitcher. Follow with the simple syrup, 4 Cups of Water
   and Ice Cubes.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59423-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Makes
   six 8 oz. servings.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   src="https://www.facebook.com/plugins/video.php?href=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.
   facebook.com%2FBestBitesAOL%2Fvideos%2F2033981753596496%2F&amp;show_tex
   t=0&amp;width=476" width="476" height="476" frameborder="0"
   scrolling="no"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></body></html></p> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-pick-a-perfect-watermelon/ Mon, 28 May
   2018 12:29:00 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Cooking Tips &
   Tricks How To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52448 How To Pick A
   Perfect Watermelon every time.&#160;There&#8217;s a definite... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/how-to-pick-a-perfect-watermelon/">Cont
   inue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52449 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/How-To-Pick-A
   -Perfect-Watermelon.jpg" alt="How To Pick A Perfect Watermelon every
   time.&nbsp;There's a definite art to picking the very best
   watermelons." width="600" height="900" data-id="52449"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/How-To-Pic
   k-A-Perfect-Watermelon.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/How-To-Pick-A-Perf
   ect-Watermelon-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>How To Pick A Perfect Watermelon every
   time.&nbsp;There&rsquo;s a definite art to picking the very best
   watermelons. It involves weighing the watermelon between your hands,
   turning it over, and giving it a firm&nbsp;<em>thwap!</em>&nbsp;on the
   underside. Why? A heavy watermelon with a splotch on its belly and a
   hollow sound means it is brimming with juice and at the peak of its
   ripeness.</p> <ol class="X5LH0c"> <li class="TrT0Xe">Ripe melons have a
   hollow sound when you tap or slap the outside.&nbsp;A watermelon is
   ripe when you hear &ldquo;punk&rdquo; rather than &ldquo;pank&rdquo; or
   &ldquo;pink&rdquo; when you tap it with your finger.</li> <li
   class="TrT0Xe">It should feel relatively heavy when lifted.</li>
   <li>Make sure it has a prominent yellow spot. This is where it sat on
   the ground ripening. No spot = premature pick = not ripe.</li> <li>Look
   for &ldquo;webbing&rdquo;. This is the brown, course web looking
   materiel. This is caused when bees pollinate the flower and scar the
   membranes that later forms the fruit. The more pollination = more
   webbing = sweeter fruit.</li> <li>Shake it. If you hear things moving
   inside, it&rsquo;s overly ripe.</li> </ol> <p></body></html></p> <div
   class='code-block code-block-2' style='margin: 8px auto; text-align:
   center; display: block; clear: both;'> <script async
   src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script
   > <!-- MYHoney new responsive --> <ins class="adsbygoogle"
   style="display:block" data-ad-client="ca-pub-8667002719249551"
   data-ad-slot="3723820843" data-ad-format="auto"
   data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle =
   window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></div>

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">seedless grapes</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">I use a mixture of green and red
   grapes</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1/2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cup</span> <span

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes

   v> <div class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container
   wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header
   wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Beat
   together the sour cream, cream cheese, vanilla and Sugar until
   creamy</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-1"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Fold in
   grapes</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Mix
   together for topping the finely chopped pecans and brown sugar
   (optional)</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spread
   the grape salad in a 13 x 9 dish or bowl and sprinkle with topping or
   serve in individual cups and sprinkle mixture over.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Chill
   overnight for up to 24 hours and serve</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59419-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Will
   make 8 servings</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p> <p

   https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52429 Taco Hamburger Casserole. A
   delicious recipe made with ground beef,... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/taco-hamburger-casserole/">Continue

   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52430 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Taco-Hamburge
   r-Casserole.jpg" alt="Taco Hamburger Casserole. A delicious recipe made
   with ground beef, taco seasoning, cheese, sour cream and biscuit. Serve
   it for a party or a family treat." width="600" height="900"
   data-id="52430"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Taco-Hambu
   rger-Casserole.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Taco-Hamburger-Cas
   serole-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></p>
   <p>Taco Hamburger Casserole. A delicious recipe made with ground beef,
   taco seasoning, cheese, sour cream and biscuit.</p> <p>Serve it for a
   party or a family treat.</p> <p>You will need:</p> <ul> <li>1 1/2
   pounds ground beef</li> <li>1 (10 oz.) can fire-roasted diced tomatoes
   with green chiles</li> <li>1 (4 oz.) can diced green chiles</li> <li>1
   (1.25 oz.) packet taco seasoning</li> <li>2 1/2 cups biscuit mix</li>
   <li>1 3/4 cups sharp cheddar cheese, shredded, divided</li> <li>1 red
   bell pepper, diced</li> <li>1/2 yellow onion, diced</li> <li>1 cup
   water</li> <li>1/2 cup sour cream</li> <li>1/2 cup mayonnaise</li>
   <li>1 teaspoon garlic powder</li> <li>Kosher salt and freshly ground
   pepper, to taste</li> </ul> <p>Watch video for instructions:</p>

   _text=0&amp;width=476" width="476" height="476" frameborder="0"
   scrolling="no"
   allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></body></html></p> <div

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Chicken:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"

   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span

   cutlets</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">seasoned breadcrumbs</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">grated Parmesan
   cheese</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">butter</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">melted (or olive
   oil)</span></li><li class="wprm-recipe-ingredient"
   style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">6</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">mozzarella cheese</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">cooking
   spray</span></li></ul></div><div
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-group-name wprm-block-text-bold">Marinara
   sauce:</h4><ul class="wprm-recipe-ingredients"><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">olive oil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">cloves</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">garlic</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes
   wprm-recipe-ingredient-notes-faded">smashed</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">28</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">oz</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">can crushed tomatoes</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">small bay leaf</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">1</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">oregano</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-amount">2</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-unit">tbsp</span> <span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">chopped fresh basil</span></li><li
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient" style="list-style-type: disc;"><span
   class="wprm-recipe-ingredient-name">salt and fresh pepper to
   taste</span></li></ul></div></div> <div
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3
   class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-instructions-header
   wprm-block-text-bold">Instructions</h3><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4 class="wprm-recipe-group-name
   wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Chicken:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Preheat
   the air fryer 360F for 9 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Spray
   the basked lightly with spray.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Combine
   breadcrumbs and parmesan cheese in a bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Melt
   the butter in another bowl.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Lightly
   brush the butter onto the chicken, then dip into breadcrumb
   mixture.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-5"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">When
   the air fryer is ready, place 2 pieces in the basket and spray the top
   with oil.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-6"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook 6
   minutes, turn and top each with 1 tbsp sauce and 1 1/2 tbsp of shredded
   mozzarella cheese.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-7"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cook 3
   more minutes or until cheese is melted.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-0-8" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Set
   aside and keep warm, repeat with the remaining 2 pieces.</div>
   </li></ul></div><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><h4
   class="wprm-recipe-group-name wprm-recipe-instruction-group-name
   wprm-block-text-bold">Marina Sauce:</h4><ul
   class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-0"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">In a
   medium pot, heat olive oil over medium heat.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   garlic and saute until golden, being careful not to burn.</div>
   </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-2"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Add
   crushed tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano, and bay leaf. Stir and reduce
   heat to low.</div> </li><li id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-3"
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Cover
   and let simmer about 15  20 minutes.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Remove
   from heat and add fresh basil.</div> </li><li
   id="wprm-recipe-59417-step-1-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction"
   style="list-style-type: decimal;"><div
   class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 5px">Serve
   over chicken.</div> </li></ul></div></div> </div></div></p>

   our&nbsp;<a
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/category/favorite-recipes/air-fryer-rec
   ipes/">Air Fryer Recipes</a></strong></p> <p></body></html></p> <div

   https://myhoneysplace.com/10-great-ways-to-improve-your-memory/ Wed, 23
   May 2018 15:52:04 +0000 My Honeys Place Amazing Information Health How
   To and Tips https://myhoneysplace.com/?p=52389 With the right
   stimulation, your brain can form new neural... <a
   class="continue-reading-link"
   href="https://myhoneysplace.com/10-great-ways-to-improve-your-memory/">
   Continue reading</a> <p><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0
   Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd"><br />
   <html><body><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52391 size-full"
   src="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/10-Great-Ways
   -To-Improve-Your-Memory.jpg" alt="10 Great Ways To Improve Your Memory.
   With the right stimulation, your brain can form new neural pathways,
   alter existing connections, and adapt and react in ever-changing ways."
   width="600" height="900" data-id="52391"
   srcset="https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/10-Great-W
   ays-To-Improve-Your-Memory.jpg 600w,
   https://myhoneysplace.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/10-Great-Ways-To-I
   mprove-Your-Memory-267x400.jpg 267w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw,
   600px"></p> <p>With the right stimulation, your brain can form new
   neural pathways, alter existing connections, and adapt and react in
   ever-changing ways.&nbsp;Fuzzy thinking and memory loss is a normal
   part of aging. But behavioral strategies and memory-enhancing
   techniques can help improve the ability to learn new information and
   retain it over time.</p> <p><strong>Give your brain a
   boost:</strong>&nbsp;Think of something new you&rsquo;ve always wanted
   to try, like learning how to play the guitar, make pottery, juggle,
   play chess, speak French, dance the tango, or master your golf swing.
   Any of these activities can help you improve your memory, so long as
   they keep you challenged and engaged.&nbsp;If you don&rsquo;t
   sufficiently challenge your brain with new, surprising information, it
   eventually begins to deteriorate.</p>
   <p><strong>Exercise:&nbsp;</strong>Aerobic exercise is particularly
   good for the brain, so choose activities that keep your blood pumping.
   In general, anything that is good for your heart is great for your
   brain.</p> <p><strong>Socialize:</strong>&nbsp;Humans are highly social
   animals. We&rsquo;re not meant to survive, let alone thrive, in
   isolation. Relationships stimulate our brains&mdash;in fact,
   interacting with others may be the best kind of brain
   exercise.&nbsp;Studies have indicted that caring for a dog, creating
   art, and spending time with a grandchild can boost different aspects of
   memory and reasoning.</p> <p><strong>Laugh:&nbsp;</strong>Share your
   embarrassing moments. The best way to take ourselves less seriously is
   to talk about the times when we took ourselves too
   seriously.&nbsp;You&rsquo;ve heard that&nbsp;laughter is the best
   medicine, and that holds true for the brain and the memory, as well as
   the body. Unlike emotional responses, which are limited to specific
   areas of the brain, laughter engages multiple regions across the whole
   brain.</p> <p><strong>Read a book:</strong>&nbsp;An analysis of records
   of 5,635 participants in the Health and Retirement Study linked regular
   book reading with a 20% reduced risk of dying over a 12-year
   period.</p> <p><strong>Take care of your
   teeth</strong>:&nbsp;Periodontal disease, the leading cause of adult
   tooth loss, is an inflammatory condition that may increase the risk of
   diabetes, heart disease, and dementia. The best defenses are regular
   brushing and flossing, along with not smoking.</p> <p><strong>Listen to
   music:</strong>&nbsp;Music aids formation and recovery of memory.</p>
   <p><strong>Use tools:</strong>&nbsp;Using tools such as calendars,
   cellphone alarms, and organizing apps can aid with memory.&nbsp;Have
   one central place to jot down important appointments, to-dos, and
   notes. If you&rsquo;re tech savvy, that can be a smartphone app. Or,
   you can use an old-fashioned paper organizer, calendar, or notebook.
   You can even put up an erasable board in your kitchen to write down
   items. Use an address book.&nbsp;Jot down the names, addresses, and
   phone numbers you need&mdash;including those of family, friends, your
   doctors, and the companies with which you do business (bank, dry
   cleaner, mechanic, etc.). Keep them together in a paper book or use the
   contacts tool on your computer or phone, and update them as needed.</p>
   <p><strong>Get enough sleep:</strong>&nbsp;When people don&rsquo;t get
   enough sleep, their attention and concentration abilities decline.
   Their reaction time lengthens, they&rsquo;re inattentive, and they
   don&rsquo;t respond as well to&nbsp;environmental signals. That means
   they can&rsquo;t take in new information or react to dangerous
   situations. But people can make up for lost sleep and restore focus and
   clarity by seeing a doctor about a possible underlying cause of sleep
   trouble, seeing a sleep specialist, cutting out caffeine and foods that
   cause heartburn, practicing good sleep hygiene, and exercising earlier
   in the day.</p> <p><strong>Mediate:</strong>&nbsp;Meditation&nbsp;can
   increase&nbsp;blood&nbsp;flow in the&nbsp;brain&nbsp;and improve
   memory, according to researchers who tested a specific kind of
   meditation and found the improvement after just eight weeks. Read about
   this study: <a
   href="https://www.webmd.com/alzheimers/news/20100303/can-meditation-rev
   erse-memory-loss#1" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Can meditation
   reverse memory loss.</a></p> <p>Also read <a
   href="https://www.wikihow.com/Meditate" target="_blank"
   rel="noopener">How To Mediate</a></body></html></p> <div
